V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

72#define TRACE(...) \
73 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) { \
74 std::cout << __VA_ARGS__ << std::endl; \
75 }
76
77#define FAIL(...) \
78 TRACE("Failed " << __func__ << ":" << __LINE__ << ": " << __VA_ARGS__); \
79 return {};

85enum class CpuOperation {
86 kFloat64Round,
87};
88
89// TODO(leszeks): Add a generic mechanism for marking nodes as optionally
90// supported.
91bool IsSupported(CpuOperation op) {
92 switch (op) {
93 case CpuOperation::kFloat64Round:
94#if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_IA32)
95 return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1) || CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX);
96#elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
97 return CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ARMv8);
98#elif defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_PPC64) || \
99 defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64) || \
100 defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_LOONG64) || \
101 defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_MIPS64)
102 return true;
103#else
104#error "V8 does not support this architecture."
105#endif
106 }
107}

109class FunctionContextSpecialization final : public AllStatic {
110 public:
111 static compiler::OptionalContextRef TryToRef(
112 const MaglevCompilationUnit* unit, ValueNode* context, size_t* depth) {
113 DCHECK(unit->info()->specialize_to_function_context());
114 if (Constant* n = context->TryCast<Constant>()) {
115 return n->ref().AsContext().previous(unit->broker(), depth);
116 }
117 return {};
118 }
119};
120
121} // namespace
122
123ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetParentContext(ValueNode* node) {
124 if (CreateFunctionContext* n = node->TryCast<CreateFunctionContext>()) {
125 return n->context().node();
126 }
127
128 if (InlinedAllocation* alloc = node->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
129 return alloc->object()->get(
130 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
131 }
132
133 if (CallRuntime* n = node->TryCast<CallRuntime>()) {
134 switch (n->function_id()) {
135 case Runtime::kPushBlockContext:
136 case Runtime::kPushCatchContext:
137 case Runtime::kNewFunctionContext:
138 return n->context().node();
139 default:
140 break;
141 }
142 }
143
144 return nullptr;
145}
146
147// Attempts to walk up the context chain through the graph in order to reduce
148// depth and thus the number of runtime loads.
149void MaglevGraphBuilder::MinimizeContextChainDepth(ValueNode** context,
150 size_t* depth) {
151 while (*depth > 0) {
152 ValueNode* parent_context = TryGetParentContext(*context);
153 if (parent_context == nullptr) return;
154 *context = parent_context;
155 (*depth)--;
156 }
157}
158
159void MaglevGraphBuilder::EscapeContext() {
160 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
161 if (InlinedAllocation* alloc = context->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
162 alloc->ForceEscaping();
163 }
164}
165
166class CallArguments {
167 public:
168 enum Mode {
169 kDefault,
170 kWithSpread,
171 kWithArrayLike,
172 };
173
174 CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
175 interpreter::RegisterList reglist,
176 const InterpreterFrameState& frame, Mode mode = kDefault)
177 : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode),
178 args_(reglist.register_count()),
179 mode_(mode) {
180 for (int i = 0; i < reglist.register_count(); i++) {
181 args_[i] = frame.get(reglist[i]);
182 }
183 DCHECK_IMPLIES(args_.size() == 0,
184 receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
185 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode != kDefault,
186 receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
187 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == kWithArrayLike, args_.size() == 2);
188 }
189
190 explicit CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode)
191 : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode), args_(), mode_(kDefault) {
192 DCHECK_EQ(receiver_mode, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
193 }
194
195 CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
196 std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> args, Mode mode = kDefault)
197 : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode), args_(args), mode_(mode) {
198 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode != kDefault,
199 receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
200 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == kWithArrayLike, args_.size() == 2);
201 CheckArgumentsAreNotConversionNodes();
202 }
203
204 CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
205 base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8>&& args, Mode mode = kDefault)
206 : receiver_mode_(receiver_mode), args_(std::move(args)), mode_(mode) {
207 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode != kDefault,
208 receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
209 DCHECK_IMPLIES(mode == kWithArrayLike, args_.size() == 2);
210 CheckArgumentsAreNotConversionNodes();
211 }
212
213 ValueNode* receiver() const {
214 if (receiver_mode_ == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
215 return nullptr;
216 }
217 return args_[0];
218 }
219
220 void set_receiver(ValueNode* receiver) {
221 if (receiver_mode_ == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
222 args_.insert(args_.data(), receiver);
223 receiver_mode_ = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
224 } else {
225 DCHECK(!receiver->properties().is_conversion());
226 args_[0] = receiver;
227 }
228 }
229
230 ValueNode* array_like_argument() {
231 DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kWithArrayLike);
232 DCHECK_GT(count(), 0);
233 return args_[args_.size() - 1];
234 }
235
236 size_t count() const {
237 if (receiver_mode_ == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
238 return args_.size();
239 }
240 return args_.size() - 1;
241 }
242
243 size_t count_with_receiver() const { return count() + 1; }
244
245 ValueNode* operator[](size_t i) const {
246 if (receiver_mode_ != ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
247 i++;
248 }
249 if (i >= args_.size()) return nullptr;
250 return args_[i];
251 }
252
253 void set_arg(size_t i, ValueNode* node) {
254 if (receiver_mode_ != ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
255 i++;
256 }
257 DCHECK_LT(i, args_.size());
258 DCHECK(!node->properties().is_conversion());
259 args_[i] = node;
260 }
261
262 Mode mode() const { return mode_; }
263
264 ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode() const { return receiver_mode_; }
265
266 void PopArrayLikeArgument() {
267 DCHECK_EQ(mode_, kWithArrayLike);
268 DCHECK_GT(count(), 0);
269 args_.pop_back();
270 }
271
272 void PopReceiver(ConvertReceiverMode new_receiver_mode) {
273 DCHECK_NE(receiver_mode_, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
274 DCHECK_NE(new_receiver_mode, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
275 DCHECK_GT(args_.size(), 0); // We have at least a receiver to pop!
276 // TODO(victorgomes): Do this better!
277 for (size_t i = 0; i < args_.size() - 1; i++) {
278 args_[i] = args_[i + 1];
279 }
280 args_.pop_back();
281
282 // If there is no non-receiver argument to become the new receiver,
283 // consider the new receiver to be known undefined.
284 receiver_mode_ = args_.empty() ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined
285 : new_receiver_mode;
286 }
287
288 private:
289 ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode_;
290 base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> args_;
291 Mode mode_;
292
293 void CheckArgumentsAreNotConversionNodes() {
294#ifdef DEBUG
295 // Arguments can leak to the interpreter frame if the call is inlined,
296 // conversions should be stored in known_node_aspects/NodeInfo.
297 for (ValueNode* arg : args_) {
298 DCHECK(!arg->properties().is_conversion());
299 }
300#endif // DEBUG
301 }
302};
303
304class V8_NODISCARD MaglevGraphBuilder::SaveCallSpeculationScope {
305 public:
306 explicit SaveCallSpeculationScope(
307 MaglevGraphBuilder* builder,
308 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source = compiler::FeedbackSource())
309 : builder_(builder) {
310 saved_ = builder_->current_speculation_feedback_;
311 // Only set the current speculation feedback if speculation is allowed.
312 if (IsSpeculationAllowed(builder_->broker(), feedback_source)) {
313 builder->current_speculation_feedback_ = feedback_source;
314 } else {
315 builder->current_speculation_feedback_ = compiler::FeedbackSource();
316 }
317 }
318 ~SaveCallSpeculationScope() {
319 builder_->current_speculation_feedback_ = saved_;
320 }
321
322 const compiler::FeedbackSource& value() { return saved_; }
323
324 private:
325 MaglevGraphBuilder* builder_;
326 compiler::FeedbackSource saved_;
327
328 static bool IsSpeculationAllowed(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
329 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source) {
330 if (!feedback_source.IsValid()) return false;
331 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
332 broker->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
333 if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) return false;
334 return processed_feedback.AsCall().speculation_mode() ==
335 SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation;
336 }
337};

339class V8_NODISCARD MaglevGraphBuilder::DeoptFrameScope {
340 public:
341 DeoptFrameScope(MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, Builtin continuation,
342 compiler::OptionalJSFunctionRef maybe_js_target = {})
343 : builder_(builder),
344 parent_(builder->current_deopt_scope_),
345 data_(DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData{
346 continuation, {}, builder->GetContext(), maybe_js_target}) {
347 builder_->current_interpreter_frame().virtual_objects().Snapshot();
348 builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = this;
349 builder_->AddDeoptUse(
350 data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>().context);
351 DCHECK(data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>()
352 .parameters.empty());
353 }
354
355 DeoptFrameScope(MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, Builtin continuation,
356 compiler::OptionalJSFunctionRef maybe_js_target,
357 base::Vector<ValueNode* const> parameters)
358 : builder_(builder),
359 parent_(builder->current_deopt_scope_),
360 data_(DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData{
361 continuation, builder->zone()->CloneVector(parameters),
362 builder->GetContext(), maybe_js_target}) {
363 builder_->current_interpreter_frame().virtual_objects().Snapshot();
364 builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = this;
365 builder_->AddDeoptUse(
366 data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>().context);
367 if (parameters.size() > 0) {
368 if (InlinedAllocation* receiver =
369 parameters[0]->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
370 // We escape the first argument, since the builtin continuation call can
371 // trigger a stack iteration, which expects the receiver to be a
372 // meterialized object.
373 receiver->ForceEscaping();
374 }
375 }
376 for (ValueNode* node :
377 data_.get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>().parameters) {
378 builder_->AddDeoptUse(node);
379 }
380 }
381
382 DeoptFrameScope(MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, ValueNode* receiver)
383 : builder_(builder),
384 parent_(builder->current_deopt_scope_),
385 data_(DeoptFrame::ConstructInvokeStubFrameData{
386 *builder->compilation_unit(), builder->current_source_position_,
387 receiver, builder->GetContext()}) {
388 builder_->current_interpreter_frame().virtual_objects().Snapshot();
389 builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = this;
390 builder_->AddDeoptUse(
391 data_.get<DeoptFrame::ConstructInvokeStubFrameData>().receiver);
392 builder_->AddDeoptUse(
393 data_.get<DeoptFrame::ConstructInvokeStubFrameData>().context);
394 }
395
396 ~DeoptFrameScope() {
397 builder_->current_deopt_scope_ = parent_;
398 // We might have cached a checkpointed frame which includes this scope;
399 // reset it just in case.
400 builder_->latest_checkpointed_frame_.reset();
401 }
402
403 DeoptFrameScope* parent() const { return parent_; }
404
405 bool IsLazyDeoptContinuationFrame() const {
406 if (data_.tag() != DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame) {
407 return false;
408 }
409 switch (data_.get<DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame>()
410 .builtin_id) {
411 case Builtin::kGetIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation:
412 case Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation:
413 case Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation:
414 case Builtin::kGenericLazyDeoptContinuation:
415 case Builtin::kToBooleanLazyDeoptContinuation:
416 return true;
417 default:
418 return false;
419 }
420 }
421
422 DeoptFrame::FrameData& data() { return data_; }
423 const DeoptFrame::FrameData& data() const { return data_; }
424
425 private:
426 MaglevGraphBuilder* builder_;
427 DeoptFrameScope* parent_;
428 DeoptFrame::FrameData data_;
429};

443class MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label {
444 public:
445 Label(MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_builder, int predecessor_count)
446 : predecessor_count_(predecessor_count),
447 liveness_(
448 sub_builder->builder_->zone()->New<compiler::BytecodeLivenessState>(
449 sub_builder->compilation_unit_->register_count(),
450 sub_builder->builder_->zone())) {}
451 Label(MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_builder, int predecessor_count,
452 std::initializer_list<Variable*> vars)
453 : Label(sub_builder, predecessor_count) {
454 for (Variable* var : vars) {
455 liveness_->MarkRegisterLive(var->pseudo_register_.index());
456 }
457 }
458
459 private:
460 explicit Label(MergePointInterpreterFrameState* merge_state,
461 BasicBlock* basic_block)
462 : merge_state_(merge_state), ref_(basic_block) {}
463
464 friend class MaglevSubGraphBuilder;
465 friend class BranchBuilder;
466 MergePointInterpreterFrameState* merge_state_ = nullptr;
467 int predecessor_count_ = -1;
468 compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness_ = nullptr;
469 BasicBlockRef ref_;
470};

484class MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::
485 BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs {
486 public:
487 explicit BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs(
488 MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_builder)
489 : sub_builder_(sub_builder) {
490 sub_builder_->TakeKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsFromParent();
491 }
492 ~BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs() {
493 sub_builder_->MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent();
494 }
495
496 private:
497 MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_builder_;

499
500void MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::StartFallthroughBlock(
501 BasicBlock* predecessor) {
502 switch (mode()) {
503 case kBytecodeJumpTarget: {
504 auto& data = data_.bytecode_target;
505 if (data.patch_accumulator_scope &&
506 (data.patch_accumulator_scope->node_ == builder_->GetAccumulator())) {
507 SetAccumulatorInBranch(BranchType::kBranchIfTrue);
508 builder_->MergeIntoFrameState(predecessor, data.jump_target_offset);
509 SetAccumulatorInBranch(BranchType::kBranchIfFalse);
510 builder_->StartFallthroughBlock(data.fallthrough_offset, predecessor);
511 } else {
512 builder_->MergeIntoFrameState(predecessor, data.jump_target_offset);
513 builder_->StartFallthroughBlock(data.fallthrough_offset, predecessor);
514 }
515 break;
516 }
517 case kLabelJumpTarget:
518 auto& data = data_.label_target;
519 sub_builder_->MergeIntoLabel(data.jump_label, predecessor);
520 builder_->StartNewBlock(predecessor, nullptr, data.fallthrough);
521 break;
522 }
523}
524
525void MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::SetAccumulatorInBranch(
526 BranchType jump_type) const {
527 DCHECK_EQ(mode(), kBytecodeJumpTarget);
528 auto& data = data_.bytecode_target;
529 if (branch_specialization_mode_ == BranchSpecializationMode::kAlwaysBoolean) {
530 builder_->SetAccumulatorInBranch(builder_->GetBooleanConstant(
531 data.patch_accumulator_scope->jump_type_ == jump_type));
532 } else if (data.patch_accumulator_scope->jump_type_ == jump_type) {
533 builder_->SetAccumulatorInBranch(
534 builder_->GetRootConstant(data.patch_accumulator_scope->root_index_));
535 } else {
536 builder_->SetAccumulatorInBranch(data.patch_accumulator_scope->node_);
537 }
538}
539
540BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::jump_target() {
541 switch (mode()) {
542 case kBytecodeJumpTarget:
543 return &builder_->jump_targets_[data_.bytecode_target.jump_target_offset];
544 case kLabelJumpTarget:
545 return &data_.label_target.jump_label->ref_;
546 }
547}
548
549BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::fallthrough() {
550 switch (mode()) {
551 case kBytecodeJumpTarget:
552 return &builder_->jump_targets_[data_.bytecode_target.fallthrough_offset];
553 case kLabelJumpTarget:
554 return &data_.label_target.fallthrough;
555 }
556}
557
558BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::true_target() {
559 return jump_type_ == BranchType::kBranchIfTrue ? jump_target()
560 : fallthrough();
561}
562
563BasicBlockRef* MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::false_target() {
564 return jump_type_ == BranchType::kBranchIfFalse ? jump_target()
565 : fallthrough();
566}
567
568MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::FromBool(
569 bool value) const {
570 switch (mode()) {
571 case kBytecodeJumpTarget: {
572 BranchType type_if_need_to_jump =
573 (value ? BranchType::kBranchIfTrue : BranchType::kBranchIfFalse);
574 builder_->MarkBranchDeadAndJumpIfNeeded(jump_type_ ==
575 type_if_need_to_jump);
576 return BranchResult::kDefault;
577 }
578 case kLabelJumpTarget:
579 return value ? BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue : BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse;
580 }
581}
582
583template <typename ControlNodeT, typename... Args>
584MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchBuilder::Build(
585 std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> control_inputs, Args&&... args) {
586 static_assert(IsConditionalControlNode(Node::opcode_of<ControlNodeT>));
587 BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<ControlNodeT>(
588 control_inputs, std::forward<Args>(args)..., true_target(),
589 false_target());
590 StartFallthroughBlock(block);
591 return BranchResult::kDefault;
592}
593
594MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder(
595 MaglevGraphBuilder* builder, int variable_count)
596 : builder_(builder),
597 compilation_unit_(MaglevCompilationUnit::NewDummy(
598 builder->zone(), builder->compilation_unit(), variable_count, 0, 0)),
599 pseudo_frame_(*compilation_unit_, nullptr, VirtualObject::List()) {
600 // We need to set a context, since this is unconditional in the frame state,
601 // so set it to the real context.
602 pseudo_frame_.set(interpreter::Register::current_context(),
603 builder_->current_interpreter_frame().get(
604 interpreter::Register::current_context()));
605 DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
606}
607
608MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::LoopLabel
609MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::BeginLoop(
610 std::initializer_list<Variable*> loop_vars) {
611 // Create fake liveness and loop info for the loop, with all given loop vars
612 // set to be live and assigned inside the loop.
613 compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* loop_header_liveness =
614 builder_->zone()->New<compiler::BytecodeLivenessState>(
615 compilation_unit_->register_count(), builder_->zone());
616 compiler::LoopInfo* loop_info = builder_->zone()->New<compiler::LoopInfo>(
617 -1, 0, kMaxInt, compilation_unit_->parameter_count(),
618 compilation_unit_->register_count(), builder_->zone());
619 for (Variable* var : loop_vars) {
620 loop_header_liveness->MarkRegisterLive(var->pseudo_register_.index());
621 loop_info->assignments().Add(var->pseudo_register_);
622 }
623
624 // Finish the current block, jumping (as a fallthrough) to the loop header.
625 BasicBlockRef loop_header_ref;
626 BasicBlock* loop_predecessor =
627 builder_->FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &loop_header_ref);
628
629 // Create a state for the loop header, with two predecessors (the above jump
630 // and the back edge), and initialise with the current state.
631 MergePointInterpreterFrameState* loop_state =
632 MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForLoop(
633 pseudo_frame_, *compilation_unit_, 0, 2, loop_header_liveness,
634 loop_info);
635
636 {
637 BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs borrow(this);
638 loop_state->Merge(builder_, *compilation_unit_, pseudo_frame_,
639 loop_predecessor);
640 }
641
642 // Start a new basic block for the loop.
643 DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
644 pseudo_frame_.CopyFrom(*compilation_unit_, *loop_state);
645 MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent();
646
647 builder_->ProcessMergePointPredecessors(*loop_state, loop_header_ref);
648 builder_->StartNewBlock(nullptr, loop_state, loop_header_ref);
649
650 return LoopLabel{loop_state, loop_header_ref.block_ptr()};
651}
652
653template <typename ControlNodeT, typename... Args>
654void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::GotoIfTrue(
655 Label* true_target, std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> control_inputs,
656 Args&&... args) {
657 static_assert(IsConditionalControlNode(Node::opcode_of<ControlNodeT>));
658
659 BasicBlockRef fallthrough_ref;
660
661 // Pass through to FinishBlock, converting Labels to BasicBlockRefs and the
662 // fallthrough label to the fallthrough ref.
663 BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<ControlNodeT>(
664 control_inputs, std::forward<Args>(args)..., &true_target->ref_,
665 &fallthrough_ref);
666
667 MergeIntoLabel(true_target, block);
668
669 builder_->StartNewBlock(block, nullptr, fallthrough_ref);
670}
671
672template <typename ControlNodeT, typename... Args>
673void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::GotoIfFalse(
674 Label* false_target, std::initializer_list<ValueNode*> control_inputs,
675 Args&&... args) {
676 static_assert(IsConditionalControlNode(Node::opcode_of<ControlNodeT>));
677
678 BasicBlockRef fallthrough_ref;
679
680 // Pass through to FinishBlock, converting Labels to BasicBlockRefs and the
681 // fallthrough label to the fallthrough ref.
682 BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<ControlNodeT>(
683 control_inputs, std::forward<Args>(args)..., &fallthrough_ref,
684 &false_target->ref_);
685
686 MergeIntoLabel(false_target, block);
687
688 builder_->StartNewBlock(block, nullptr, fallthrough_ref);
689}
690
691void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::GotoOrTrim(Label* label) {
692 if (builder_->current_block_ == nullptr) {
693 ReducePredecessorCount(label);
694 return;
695 }
696 Goto(label);
697}
698
699void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Goto(Label* label) {
700 CHECK_NOT_NULL(builder_->current_block_);
701 BasicBlock* block = builder_->FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &label->ref_);
702 MergeIntoLabel(label, block);
703}
704
705void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::ReducePredecessorCount(
706 Label* label, unsigned num) {
707 DCHECK_GE(label->predecessor_count_, num);
708 if (num == 0) {
709 return;
710 }
711 label->predecessor_count_ -= num;
712 if (label->merge_state_ != nullptr) {
713 label->merge_state_->MergeDead(*compilation_unit_, num);
714 }
715}
716
717void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::EndLoop(LoopLabel* loop_label) {
718 if (builder_->current_block_ == nullptr) {
719 loop_label->merge_state_->MergeDeadLoop(*compilation_unit_);
720 return;
721 }
722
723 BasicBlock* block =
724 builder_->FinishBlock<JumpLoop>({}, loop_label->loop_header_);
725 {
726 BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs borrow(this);
727 loop_label->merge_state_->MergeLoop(builder_, *compilation_unit_,
728 pseudo_frame_, block);
729 }
730 block->set_predecessor_id(loop_label->merge_state_->predecessor_count() - 1);
731}
732
733ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::TrimPredecessorsAndBind(
734 Label* label) {
735 int predecessors_so_far = label->merge_state_ == nullptr
736 ? 0
737 : label->merge_state_->predecessors_so_far();
738 DCHECK_LE(predecessors_so_far, label->predecessor_count_);
739 builder_->current_block_ = nullptr;
740 ReducePredecessorCount(label,
741 label->predecessor_count_ - predecessors_so_far);
742 if (predecessors_so_far == 0) return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
743 Bind(label);
744 return ReduceResult::Done();
745}
746
747void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Bind(Label* label) {
748 DCHECK_NULL(builder_->current_block_);
749
750 DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
751 pseudo_frame_.CopyFrom(*compilation_unit_, *label->merge_state_);
752 MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent();
753
754 CHECK_EQ(label->merge_state_->predecessors_so_far(),
755 label->predecessor_count_);
756
757 builder_->ProcessMergePointPredecessors(*label->merge_state_, label->ref_);
758 builder_->StartNewBlock(nullptr, label->merge_state_, label->ref_);
759}
760
761void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::set(Variable& var,
762 ValueNode* value) {
763 pseudo_frame_.set(var.pseudo_register_, value);
764}
765ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::get(
766 const Variable& var) const {
767 return pseudo_frame_.get(var.pseudo_register_);
768}
769
770template <typename FCond, typename FTrue, typename FFalse>
771ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Branch(
772 std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*> vars, FCond cond,
773 FTrue if_true, FFalse if_false) {
774 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label else_branch(this, 1);
775 BranchBuilder builder(builder_, this, BranchType::kBranchIfFalse,
776 &else_branch);
777 BranchResult branch_result = cond(builder);
778 if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue) {
779 return if_true();
780 }
781 if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse) {
782 return if_false();
783 }
784 DCHECK(branch_result == BranchResult::kDefault);
785 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(this, 2, vars);
786 MaybeReduceResult result_if_true = if_true();
787 CHECK(result_if_true.IsDone());
788 GotoOrTrim(&done);
789 Bind(&else_branch);
790 MaybeReduceResult result_if_false = if_false();
791 CHECK(result_if_false.IsDone());
792 if (result_if_true.IsDoneWithAbort() && result_if_false.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
793 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
794 }
795 GotoOrTrim(&done);
796 Bind(&done);
797 return ReduceResult::Done();
798}
799
800template <typename FCond, typename FTrue, typename FFalse>
801ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::Select(FCond cond, FTrue if_true,
802 FFalse if_false) {
803 MaglevSubGraphBuilder subgraph(this, 1);
804 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label else_branch(&subgraph, 1);
805 BranchBuilder builder(this, &subgraph, BranchType::kBranchIfFalse,
806 &else_branch);
807 BranchResult branch_result = cond(builder);
808 if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue) {
809 return if_true();
810 }
811 if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse) {
812 return if_false();
813 }
814 DCHECK(branch_result == BranchResult::kDefault);
815 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable ret_val(0);
816 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(&subgraph, 2, {&ret_val});
817 subgraph.set(ret_val, if_true());
818 subgraph.Goto(&done);
819 subgraph.Bind(&else_branch);
820 subgraph.set(ret_val, if_false());
821 subgraph.Goto(&done);
822 subgraph.Bind(&done);
823 return subgraph.get(ret_val);
824}
825
826template <typename FCond, typename FTrue, typename FFalse>
827MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::SelectReduction(FCond cond, FTrue if_true,
828 FFalse if_false) {
829 MaglevSubGraphBuilder subgraph(this, 1);
830 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label else_branch(&subgraph, 1);
831 BranchBuilder builder(this, &subgraph, BranchType::kBranchIfFalse,
832 &else_branch);
833 BranchResult branch_result = cond(builder);
834 if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysTrue) {
835 return if_true();
836 }
837 if (branch_result == BranchResult::kAlwaysFalse) {
838 return if_false();
839 }
840 DCHECK(branch_result == BranchResult::kDefault);
841 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable ret_val(0);
842 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(&subgraph, 2, {&ret_val});
843 MaybeReduceResult result_if_true = if_true();
844 CHECK(result_if_true.IsDone());
845 if (result_if_true.IsDoneWithValue()) {
846 subgraph.set(ret_val, result_if_true.value());
847 }
848 subgraph.GotoOrTrim(&done);
849 subgraph.Bind(&else_branch);
850 MaybeReduceResult result_if_false = if_false();
851 CHECK(result_if_false.IsDone());
852 if (result_if_true.IsDoneWithAbort() && result_if_false.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
853 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
854 }
855 if (result_if_false.IsDoneWithValue()) {
856 subgraph.set(ret_val, result_if_false.value());
857 }
858 subgraph.GotoOrTrim(&done);
859 subgraph.Bind(&done);
860 return subgraph.get(ret_val);
861}
862
863// Known node aspects for the pseudo frame are null aside from when merging --
864// before each merge, we should borrow the node aspects from the parent
865// builder, and after each merge point, we should copy the node aspects back
866// to the parent. This is so that the parent graph builder can update its own
867// known node aspects without having to worry about this pseudo frame.
868void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::
869 TakeKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsFromParent() {
870 DCHECK_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
871 DCHECK(pseudo_frame_.virtual_objects().is_empty());
872 pseudo_frame_.set_known_node_aspects(
873 builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects());
874 pseudo_frame_.set_virtual_objects(
875 builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects());
876}
877
878void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::
879 MoveKnownNodeAspectsAndVOsToParent() {
880 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
881 builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.set_known_node_aspects(
882 pseudo_frame_.known_node_aspects());
883 pseudo_frame_.clear_known_node_aspects();
884 builder_->current_interpreter_frame_.set_virtual_objects(
885 pseudo_frame_.virtual_objects());
886 pseudo_frame_.set_virtual_objects(VirtualObject::List());
887}
888
889void MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevSubGraphBuilder::MergeIntoLabel(
890 Label* label, BasicBlock* predecessor) {
891 BorrowParentKnownNodeAspectsAndVOs borrow(this);
892
893 if (label->merge_state_ == nullptr) {
894 // If there's no merge state, allocate a new one.
895 label->merge_state_ = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::New(
896 *compilation_unit_, pseudo_frame_, 0, label->predecessor_count_,
897 predecessor, label->liveness_);
898 } else {
899 // If there already is a frame state, merge.
900 label->merge_state_->Merge(builder_, *compilation_unit_, pseudo_frame_,
901 predecessor);
902 }
903}
904
905MaglevGraphBuilder::MaglevGraphBuilder(
906 LocalIsolate* local_isolate, MaglevCompilationUnit* compilation_unit,
907 Graph* graph, float call_frequency, BytecodeOffset caller_bytecode_offset,
908 bool caller_is_inside_loop, int inlining_id, MaglevGraphBuilder* parent)
909 : local_isolate_(local_isolate),
910 compilation_unit_(compilation_unit),
911 parent_(parent),
912 graph_(graph),
913 bytecode_analysis_(bytecode().object(), zone(),
914 compilation_unit->osr_offset(), true),
915 iterator_(bytecode().object()),
916 source_position_iterator_(bytecode().SourcePositionTable(broker())),
917 allow_loop_peeling_(v8_flags.maglev_loop_peeling),
918 loop_effects_stack_(zone()),
919 decremented_predecessor_offsets_(zone()),
920 loop_headers_to_peel_(bytecode().length(), zone()),
921 current_source_position_(SourcePosition(
922 compilation_unit_->shared_function_info().StartPosition(),
923 inlining_id)),
924 call_frequency_(call_frequency),
925 // Add an extra jump_target slot for the inline exit if needed.
926 jump_targets_(zone()->AllocateArray<BasicBlockRef>(
927 bytecode().length() + (is_inline() ? 1 : 0))),
928 // Overallocate merge_states_ by one to allow always looking up the
929 // next offset. This overallocated slot can also be used for the inline
930 // exit when needed.
931 merge_states_(zone()->AllocateArray<MergePointInterpreterFrameState*>(
932 bytecode().length() + 1)),
933 current_interpreter_frame_(
934 *compilation_unit_,
935 is_inline() ? parent->current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects()
936 : compilation_unit_->zone()->New<KnownNodeAspects>(
937 compilation_unit_->zone()),
938 is_inline() ? parent->current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects()
939 : VirtualObject::List()),
940 caller_bytecode_offset_(caller_bytecode_offset),
941 caller_is_inside_loop_(caller_is_inside_loop),
942 entrypoint_(compilation_unit->is_osr()
943 ? bytecode_analysis_.osr_entry_point()
944 : 0),
945 inlining_id_(inlining_id),
946 catch_block_stack_(zone()),
947 unobserved_context_slot_stores_(zone()) {
948 memset(merge_states_, 0,
949 (bytecode().length() + 1) * sizeof(InterpreterFrameState*));
950 // Default construct basic block refs.
951 // TODO(leszeks): This could be a memset of nullptr to ..._jump_targets_.
952 for (int i = 0; i < bytecode().length(); ++i) {
953 new (&jump_targets_[i]) BasicBlockRef();
954 }
955
956 if (is_inline()) {
957 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(parent_);
958 DCHECK_GT(compilation_unit->inlining_depth(), 0);
959 // The allocation/initialisation logic here relies on inline_exit_offset
960 // being the offset one past the end of the bytecode.
961 DCHECK_EQ(inline_exit_offset(), bytecode().length());
962 merge_states_[inline_exit_offset()] = nullptr;
963 new (&jump_targets_[inline_exit_offset()]) BasicBlockRef();
964 if (parent_->loop_effects_) {
965 loop_effects_ = parent->loop_effects_;
966 loop_effects_stack_.push_back(loop_effects_);
967 }
968 unobserved_context_slot_stores_ = parent_->unobserved_context_slot_stores_;
969 }
970
971 CHECK_IMPLIES(compilation_unit_->is_osr(), graph_->is_osr());
972 CHECK_EQ(compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_osr_offset() !=
973 BytecodeOffset::None(),
974 graph_->is_osr());
975 if (compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
976 CHECK(!is_inline());
977
978 // Make sure that we're at a valid OSR entrypoint.
979 //
980 // This is also a defense-in-depth check to make sure that we're not
981 // compiling invalid bytecode if the OSR offset is wrong (e.g. because it
982 // belongs to different bytecode).
983 //
984 // OSR'ing into the middle of a loop is currently not supported. There
985 // should not be any issue with OSR'ing outside of loops, just we currently
986 // dont do it...
987 interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode().object());
988 it.AdvanceTo(compilation_unit_->osr_offset().ToInt());
989 CHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
990 CHECK_EQ(entrypoint_, it.GetJumpTargetOffset());
991
992 iterator_.AdvanceTo(entrypoint_);
993
994 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
995 std::cout << "- Non-standard entrypoint @" << entrypoint_
996 << " by OSR from @" << compilation_unit_->osr_offset().ToInt()
997 << std::endl;
998 }
999 }
1000 CHECK_IMPLIES(!compilation_unit_->is_osr(), entrypoint_ == 0);
1001
1002 CalculatePredecessorCounts();
1003}
1004
1005void MaglevGraphBuilder::StartPrologue() {
1006 current_block_ = zone()->New<BasicBlock>(nullptr, zone());
1007}
1008
1009BasicBlock* MaglevGraphBuilder::EndPrologue() {
1010 BasicBlock* first_block;
1011 if (!is_inline() &&
1012 (v8_flags.maglev_hoist_osr_value_phi_untagging && graph_->is_osr())) {
1013 first_block =
1014 FinishBlock<CheckpointedJump>({}, &jump_targets_[entrypoint_]);
1015 } else {
1016 first_block = FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[entrypoint_]);
1017 }
1018 MergeIntoFrameState(first_block, entrypoint_);
1019 return first_block;
1020}
1021
1022void MaglevGraphBuilder::SetArgument(int i, ValueNode* value) {
1023 interpreter::Register reg = interpreter::Register::FromParameterIndex(i);
1024 current_interpreter_frame_.set(reg, value);
1025}
1026
1027ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetArgument(int i) {
1028 DCHECK_LT(i, parameter_count());
1029 interpreter::Register reg = interpreter::Register::FromParameterIndex(i);
1030 return current_interpreter_frame_.get(reg);
1031}
1032
1033ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInlinedArgument(int i) {
1034 DCHECK(is_inline());
1035 DCHECK_LT(i, argument_count());
1036 return inlined_arguments_[i];
1037}
1038
1039void MaglevGraphBuilder::InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register reg,
1040 ValueNode* value) {
1041 current_interpreter_frame_.set(
1042 reg, value ? value : AddNewNode<InitialValue>({}, reg));
1043}
1044
1045void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildRegisterFrameInitialization(
1046 ValueNode* context, ValueNode* closure, ValueNode* new_target) {
1047 if (closure == nullptr &&
1048 compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context()) {
1049 compiler::JSFunctionRef function = compiler::MakeRefAssumeMemoryFence(
1050 broker(), broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
1051 compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_function()));
1052 closure = GetConstant(function);
1053 context = GetConstant(function.context(broker()));
1054 }
1055 InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register::current_context(), context);
1056 InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register::function_closure(), closure);
1057
1058 interpreter::Register new_target_or_generator_register =
1059 bytecode().incoming_new_target_or_generator_register();
1060
1061 int register_index = 0;
1062
1063 if (compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
1064 for (; register_index < register_count(); register_index++) {
1065 auto val =
1066 AddNewNode<InitialValue>({}, interpreter::Register(register_index));
1067 InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register(register_index), val);
1068 graph_->osr_values().push_back(val);
1069 }
1070 return;
1071 }
1072
1073 // TODO(leszeks): Don't emit if not needed.
1074 ValueNode* undefined_value = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
1075 if (new_target_or_generator_register.is_valid()) {
1076 int new_target_index = new_target_or_generator_register.index();
1077 for (; register_index < new_target_index; register_index++) {
1078 current_interpreter_frame_.set(interpreter::Register(register_index),
1079 undefined_value);
1080 }
1081 current_interpreter_frame_.set(
1082 new_target_or_generator_register,
1083 new_target ? new_target
1084 : GetRegisterInput(kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister));
1085 register_index++;
1086 }
1087 for (; register_index < register_count(); register_index++) {
1088 InitializeRegister(interpreter::Register(register_index), undefined_value);
1089 }
1090}
1091
1092void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildMergeStates() {
1093 auto offset_and_info = bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfos().begin();
1094 auto end = bytecode_analysis().GetLoopInfos().end();
1095 while (offset_and_info != end && offset_and_info->first < entrypoint_) {
1096 ++offset_and_info;
1097 }
1098 for (; offset_and_info != end; ++offset_and_info) {
1099 int offset = offset_and_info->first;
1100 const compiler::LoopInfo& loop_info = offset_and_info->second;
1101 if (loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(offset)) {
1102 // Peeled loops are treated like normal merges at first. We will construct
1103 // the proper loop header merge state when reaching the `JumpLoop` of the
1104 // peeled iteration.
1105 continue;
1106 }
1107 const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetInLivenessFor(offset);
1108 DCHECK_NULL(merge_states_[offset]);
1109 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
1110 std::cout << "- Creating loop merge state at @" << offset << std::endl;
1111 }
1112 merge_states_[offset] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForLoop(
1113 current_interpreter_frame_, *compilation_unit_, offset,
1114 predecessor_count(offset), liveness, &loop_info);
1115 }
1116
1117 if (bytecode().handler_table_size() > 0) {
1118 HandlerTable table(*bytecode().object());
1119 for (int i = 0; i < table.NumberOfRangeEntries(); i++) {
1120 const int offset = table.GetRangeHandler(i);
1121 const bool was_used = table.HandlerWasUsed(i);
1122 const interpreter::Register context_reg(table.GetRangeData(i));
1123 const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
1124 GetInLivenessFor(offset);
1125 DCHECK_EQ(predecessor_count(offset), 0);
1126 DCHECK_NULL(merge_states_[offset]);
1127 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
1128 std::cout << "- Creating exception merge state at @" << offset
1129 << (was_used ? "" : " (never used)") << ", context register r"
1130 << context_reg.index() << std::endl;
1131 }
1132 merge_states_[offset] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForCatchBlock(
1133 *compilation_unit_, liveness, offset, was_used, context_reg, graph_);
1134 }
1135 }
1136}
1137
1138namespace {
1139
1140template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1141struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper;
1142
1143// Terminal cases
1144template <int index>
1145struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<index> {
1146 static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1147 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1148 // TODO(leszeks): This should probably actually be "UNREACHABLE" but we have
1149 // lazy deopt info for interrupt budget updates at returns, not for actual
1150 // lazy deopts, but just for stack iteration purposes.
1151 return {interpreter::Register::invalid_value(), 0};
1152 }
1153 static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return false; }
1154};
1155
1156template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1157struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOut,
1158 operands...> {
1159 static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1160 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1161 // We shouldn't have any other output operands than this one.
1162 return {iterator.GetRegisterOperand(index), 1};
1163 }
1164 static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1165};
1166
1167template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1168struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1169 index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOutPair, operands...> {
1170 static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1171 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1172 // We shouldn't have any other output operands than this one.
1173 return {iterator.GetRegisterOperand(index), 2};
1174 }
1175 static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1176};
1177
1178template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1179struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1180 index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOutTriple, operands...> {
1181 static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1182 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1183 // We shouldn't have any other output operands than this one.
1184 DCHECK(!(GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1185 index + 1, operands...>::HasOutputRegisterOperand()));
1186 return {iterator.GetRegisterOperand(index), 3};
1187 }
1188 static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1189};
1190
1191// We don't support RegOutList for lazy deopts.
1192template <int index, interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1193struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1194 index, interpreter::OperandType::kRegOutList, operands...> {
1195 static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1196 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1197 interpreter::RegisterList list = iterator.GetRegisterListOperand(index);
1198 return {list.first_register(), list.register_count()};
1199 }
1200 static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() { return true; }
1201};
1202
1203// Induction case.
1204template <int index, interpreter::OperandType operand,
1205 interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1206struct GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<index, operand, operands...> {
1207 static std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSize(
1208 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1209 return GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1210 index + 1, operands...>::GetResultLocationAndSize(iterator);
1211 }
1212 static bool HasOutputRegisterOperand() {
1213 return GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1214 index + 1, operands...>::HasOutputRegisterOperand();
1215 }
1216};
1217
1218template <interpreter::Bytecode bytecode,
1219 interpreter::ImplicitRegisterUse implicit_use,
1220 interpreter::OperandType... operands>
1221std::pair<interpreter::Register, int> GetResultLocationAndSizeForBytecode(
1222 const interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator& iterator) {
1223 // We don't support output registers for implicit registers.
1224 DCHECK(!interpreter::BytecodeOperands::WritesImplicitRegister(implicit_use));
1225 if (interpreter::BytecodeOperands::WritesAccumulator(implicit_use)) {
1226 // If we write the accumulator, we shouldn't also write an output register.
1227 DCHECK(!(GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1228 0, operands...>::HasOutputRegisterOperand()));
1229 return {interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(), 1};
1230 }
1231
1232 // Use template magic to output a the appropriate GetRegisterOperand call and
1233 // size for this bytecode.
1234 return GetResultLocationAndSizeHelper<
1235 0, operands...>::GetResultLocationAndSize(iterator);
1236}
1237
1238} // namespace
1239
1240std::pair<interpreter::Register, int>
1241MaglevGraphBuilder::GetResultLocationAndSize() const {
1242 using Bytecode = interpreter::Bytecode;
1243 using OperandType = interpreter::OperandType;
1244 using ImplicitRegisterUse = interpreter::ImplicitRegisterUse;
1245 Bytecode bytecode = iterator_.current_bytecode();
1246 // TODO(leszeks): Only emit these cases for bytecodes we know can lazy deopt.
1247 switch (bytecode) {
1248#define CASE(Name, ...) \
1249 case Bytecode::k##Name: \
1250 return GetResultLocationAndSizeForBytecode<Bytecode::k##Name, \
1251 __VA_ARGS__>(iterator_);
1252 BYTECODE_LIST(CASE, CASE)
1253#undef CASE
1254 }
1255 UNREACHABLE();
1256}
1257
1258#ifdef DEBUG
1259bool MaglevGraphBuilder::HasOutputRegister(interpreter::Register reg) const {
1260 interpreter::Bytecode bytecode = iterator_.current_bytecode();
1261 if (reg == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1262 return interpreter::Bytecodes::WritesAccumulator(bytecode);
1263 }
1264 for (int i = 0; i < interpreter::Bytecodes::NumberOfOperands(bytecode); ++i) {
1265 if (interpreter::Bytecodes::IsRegisterOutputOperandType(
1266 interpreter::Bytecodes::GetOperandType(bytecode, i))) {
1267 interpreter::Register operand_reg = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(i);
1268 int operand_range = iterator_.GetRegisterOperandRange(i);
1269 if (base::IsInRange(reg.index(), operand_reg.index(),
1270 operand_reg.index() + operand_range)) {
1271 return true;
1272 }
1273 }
1274 }
1275 return false;
1276}
1277#endif
1278
1279DeoptFrame* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetParentDeoptFrame() {
1280 if (parent_ == nullptr) return nullptr;
1281 if (parent_deopt_frame_ == nullptr) {
1282 // The parent resumes after the call, which is roughly equivalent to a lazy
1283 // deopt. Use the helper function directly so that we can mark the
1284 // accumulator as dead (since it'll be overwritten by this function's
1285 // return value anyway).
1286 // TODO(leszeks): This is true for our current set of
1287 // inlinings/continuations, but there might be cases in the future where it
1288 // isn't. We may need to store the relevant overwritten register in
1289 // LazyDeoptFrameScope.
1290 DCHECK(interpreter::Bytecodes::WritesAccumulator(
1291 parent_->iterator_.current_bytecode()));
1292
1293 parent_deopt_frame_ =
1294 zone()->New<DeoptFrame>(parent_->GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(
1295 interpreter::Register::invalid_value(), 0,
1296 parent_->current_deopt_scope_, true));
1297 // Only create InlinedArgumentsDeoptFrame if we have a mismatch between
1298 // formal parameter and arguments count.
1299 if (HasMismatchedArgumentAndParameterCount()) {
1300 parent_deopt_frame_ = zone()->New<InlinedArgumentsDeoptFrame>(
1301 *compilation_unit_, caller_bytecode_offset_, GetClosure(),
1302 inlined_arguments_, parent_deopt_frame_);
1303 AddDeoptUse(GetClosure());
1304 for (ValueNode* arg :
1305 parent_deopt_frame_->as_inlined_arguments().arguments()) {
1306 AddDeoptUse(arg);
1307 }
1308 }
1309 }
1310 return parent_deopt_frame_;
1311}
1312
1313DeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetLatestCheckpointedFrame() {
1314 if (in_prologue_) {
1315 return GetDeoptFrameForEntryStackCheck();
1316 }
1317 if (!latest_checkpointed_frame_) {
1318 current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().Snapshot();
1319 latest_checkpointed_frame_.emplace(InterpretedDeoptFrame(
1320 *compilation_unit_,
1321 zone()->New<CompactInterpreterFrameState>(
1322 *compilation_unit_, GetInLiveness(), current_interpreter_frame_),
1323 GetClosure(), BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()),
1324 current_source_position_, GetParentDeoptFrame()));
1325
1326 latest_checkpointed_frame_->as_interpreted().frame_state()->ForEachValue(
1327 *compilation_unit_,
1328 [&](ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register) { AddDeoptUse(node); });
1329 AddDeoptUse(latest_checkpointed_frame_->as_interpreted().closure());
1330
1331 // Skip lazy deopt builtin continuations.
1332 const DeoptFrameScope* deopt_scope = current_deopt_scope_;
1333 while (deopt_scope != nullptr &&
1334 deopt_scope->IsLazyDeoptContinuationFrame()) {
1335 deopt_scope = deopt_scope->parent();
1336 }
1337
1338 if (deopt_scope != nullptr) {
1339 // Support exactly one eager deopt builtin continuation. This can be
1340 // expanded in the future if necessary.
1341 DCHECK_NULL(deopt_scope->parent());
1342 DCHECK_EQ(deopt_scope->data().tag(),
1343 DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame);
1344#ifdef DEBUG
1345 if (deopt_scope->data().tag() ==
1346 DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame) {
1347 const DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData& frame =
1348 deopt_scope->data().get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>();
1349 if (frame.maybe_js_target) {
1350 int stack_parameter_count =
1351 Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(frame.builtin_id);
1352 DCHECK_EQ(stack_parameter_count, frame.parameters.length());
1353 } else {
1354 CallInterfaceDescriptor descriptor =
1355 Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(frame.builtin_id);
1356 DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetParameterCount(), frame.parameters.length());
1357 }
1358 }
1359#endif
1360
1361 // Wrap the above frame in the scope frame.
1362 latest_checkpointed_frame_.emplace(
1363 deopt_scope->data(),
1364 zone()->New<DeoptFrame>(*latest_checkpointed_frame_));
1365 }
1366 }
1367 return *latest_checkpointed_frame_;
1368}
1369
1370DeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeopt(
1371 interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) {
1372 return GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(result_location, result_size,
1373 current_deopt_scope_, false);
1374}
1375
1376DeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(
1377 interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size,
1378 DeoptFrameScope* scope, bool mark_accumulator_dead) {
1379 if (scope == nullptr) {
1380 compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
1381 zone()->New<compiler::BytecodeLivenessState>(*GetOutLiveness(), zone());
1382 // Remove result locations from liveness.
1383 if (result_location == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1384 DCHECK_EQ(result_size, 1);
1385 liveness->MarkAccumulatorDead();
1386 mark_accumulator_dead = false;
1387 } else {
1388 DCHECK(!result_location.is_parameter());
1389 for (int i = 0; i < result_size; i++) {
1390 liveness->MarkRegisterDead(result_location.index() + i);
1391 }
1392 }
1393 // Explicitly drop the accumulator if needed.
1394 if (mark_accumulator_dead && liveness->AccumulatorIsLive()) {
1395 liveness->MarkAccumulatorDead();
1396 }
1397 current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().Snapshot();
1398 InterpretedDeoptFrame ret(
1399 *compilation_unit_,
1400 zone()->New<CompactInterpreterFrameState>(*compilation_unit_, liveness,
1401 current_interpreter_frame_),
1402 GetClosure(), BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()),
1403 current_source_position_, GetParentDeoptFrame());
1404 ret.frame_state()->ForEachValue(
1405 *compilation_unit_, [this](ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register reg) {
1406 // Receiver and closure values have to be materialized, even if
1407 // they don't otherwise escape.
1408 if (reg == interpreter::Register::receiver() ||
1409 reg == interpreter::Register::function_closure()) {
1410 node->add_use();
1411 } else {
1412 AddDeoptUse(node);
1413 }
1414 });
1415 AddDeoptUse(ret.closure());
1416 return ret;
1417 }
1418
1419 // Currently only support builtin continuations for bytecodes that write to
1420 // the accumulator
1421 DCHECK(interpreter::Bytecodes::WritesOrClobbersAccumulator(
1422 iterator_.current_bytecode()));
1423
1424#ifdef DEBUG
1425 if (scope->data().tag() == DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame) {
1426 const DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData& frame =
1427 current_deopt_scope_->data()
1428 .get<DeoptFrame::BuiltinContinuationFrameData>();
1429 if (frame.maybe_js_target) {
1430 int stack_parameter_count =
1431 Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(frame.builtin_id);
1432 // The deopt input value is passed by the deoptimizer, so shouldn't be a
1433 // parameter here.
1434 DCHECK_EQ(stack_parameter_count, frame.parameters.length() + 1);
1435 } else {
1436 CallInterfaceDescriptor descriptor =
1437 Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(frame.builtin_id);
1438 // The deopt input value is passed by the deoptimizer, so shouldn't be a
1439 // parameter here.
1440 DCHECK_EQ(descriptor.GetParameterCount(), frame.parameters.length() + 1);
1441 // The deopt input value is passed on the stack.
1442 DCHECK_GT(descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(), 0);
1443 }
1444 }
1445#endif
1446
1447 // Mark the accumulator dead in parent frames since we know that the
1448 // continuation will write it.
1449 return DeoptFrame(scope->data(),
1450 zone()->New<DeoptFrame>(GetDeoptFrameForLazyDeoptHelper(
1451 result_location, result_size, scope->parent(),
1452 scope->data().tag() ==
1453 DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame)));
1454}
1455
1456InterpretedDeoptFrame MaglevGraphBuilder::GetDeoptFrameForEntryStackCheck() {
1457 if (entry_stack_check_frame_) return *entry_stack_check_frame_;
1458 DCHECK_EQ(iterator_.current_offset(), entrypoint_);
1459 DCHECK_NULL(parent_);
1460 entry_stack_check_frame_.emplace(
1461 *compilation_unit_,
1462 zone()->New<CompactInterpreterFrameState>(
1463 *compilation_unit_,
1464 GetInLivenessFor(graph_->is_osr() ? bailout_for_entrypoint() : 0),
1465 current_interpreter_frame_),
1466 GetClosure(), BytecodeOffset(bailout_for_entrypoint()),
1467 current_source_position_, nullptr);
1468
1469 (*entry_stack_check_frame_)
1470 .frame_state()
1471 ->ForEachValue(
1472 *compilation_unit_,
1473 [&](ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register) { AddDeoptUse(node); });
1474 AddDeoptUse((*entry_stack_check_frame_).closure());
1475 return *entry_stack_check_frame_;
1476}
1477
1478ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetTaggedValue(
1479 ValueNode* value, UseReprHintRecording record_use_repr_hint) {
1480 if (V8_LIKELY(record_use_repr_hint == UseReprHintRecording::kRecord)) {
1481 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTagged);
1482 }
1483
1484 ValueRepresentation representation =
1485 value->properties().value_representation();
1486 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kTagged) return value;
1487
1488 if (Int32Constant* as_int32_constant = value->TryCast<Int32Constant>();
1489 as_int32_constant && Smi::IsValid(as_int32_constant->value())) {
1490 return GetSmiConstant(as_int32_constant->value());
1491 }
1492
1493 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1494 auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1495
1496 if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.tagged()) {
1497 return alt;
1498 }
1499
1500 switch (representation) {
1501 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32: {
1502 if (NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1503 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagInt32>({value}));
1504 }
1505 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<Int32ToNumber>({value}));
1506 }
1507 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32: {
1508 if (NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1509 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagUint32>({value}));
1510 }
1511 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<Uint32ToNumber>({value}));
1512 }
1513 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64: {
1514 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<Float64ToTagged>(
1515 {value}, Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi));
1516 }
1517 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1518 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64ToTagged>(
1519 {value}, HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kForceHeapNumber));
1520 }
1521
1522 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
1523 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1524 UNREACHABLE();
1525 }
1526 UNREACHABLE();
1527}
1528
1529ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::GetSmiValue(
1530 ValueNode* value, UseReprHintRecording record_use_repr_hint) {
1531 if (V8_LIKELY(record_use_repr_hint == UseReprHintRecording::kRecord)) {
1532 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTagged);
1533 }
1534
1535 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1536
1537 ValueRepresentation representation =
1538 value->properties().value_representation();
1539 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kTagged) {
1540 return BuildCheckSmi(value, !value->Is<Phi>());
1541 }
1542
1543 auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1544
1545 if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.tagged()) {
1546 // HoleyFloat64ToTagged does not canonicalize Smis by default, since it can
1547 // be expensive. If we are reading a Smi value, we should try to
1548 // canonicalize now.
1549 if (HoleyFloat64ToTagged* conversion_node =
1550 alt->TryCast<HoleyFloat64ToTagged>()) {
1551 conversion_node->SetMode(
1552 HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi);
1553 }
1554 return BuildCheckSmi(alt, !value->Is<Phi>());
1555 }
1556
1557 switch (representation) {
1558 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32: {
1559 if (NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1560 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagInt32>({value}));
1561 }
1562 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagInt32>({value}));
1563 }
1564 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32: {
1565 if (NodeTypeIsSmi(node_info->type())) {
1566 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiTagUint32>({value}));
1567 }
1568 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagUint32>({value}));
1569 }
1570 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64: {
1571 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagFloat64>({value}));
1572 }
1573 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1574 return alternative.set_tagged(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiTagFloat64>({value}));
1575 }
1576
1577 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
1578 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1579 UNREACHABLE();
1580 }
1581 UNREACHABLE();
1582}
1583
1584namespace {
1585CheckType GetCheckType(NodeType type) {
1586 return NodeTypeIs(type, NodeType::kAnyHeapObject)
1587 ? CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck
1588 : CheckType::kCheckHeapObject;
1589}
1590} // namespace
1591
1592ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInternalizedString(
1593 interpreter::Register reg) {
1594 ValueNode* node = current_interpreter_frame_.get(reg);
1595 NodeType old_type;
1596 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kInternalizedString, &old_type)) return node;
1597 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(node);
1598 if (known_info->alternative().checked_value()) {
1599 node = known_info->alternative().checked_value();
1600 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kInternalizedString, &old_type)) return node;
1601 }
1602
1603 if (!NodeTypeIs(old_type, NodeType::kString)) {
1604 known_info->CombineType(NodeType::kString);
1605 }
1606
1607 // This node may unwrap ThinStrings.
1608 ValueNode* maybe_unwrapping_node =
1609 AddNewNode<CheckedInternalizedString>({node}, GetCheckType(old_type));
1610 known_info->alternative().set_checked_value(maybe_unwrapping_node);
1611
1612 current_interpreter_frame_.set(reg, maybe_unwrapping_node);
1613 return maybe_unwrapping_node;
1614}
1615
1616ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(
1617 ValueNode* value, NodeType allowed_input_type,
1618 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
1619 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTruncatedInt32);
1620
1621 ValueRepresentation representation =
1622 value->properties().value_representation();
1623 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kInt32) return value;
1624 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kUint32) {
1625 // This node is cheap (no code gen, just a bitcast), so don't cache it.
1626 return AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({value});
1627 }
1628
1629 // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
1630 switch (value->opcode()) {
1631 case Opcode::kConstant: {
1632 compiler::ObjectRef object = value->Cast<Constant>()->object();
1633 if (!object.IsHeapNumber()) break;
1634 int32_t truncated_value = DoubleToInt32(object.AsHeapNumber().value());
1635 if (!Smi::IsValid(truncated_value)) break;
1636 return GetInt32Constant(truncated_value);
1637 }
1638 case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
1639 return GetInt32Constant(value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value());
1640 case Opcode::kRootConstant: {
1641 Tagged<Object> root_object =
1642 local_isolate_->root(value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index());
1643 if (!IsOddball(root_object, local_isolate_)) break;
1644 int32_t truncated_value =
1645 DoubleToInt32(Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw());
1646 // All oddball ToNumber truncations are valid Smis.
1647 DCHECK(Smi::IsValid(truncated_value));
1648 return GetInt32Constant(truncated_value);
1649 }
1650 case Opcode::kFloat64Constant: {
1651 int32_t truncated_value =
1652 DoubleToInt32(value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar());
1653 if (!Smi::IsValid(truncated_value)) break;
1654 return GetInt32Constant(truncated_value);
1655 }
1656
1657 // We could emit unconditional eager deopts for other kinds of constant, but
1658 // it's not necessary, the appropriate checking conversion nodes will deopt.
1659 default:
1660 break;
1661 }
1662
1663 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1664 auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1665
1666 // If there is an int32_alternative, then that works as a truncated value
1667 // too.
1668 if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.int32()) {
1669 return alt;
1670 }
1671 if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.truncated_int32_to_number()) {
1672 return alt;
1673 }
1674
1675 switch (representation) {
1676 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
1677 NodeType old_type;
1678 EnsureType(value, allowed_input_type, &old_type);
1679 if (NodeTypeIsSmi(old_type)) {
1680 // Smi untagging can be cached as an int32 alternative, not just a
1681 // truncated alternative.
1682 return alternative.set_int32(BuildSmiUntag(value));
1683 }
1684 if (allowed_input_type == NodeType::kSmi) {
1685 return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedSmiUntag>({value}));
1686 }
1687 if (NodeTypeIs(old_type, allowed_input_type)) {
1688 return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1689 AddNewNode<TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32>({value},
1690 conversion_type));
1691 }
1692 return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1693 AddNewNode<CheckedTruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32>({value},
1694 conversion_type));
1695 }
1696 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
1697 // Ignore conversion_type for HoleyFloat64, and treat them like Float64.
1698 // ToNumber of undefined is anyway a NaN, so we'll simply truncate away
1699 // the NaN-ness of the hole, and don't need to do extra oddball checks so
1700 // we can ignore the hint (though we'll miss updating the feedback).
1701 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1702 return alternative.set_truncated_int32_to_number(
1703 AddNewNode<TruncateFloat64ToInt32>({value}));
1704 }
1705
1706 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
1707 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
1708 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1709 UNREACHABLE();
1710 }
1711 UNREACHABLE();
1712}
1713
1714std::optional<int32_t> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetInt32Constant(
1715 ValueNode* value) {
1716 switch (value->opcode()) {
1717 case Opcode::kInt32Constant:
1718 return value->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
1719 case Opcode::kUint32Constant: {
1720 uint32_t uint32_value = value->Cast<Uint32Constant>()->value();
1721 if (uint32_value <= INT32_MAX) {
1722 return static_cast<int32_t>(uint32_value);
1723 }
1724 return {};
1725 }
1726 case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
1727 return value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value();
1728 case Opcode::kFloat64Constant: {
1729 double double_value =
1730 value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
1731 if (!IsInt32Double(double_value)) return {};
1732 return FastD2I(value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar());
1733 }
1734 default:
1735 break;
1736 }
1737 if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(value)) {
1738 return TryGetInt32Constant(*c);
1739 }
1740 return {};
1741}
1742
1743std::optional<uint32_t> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetUint32Constant(
1744 ValueNode* value) {
1745 switch (value->opcode()) {
1746 case Opcode::kInt32Constant: {
1747 int32_t int32_value = value->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
1748 if (int32_value >= 0) {
1749 return static_cast<uint32_t>(int32_value);
1750 }
1751 return {};
1752 }
1753 case Opcode::kUint32Constant:
1754 return value->Cast<Uint32Constant>()->value();
1755 case Opcode::kSmiConstant: {
1756 int32_t smi_value = value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value();
1757 if (smi_value >= 0) {
1758 return static_cast<uint32_t>(smi_value);
1759 }
1760 return {};
1761 }
1762 case Opcode::kFloat64Constant: {
1763 double double_value =
1764 value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
1765 if (!IsUint32Double(double_value)) return {};
1766 return FastD2UI(value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar());
1767 }
1768 default:
1769 break;
1770 }
1771 if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(value)) {
1772 return TryGetUint32Constant(*c);
1773 }
1774 return {};
1775}
1776
1777ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInt32(ValueNode* value,
1778 bool can_be_heap_number) {
1779 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kInt32);
1780
1781 ValueRepresentation representation =
1782 value->properties().value_representation();
1783 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kInt32) return value;
1784
1785 // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
1786 if (auto cst = TryGetInt32Constant(value)) {
1787 return GetInt32Constant(cst.value());
1788 }
1789 // We could emit unconditional eager deopts for other kinds of constant, but
1790 // it's not necessary, the appropriate checking conversion nodes will deopt.
1791
1792 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1793 auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1794
1795 if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.int32()) {
1796 return alt;
1797 }
1798
1799 switch (representation) {
1800 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
1801 if (can_be_heap_number && !CheckType(value, NodeType::kSmi)) {
1802 return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedNumberToInt32>({value}));
1803 }
1804 return alternative.set_int32(BuildSmiUntag(value));
1805 }
1806 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32: {
1807 if (node_info->is_smi()) {
1808 return alternative.set_int32(
1809 AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({value}));
1810 }
1811 return alternative.set_int32(AddNewNode<CheckedUint32ToInt32>({value}));
1812 }
1813 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
1814 // The check here will also work for the hole NaN, so we can treat
1815 // HoleyFloat64 as Float64.
1816 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1817 return alternative.set_int32(
1818 AddNewNode<CheckedTruncateFloat64ToInt32>({value}));
1819 }
1820
1821 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
1822 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1823 UNREACHABLE();
1824 }
1825 UNREACHABLE();
1826}
1827
1828std::optional<double> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetFloat64Constant(
1829 ValueNode* value, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
1830 switch (value->opcode()) {
1831 case Opcode::kConstant: {
1832 compiler::ObjectRef object = value->Cast<Constant>()->object();
1833 if (object.IsHeapNumber()) {
1834 return object.AsHeapNumber().value();
1835 }
1836 // Oddballs should be RootConstants.
1837 DCHECK(!IsOddball(*object.object()));
1838 return {};
1839 }
1840 case Opcode::kInt32Constant:
1841 return value->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
1842 case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
1843 return value->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value();
1844 case Opcode::kFloat64Constant:
1845 return value->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
1846 case Opcode::kRootConstant: {
1847 Tagged<Object> root_object =
1848 local_isolate_->root(value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index());
1849 if (conversion_type == TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean &&
1850 IsBoolean(root_object)) {
1851 return Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw();
1852 }
1853 if (conversion_type == TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball &&
1854 IsOddball(root_object)) {
1855 return Cast<Oddball>(root_object)->to_number_raw();
1856 }
1857 if (IsHeapNumber(root_object)) {
1858 return Cast<HeapNumber>(root_object)->value();
1859 }
1860 return {};
1861 }
1862 default:
1863 break;
1864 }
1865 if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(value)) {
1866 return TryGetFloat64Constant(*c, conversion_type);
1867 }
1868 return {};
1869}
1870
1871ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetFloat64(ValueNode* value) {
1872 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kFloat64);
1873 return GetFloat64ForToNumber(value, NodeType::kNumber,
1874 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
1875}
1876
1877ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetFloat64ForToNumber(
1878 ValueNode* value, NodeType allowed_input_type,
1879 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
1880 ValueRepresentation representation =
1881 value->properties().value_representation();
1882 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64) return value;
1883
1884 // Process constants first to avoid allocating NodeInfo for them.
1885 if (auto cst = TryGetFloat64Constant(value, conversion_type)) {
1886 return GetFloat64Constant(cst.value());
1887 }
1888 // We could emit unconditional eager deopts for other kinds of constant, but
1889 // it's not necessary, the appropriate checking conversion nodes will deopt.
1890
1891 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
1892 auto& alternative = node_info->alternative();
1893
1894 if (ValueNode* alt = alternative.float64()) {
1895 return alt;
1896 }
1897
1898 switch (representation) {
1899 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
1900 auto combined_type = CombineType(allowed_input_type, node_info->type());
1901 if (NodeTypeIs(combined_type, NodeType::kSmi)) {
1902 // Get the float64 value of a Smi value its int32 representation.
1903 return GetFloat64(GetInt32(value));
1904 }
1905 if (NodeTypeIs(combined_type, NodeType::kNumber)) {
1906 // Number->Float64 conversions are exact alternatives, so they can
1907 // also become the canonical float64_alternative.
1908 return alternative.set_float64(BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(
1909 value, NodeType::kNumber,
1910 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber));
1911 }
1912 if (NodeTypeIs(combined_type, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball)) {
1913 // NumberOrOddball->Float64 conversions are not exact alternatives,
1914 // since they lose the information that this is an oddball, so they
1915 // can only become the canonical float64_alternative if they are a
1916 // known number (and therefore not oddball).
1917 return BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(value, combined_type,
1918 conversion_type);
1919 }
1920 // The type is impossible. We could generate an unconditional deopt here,
1921 // but it's too invasive. So we just generate a check which will always
1922 // deopt.
1923 return BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(value, allowed_input_type,
1924 conversion_type);
1925 }
1926 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
1927 return alternative.set_float64(AddNewNode<ChangeInt32ToFloat64>({value}));
1928 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
1929 return alternative.set_float64(
1930 AddNewNode<ChangeUint32ToFloat64>({value}));
1931 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
1932 switch (allowed_input_type) {
1933 case NodeType::kSmi:
1934 case NodeType::kNumber:
1935 case NodeType::kNumberOrBoolean:
1936 // Number->Float64 conversions are exact alternatives, so they can
1937 // also become the canonical float64_alternative. The HoleyFloat64
1938 // representation can represent undefined but no other oddballs, so
1939 // booleans cannot occur here and kNumberOrBoolean can be grouped with
1940 // kNumber.
1941 return alternative.set_float64(
1942 AddNewNode<CheckedHoleyFloat64ToFloat64>({value}));
1943 case NodeType::kNumberOrOddball:
1944 // NumberOrOddball->Float64 conversions are not exact alternatives,
1945 // since they lose the information that this is an oddball, so they
1946 // cannot become the canonical float64_alternative.
1947 return AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64ToMaybeNanFloat64>({value});
1948 default:
1949 UNREACHABLE();
1950 }
1951 }
1952 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
1953 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1954 UNREACHABLE();
1955 }
1956 UNREACHABLE();
1957}
1958
1959ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
1960 ValueNode* value, NodeType allowed_input_type,
1961 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
1962 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64);
1963 ValueRepresentation representation =
1964 value->properties().value_representation();
1965 // Ignore the hint for
1966 if (representation == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) return value;
1967 return GetFloat64ForToNumber(value, allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
1968}
1969
1970namespace {
1971int32_t ClampToUint8(int32_t value) {
1972 if (value < 0) return 0;
1973 if (value > 255) return 255;
1974 return value;
1975}
1976} // namespace
1977
1978ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetUint8ClampedForToNumber(ValueNode* value) {
1979 switch (value->properties().value_representation()) {
1980 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
1981 UNREACHABLE();
1982 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged: {
1983 if (SmiConstant* constant = value->TryCast<SmiConstant>()) {
1984 return GetInt32Constant(ClampToUint8(constant->value().value()));
1985 }
1986 NodeInfo* info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(value);
1987 if (info && info->alternative().int32()) {
1988 return AddNewNode<Int32ToUint8Clamped>({info->alternative().int32()});
1989 }
1990 return AddNewNode<CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped>({value});
1991 }
1992 // HoleyFloat64 is treated like Float64. ToNumber of undefined is anyway a
1993 // NaN, so we'll simply truncate away the NaN-ness of the hole, and don't
1994 // need to do extra oddball checks (though we'll miss updating the
1995 // feedback).
1996 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
1997 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
1998 // TODO(leszeks): Handle Float64Constant, which requires the correct
1999 // rounding for clamping.
2000 return AddNewNode<Float64ToUint8Clamped>({value});
2001 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
2002 if (Int32Constant* constant = value->TryCast<Int32Constant>()) {
2003 return GetInt32Constant(ClampToUint8(constant->value()));
2004 }
2005 return AddNewNode<Int32ToUint8Clamped>({value});
2006 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
2007 return AddNewNode<Uint32ToUint8Clamped>({value});
2008 }
2009 UNREACHABLE();
2010}

2012namespace {
2013template <Operation kOperation>
2014struct NodeForOperationHelper;
2015
2016#define NODE_FOR_OPERATION_HELPER(Name) \
2017 template <> \
2018 struct NodeForOperationHelper<Operation::k##Name> { \
2019 using generic_type = Generic##Name; \
2020 };
2021OPERATION_LIST(NODE_FOR_OPERATION_HELPER)
2022#undef NODE_FOR_OPERATION_HELPER
2023
2024template <Operation kOperation>
2025using GenericNodeForOperation =
2026 typename NodeForOperationHelper<kOperation>::generic_type;
2027
2028// Bitwise operations reinterprets the numeric input as Int32 bits for a
2029// bitwise operation, which means we want to do slightly different conversions.
2030template <Operation kOperation>
2031constexpr bool BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32() {
2032 switch (kOperation) {
2033 case Operation::kBitwiseNot:
2034 case Operation::kBitwiseAnd:
2035 case Operation::kBitwiseOr:
2036 case Operation::kBitwiseXor:
2037 case Operation::kShiftLeft:
2038 case Operation::kShiftRight:
2039 case Operation::kShiftRightLogical:
2040 return true;
2041 default:
2042 return false;
2043 }
2044}
2045} // namespace
2046
2047// MAP_OPERATION_TO_NODES are tuples with the following format:
2048// - Operation name,
2049// - Int32 operation node,
2050// - Identity of int32 operation (e.g, 0 for add/sub and 1 for mul/div), if it
2051// exists, or otherwise {}.
2052#define MAP_BINARY_OPERATION_TO_INT32_NODE(V) \
2053 V(Add, Int32AddWithOverflow, 0) \
2054 V(Subtract, Int32SubtractWithOverflow, 0) \
2055 V(Multiply, Int32MultiplyWithOverflow, 1) \
2056 V(Divide, Int32DivideWithOverflow, 1) \
2057 V(Modulus, Int32ModulusWithOverflow, {}) \
2058 V(BitwiseAnd, Int32BitwiseAnd, ~0) \
2059 V(BitwiseOr, Int32BitwiseOr, 0) \
2060 V(BitwiseXor, Int32BitwiseXor, 0) \
2061 V(ShiftLeft, Int32ShiftLeft, 0) \
2062 V(ShiftRight, Int32ShiftRight, 0) \
2063 V(ShiftRightLogical, Int32ShiftRightLogical, {})
2064
2065#define MAP_UNARY_OPERATION_TO_INT32_NODE(V) \
2066 V(BitwiseNot, Int32BitwiseNot) \
2067 V(Increment, Int32IncrementWithOverflow) \
2068 V(Decrement, Int32DecrementWithOverflow) \
2069 V(Negate, Int32NegateWithOverflow)
2070
2071// MAP_OPERATION_TO_FLOAT64_NODE are tuples with the following format:
2072// (Operation name, Float64 operation node).
2073#define MAP_OPERATION_TO_FLOAT64_NODE(V) \
2074 V(Add, Float64Add) \
2075 V(Subtract, Float64Subtract) \
2076 V(Multiply, Float64Multiply) \
2077 V(Divide, Float64Divide) \
2078 V(Modulus, Float64Modulus) \
2079 V(Exponentiate, Float64Exponentiate)
2080
2081template <Operation kOperation>
2082static constexpr std::optional<int> Int32Identity() {
2083 switch (kOperation) {
2084#define CASE(op, _, identity) \
2085 case Operation::k##op: \
2086 return identity;
2087 MAP_BINARY_OPERATION_TO_INT32_NODE(CASE)
2088#undef CASE
2089 default:
2090 UNREACHABLE();
2091 }
2092}
2093
2094namespace {
2095template <Operation kOperation>
2096struct Int32NodeForHelper;
2097#define SPECIALIZATION(op, OpNode, ...) \
2098 template <> \
2099 struct Int32NodeForHelper<Operation::k##op> { \
2100 using type = OpNode; \
2101 };
2102MAP_UNARY_OPERATION_TO_INT32_NODE(SPECIALIZATION)
2103MAP_BINARY_OPERATION_TO_INT32_NODE(SPECIALIZATION)
2104#undef SPECIALIZATION
2105
2106template <Operation kOperation>
2107using Int32NodeFor = typename Int32NodeForHelper<kOperation>::type;
2108
2109template <Operation kOperation>
2110struct Float64NodeForHelper;
2111#define SPECIALIZATION(op, OpNode) \
2112 template <> \
2113 struct Float64NodeForHelper<Operation::k##op> { \
2114 using type = OpNode; \
2115 };
2116MAP_OPERATION_TO_FLOAT64_NODE(SPECIALIZATION)
2117#undef SPECIALIZATION
2118
2119template <Operation kOperation>
2120using Float64NodeFor = typename Float64NodeForHelper<kOperation>::type;
2121} // namespace

2123template <Operation kOperation>
2124void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericUnaryOperationNode() {
2125 FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(0);
2126 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
2127 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GenericNodeForOperation<kOperation>>(
2128 {value}, compiler::FeedbackSource{feedback(), slot_index}));
2129}

2131template <Operation kOperation>
2132void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericBinaryOperationNode() {
2133 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2134 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2135 FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(1);
2136 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GenericNodeForOperation<kOperation>>(
2137 {left, right}, compiler::FeedbackSource{feedback(), slot_index}));
2138}
