2140template <Operation kOperation>
2141void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericBinarySmiOperationNode() {
2142 ValueNode* left = GetAccumulator();
2143 int constant = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0);
2144 ValueNode* right = GetSmiConstant(constant);
2145 FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(1);
2146 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GenericNodeForOperation<kOperation>>(
2147 {left, right}, compiler::FeedbackSource{feedback(), slot_index}));
2148}
2149
2150template <Operation kOperation>
2151MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldInt32UnaryOperation(
2152 ValueNode* node) {
2153 auto cst = TryGetInt32Constant(node);
2154 if (!cst.has_value()) return {};
2155 switch (kOperation) {
2156 case Operation::kBitwiseNot:
2157 return GetInt32Constant(~cst.value());
2158 case Operation::kIncrement:
2159 if (cst.value() < INT32_MAX) {
2160 return GetInt32Constant(cst.value() + 1);
2161 }
2162 return {};
2163 case Operation::kDecrement:
2164 if (cst.value() > INT32_MIN) {
2165 return GetInt32Constant(cst.value() - 1);
2166 }
2167 return {};
2168 case Operation::kNegate:
2169 if (cst.value() == 0) {
2170 return {};
2171 }
2172 if (cst.value() != INT32_MIN) {
2173 return GetInt32Constant(-cst.value());
2174 }
2175 return {};
2176 default:
2177 UNREACHABLE();
2178 }
2179}
2180
2181template <Operation kOperation>
2182ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInt32UnaryOperationNode() {
2183 // Use BuildTruncatingInt32BitwiseNotForToNumber with Smi input hint
2184 // for truncating operations.
2185 static_assert(!BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>());
2186 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
2187 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(TryFoldInt32UnaryOperation<kOperation>(value),
2188 SetAccumulator);
2189 using OpNodeT = Int32NodeFor<kOperation>;
2190 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<OpNodeT>({value}));
2191 return ReduceResult::Done();
2192}
2193
2194ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTruncatingInt32BitwiseNotForToNumber(
2195 NodeType allowed_input_type,
2196 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2197 ValueNode* value =
2198 GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator(),
2199 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2200 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2201 TryFoldInt32UnaryOperation<Operation::kBitwiseNot>(value),
2202 SetAccumulator);
2203 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Int32BitwiseNot>({value}));
2204 return ReduceResult::Done();
2205}
2206
2207template <Operation kOperation>
2208MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation(
2209 ValueNode* left, ValueNode* right) {
2210 auto cst_right = TryGetInt32Constant(right);
2211 if (!cst_right.has_value()) return {};
2212 return TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation<kOperation>(left, cst_right.value());
2213}
2214
2215template <Operation kOperation>
2216MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation(
2217 ValueNode* left, int32_t cst_right) {
2218 auto cst_left = TryGetInt32Constant(left);
2219 if (!cst_left.has_value()) return {};
2220 switch (kOperation) {
2221 case Operation::kAdd: {
2222 int64_t result = static_cast<int64_t>(cst_left.value()) +
2223 static_cast<int64_t>(cst_right);
2224 if (result >= INT32_MIN && result <= INT32_MAX) {
2225 return GetInt32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(result));
2226 }
2227 return {};
2228 }
2229 case Operation::kSubtract: {
2230 int64_t result = static_cast<int64_t>(cst_left.value()) -
2231 static_cast<int64_t>(cst_right);
2232 if (result >= INT32_MIN && result <= INT32_MAX) {
2233 return GetInt32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(result));
2234 }
2235 return {};
2236 }
2237 case Operation::kMultiply: {
2238 int64_t result = static_cast<int64_t>(cst_left.value()) *
2239 static_cast<int64_t>(cst_right);
2240 if (result >= INT32_MIN && result <= INT32_MAX) {
2241 return GetInt32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(result));
2242 }
2243 return {};
2244 }
2245 case Operation::kModulus:
2246 // TODO(v8:7700): Constant fold mod.
2247 return {};
2248 case Operation::kDivide:
2249 // TODO(v8:7700): Constant fold division.
2250 return {};
2251 case Operation::kBitwiseAnd:
2252 return GetInt32Constant(cst_left.value() & cst_right);
2253 case Operation::kBitwiseOr:
2254 return GetInt32Constant(cst_left.value() | cst_right);
2255 case Operation::kBitwiseXor:
2256 return GetInt32Constant(cst_left.value() ^ cst_right);
2257 case Operation::kShiftLeft:
2258 return GetInt32Constant(cst_left.value()
2259 << (static_cast<uint32_t>(cst_right) % 32));
2260 case Operation::kShiftRight:
2261 return GetInt32Constant(cst_left.value() >>
2262 (static_cast<uint32_t>(cst_right) % 32));
2263 case Operation::kShiftRightLogical:
2264 return GetUint32Constant(static_cast<uint32_t>(cst_left.value()) >>
2265 (static_cast<uint32_t>(cst_right) % 32));
2266 default:
2267 UNREACHABLE();
2268 }
2269}
2270
2271template <Operation kOperation>
2272ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInt32BinaryOperationNode() {
2273 // Use BuildTruncatingInt32BinaryOperationNodeForToNumber with Smi input hint
2274 // for truncating operations.
2275 static_assert(!BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>());
2276 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2277 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2278 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2279 TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation<kOperation>(left, right), SetAccumulator);
2280 using OpNodeT = Int32NodeFor<kOperation>;
2281 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<OpNodeT>({left, right}));
2282 return ReduceResult::Done();
2283}
2284
2285template <Operation kOperation>
2286ReduceResult
2287MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTruncatingInt32BinaryOperationNodeForToNumber(
2288 NodeType allowed_input_type,
2289 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2290 static_assert(BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>());
2291 ValueNode* left;
2292 ValueNode* right;
2293 if (IsRegisterEqualToAccumulator(0)) {
2294 left = right = GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(
2295 current_interpreter_frame_.get(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0)),
2296 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2297 } else {
2298 left = GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(
2299 current_interpreter_frame_.get(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0)),
2300 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2301 right =
2302 GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator(),
2303 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2304 }
2305 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2306 TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation<kOperation>(left, right), SetAccumulator);
2307 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Int32NodeFor<kOperation>>({left, right}));
2308 return ReduceResult::Done();
2309}
2310
2311template <Operation kOperation>
2312ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInt32BinarySmiOperationNode() {
2313 // Truncating Int32 nodes treat their input as a signed int32 regardless
2314 // of whether it's really signed or not, so we allow Uint32 by loading a
2315 // TruncatedInt32 value.
2316 static_assert(!BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>());
2317 ValueNode* left = GetAccumulator();
2318 int32_t constant = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0);
2319 if (std::optional<int>(constant) == Int32Identity<kOperation>()) {
2320 // Deopt if {left} is not an Int32.
2321 EnsureInt32(left);
2322 // If the constant is the unit of the operation, it already has the right
2323 // value, so just return.
2324 return ReduceResult::Done();
2325 }
2326 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2327 TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation<kOperation>(left, constant), SetAccumulator);
2328 ValueNode* right = GetInt32Constant(constant);
2329 using OpNodeT = Int32NodeFor<kOperation>;
2330 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<OpNodeT>({left, right}));
2331 return ReduceResult::Done();
2332}
2333
2334template <Operation kOperation>
2335ReduceResult
2336MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTruncatingInt32BinarySmiOperationNodeForToNumber(
2337 NodeType allowed_input_type,
2338 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2339 static_assert(BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>());
2340 ValueNode* left =
2341 GetTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator(),
2342 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2343 int32_t constant = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0);
2344 if (std::optional<int>(constant) == Int32Identity<kOperation>()) {
2345 // If the constant is the unit of the operation, it already has the right
2346 // value, so use the truncated value (if not just a conversion) and return.
2347 if (!left->properties().is_conversion()) {
2348 current_interpreter_frame_.set_accumulator(left);
2349 }
2350 return ReduceResult::Done();
2351 }
2352 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2353 TryFoldInt32BinaryOperation<kOperation>(left, constant), SetAccumulator);
2354 ValueNode* right = GetInt32Constant(constant);
2355 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Int32NodeFor<kOperation>>({left, right}));
2356 return ReduceResult::Done();
2357}
2358
2359ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetNumberConstant(double constant) {
2360 if (IsSmiDouble(constant)) {
2361 return GetInt32Constant(FastD2I(constant));
2362 }
2363 return GetFloat64Constant(constant);
2364}

2366template <Operation kOperation>
2367MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldFloat64UnaryOperationForToNumber(
2368 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, ValueNode* value) {
2369 auto cst = TryGetFloat64Constant(value, conversion_type);
2370 if (!cst.has_value()) return {};
2371 switch (kOperation) {
2372 case Operation::kNegate:
2373 return GetNumberConstant(-cst.value());
2374 case Operation::kIncrement:
2375 return GetNumberConstant(cst.value() + 1);
2376 case Operation::kDecrement:
2377 return GetNumberConstant(cst.value() - 1);
2378 default:
2379 UNREACHABLE();
2380 }
2381}
2382
2383template <Operation kOperation>
2384MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldFloat64BinaryOperationForToNumber(
2385 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, ValueNode* left,
2386 ValueNode* right) {
2387 auto cst_right = TryGetFloat64Constant(right, conversion_type);
2388 if (!cst_right.has_value()) return {};
2389 return TryFoldFloat64BinaryOperationForToNumber<kOperation>(
2390 conversion_type, left, cst_right.value());
2391}
2392
2393template <Operation kOperation>
2394MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldFloat64BinaryOperationForToNumber(
2395 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type, ValueNode* left,
2396 double cst_right) {
2397 auto cst_left = TryGetFloat64Constant(left, conversion_type);
2398 if (!cst_left.has_value()) return {};
2399 switch (kOperation) {
2400 case Operation::kAdd:
2401 return GetNumberConstant(cst_left.value() + cst_right);
2402 case Operation::kSubtract:
2403 return GetNumberConstant(cst_left.value() - cst_right);
2404 case Operation::kMultiply:
2405 return GetNumberConstant(cst_left.value() * cst_right);
2406 case Operation::kDivide:
2407 return GetNumberConstant(cst_left.value() / cst_right);
2408 case Operation::kModulus:
2409 // TODO(v8:7700): Constant fold mod.
2410 return {};
2411 case Operation::kExponentiate:
2412 return GetNumberConstant(math::pow(cst_left.value(), cst_right));
2413 default:
2414 UNREACHABLE();
2415 }
2416}
2417
2418template <Operation kOperation>
2419ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildFloat64BinarySmiOperationNodeForToNumber(
2420 NodeType allowed_input_type,
2421 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2422 // TODO(v8:7700): Do constant identity folding. Make sure to normalize
2423 // HoleyFloat64 nodes if folded.
2424 ValueNode* left = GetAccumulatorHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(allowed_input_type,
2425 conversion_type);
2426 double constant = static_cast<double>(iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0));
2427 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2428 TryFoldFloat64BinaryOperationForToNumber<kOperation>(conversion_type,
2429 left, constant),
2430 SetAccumulator);
2431 ValueNode* right = GetFloat64Constant(constant);
2432 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Float64NodeFor<kOperation>>({left, right}));
2433 return ReduceResult::Done();
2434}
2435
2436template <Operation kOperation>
2437ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildFloat64UnaryOperationNodeForToNumber(
2438 NodeType allowed_input_type,
2439 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2440 // TODO(v8:7700): Do constant identity folding. Make sure to normalize
2441 // HoleyFloat64 nodes if folded.
2442 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulatorHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(allowed_input_type,
2443 conversion_type);
2444 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2445 TryFoldFloat64UnaryOperationForToNumber<kOperation>(conversion_type,
2446 value),
2447 SetAccumulator);
2448 switch (kOperation) {
2449 case Operation::kNegate:
2450 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Float64Negate>({value}));
2451 break;
2452 case Operation::kIncrement:
2453 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Float64Add>({value, GetFloat64Constant(1)}));
2454 break;
2455 case Operation::kDecrement:
2456 SetAccumulator(
2457 AddNewNode<Float64Subtract>({value, GetFloat64Constant(1)}));
2458 break;
2459 default:
2460 UNREACHABLE();
2461 }
2462 return ReduceResult::Done();
2463}
2464
2465template <Operation kOperation>
2466ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildFloat64BinaryOperationNodeForToNumber(
2467 NodeType allowed_input_type,
2468 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
2469 // TODO(v8:7700): Do constant identity folding. Make sure to normalize
2470 // HoleyFloat64 nodes if folded.
2471 ValueNode* left = LoadRegisterHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(0, allowed_input_type,
2472 conversion_type);
2473 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulatorHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(allowed_input_type,
2474 conversion_type);
2475 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
2476 TryFoldFloat64BinaryOperationForToNumber<kOperation>(conversion_type,
2477 left, right),
2478 SetAccumulator);
2479 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Float64NodeFor<kOperation>>({left, right}));
2480 return ReduceResult::Done();
2481}
2482
2483namespace {
2484std::tuple<NodeType, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType>
2485BinopHintToNodeTypeAndConversionType(BinaryOperationHint hint) {
2486 switch (hint) {
2487 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
2488 return std::make_tuple(NodeType::kSmi,
2489 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
2490 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
2491 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumber:
2492 return std::make_tuple(NodeType::kNumber,
2493 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
2494 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
2495 return std::make_tuple(NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
2496 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball);
2497 case BinaryOperationHint::kNone:
2498 case BinaryOperationHint::kString:
2499 case BinaryOperationHint::kStringOrStringWrapper:
2500 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt:
2501 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt64:
2502 case BinaryOperationHint::kAny:
2503 UNREACHABLE();
2504 }
2505}
2506} // namespace
2507
2508template <Operation kOperation>
2509ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitUnaryOperation() {
2510 FeedbackNexus nexus = FeedbackNexusForOperand(0);
2511 BinaryOperationHint feedback_hint = nexus.GetBinaryOperationFeedback();
2512 switch (feedback_hint) {
2513 case BinaryOperationHint::kNone:
2514 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
2515 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForBinaryOperation);
2516 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
2517 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
2518 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumber:
2519 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball: {
2520 auto [allowed_input_type, conversion_type] =
2521 BinopHintToNodeTypeAndConversionType(feedback_hint);
2522 if constexpr (BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>()) {
2523 static_assert(kOperation == Operation::kBitwiseNot);
2524 return BuildTruncatingInt32BitwiseNotForToNumber(allowed_input_type,
2525 conversion_type);
2526 } else if (feedback_hint == BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2527 return BuildInt32UnaryOperationNode<kOperation>();
2528 }
2529 return BuildFloat64UnaryOperationNodeForToNumber<kOperation>(
2530 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2531 break;
2532 }
2533 case BinaryOperationHint::kString:
2534 case BinaryOperationHint::kStringOrStringWrapper:
2535 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt:
2536 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt64:
2537 case BinaryOperationHint::kAny:
2538 // Fallback to generic node.
2539 break;
2540 }
2541 BuildGenericUnaryOperationNode<kOperation>();
2542 return ReduceResult::Done();
2543}
2544
2545template <Operation kOperation>
2546ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitBinaryOperation() {
2547 FeedbackNexus nexus = FeedbackNexusForOperand(1);
2548 BinaryOperationHint feedback_hint = nexus.GetBinaryOperationFeedback();
2549 switch (feedback_hint) {
2550 case BinaryOperationHint::kNone:
2551 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
2552 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForBinaryOperation);
2553 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
2554 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
2555 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumber:
2556 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball: {
2557 auto [allowed_input_type, conversion_type] =
2558 BinopHintToNodeTypeAndConversionType(feedback_hint);
2559 if constexpr (BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>()) {
2560 return BuildTruncatingInt32BinaryOperationNodeForToNumber<kOperation>(
2561 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2562 } else if (feedback_hint == BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2563 if constexpr (kOperation == Operation::kExponentiate) {
2564 // Exponentiate never updates the feedback to be a Smi.
2565 UNREACHABLE();
2566 } else {
2567 return BuildInt32BinaryOperationNode<kOperation>();
2568 }
2569 } else {
2570 return BuildFloat64BinaryOperationNodeForToNumber<kOperation>(
2571 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2572 }
2573 break;
2574 }
2575 case BinaryOperationHint::kString:
2576 if constexpr (kOperation == Operation::kAdd) {
2577 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2578 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2579 if (RootConstant* root_constant = left->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
2580 if (root_constant->index() == RootIndex::kempty_string) {
2581 BuildCheckString(right);
2582 // The right side is already in the accumulator register.
2583 return ReduceResult::Done();
2584 }
2585 }
2586 if (RootConstant* root_constant = right->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
2587 if (root_constant->index() == RootIndex::kempty_string) {
2588 BuildCheckString(left);
2589 MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(
2590 iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0),
2591 interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
2592 return ReduceResult::Done();
2593 }
2594 }
2595 BuildCheckString(left);
2596 BuildCheckString(right);
2597 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<StringConcat>({left, right}));
2598 return ReduceResult::Done();
2599 }
2600 break;
2601 case BinaryOperationHint::kStringOrStringWrapper:
2602 if constexpr (kOperation == Operation::kAdd) {
2603 if (broker()
2604 ->dependencies()
2605 ->DependOnStringWrapperToPrimitiveProtector()) {
2606 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2607 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2608 BuildCheckStringOrStringWrapper(left);
2609 BuildCheckStringOrStringWrapper(right);
2610 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<StringWrapperConcat>({left, right}));
2611 return ReduceResult::Done();
2612 }
2613 }
2614 [[fallthrough]];
2615 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt:
2616 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt64:
2617 case BinaryOperationHint::kAny:
2618 // Fallback to generic node.
2619 break;
2620 }
2621 BuildGenericBinaryOperationNode<kOperation>();
2622 return ReduceResult::Done();
2623}
2624
2625template <Operation kOperation>
2626ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitBinarySmiOperation() {
2627 FeedbackNexus nexus = FeedbackNexusForOperand(1);
2628 BinaryOperationHint feedback_hint = nexus.GetBinaryOperationFeedback();
2629 switch (feedback_hint) {
2630 case BinaryOperationHint::kNone:
2631 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
2632 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForBinaryOperation);
2633 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
2634 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
2635 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumber:
2636 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball: {
2637 const auto [allowed_input_type, conversion_type] =
2638 BinopHintToNodeTypeAndConversionType(feedback_hint);
2639 if constexpr (BinaryOperationIsBitwiseInt32<kOperation>()) {
2640 return BuildTruncatingInt32BinarySmiOperationNodeForToNumber<
2641 kOperation>(allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2642 } else if (feedback_hint == BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2643 if constexpr (kOperation == Operation::kExponentiate) {
2644 // Exponentiate never updates the feedback to be a Smi.
2645 UNREACHABLE();
2646 } else {
2647 return BuildInt32BinarySmiOperationNode<kOperation>();
2648 }
2649 } else {
2650 return BuildFloat64BinarySmiOperationNodeForToNumber<kOperation>(
2651 allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2652 }
2653 break;
2654 }
2655 case BinaryOperationHint::kString:
2656 case BinaryOperationHint::kStringOrStringWrapper:
2657 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt:
2658 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt64:
2659 case BinaryOperationHint::kAny:
2660 // Fallback to generic node.
2661 break;
2662 }
2663 BuildGenericBinarySmiOperationNode<kOperation>();
2664 return ReduceResult::Done();
2665}
2666
2667template <Operation kOperation, typename type>
2668bool OperationValue(type left, type right) {
2669 switch (kOperation) {
2670 case Operation::kEqual:
2671 case Operation::kStrictEqual:
2672 return left == right;
2673 case Operation::kLessThan:
2674 return left < right;
2675 case Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
2676 return left <= right;
2677 case Operation::kGreaterThan:
2678 return left > right;
2679 case Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
2680 return left >= right;
2681 }
2682}
2683
2684// static
2685compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetConstant(
2686 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker, LocalIsolate* isolate, ValueNode* node) {
2687 if (Constant* c = node->TryCast<Constant>()) {
2688 return c->object();
2689 }
2690 if (RootConstant* c = node->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
2691 return MakeRef(broker, isolate->root_handle(c->index())).AsHeapObject();
2692 }
2693 return {};
2694}
2695
2696compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetConstant(
2697 ValueNode* node, ValueNode** constant_node) {
2698 if (auto result = TryGetConstant(broker(), local_isolate(), node)) {
2699 if (constant_node) *constant_node = node;
2700 return result;
2701 }
2702 if (auto c = TryGetConstantAlternative(node)) {
2703 return TryGetConstant(*c, constant_node);
2704 }
2705 return {};
2706}
2707
2708std::optional<ValueNode*> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetConstantAlternative(
2709 ValueNode* node) {
2710 const NodeInfo* info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
2711 if (info) {
2712 if (auto c = info->alternative().checked_value()) {
2713 if (IsConstantNode(c->opcode())) {
2714 return c;
2715 }
2716 }
2717 }
2718 return {};
2719}
2720
2721template <Operation kOperation>
2722bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCompareEqualAgainstConstant() {
2723 if (kOperation != Operation::kStrictEqual && kOperation != Operation::kEqual)
2724 return false;
2725
2726 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2727 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2728
2729 ValueNode* other = right;
2730 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(left);
2731 if (!maybe_constant) {
2732 maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(right);
2733 other = left;
2734 }
2735 if (!maybe_constant) return false;
2736
2737 if (CheckType(other, NodeType::kBoolean)) {
2738 auto CompareOtherWith = [&](bool constant) {
2739 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef const_other = TryGetConstant(other);
2740 if (const_other) {
2741 auto bool_other = const_other->TryGetBooleanValue(broker());
2742 if (bool_other.has_value()) {
2743 SetAccumulator(GetBooleanConstant(constant == *bool_other));
2744 return;
2745 }
2746 }
2747 if (constant) {
2748 SetAccumulator(other);
2749 } else {
2750 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<LogicalNot>({other}));
2751 }
2752 };
2753
2754 if (maybe_constant.equals(broker_->true_value())) {
2755 CompareOtherWith(true);
2756 return true;
2757 } else if (maybe_constant.equals(broker_->false_value())) {
2758 CompareOtherWith(false);
2759 return true;
2760 } else if (kOperation == Operation::kEqual) {
2761 // For `bool == num` we can convert the actual comparison `ToNumber(bool)
2762 // == num` into `(num == 1) ? bool : ((num == 0) ? !bool : false)`,
2763 std::optional<double> val = {};
2764 if (maybe_constant.value().IsSmi()) {
2765 val = maybe_constant.value().AsSmi();
2766 } else if (maybe_constant.value().IsHeapNumber()) {
2767 val = maybe_constant.value().AsHeapNumber().value();
2768 }
2769 if (val) {
2770 if (*val == 0) {
2771 CompareOtherWith(false);
2772 } else if (*val == 1) {
2773 CompareOtherWith(true);
2774 } else {
2775 // The constant number is neither equal to `ToNumber(true)` nor
2776 // `ToNumber(false)`.
2777 SetAccumulator(GetBooleanConstant(false));
2778 }
2779 return true;
2780 }
2781 }
2782 }
2783
2784 if (kOperation != Operation::kStrictEqual) return false;
2785
2786 InstanceType type = maybe_constant.value().map(broker()).instance_type();
2787 if (!InstanceTypeChecker::IsReferenceComparable(type)) return false;
2788
2789 // If the constant is the undefined value, we can compare it
2790 // against holey floats.
2791 if (maybe_constant->IsUndefined()) {
2792 ValueNode* holey_float = nullptr;
2793 if (left->properties().value_representation() ==
2794 ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
2795 holey_float = left;
2796 } else if (right->properties().value_representation() ==
2797 ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
2798 holey_float = right;
2799 }
2800 if (holey_float) {
2801 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64IsHole>({holey_float}));
2802 return true;
2803 }
2804 }
2805
2806 if (left->properties().value_representation() !=
2807 ValueRepresentation::kTagged ||
2808 right->properties().value_representation() !=
2809 ValueRepresentation::kTagged) {
2810 SetAccumulator(GetBooleanConstant(false));
2811 } else {
2812 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(left, right));
2813 }
2814 return true;
2815}
2816
2817template <Operation kOperation>
2818ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCompareOperation() {
2819 if (TryReduceCompareEqualAgainstConstant<kOperation>())
2820 return ReduceResult::Done();
2821
2822 // Compare opcodes are not always commutative. We sort the ones which are for
2823 // better CSE coverage.
2824 auto SortCommute = [](ValueNode*& left, ValueNode*& right) {
2825 if (!v8_flags.maglev_cse) return;
2826 if (kOperation != Operation::kEqual &&
2827 kOperation != Operation::kStrictEqual) {
2828 return;
2829 }
2830 if (left > right) {
2831 std::swap(left, right);
2832 }
2833 };
2834
2835 auto TryConstantFoldInt32 = [&](ValueNode* left, ValueNode* right) {
2836 if (left->Is<Int32Constant>() && right->Is<Int32Constant>()) {
2837 int left_value = left->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
2838 int right_value = right->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
2839 SetAccumulator(GetBooleanConstant(
2840 OperationValue<kOperation>(left_value, right_value)));
2841 return true;
2842 }
2843 return false;
2844 };
2845
2846 auto TryConstantFoldEqual = [&](ValueNode* left, ValueNode* right) {
2847 if (left == right) {
2848 SetAccumulator(
2849 GetBooleanConstant(kOperation == Operation::kEqual ||
2850 kOperation == Operation::kStrictEqual ||
2851 kOperation == Operation::kLessThanOrEqual ||
2852 kOperation == Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual));
2853 return true;
2854 }
2855 return false;
2856 };
2857
2858 auto MaybeOddballs = [&]() {
2859 auto MaybeOddball = [&](ValueNode* value) {
2860 ValueRepresentation rep = value->value_representation();
2861 switch (rep) {
2862 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
2863 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
2864 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
2865 return false;
2866 default:
2867 break;
2868 }
2869 return !CheckType(value, NodeType::kNumber);
2870 };
2871 return MaybeOddball(LoadRegister(0)) || MaybeOddball(GetAccumulator());
2872 };
2873
2874 FeedbackNexus nexus = FeedbackNexusForOperand(1);
2875 switch (nexus.GetCompareOperationFeedback()) {
2876 case CompareOperationHint::kNone:
2877 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
2878 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCompareOperation);
2879
2880 case CompareOperationHint::kSignedSmall: {
2881 // TODO(victorgomes): Add a smart equality operator, that compares for
2882 // constants in different representations.
2883 ValueNode* left = GetInt32(LoadRegister(0));
2884 ValueNode* right = GetInt32(GetAccumulator());
2885 if (TryConstantFoldEqual(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2886 if (TryConstantFoldInt32(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2887 SortCommute(left, right);
2888 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Int32Compare>({left, right}, kOperation));
2889 return ReduceResult::Done();
2890 }
2891 case CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
2892 // TODO(leszeks): we could support all kNumberOrOddball with
2893 // BranchIfFloat64Compare, but we'd need to special case comparing
2894 // oddballs with NaN value (e.g. undefined) against themselves.
2895 if (MaybeOddballs()) {
2896 break;
2897 }
2898 [[fallthrough]];
2899 case CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
2900 if (kOperation == Operation::kStrictEqual && MaybeOddballs()) {
2901 break;
2902 }
2903 [[fallthrough]];
2904 case CompareOperationHint::kNumber: {
2905 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2906 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2907 if (left->value_representation() == ValueRepresentation::kInt32 &&
2908 right->value_representation() == ValueRepresentation::kInt32) {
2909 if (TryConstantFoldEqual(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2910 if (TryConstantFoldInt32(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2911 SortCommute(left, right);
2912 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Int32Compare>({left, right}, kOperation));
2913 return ReduceResult::Done();
2914 }
2915 // In compare operations, booleans should be converted to Float64 but
2916 // non-boolean oddballs shouldn't. Even if the feedback type was
2917 // kNumberOrOddball, we'd still pass
2918 // TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean.
2919 NodeType allowed_input_type;
2920 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type;
2921 if (nexus.GetCompareOperationFeedback() ==
2922 CompareOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean) {
2923 allowed_input_type = NodeType::kNumberOrBoolean;
2924 conversion_type = TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean;
2925 } else {
2926 allowed_input_type = NodeType::kNumber;
2927 conversion_type = TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber;
2928 }
2929 left = GetFloat64ForToNumber(left, allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2930 right = GetFloat64ForToNumber(right, allowed_input_type, conversion_type);
2931 if (left->Is<Float64Constant>() && right->Is<Float64Constant>()) {
2932 double left_value = left->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
2933 double right_value =
2934 right->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value().get_scalar();
2935 SetAccumulator(GetBooleanConstant(
2936 OperationValue<kOperation>(left_value, right_value)));
2937 return ReduceResult::Done();
2938 }
2939 SortCommute(left, right);
2940 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<Float64Compare>({left, right}, kOperation));
2941 return ReduceResult::Done();
2942 }
2943 case CompareOperationHint::kInternalizedString: {
2944 DCHECK(kOperation == Operation::kEqual ||
2945 kOperation == Operation::kStrictEqual);
2946 ValueNode *left, *right;
2947 if (IsRegisterEqualToAccumulator(0)) {
2948 left = right = GetInternalizedString(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0));
2949 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTrueValue));
2950 return ReduceResult::Done();
2951 }
2952 left = GetInternalizedString(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0));
2953 right =
2954 GetInternalizedString(interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
2955 if (TryConstantFoldEqual(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2956 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(left, right));
2957 return ReduceResult::Done();
2958 }
2959 case CompareOperationHint::kSymbol: {
2960 DCHECK(kOperation == Operation::kEqual ||
2961 kOperation == Operation::kStrictEqual);
2962
2963 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2964 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2965 BuildCheckSymbol(left);
2966 BuildCheckSymbol(right);
2967 if (TryConstantFoldEqual(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2968 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(left, right));
2969 return ReduceResult::Done();
2970 }
2971 case CompareOperationHint::kString: {
2972 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
2973 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
2974 BuildCheckString(left);
2975 BuildCheckString(right);
2976
2977 ValueNode* result;
2978 if (TryConstantFoldEqual(left, right)) return ReduceResult::Done();
2979 ValueNode* tagged_left = GetTaggedValue(left);
2980 ValueNode* tagged_right = GetTaggedValue(right);
2981 switch (kOperation) {
2982 case Operation::kEqual:
2983 case Operation::kStrictEqual:
2984 result = AddNewNode<StringEqual>({tagged_left, tagged_right});
2985 break;
2986 case Operation::kLessThan:
2987 result = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringLessThan>(
2988 {tagged_left, tagged_right});
2989 break;
2990 case Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
2991 result = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringLessThanOrEqual>(
2992 {tagged_left, tagged_right});
2993 break;
2994 case Operation::kGreaterThan:
2995 result = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringGreaterThan>(
2996 {tagged_left, tagged_right});
2997 break;
2998 case Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
2999 result = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringGreaterThanOrEqual>(
3000 {tagged_left, tagged_right});
3001 break;
3002 }
3003
3004 SetAccumulator(result);
3005 return ReduceResult::Done();
3006 }
3007 case CompareOperationHint::kAny:
3008 case CompareOperationHint::kBigInt64:
3009 case CompareOperationHint::kBigInt:
3010 case CompareOperationHint::kReceiverOrNullOrUndefined:
3011 break;
3012 case CompareOperationHint::kReceiver: {
3013 DCHECK(kOperation == Operation::kEqual ||
3014 kOperation == Operation::kStrictEqual);
3015
3016 ValueNode* left = LoadRegister(0);
3017 ValueNode* right = GetAccumulator();
3018 BuildCheckJSReceiver(left);
3019 BuildCheckJSReceiver(right);
3020 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(left, right));
3021 return ReduceResult::Done();
3022 }
3023 }
3024
3025 BuildGenericBinaryOperationNode<kOperation>();
3026 return ReduceResult::Done();
3027}
3028
3029ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdar() {
3030 MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0),
3031 interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
3032 return ReduceResult::Done();
3033}

3035ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaZero() {
3036 SetAccumulator(GetSmiConstant(0));
3037 return ReduceResult::Done();
3038}

3040 int constant = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0);
3041 SetAccumulator(GetSmiConstant(constant));
3042 return ReduceResult::Done();
3043}
3044ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaUndefined() {
3045 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
3046 return ReduceResult::Done();
3047}
3048ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaNull() {
3049 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNullValue));
3050 return ReduceResult::Done();
3051}

3053 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue));

3064ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaConstant() {

3066 return ReduceResult::Done();
3067}
3068
3069bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TrySpecializeLoadContextSlotToFunctionContext(
3070 ValueNode* context, int slot_index, ContextSlotMutability slot_mutability) {
3071 DCHECK(compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context());
3072
3073 if (slot_mutability == kMutable) return false;
3074
3075 auto constant = TryGetConstant(context);
3076 if (!constant) return false;
3077
3078 compiler::ContextRef context_ref = constant.value().AsContext();
3079
3080 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_slot_value =
3081 context_ref.get(broker(), slot_index);
3082 if (!maybe_slot_value.has_value()) return false;
3083
3084 compiler::ObjectRef slot_value = maybe_slot_value.value();
3085 if (slot_value.IsHeapObject()) {
3086 // Even though the context slot is immutable, the context might have escaped
3087 // before the function to which it belongs has initialized the slot. We
3088 // must be conservative and check if the value in the slot is currently the
3089 // hole or undefined. Only if it is neither of these, can we be sure that it
3090 // won't change anymore.
3091 //
3092 // See also: JSContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadContext.
3093 compiler::OddballType oddball_type =
3094 slot_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker()).oddball_type(broker());
3095 if (oddball_type == compiler::OddballType::kUndefined ||
3096 slot_value.IsTheHole()) {
3097 return false;
3098 }
3099 }
3100
3101 // Fold the load of the immutable slot.
3102
3103 SetAccumulator(GetConstant(slot_value));
3104 return true;
3105}
3106
3107ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::TrySpecializeLoadScriptContextSlot(
3108 ValueNode* context_node, int index) {
3109 if (!context_node->Is<Constant>()) return {};
3110 compiler::ContextRef context =
3111 context_node->Cast<Constant>()->ref().AsContext();
3112 DCHECK(context.object()->IsScriptContext());
3113 auto maybe_property = context.object()->GetScriptContextSideProperty(index);
3114 auto property =
3115 maybe_property ? maybe_property.value() : ContextSidePropertyCell::kOther;
3116 int offset = Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index);
3117 switch (property) {
3118 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kConst: {
3119 compiler::OptionalObjectRef constant = context.get(broker(), index);
3120 if (!constant.has_value()) {
3121 return BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot>(context_node,
3122 offset);
3123 }
3124 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3125 context, index, property, broker());
3126 return GetConstant(*constant);
3127 }
3128 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kSmi: {
3129 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3130 context, index, property, broker());
3131 ValueNode* value = BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot>(
3132 context_node, offset);
3133 EnsureType(value, NodeType::kSmi);
3134 return value;
3135 }
3136 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kMutableInt32:
3137 if (auto mutable_heap_number = context.get(broker(), index)) {
3138 if (!mutable_heap_number->IsHeapNumber()) {
3139 // TODO(victorgomes): In case the tag is out of date by now we could
3140 // retry this reduction.
3141 break;
3142 }
3143 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3144 context, index, property, broker());
3145 return AddNewNode<LoadInt32>(
3146 {GetConstant(*mutable_heap_number)},
3147 static_cast<int>(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_)));
3148 }
3149 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3150 context, index, property, broker());
3151 return AddNewNode<LoadHeapInt32>({context_node}, offset);
3152 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kMutableHeapNumber:
3153 if (auto mutable_heap_number = context.get(broker(), index)) {
3154 if (!mutable_heap_number->IsHeapNumber()) {
3155 // TODO(victorgomes): In case the tag is out of date by now we could
3156 // retry this reduction.
3157 break;
3158 }
3159 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3160 context, index, property, broker());
3161 return AddNewNode<LoadFloat64>(
3162 {GetConstant(*mutable_heap_number)},
3163 static_cast<int>(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_)));
3164 }
3165 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3166 context, index, property, broker());
3167 return AddNewNode<LoadDoubleField>({context_node}, offset);
3168 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kOther:
3169 break;
3170 default:
3171 UNREACHABLE();
3172 }
3173 return BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot>(context_node,
3174 offset);
3175}
3176
3177ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::LoadAndCacheContextSlot(
3178 ValueNode* context, int index, ContextSlotMutability slot_mutability,
3179 ContextKind context_kind) {
3180 int offset = Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index);
3181 ValueNode*& cached_value =
3182 slot_mutability == kMutable
3183 ? known_node_aspects().loaded_context_slots[{context, offset}]
3184 : known_node_aspects().loaded_context_constants[{context, offset}];
3185 if (cached_value) {
3186 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
3187 std::cout << " * Reusing cached context slot "
3188 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), context) << "[" << offset
3189 << "]: " << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), cached_value)
3190 << std::endl;
3191 }
3192 return cached_value;
3193 }
3194 known_node_aspects().UpdateMayHaveAliasingContexts(context);
3195 if (context_kind == ContextKind::kScriptContext) {
3196 cached_value = TrySpecializeLoadScriptContextSlot(context, index);
3197 if (cached_value) return cached_value;
3198 return cached_value =
3199 BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForScriptContextSlot>(
3200 context, index);
3201 }
3202 return cached_value = BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot>(
3203 context, offset);
3204}
3205
3206bool MaglevGraphBuilder::ContextMayAlias(
3207 ValueNode* context, compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef scope_info) {
3208 // Distinguishing contexts by their scope info only works if scope infos are
3209 // guaranteed to be unique.
3210 if (!scope_info.has_value()) {
3211 return true;
3212 }
3213 auto other = graph()->TryGetScopeInfo(context, broker());
3214 if (!other.has_value()) {
3215 return true;
3216 }
3217 return scope_info->equals(*other);
3218}
3219
3220MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TrySpecializeStoreScriptContextSlot(
3221 ValueNode* context, int index, ValueNode* value, Node** store) {
3222 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(store);
3223 DCHECK(v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_number ||
3224 v8_flags.const_tracking_let);
3225 if (!context->Is<Constant>()) {
3226 *store = AddNewNode<StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier>(
3227 {context, value}, index);
3228 return ReduceResult::Done();
3229 }
3230
3231 compiler::ContextRef context_ref =
3232 context->Cast<Constant>()->ref().AsContext();
3233 DCHECK(context_ref.object()->IsScriptContext());
3234 auto maybe_property =
3235 context_ref.object()->GetScriptContextSideProperty(index);
3236 if (!maybe_property) {
3237 *store = AddNewNode<StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier>(
3238 {context, value}, index);
3239 return ReduceResult::Done();
3240 }
3241 auto property = maybe_property.value();
3242 int offset = Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index);
3243 if (property == ContextSidePropertyCell::kConst) {
3244 compiler::OptionalObjectRef constant = context_ref.get(broker(), index);
3245 if (!constant.has_value() ||
3246 (constant->IsString() && !constant->IsInternalizedString())) {
3247 *store = AddNewNode<StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier>(
3248 {context, value}, index);
3249 return ReduceResult::Done();
3250 }
3251 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3252 context_ref, index, property, broker());
3253 return BuildCheckValue(value, *constant);
3254 }
3255
3256 if (!v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_number) {
3257 *store = BuildStoreTaggedField(context, value, offset,
3258 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
3259 return ReduceResult::Done();
3260 }
3261
3262 switch (property) {
3263 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kConst:
3264 UNREACHABLE();
3265 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kSmi:
3266 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckSmi(value));
3267 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3268 context_ref, index, property, broker());
3269 *store = BuildStoreTaggedField(context, value, offset,
3270 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
3271 break;
3272 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kMutableInt32:
3273 EnsureInt32(value, true);
3274 if (auto mutable_heap_number = context_ref.get(broker(), index)) {
3275 if (!mutable_heap_number->IsHeapNumber()) {
3276 // TODO(victorgomes): In case the tag is out of date by now we could
3277 // retry this reduction.
3278 return {};
3279 }
3280 *store = AddNewNode<StoreInt32>(
3281 {GetConstant(*mutable_heap_number), value},
3282 static_cast<int>(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_)));
3283 } else {
3284 *store = AddNewNode<StoreHeapInt32>({context, value}, offset);
3285 }
3286 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3287 context_ref, index, property, broker());
3288 break;
3289 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kMutableHeapNumber:
3290 BuildCheckNumber(value);
3291 if (auto mutable_heap_number = context_ref.get(broker(), index)) {
3292 if (!mutable_heap_number->IsHeapNumber()) {
3293 // TODO(victorgomes): In case the tag is out of date by now we could
3294 // retry this reduction.
3295 return {};
3296 }
3297 *store = AddNewNode<StoreFloat64>(
3298 {GetConstant(*mutable_heap_number), value},
3299 static_cast<int>(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_)));
3300 } else {
3301 *store = AddNewNode<StoreDoubleField>({context, value}, offset);
3302 }
3303 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnScriptContextSlotProperty(
3304 context_ref, index, property, broker());
3305 break;
3306 case ContextSidePropertyCell::kOther:
3307 *store = BuildStoreTaggedField(context, value, offset,
3308 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
3309 break;
3310 default:
3311 UNREACHABLE();
3312 }
3313 return ReduceResult::Done();
3314}
3315
3316ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::StoreAndCacheContextSlot(
3317 ValueNode* context, int index, ValueNode* value, ContextKind context_kind) {
3318 int offset = Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index);
3319 DCHECK_EQ(
3320 known_node_aspects().loaded_context_constants.count({context, offset}),
3321 0);
3322
3323 Node* store = nullptr;
3324 if ((v8_flags.script_context_mutable_heap_number ||
3325 v8_flags.const_tracking_let) &&
3326 context_kind == ContextKind::kScriptContext) {
3327 MaybeReduceResult result =
3328 TrySpecializeStoreScriptContextSlot(context, index, value, &store);
3329 RETURN_IF_ABORT(result);
3330 if (!store && result.IsDone()) {
3331 // If we didn't need to emit any store, there is nothing to cache.
3332 return result.Checked();
3333 }
3334 }
3335
3336 if (!store) {
3337 store = BuildStoreTaggedField(context, value, offset,
3338 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
3339 }
3340
3341 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
3342 std::cout << " * Recording context slot store "
3343 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), context) << "[" << offset
3344 << "]: " << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), value) << std::endl;
3345 }
3346 known_node_aspects().UpdateMayHaveAliasingContexts(context);
3347 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedContextSlots& loaded_context_slots =
3348 known_node_aspects().loaded_context_slots;
3349 if (known_node_aspects().may_have_aliasing_contexts() ==
3350 KnownNodeAspects::ContextSlotLoadsAlias::Yes) {
3351 compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef scope_info =
3352 graph()->TryGetScopeInfo(context, broker());
3353 for (auto& cache : loaded_context_slots) {
3354 if (std::get<int>(cache.first) == offset &&
3355 std::get<ValueNode*>(cache.first) != context) {
3356 if (ContextMayAlias(std::get<ValueNode*>(cache.first), scope_info) &&
3357 cache.second != value) {
3358 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
3359 std::cout << " * Clearing probably aliasing value "
3360 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(),
3361 std::get<ValueNode*>(cache.first))
3362 << "[" << offset
3363 << "]: " << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), value)
3364 << std::endl;
3365 }
3366 cache.second = nullptr;
3367 if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
3368 loop_effects_->context_slot_written.insert(cache.first);
3369 loop_effects_->may_have_aliasing_contexts = true;
3370 }
3371 }
3372 }
3373 }
3374 }
3375 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedContextSlotsKey key{context, offset};
3376 auto updated = loaded_context_slots.emplace(key, value);
3377 if (updated.second) {
3378 if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
3379 loop_effects_->context_slot_written.insert(key);
3380 }
3381 unobserved_context_slot_stores_[key] = store;
3382 } else {
3383 if (updated.first->second != value) {
3384 updated.first->second = value;
3385 if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
3386 loop_effects_->context_slot_written.insert(key);
3387 }
3388 }
3389 if (known_node_aspects().may_have_aliasing_contexts() !=
3390 KnownNodeAspects::ContextSlotLoadsAlias::Yes) {
3391 auto last_store = unobserved_context_slot_stores_.find(key);
3392 if (last_store != unobserved_context_slot_stores_.end()) {
3393 MarkNodeDead(last_store->second);
3394 last_store->second = store;
3395 } else {
3396 unobserved_context_slot_stores_[key] = store;
3397 }
3398 }
3399 }
3400 return ReduceResult::Done();
3401}
3402
3403void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadContextSlot(
3404 ValueNode* context, size_t depth, int slot_index,
3405 ContextSlotMutability slot_mutability, ContextKind context_kind) {
3406 context = GetContextAtDepth(context, depth);
3407 if (compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context() &&
3408 TrySpecializeLoadContextSlotToFunctionContext(context, slot_index,
3409 slot_mutability)) {
3410 return; // Our work here is done.
3411 }
3412
3413 // Always load the slot here as if it were mutable. Immutable slots have a
3414 // narrow range of mutability if the context escapes before the slot is
3415 // initialized, so we can't safely assume that the load can be cached in case
3416 // it's a load before initialization (e.g. var a = a + 42).
3417 current_interpreter_frame_.set_accumulator(
3418 LoadAndCacheContextSlot(context, slot_index, kMutable, context_kind));
3419}
3420
3421ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreContextSlot(
3422 ValueNode* context, size_t depth, int slot_index, ValueNode* value,
3423 ContextKind context_kind) {
3424 context = GetContextAtDepth(context, depth);
3425 return StoreAndCacheContextSlot(context, slot_index, value, context_kind);
3426}

3534
3535ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTaggedEqual(ValueNode* lhs,
3536 ValueNode* rhs) {
3537 ValueNode* tagged_lhs = GetTaggedValue(lhs);
3538 ValueNode* tagged_rhs = GetTaggedValue(rhs);
3539 if (tagged_lhs == tagged_rhs) {
3540 return GetBooleanConstant(true);
3541 }
3542 if (HaveDifferentTypes(tagged_lhs, tagged_rhs)) {
3543 return GetBooleanConstant(false);
3544 }
3545 // TODO(victorgomes): We could retrieve the HeapObjectRef in Constant and
3546 // compare them.
3547 if (IsConstantNode(tagged_lhs->opcode()) && !tagged_lhs->Is<Constant>() &&
3548 tagged_lhs->opcode() == tagged_rhs->opcode()) {
3549 // Constants nodes are canonicalized, except for the node holding
3550 // HeapObjectRef, so equal constants should have been handled above.
3551 return GetBooleanConstant(false);
3552 }
3553 return AddNewNode<TaggedEqual>({tagged_lhs, tagged_rhs});
3554}
3555
3556ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTaggedEqual(ValueNode* lhs,
3557 RootIndex rhs_index) {
3558 return BuildTaggedEqual(lhs, GetRootConstant(rhs_index));
3559}
3560
3561ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestReferenceEqual() {
3562 ValueNode* lhs = LoadRegister(0);
3563 ValueNode* rhs = GetAccumulator();
3564 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(lhs, rhs));
3565 return ReduceResult::Done();
3566}
3567
3568ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTestUndetectable(ValueNode* value) {
3569 if (value->properties().value_representation() ==
3570 ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
3571 return AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64IsHole>({value});
3572 } else if (value->properties().value_representation() !=
3573 ValueRepresentation::kTagged) {
3574 return GetBooleanConstant(false);
3575 }
3576
3577 if (auto maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(value)) {
3578 auto map = maybe_constant.value().map(broker());
3579 return GetBooleanConstant(map.is_undetectable());
3580 }
3581
3582 NodeType node_type;
3583 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kSmi, &node_type)) {
3584 return GetBooleanConstant(false);
3585 }
3586
3587 auto it = known_node_aspects().FindInfo(value);
3588 if (known_node_aspects().IsValid(it)) {
3589 NodeInfo& info = it->second;
3590 if (info.possible_maps_are_known()) {
3591 // We check if all the possible maps have the same undetectable bit value.
3592 DCHECK_GT(info.possible_maps().size(), 0);
3593 bool first_is_undetectable = info.possible_maps()[0].is_undetectable();
3594 bool all_the_same_value =
3595 std::all_of(info.possible_maps().begin(), info.possible_maps().end(),
3596 [first_is_undetectable](compiler::MapRef map) {
3597 bool is_undetectable = map.is_undetectable();
3598 return (first_is_undetectable && is_undetectable) ||
3599 (!first_is_undetectable && !is_undetectable);
3600 });
3601 if (all_the_same_value) {
3602 return GetBooleanConstant(first_is_undetectable);
3603 }
3604 }
3605 }
3606
3607 enum CheckType type = GetCheckType(node_type);
3608 return AddNewNode<TestUndetectable>({value}, type);
3609}
3610
3611MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUndetectable(
3612 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* value) {
3613 ValueNode* result = BuildTestUndetectable(value);
3614 switch (result->opcode()) {
3615 case Opcode::kRootConstant:
3616 switch (result->Cast<RootConstant>()->index()) {
3617 case RootIndex::kTrueValue:
3618 case RootIndex::kUndefinedValue:
3619 case RootIndex::kNullValue:
3620 return builder.AlwaysTrue();
3621 default:
3622 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
3623 }
3624 case Opcode::kHoleyFloat64IsHole:
3625 return BuildBranchIfFloat64IsHole(
3626 builder, result->Cast<HoleyFloat64IsHole>()->input().node());
3627 case Opcode::kTestUndetectable:
3628 return builder.Build<BranchIfUndetectable>(
3629 {result->Cast<TestUndetectable>()->value().node()},
3630 result->Cast<TestUndetectable>()->check_type());
3631 default:
3632 UNREACHABLE();
3633 }
3634}
3635
3636ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestUndetectable() {
3637 SetAccumulator(BuildTestUndetectable(GetAccumulator()));
3638 return ReduceResult::Done();
3639}
3640
3641ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestNull() {
3642 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
3643 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(value, RootIndex::kNullValue));
3644 return ReduceResult::Done();
3645}
3646
3647ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestUndefined() {
3648 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
3649 SetAccumulator(BuildTaggedEqual(value, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
3650 return ReduceResult::Done();
3651}
3652
3653template <typename Function>
3654MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceTypeOf(
3655 ValueNode* value, const Function& GetResult) {
3656 // Similar to TF, we assume that all undetectable receiver objects are also
3657 // callables. In practice, there is only one: document.all.
3658 switch (CheckTypes(
3659 value, {NodeType::kBoolean, NodeType::kNumber, NodeType::kString,
3660 NodeType::kSymbol, NodeType::kCallable, NodeType::kJSArray})) {
3661 case NodeType::kBoolean:
3662 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kBoolean, RootIndex::kboolean_string);
3663 case NodeType::kNumber:
3664 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kNumber, RootIndex::knumber_string);
3665 case NodeType::kString:
3666 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kString, RootIndex::kstring_string);
3667 case NodeType::kSymbol:
3668 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kSymbol, RootIndex::ksymbol_string);
3669 case NodeType::kCallable:
3670 return Select(
3671 [&](auto& builder) {
3672 return BuildBranchIfUndetectable(builder, value);
3673 },
3674 [&] {
3675 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kUndefined,
3676 RootIndex::kundefined_string);
3677 },
3678 [&] {
3679 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kFunction,
3680 RootIndex::kfunction_string);
3681 });
3682 case NodeType::kJSArray:
3683 // TODO(victorgomes): Track JSReceiver, non-callable types in Maglev.
3684 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kObject, RootIndex::kobject_string);
3685 default:
3686 break;
3687 }
3688
3689 if (IsNullValue(value)) {
3690 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kObject, RootIndex::kobject_string);
3691 }
3692 if (IsUndefinedValue(value)) {
3693 return GetResult(TypeOfLiteralFlag::kUndefined,
3694 RootIndex::kundefined_string);
3695 }
3696
3697 return {};
3698}
3699
3700MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceTypeOf(ValueNode* value) {
3701 return TryReduceTypeOf(value,
3702 [&](TypeOfLiteralFlag _, RootIndex idx) -> ValueNode* {
3703 return GetRootConstant(idx);
3704 });
3705}
3706
3707ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestTypeOf() {
3708 // TODO(v8:7700): Add a branch version of TestTypeOf that does not need to
3709 // materialise the boolean value.
3710 TypeOfLiteralFlag literal =
3711 interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::Decode(GetFlag8Operand(0));
3712 if (literal == TypeOfLiteralFlag::kOther) {
3713 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kFalseValue));
3714 return ReduceResult::Done();
3715 }
3716 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
3717 auto GetResult = [&](TypeOfLiteralFlag expected, RootIndex _) {
3718 return GetRootConstant(literal == expected ? RootIndex::kTrueValue
3719 : RootIndex::kFalseValue);
3720 };
3721 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReduceTypeOf(value, GetResult), SetAccumulator);
3722
3723 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<TestTypeOf>({value}, literal));
3724 return ReduceResult::Done();
3725}
3726
3727MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildScriptContextStore(
3728 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3729 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsScriptContextSlot());
3730 if (global_access_feedback.immutable()) return {};
3731 auto script_context = GetConstant(global_access_feedback.script_context());
3732 return StoreAndCacheContextSlot(
3733 script_context, global_access_feedback.slot_index(), GetAccumulator(),
3734 ContextKind::kScriptContext);
3735}
3736
3737MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertyCellStore(
3738 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3739 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsPropertyCell());
3740
3741 compiler::PropertyCellRef property_cell =
3742 global_access_feedback.property_cell();
3743 if (!property_cell.Cache(broker())) return {};
3744
3745 compiler::ObjectRef property_cell_value = property_cell.value(broker());
3746 if (property_cell_value.IsPropertyCellHole()) {
3747 // The property cell is no longer valid.
3748 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
3749 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
3750 }
3751
3752 PropertyDetails property_details = property_cell.property_details();
3753 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, property_details.kind());
3754
3755 if (property_details.IsReadOnly()) {
3756 // Don't even bother trying to lower stores to read-only data
3757 // properties.
3758 // TODO(neis): We could generate code that checks if the new value
3759 // equals the old one and then does nothing or deopts, respectively.
3760 return {};
3761 }
3762
3763 switch (property_details.cell_type()) {
3764 case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
3765 return {};
3766 case PropertyCellType::kConstant: {
3767 // TODO(victorgomes): Support non-internalized string.
3768 if (property_cell_value.IsString() &&
3769 !property_cell_value.IsInternalizedString()) {
3770 return {};
3771 }
3772 // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the new
3773 // value doesn't match the previous value stored inside the cell.
3774 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
3775 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
3776 return BuildCheckValue(value, property_cell_value);
3777 }
3778 case PropertyCellType::kConstantType: {
3779 // We rely on stability further below.
3780 if (property_cell_value.IsHeapObject() &&
3781 !property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker()).is_stable()) {
3782 return {};
3783 }
3784 // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the new
3785 // value's type doesn't match the type of the previous value in the cell.
3786 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
3787 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
3788 if (property_cell_value.IsHeapObject()) {
3789 compiler::MapRef property_cell_value_map =
3790 property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker());
3791 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(property_cell_value_map);
3792 BuildCheckHeapObject(value);
3793 RETURN_IF_ABORT(
3794 BuildCheckMaps(value, base::VectorOf({property_cell_value_map})));
3795 } else {
3796 RETURN_IF_ABORT(GetSmiValue(value));
3797 }
3798 ValueNode* property_cell_node = GetConstant(property_cell.AsHeapObject());
3799 BuildStoreTaggedField(property_cell_node, value,
3800 PropertyCell::kValueOffset,
3801 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
3802 break;
3803 }
3804 case PropertyCellType::kMutable: {
3805 // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the
3806 // property ever becomes read-only.
3807 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
3808 ValueNode* property_cell_node = GetConstant(property_cell.AsHeapObject());
3809 BuildStoreTaggedField(property_cell_node, GetAccumulator(),
3810 PropertyCell::kValueOffset,
3811 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
3812 break;
3813 }
3814 case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
3815 UNREACHABLE();
3816 }
3817 return ReduceResult::Done();
3818}
3819
3820MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildScriptContextConstantLoad(
3821 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3822 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsScriptContextSlot());
3823 if (!global_access_feedback.immutable()) return {};
3824 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_slot_value =
3825 global_access_feedback.script_context().get(
3826 broker(), global_access_feedback.slot_index());
3827 if (!maybe_slot_value) return {};
3828 return GetConstant(maybe_slot_value.value());
3829}
3830
3831MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildScriptContextLoad(
3832 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3833 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsScriptContextSlot());
3834 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildScriptContextConstantLoad(global_access_feedback));
3835 auto script_context = GetConstant(global_access_feedback.script_context());
3836 ContextSlotMutability mutability =
3837 global_access_feedback.immutable() ? kImmutable : kMutable;
3838 return LoadAndCacheContextSlot(script_context,
3839 global_access_feedback.slot_index(),
3840 mutability, ContextKind::kScriptContext);
3841}
3842
3843MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertyCellLoad(
3844 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3845 // TODO(leszeks): A bunch of this is copied from
3846 // js-native-context-specialization.cc -- I wonder if we can unify it
3847 // somehow.
3848 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsPropertyCell());
3849
3850 compiler::PropertyCellRef property_cell =
3851 global_access_feedback.property_cell();
3852 if (!property_cell.Cache(broker())) return {};
3853
3854 compiler::ObjectRef property_cell_value = property_cell.value(broker());
3855 if (property_cell_value.IsPropertyCellHole()) {
3856 // The property cell is no longer valid.
3857 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
3858 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
3859 }
3860
3861 PropertyDetails property_details = property_cell.property_details();
3862 PropertyCellType property_cell_type = property_details.cell_type();
3863 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, property_details.kind());
3864
3865 if (!property_details.IsConfigurable() && property_details.IsReadOnly()) {
3866 return GetConstant(property_cell_value);
3867 }
3868
3869 // Record a code dependency on the cell if we can benefit from the
3870 // additional feedback, or the global property is configurable (i.e.
3871 // can be deleted or reconfigured to an accessor property).
3872 if (property_cell_type != PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
3873 property_details.IsConfigurable()) {
3874 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
3875 }
3876
3877 // Load from constant/undefined global property can be constant-folded.
3878 if (property_cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstant ||
3879 property_cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
3880 return GetConstant(property_cell_value);
3881 }
3882
3883 ValueNode* property_cell_node = GetConstant(property_cell.AsHeapObject());
3884 return BuildLoadTaggedField(property_cell_node, PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
3885}
3886
3887MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildGlobalStore(
3888 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3889 if (global_access_feedback.IsScriptContextSlot()) {
3890 return TryBuildScriptContextStore(global_access_feedback);
3891 } else if (global_access_feedback.IsPropertyCell()) {
3892 return TryBuildPropertyCellStore(global_access_feedback);
3893 } else {
3894 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsMegamorphic());
3895 return {};
3896 }
3897}
3898
3899MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildGlobalLoad(
3900 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback) {
3901 if (global_access_feedback.IsScriptContextSlot()) {
3902 return TryBuildScriptContextLoad(global_access_feedback);
3903 } else if (global_access_feedback.IsPropertyCell()) {
3904 return TryBuildPropertyCellLoad(global_access_feedback);
3905 } else {
3906 DCHECK(global_access_feedback.IsMegamorphic());
3907 return {};
3908 }
3909}

3911ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaGlobal() {
3912 // LdaGlobal <name_index> <slot>
3913
3914 static const int kNameOperandIndex = 0;
3915 static const int kSlotOperandIndex = 1;
3916
3917 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(kNameOperandIndex);
3918 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(kSlotOperandIndex);
3919 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
3920 return BuildLoadGlobal(name, feedback_source, TypeofMode::kNotInside);
3921}

3927 static const int kSlotOperandIndex = 1;
3928
3929 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(kNameOperandIndex);

3934
3935ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitStaGlobal() {
3936 // StaGlobal <name_index> <slot>
3937 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
3938 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
3939
3940 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& access_feedback =
3941 broker()->GetFeedbackForGlobalAccess(feedback_source);
3942
3943 if (access_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
3944 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
3945 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericGlobalAccess);
3946 }
3947
3948 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback =
3949 access_feedback.AsGlobalAccess();
3950 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildGlobalStore(global_access_feedback));
3951
3952 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
3953 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(0);
3954 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
3955 AddNewNode<StoreGlobal>({context, value}, name, feedback_source);
3956 return ReduceResult::Done();
3957}

3961 ValueNode* name = GetConstant(GetRefOperand<Name>(0));
3962 SetAccumulator(BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadLookupSlot, {name}).value());
3963 return ReduceResult::Done();
3964}

3969 ValueNode* slot = GetTaggedIndexConstant(iterator_.GetIndexOperand(1));
3970 ValueNode* depth =
3971 GetTaggedIndexConstant(iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2));
3972 SetAccumulator(
3973 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kLookupContextTrampoline>({name, depth, slot}));
3974 return ReduceResult::Done();

3981 ValueNode* depth =
3982 GetTaggedIndexConstant(iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2));

3987
3988bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CheckContextExtensions(size_t depth) {
3989 compiler::OptionalScopeInfoRef maybe_scope_info =
3990 graph()->TryGetScopeInfo(GetContext(), broker());
3991 if (!maybe_scope_info.has_value()) return false;
3992 compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = maybe_scope_info.value();
3993 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < depth; d++) {
3994 CHECK_NE(scope_info.scope_type(), ScopeType::SCRIPT_SCOPE);
3995 CHECK_NE(scope_info.scope_type(), ScopeType::REPL_MODE_SCOPE);
3996 if (scope_info.HasContextExtensionSlot() &&
3997 !broker()->dependencies()->DependOnEmptyContextExtension(scope_info)) {
3998 // Using EmptyContextExtension dependency is not possible for this
3999 // scope_info, so generate dynamic checks.
4000 ValueNode* context = GetContextAtDepth(GetContext(), d);
4001 // Only support known contexts so that we can check that there's no
4002 // extension at compile time. Otherwise we could end up in a deopt loop
4003 // once we do get an extension.
4004 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_ref = TryGetConstant(context);
4005 if (!maybe_ref) return false;
4006 compiler::ContextRef context_ref = maybe_ref.value().AsContext();
4007 compiler::OptionalObjectRef extension_ref =
4008 context_ref.get(broker(), Context::EXTENSION_INDEX);
4009 // The extension may be concurrently installed while we're checking the
4010 // context, in which case it may still be uninitialized. This still
4011 // means an extension is about to appear, so we should block this
4012 // optimization.
4013 if (!extension_ref) return false;
4014 if (!extension_ref->IsUndefined()) return false;
4015 ValueNode* extension = LoadAndCacheContextSlot(
4016 context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX, kMutable, ContextKind::kDefault);
4017 AddNewNode<CheckValue>({extension}, broker()->undefined_value());
4018 }
4019 CHECK_IMPLIES(!scope_info.HasOuterScopeInfo(), d + 1 == depth);
4020 if (scope_info.HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
4021 scope_info = scope_info.OuterScopeInfo(broker());
4022 }
4023 }
4024 return true;
4025}
4026
4027ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaLookupGlobalSlot() {
4028 // LdaLookupGlobalSlot <name_index> <feedback_slot> <depth>
4029 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(0);
4030 if (CheckContextExtensions(iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2))) {
4031 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
4032 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
4033 return BuildLoadGlobal(name, feedback_source, TypeofMode::kNotInside);
4034 } else {
4035 ValueNode* name_node = GetConstant(name);
4036 ValueNode* slot = GetTaggedIndexConstant(iterator_.GetIndexOperand(1));
4037 ValueNode* depth =
4038 GetTaggedIndexConstant(iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(2));
4039 ValueNode* result;
4040 if (parent_) {
4041 ValueNode* vector = GetConstant(feedback());
4042 result = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kLookupGlobalIC>(
4043 {name_node, depth, slot, vector});
4044 } else {
4045 result = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kLookupGlobalICTrampoline>(
4046 {name_node, depth, slot});
4047 }
4048 SetAccumulator(result);
4049 return ReduceResult::Done();
4050 }
4051}

4057 BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof, {name}).value());
4058 return ReduceResult::Done();

4104namespace {
4105Runtime::FunctionId StaLookupSlotFunction(uint8_t sta_lookup_slot_flags) {
4106 using Flags = interpreter::StoreLookupSlotFlags;
4107 switch (Flags::GetLanguageMode(sta_lookup_slot_flags)) {
4108 case LanguageMode::kStrict:
4109 return Runtime::kStoreLookupSlot_Strict;
4110 case LanguageMode::kSloppy:
4111 if (Flags::IsLookupHoistingMode(sta_lookup_slot_flags)) {
4112 return Runtime::kStoreLookupSlot_SloppyHoisting;
4113 } else {
4114 return Runtime::kStoreLookupSlot_Sloppy;
4115 }
4116 }
4117}
4118} // namespace
4119
4120ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitStaLookupSlot() {
4121 // StaLookupSlot <name_index> <flags>
4122 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
4123 ValueNode* name = GetConstant(GetRefOperand<Name>(0));
4124 uint32_t flags = GetFlag8Operand(1);
4125 EscapeContext();
4126 SetAccumulator(
4127 BuildCallRuntime(StaLookupSlotFunction(flags), {name, value}).value());
4128 return ReduceResult::Done();
4129}
4130
4131NodeType StaticTypeForNode(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
4132 LocalIsolate* isolate, ValueNode* node) {
4133 switch (node->properties().value_representation()) {
4134 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
4135 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
4136 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
4137 return NodeType::kNumber;
4138 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
4139 return NodeType::kNumberOrOddball;
4140 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
4141 UNREACHABLE();
4142 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
4143 break;
4144 }
4145 switch (node->opcode()) {
4146 case Opcode::kPhi:
4147 return node->Cast<Phi>()->type();
4148 case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagInt32:
4149 case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagUint32:
4150 case Opcode::kCheckedSmiTagFloat64:
4151 case Opcode::kUnsafeSmiTagInt32:
4152 case Opcode::kUnsafeSmiTagUint32:
4153 case Opcode::kSmiConstant:
4154 return NodeType::kSmi;
4155 case Opcode::kInt32ToNumber:
4156 case Opcode::kUint32ToNumber:
4157 case Opcode::kFloat64ToTagged:
4158 return NodeType::kNumber;
4159 case Opcode::kHoleyFloat64ToTagged:
4160 return NodeType::kNumberOrOddball;
4161 case Opcode::kAllocationBlock:
4162 case Opcode::kInlinedAllocation:
4163 return StaticTypeForMap(node->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->object()->map(),
4164 broker);
4165 case Opcode::kRootConstant: {
4166 RootConstant* constant = node->Cast<RootConstant>();
4167 switch (constant->index()) {
4168 case RootIndex::kTrueValue:
4169 case RootIndex::kFalseValue:
4170 return NodeType::kBoolean;
4171 case RootIndex::kUndefinedValue:
4172 case RootIndex::kNullValue:
4173 return NodeType::kOddball;
4174 default:
4175 break;
4176 }
4177 [[fallthrough]];
4178 }
4179 case Opcode::kConstant: {
4180 compiler::HeapObjectRef ref =
4181 MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetConstant(broker, isolate, node).value();
4182 return StaticTypeForConstant(broker, ref);
4183 }
4184 case Opcode::kToNumberOrNumeric:
4185 if (node->Cast<ToNumberOrNumeric>()->mode() ==
4186 Object::Conversion::kToNumber) {
4187 return NodeType::kNumber;
4188 }
4189 // TODO(verwaest): Check what we need here.
4190 return NodeType::kUnknown;
4191 case Opcode::kToString:
4192 case Opcode::kNumberToString:
4193 case Opcode::kStringConcat:
4194 case Opcode::kStringWrapperConcat:
4195 return NodeType::kString;
4196 case Opcode::kCheckedInternalizedString:
4197 return NodeType::kInternalizedString;
4198 case Opcode::kToObject:
4199 case Opcode::kCreateObjectLiteral:
4200 case Opcode::kCreateShallowObjectLiteral:
4201 return NodeType::kJSReceiver;
4202 case Opcode::kCreateArrayLiteral:
4203 case Opcode::kCreateShallowArrayLiteral:
4204 return NodeType::kJSArray;
4205 case Opcode::kToName:
4206 return NodeType::kName;
4207 case Opcode::kFastCreateClosure:
4208 case Opcode::kCreateClosure:
4209 return NodeType::kCallable;
4210 case Opcode::kInt32Compare:
4211 case Opcode::kFloat64Compare:
4212 case Opcode::kGenericEqual:
4213 case Opcode::kGenericStrictEqual:
4214 case Opcode::kGenericLessThan:
4215 case Opcode::kGenericLessThanOrEqual:
4216 case Opcode::kGenericGreaterThan:
4217 case Opcode::kGenericGreaterThanOrEqual:
4218 case Opcode::kLogicalNot:
4219 case Opcode::kStringEqual:
4220 case Opcode::kTaggedEqual:
4221 case Opcode::kTaggedNotEqual:
4222 case Opcode::kTestInstanceOf:
4223 case Opcode::kTestTypeOf:
4224 case Opcode::kTestUndetectable:
4225 case Opcode::kToBoolean:
4226 case Opcode::kToBooleanLogicalNot:
4227 return NodeType::kBoolean;
4228 // Not value nodes:
4229#define GENERATE_CASE(Name) case Opcode::k##Name:
4230 CONTROL_NODE_LIST(GENERATE_CASE)
4231 NON_VALUE_NODE_LIST(GENERATE_CASE)
4232#undef GENERATE_CASE
4233 UNREACHABLE();
4234 case Opcode::kTransitionElementsKind:
4235 // Unsorted value nodes. TODO(maglev): See which of these should return
4236 // something else than kUnknown.
4237 case Opcode::kIdentity:
4238 case Opcode::kArgumentsElements:
4239 case Opcode::kArgumentsLength:
4240 case Opcode::kRestLength:
4241 case Opcode::kCall:
4242 case Opcode::kCallBuiltin:
4243 case Opcode::kCallCPPBuiltin:
4244 case Opcode::kCallForwardVarargs:
4245 case Opcode::kCallRuntime:
4246 case Opcode::kCallWithArrayLike:
4247 case Opcode::kCallWithSpread:
4248 case Opcode::kCallKnownApiFunction:
4249 case Opcode::kCallKnownJSFunction:
4250 case Opcode::kCallSelf:
4251 case Opcode::kConstruct:
4252 case Opcode::kCheckConstructResult:
4253 case Opcode::kCheckDerivedConstructResult:
4254 case Opcode::kConstructWithSpread:
4255 case Opcode::kConvertReceiver:
4256 case Opcode::kConvertHoleToUndefined:
4257 case Opcode::kCreateFunctionContext:
4258 case Opcode::kCreateRegExpLiteral:
4259 case Opcode::kDeleteProperty:
4260 case Opcode::kEnsureWritableFastElements:
4261 case Opcode::kExtendPropertiesBackingStore:
4262 case Opcode::kForInPrepare:
4263 case Opcode::kForInNext:
4264 case Opcode::kGeneratorRestoreRegister:
4265 case Opcode::kGetIterator:
4266 case Opcode::kGetSecondReturnedValue:
4267 case Opcode::kGetTemplateObject:
4268 case Opcode::kHasInPrototypeChain:
4269 case Opcode::kInitialValue:
4270 case Opcode::kLoadTaggedField:
4271 case Opcode::kLoadTaggedFieldForProperty:
4272 case Opcode::kLoadTaggedFieldForContextSlot:
4273 case Opcode::kLoadTaggedFieldForScriptContextSlot:
4274 case Opcode::kLoadDoubleField:
4275 case Opcode::kLoadFloat64:
4276 case Opcode::kLoadInt32:
4277 case Opcode::kLoadHeapInt32:
4278 case Opcode::kLoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex:
4279 case Opcode::kLoadFixedArrayElement:
