4396
4397bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CheckStaticType(ValueNode* node, NodeType type,
4398 NodeType* current_type) {
4399 NodeType static_type = StaticTypeForNode(broker(), local_isolate(), node);
4400 if (current_type) *current_type = static_type;
4401 return NodeTypeIs(static_type, type);
4402}
4403
4404bool MaglevGraphBuilder::EnsureType(ValueNode* node, NodeType type,
4405 NodeType* old_type) {
4406 if (CheckStaticType(node, type, old_type)) return true;
4407 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(node);
4408 if (old_type) *old_type = known_info->type();
4409 if (NodeTypeIs(known_info->type(), type)) return true;
4410 known_info->CombineType(type);
4411 if (auto phi = node->TryCast<Phi>()) {
4412 known_info->CombineType(phi->type());
4413 }
4414 return false;
4415}
4416
4417template <typename Function>
4418bool MaglevGraphBuilder::EnsureType(ValueNode* node, NodeType type,
4419 Function ensure_new_type) {
4420 if (CheckStaticType(node, type)) return true;
4421 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(node);
4422 if (NodeTypeIs(known_info->type(), type)) return true;
4423 ensure_new_type(known_info->type());
4424 known_info->CombineType(type);
4425 return false;
4426}
4427
4428void MaglevGraphBuilder::SetKnownValue(ValueNode* node, compiler::ObjectRef ref,
4429 NodeType new_node_type) {
4430 DCHECK(!node->Is<Constant>());
4431 DCHECK(!node->Is<RootConstant>());
4432 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(node);
4433 // ref type should be compatible with type.
4434 DCHECK(NodeTypeIs(StaticTypeForConstant(broker(), ref), new_node_type));
4435 if (ref.IsHeapObject()) {
4436 DCHECK(IsInstanceOfNodeType(ref.AsHeapObject().map(broker()),
4437 known_info->type(), broker()));
4438 } else {
4439 DCHECK(!NodeTypeIs(known_info->type(), NodeType::kAnyHeapObject));
4440 }
4441 known_info->CombineType(new_node_type);
4442 known_info->alternative().set_checked_value(GetConstant(ref));
4443}
4444
4445NodeType MaglevGraphBuilder::CheckTypes(ValueNode* node,
4446 std::initializer_list<NodeType> types) {
4447 auto it = known_node_aspects().FindInfo(node);
4448 bool has_kna = known_node_aspects().IsValid(it);
4449 for (NodeType type : types) {
4450 if (CheckStaticType(node, type)) return type;
4451 if (has_kna) {
4452 if (NodeTypeIs(it->second.type(), type)) return type;
4453 }
4454 }
4455 return NodeType::kUnknown;
4456}
4457
4458bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CheckType(ValueNode* node, NodeType type,
4459 NodeType* current_type) {
4460 if (CheckStaticType(node, type, current_type)) return true;
4461 auto it = known_node_aspects().FindInfo(node);
4462 if (!known_node_aspects().IsValid(it)) return false;
4463 if (current_type) *current_type = it->second.type();
4464 return NodeTypeIs(it->second.type(), type);
4465}
4466
4467NodeType MaglevGraphBuilder::GetType(ValueNode* node) {
4468 auto it = known_node_aspects().FindInfo(node);
4469 if (!known_node_aspects().IsValid(it)) {
4470 return StaticTypeForNode(broker(), local_isolate(), node);
4471 }
4472 NodeType actual_type = it->second.type();
4473 if (auto phi = node->TryCast<Phi>()) {
4474 actual_type = CombineType(actual_type, phi->type());
4475 }
4476#ifdef DEBUG
4477 NodeType static_type = StaticTypeForNode(broker(), local_isolate(), node);
4478 if (!NodeTypeIs(actual_type, static_type)) {
4479 // In case we needed a numerical alternative of a smi value, the type
4480 // must generalize. In all other cases the node info type should reflect the
4481 // actual type.
4482 DCHECK(static_type == NodeType::kSmi && actual_type == NodeType::kNumber &&
4483 !known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node)->alternative().has_none());
4484 }
4485#endif // DEBUG
4486 return actual_type;
4487}
4488
4489bool MaglevGraphBuilder::HaveDifferentTypes(ValueNode* lhs, ValueNode* rhs) {
4490 return HasDifferentType(lhs, GetType(rhs));
4491}
4492
4493// Note: this is conservative, ie, returns true if {lhs} cannot be {rhs}.
4494// It might return false even if {lhs} is not {rhs}.
4495bool MaglevGraphBuilder::HasDifferentType(ValueNode* lhs, NodeType rhs_type) {
4496 NodeType lhs_type = GetType(lhs);
4497 if (lhs_type == NodeType::kUnknown || rhs_type == NodeType::kUnknown) {
4498 return false;
4499 }
4500 return IntersectType(lhs_type, rhs_type) == NodeType::kUnknown;
4501}
4502
4503bool MaglevGraphBuilder::MayBeNullOrUndefined(ValueNode* node) {
4504 NodeType static_type = StaticTypeForNode(broker(), local_isolate(), node);
4505 if (!NodeTypeMayBeNullOrUndefined(static_type)) return false;
4506 auto it = known_node_aspects().FindInfo(node);
4507 if (!known_node_aspects().IsValid(it)) return true;
4508 return NodeTypeMayBeNullOrUndefined(it->second.type());
4509}
4510
4511ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildSmiUntag(ValueNode* node) {
4512 if (EnsureType(node, NodeType::kSmi)) {
4513 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
4514 if (auto phi = node->TryCast<Phi>()) {
4515 phi->SetUseRequires31BitValue();
4516 }
4517 }
4518 return AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({node});
4519 } else {
4520 return AddNewNode<CheckedSmiUntag>({node});
4521 }
4522}
4523
4524ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildNumberOrOddballToFloat64(
4525 ValueNode* node, NodeType allowed_input_type,
4526 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType conversion_type) {
4527 NodeType old_type;
4528 if (EnsureType(node, allowed_input_type, &old_type)) {
4529 if (old_type == NodeType::kSmi) {
4530 ValueNode* untagged_smi = BuildSmiUntag(node);
4531 return AddNewNode<ChangeInt32ToFloat64>({untagged_smi});
4532 }
4533 return AddNewNode<UncheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64>({node},
4534 conversion_type);
4535 } else {
4536 return AddNewNode<CheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64>({node}, conversion_type);
4537 }
4538}
4539
4540ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckSmi(ValueNode* object,
4541 bool elidable) {
4542 if (CheckStaticType(object, NodeType::kSmi)) return object;
4543 if (CheckType(object, NodeType::kAnyHeapObject)) {
4544 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi);
4545 }
4546 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kSmi) && elidable) return object;
4547 switch (object->value_representation()) {
4548 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
4549 if (!SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
4550 AddNewNode<CheckInt32IsSmi>({object});
4551 }
4552 break;
4553 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
4554 AddNewNode<CheckUint32IsSmi>({object});
4555 break;
4556 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
4557 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
4558 AddNewNode<CheckHoleyFloat64IsSmi>({object});
4559 break;
4560 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
4561 AddNewNode<CheckSmi>({object});
4562 break;
4563 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
4564 UNREACHABLE();
4565 }
4566 return object;
4567}
4568
4569void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckHeapObject(ValueNode* object) {
4570 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kAnyHeapObject)) return;
4571 AddNewNode<CheckHeapObject>({object});
4572}
4573
4574void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckString(ValueNode* object) {
4575 NodeType known_type;
4576 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kString, &known_type)) return;
4577 AddNewNode<CheckString>({object}, GetCheckType(known_type));
4578}
4579
4580void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckStringOrStringWrapper(ValueNode* object) {
4581 NodeType known_type;
4582 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kStringOrStringWrapper, &known_type)) return;
4583 AddNewNode<CheckStringOrStringWrapper>({object}, GetCheckType(known_type));
4584}
4585
4586void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckNumber(ValueNode* object) {
4587 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kNumber)) return;
4588 AddNewNode<CheckNumber>({object}, Object::Conversion::kToNumber);
4589}
4590
4591void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckSymbol(ValueNode* object) {
4592 NodeType known_type;
4593 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kSymbol, &known_type)) return;
4594 AddNewNode<CheckSymbol>({object}, GetCheckType(known_type));
4595}
4596
4597void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckJSReceiver(ValueNode* object) {
4598 NodeType known_type;
4599 if (EnsureType(object, NodeType::kJSReceiver, &known_type)) return;
4600 AddNewNode<CheckInstanceType>({object}, GetCheckType(known_type),
4601 FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
4602}
4603
4604namespace {
4605
4606class KnownMapsMerger {
4607 public:
4608 explicit KnownMapsMerger(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone,
4609 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> requested_maps)
4610 : broker_(broker), zone_(zone), requested_maps_(requested_maps) {}
4611
4612 void IntersectWithKnownNodeAspects(
4613 ValueNode* object, const KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
4614 auto node_info_it = known_node_aspects.FindInfo(object);
4615 bool has_node_info = known_node_aspects.IsValid(node_info_it);
4616 NodeType type =
4617 has_node_info ? node_info_it->second.type() : NodeType::kUnknown;
4618 if (has_node_info && node_info_it->second.possible_maps_are_known()) {
4619 // TODO(v8:7700): Make intersection non-quadratic.
4620 for (compiler::MapRef possible_map :
4621 node_info_it->second.possible_maps()) {
4622 if (std::find(requested_maps_.begin(), requested_maps_.end(),
4623 possible_map) != requested_maps_.end()) {
4624 // No need to add dependencies, we already have them for all known
4625 // possible maps.
4626 // Filter maps which are impossible given this objects type. Since we
4627 // want to prove that an object with map `map` is not an instance of
4628 // `type`, we cannot use `StaticTypeForMap`, as it only provides an
4629 // approximation. This filtering is done to avoid creating
4630 // non-sensical types later (e.g. if we think only a non-string map
4631 // is possible, after a string check).
4632 if (IsInstanceOfNodeType(possible_map, type, broker_)) {
4633 InsertMap(possible_map);
4634 }
4635 } else {
4636 known_maps_are_subset_of_requested_maps_ = false;
4637 }
4638 }
4639 if (intersect_set_.is_empty()) {
4640 node_type_ = NodeType::kUnknown;
4641 }
4642 } else {
4643 // A missing entry here means the universal set, i.e., we don't know
4644 // anything about the possible maps of the object. Intersect with the
4645 // universal set, which means just insert all requested maps.
4646 known_maps_are_subset_of_requested_maps_ = false;
4647 existing_known_maps_found_ = false;
4648 for (compiler::MapRef map : requested_maps_) {
4649 InsertMap(map);
4650 }
4651 }
4652 }
4653
4654 void UpdateKnownNodeAspects(ValueNode* object,
4655 KnownNodeAspects& known_node_aspects) {
4656 // Update known maps.
4657 auto node_info = known_node_aspects.GetOrCreateInfoFor(
4658 object, broker_, broker_->local_isolate());
4659 node_info->SetPossibleMaps(intersect_set_, any_map_is_unstable_, node_type_,
4660 broker_);
4661 // Make sure known_node_aspects.any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable is updated
4662 // in case any_map_is_unstable changed to true for this object -- this can
4663 // happen if this was an intersection with the universal set which added new
4664 // possible unstable maps.
4665 if (any_map_is_unstable_) {
4666 known_node_aspects.any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable = true;
4667 }
4668 // At this point, known_node_aspects.any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable may be
4669 // true despite there no longer being any unstable maps for any nodes (if
4670 // this was the only node with unstable maps and this intersection removed
4671 // those). This is ok, because that's at worst just an overestimate -- we
4672 // could track whether this node's any_map_is_unstable flipped from true to
4673 // false, but this is likely overkill.
4674 // Insert stable map dependencies which weren't inserted yet. This is only
4675 // needed if our set of known maps was empty and we created it anew based on
4676 // maps we checked.
4677 if (!existing_known_maps_found_) {
4678 for (compiler::MapRef map : intersect_set_) {
4679 if (map.is_stable()) {
4680 broker_->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(map);
4681 }
4682 }
4683 } else {
4684 // TODO(victorgomes): Add a DCHECK_SLOW that checks if the maps already
4685 // exist in the CompilationDependencySet.
4686 }
4687 }
4688
4689 bool known_maps_are_subset_of_requested_maps() const {
4690 return known_maps_are_subset_of_requested_maps_;
4691 }
4692 bool emit_check_with_migration() const { return emit_check_with_migration_; }
4693
4694 const compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map>& intersect_set() const {
4695 return intersect_set_;
4696 }
4697
4698 NodeType node_type() const { return node_type_; }
4699
4700 private:
4701 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker_;
4702 Zone* zone_;
4703 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> requested_maps_;
4704 compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map> intersect_set_;
4705 bool known_maps_are_subset_of_requested_maps_ = true;
4706 bool existing_known_maps_found_ = true;
4707 bool emit_check_with_migration_ = false;
4708 bool any_map_is_unstable_ = false;
4709 NodeType node_type_ = static_cast<NodeType>(-1);
4710
4711 Zone* zone() const { return zone_; }
4712
4713 void InsertMap(compiler::MapRef map) {
4714 if (map.is_migration_target()) {
4715 emit_check_with_migration_ = true;
4716 }
4717 NodeType new_type = StaticTypeForMap(map, broker_);
4718 if (new_type == NodeType::kHeapNumber) {
4719 new_type = IntersectType(new_type, NodeType::kSmi);
4720 }
4721 node_type_ = IntersectType(node_type_, new_type);
4722 if (!map.is_stable()) {
4723 any_map_is_unstable_ = true;
4724 }
4725 intersect_set_.insert(map, zone());
4726 }
4727};
4728
4729} // namespace
4730
4731ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckMaps(
4732 ValueNode* object, base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> maps,
4733 std::optional<ValueNode*> map,
4734 bool has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target) {
4735 // TODO(verwaest): Support other objects with possible known stable maps as
4736 // well.
4737 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef constant = TryGetConstant(object)) {
4738 // For constants with stable maps that match one of the desired maps, we
4739 // don't need to emit a map check, and can use the dependency -- we
4740 // can't do this for unstable maps because the constant could migrate
4741 // during compilation.
4742 compiler::MapRef constant_map = constant.value().map(broker());
4743 if (std::find(maps.begin(), maps.end(), constant_map) != maps.end()) {
4744 if (constant_map.is_stable()) {
4745 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(constant_map);
4746 return ReduceResult::Done();
4747 }
4748 // TODO(verwaest): Reduce maps to the constant map.
4749 } else {
4750 // TODO(leszeks): Insert an unconditional deopt if the constant map
4751 // doesn't match the required map.
4752 }
4753 }
4754
4755 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(object);
4756
4757 // Calculates if known maps are a subset of maps, their map intersection and
4758 // whether we should emit check with migration.
4759 KnownMapsMerger merger(broker(), zone(), maps);
4760 merger.IntersectWithKnownNodeAspects(object, known_node_aspects());
4761
4762 // If the known maps are the subset of the maps to check, we are done.
4763 if (merger.known_maps_are_subset_of_requested_maps()) {
4764 // The node type of known_info can get out of sync with the possible maps.
4765 // For instance after merging with an effectively dead branch (i.e., check
4766 // contradicting all possible maps).
4767 // TODO(olivf) Try to combine node_info and possible maps and ensure that
4768 // narrowing the type also clears impossible possible_maps.
4769 if (!NodeTypeIs(known_info->type(), merger.node_type())) {
4770 known_info->IntersectType(merger.node_type());
4771 }
4772#ifdef DEBUG
4773 // Double check that, for every possible map, it's one of the maps we'd
4774 // want to check.
4775 for (compiler::MapRef possible_map :
4776 known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(object)->possible_maps()) {
4777 DCHECK_NE(std::find(maps.begin(), maps.end(), possible_map), maps.end());
4778 }
4779#endif
4780 return ReduceResult::Done();
4781 }
4782
4783 if (merger.intersect_set().is_empty()) {
4784 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
4785 }
4786
4787 // TODO(v8:7700): Check if the {maps} - {known_maps} size is smaller than
4788 // {maps} \intersect {known_maps}, we can emit CheckNotMaps instead.
4789
4790 // Emit checks.
4791 if (merger.emit_check_with_migration()) {
4792 AddNewNode<CheckMapsWithMigration>({object}, merger.intersect_set(),
4793 GetCheckType(known_info->type()));
4794 } else if (has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target) {
4795 AddNewNode<CheckMapsWithMigrationAndDeopt>(
4796 {object}, merger.intersect_set(), GetCheckType(known_info->type()));
4797 } else if (map) {
4798 AddNewNode<CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap>({object, *map},
4799 merger.intersect_set());
4800 } else {
4801 AddNewNode<CheckMaps>({object}, merger.intersect_set(),
4802 GetCheckType(known_info->type()));
4803 }
4804
4805 merger.UpdateKnownNodeAspects(object, known_node_aspects());
4806 return ReduceResult::Done();
4807}
4808
4809ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap(
4810 ValueNode* heap_object, ValueNode* object_map,
4811 const ZoneVector<compiler::MapRef>& transition_sources,
4812 compiler::MapRef transition_target) {
4813 // TODO(marja): Optimizations based on what we know about the intersection of
4814 // known maps and transition sources or transition target.
4815
4816 // TransitionElementsKind doesn't happen in cases where we'd need to do
4817 // CheckMapsWithMigration instead of CheckMaps.
4818 CHECK(!transition_target.is_migration_target());
4819 for (const compiler::MapRef transition_source : transition_sources) {
4820 CHECK(!transition_source.is_migration_target());
4821 }
4822
4823 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(heap_object);
4824
4825 AddNewNode<TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap>(
4826 {heap_object, object_map}, transition_sources, transition_target);
4827 // After this operation, heap_object's map is transition_target (or we
4828 // deopted).
4829 known_info->SetPossibleMaps(
4830 PossibleMaps{transition_target}, !transition_target.is_stable(),
4831 StaticTypeForMap(transition_target, broker()), broker());
4832 DCHECK(transition_target.IsJSReceiverMap());
4833 if (!transition_target.is_stable()) {
4834 known_node_aspects().any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable = true;
4835 } else {
4836 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(transition_target);
4837 }
4838 return ReduceResult::Done();
4839}
4840
4841ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCompareMaps(
4842 ValueNode* heap_object, ValueNode* object_map,
4843 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> maps, MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_graph,
4844 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label>& if_not_matched) {
4845 GetOrCreateInfoFor(heap_object);
4846 KnownMapsMerger merger(broker(), zone(), maps);
4847 merger.IntersectWithKnownNodeAspects(heap_object, known_node_aspects());
4848
4849 if (merger.intersect_set().is_empty()) {
4850 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
4851 }
4852
4853 // TODO(pthier): Support map packing.
4854 DCHECK(!V8_MAP_PACKING_BOOL);
4855
4856 // TODO(pthier): Handle map migrations.
4857 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> map_matched;
4858 const compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map>& relevant_maps = merger.intersect_set();
4859 if (relevant_maps.size() > 1) {
4860 map_matched.emplace(sub_graph, static_cast<int>(relevant_maps.size()));
4861 for (size_t map_index = 1; map_index < relevant_maps.size(); map_index++) {
4862 sub_graph->GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
4863 &*map_matched,
4864 {object_map, GetConstant(relevant_maps.at(map_index))});
4865 }
4866 }
4867 if_not_matched.emplace(sub_graph, 1);
4868 sub_graph->GotoIfFalse<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
4869 &*if_not_matched, {object_map, GetConstant(relevant_maps.at(0))});
4870 if (map_matched.has_value()) {
4871 sub_graph->Goto(&*map_matched);
4872 sub_graph->Bind(&*map_matched);
4873 }
4874 merger.UpdateKnownNodeAspects(heap_object, known_node_aspects());
4875 return ReduceResult::Done();
4876}
4877
4878ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildTransitionElementsKindAndCompareMaps(
4879 ValueNode* heap_object, ValueNode* object_map,
4880 const ZoneVector<compiler::MapRef>& transition_sources,
4881 compiler::MapRef transition_target, MaglevSubGraphBuilder* sub_graph,
4882 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label>& if_not_matched) {
4883 DCHECK(!transition_target.is_migration_target());
4884
4885 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(heap_object);
4886
4887 // TODO(pthier): Calculate and use the intersection of known maps with
4888 // (transition_sources union transition_target).
4889
4890 ValueNode* new_map = AddNewNode<TransitionElementsKind>(
4891 {heap_object, object_map}, transition_sources, transition_target);
4892
4893 // TODO(pthier): Support map packing.
4894 DCHECK(!V8_MAP_PACKING_BOOL);
4895 if_not_matched.emplace(sub_graph, 1);
4896 sub_graph->GotoIfFalse<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
4897 &*if_not_matched, {new_map, GetConstant(transition_target)});
4898 // After the branch, object's map is transition_target.
4899 DCHECK(transition_target.IsJSReceiverMap());
4900 known_info->SetPossibleMaps(
4901 PossibleMaps{transition_target}, !transition_target.is_stable(),
4902 StaticTypeForMap(transition_target, broker()), broker());
4903 if (!transition_target.is_stable()) {
4904 known_node_aspects().any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable = true;
4905 } else {
4906 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(transition_target);
4907 }
4908 return ReduceResult::Done();
4909}
4910
4911namespace {
4912AllocationBlock* GetAllocation(ValueNode* object) {
4913 if (object->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) {
4914 object = object->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->input(0).node();
4915 }
4916 if (object->Is<AllocationBlock>()) {
4917 return object->Cast<AllocationBlock>();
4918 }
4919 return nullptr;
4920}
4921} // namespace
4922
4923bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanElideWriteBarrier(ValueNode* object,
4924 ValueNode* value) {
4925 if (value->Is<RootConstant>()) return true;
4926 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kSmi)) {
4927 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(value, UseRepresentation::kTagged);
4928 return true;
4929 }
4930
4931 // No need for a write barrier if both object and value are part of the same
4932 // folded young allocation.
4933 AllocationBlock* allocation = GetAllocation(object);
4934 if (allocation != nullptr &&
4935 allocation->allocation_type() == AllocationType::kYoung &&
4936 allocation == GetAllocation(value)) {
4937 return true;
4938 }
4939
4940 // If tagged and not Smi, we cannot elide write barrier.
4941 if (value->is_tagged()) return false;
4942
4943 // If its alternative conversion node is Smi, {value} will be converted to
4944 // a Smi when tagged.
4945 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
4946 if (ValueNode* tagged_alt = node_info->alternative().tagged()) {
4947 DCHECK(tagged_alt->properties().is_conversion());
4948 return CheckType(tagged_alt, NodeType::kSmi);
4949 }
4950 return false;
4951}
4952
4953void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInitializeStore(InlinedAllocation* object,
4954 ValueNode* value, int offset) {
4955 const bool value_is_trusted = value->Is<TrustedConstant>();
4956 DCHECK(value->is_tagged());
4957 if (InlinedAllocation* inlined_value = value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
4958 // Add to the escape set.
4959 auto escape_deps = graph()->allocations_escape_map().find(object);
4960 CHECK(escape_deps != graph()->allocations_escape_map().end());
4961 escape_deps->second.push_back(inlined_value);
4962 // Add to the elided set.
4963 auto& elided_map = graph()->allocations_elide_map();
4964 auto elided_deps = elided_map.try_emplace(inlined_value, zone()).first;
4965 elided_deps->second.push_back(object);
4966 inlined_value->AddNonEscapingUses();
4967 }
4968 if (value_is_trusted) {
4969 BuildStoreTrustedPointerField(object, value, offset,
4970 value->Cast<TrustedConstant>()->tag(),
4971 StoreTaggedMode::kInitializing);
4972 } else {
4973 BuildStoreTaggedField(object, value, offset,
4974 StoreTaggedMode::kInitializing);
4975 }
4976}
4977
4978namespace {
4979bool IsEscaping(Graph* graph, InlinedAllocation* alloc) {
4980 if (alloc->IsEscaping()) return true;
4981 auto it = graph->allocations_elide_map().find(alloc);
4982 if (it == graph->allocations_elide_map().end()) return false;
4983 for (InlinedAllocation* inner_alloc : it->second) {
4984 if (IsEscaping(graph, inner_alloc)) {
4985 return true;
4986 }
4987 }
4988 return false;
4989}
4990
4991bool VerifyIsNotEscaping(VirtualObject::List vos, InlinedAllocation* alloc) {
4992 for (VirtualObject* vo : vos) {
4993 if (vo->type() != VirtualObject::kDefault) continue;
4994 if (vo->allocation() == alloc) continue;
4995 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < vo->slot_count(); i++) {
4996 ValueNode* nested_value = vo->get_by_index(i);
4997 if (!nested_value->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) continue;
4998 ValueNode* nested_alloc = nested_value->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
4999 if (nested_alloc == alloc) {
5000 if (vo->allocation()->IsEscaping()) return false;
5001 if (!VerifyIsNotEscaping(vos, vo->allocation())) return false;
5002 }
5003 }
5004 }
5005 return true;
5006}
5007} // namespace
5008
5009bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanTrackObjectChanges(ValueNode* receiver,
5010 TrackObjectMode mode) {
5011 DCHECK(!receiver->Is<VirtualObject>());
5012 if (!v8_flags.maglev_object_tracking) return false;
5013 if (!receiver->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) return false;
5014 InlinedAllocation* alloc = receiver->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
5015 if (mode == TrackObjectMode::kStore) {
5016 // If we have two objects A and B, such that A points to B (it contains B in
5017 // one of its field), we cannot change B without also changing A, even if
5018 // both can be elided. For now, we escape both objects instead.
5019 if (graph_->allocations_elide_map().find(alloc) !=
5020 graph_->allocations_elide_map().end()) {
5021 return false;
5022 }
5023 if (alloc->IsEscaping()) return false;
5024 // Ensure object is escaped if we are within a try-catch block. This is
5025 // crucial because a deoptimization point inside the catch handler could
5026 // re-materialize objects differently, depending on whether the throw
5027 // occurred before or after this store. We could potentially relax this
5028 // requirement by verifying that no throwable nodes have been emitted since
5029 // the try-block started, but for now, err on the side of caution and
5030 // always escape.
5031 if (IsInsideTryBlock()) return false;
5032 } else {
5033 DCHECK_EQ(mode, TrackObjectMode::kLoad);
5034 if (IsEscaping(graph_, alloc)) return false;
5035 }
5036 // We don't support loop phis inside VirtualObjects, so any access inside a
5037 // loop should escape the object, except for objects that were created since
5038 // the last loop header.
5039 if (IsInsideLoop()) {
5040 if (!is_loop_effect_tracking() ||
5041 !loop_effects_->allocations.contains(alloc)) {
5042 return false;
5043 }
5044 }
5045 // Iterate all live objects to be sure that the allocation is not escaping.
5046 SLOW_DCHECK(
5047 VerifyIsNotEscaping(current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects(), alloc));
5048 return true;
5049}
5050
5051VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetObjectFromAllocation(
5052 InlinedAllocation* allocation) {
5053 VirtualObject* vobject = allocation->object();
5054 // If it hasn't be snapshotted yet, it is the latest created version of this
5055 // object, we don't need to search for it.
5056 if (vobject->IsSnapshot()) {
5057 vobject = current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().FindAllocatedWith(
5058 allocation);
5059 }
5060 return vobject;
5061}
5062
5063VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetModifiableObjectFromAllocation(
5064 InlinedAllocation* allocation) {
5065 VirtualObject* vobject = allocation->object();
5066 // If it hasn't be snapshotted yet, it is the latest created version of this
5067 // object and we can still modify it, we don't need to copy it.
5068 if (vobject->IsSnapshot()) {
5069 return DeepCopyVirtualObject(
5070 current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().FindAllocatedWith(
5071 allocation));
5072 }
5073 return vobject;
5074}
5075
5076void MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildStoreTaggedFieldToAllocation(ValueNode* object,
5077 ValueNode* value,
5078 int offset) {
5079 if (offset == HeapObject::kMapOffset) return;
5080 if (!CanTrackObjectChanges(object, TrackObjectMode::kStore)) return;
5081 // This avoids loop in the object graph.
5082 if (value->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) return;
5083 InlinedAllocation* allocation = object->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
5084 VirtualObject* vobject = GetModifiableObjectFromAllocation(allocation);
5085 CHECK_EQ(vobject->type(), VirtualObject::kDefault);
5086 CHECK_NOT_NULL(vobject);
5087 vobject->set(offset, value);
5088 AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, 1);
5089 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_object_tracking) {
5090 std::cout << " * Setting value in virtual object "
5091 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), vobject) << "[" << offset
5092 << "]: " << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), value) << std::endl;
5093 }
5094}
5095
5096Node* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreTaggedField(ValueNode* object,
5097 ValueNode* value, int offset,
5098 StoreTaggedMode store_mode) {
5099 // The value may be used to initialize a VO, which can leak to IFS.
5100 // It should NOT be a conversion node, UNLESS it's an initializing value.
5101 // Initializing values are tagged before allocation, since conversion nodes
5102 // may allocate, and are not used to set a VO.
5103 DCHECK_IMPLIES(store_mode != StoreTaggedMode::kInitializing,
5104 !value->properties().is_conversion());
5105 if (store_mode != StoreTaggedMode::kInitializing) {
5106 TryBuildStoreTaggedFieldToAllocation(object, value, offset);
5107 }
5108 if (CanElideWriteBarrier(object, value)) {
5109 return AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>({object, value}, offset,
5110 store_mode);
5111 } else {
5112 return AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier>({object, value}, offset,
5113 store_mode);
5114 }
5115}
5116
5117void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
5118 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* value, int offset,
5119 StoreTaggedMode store_mode) {
5120 // The value may be used to initialize a VO, which can leak to IFS.
5121 // It should NOT be a conversion node, UNLESS it's an initializing value.
5122 // Initializing values are tagged before allocation, since conversion nodes
5123 // may allocate, and are not used to set a VO.
5124 DCHECK_IMPLIES(store_mode != StoreTaggedMode::kInitializing,
5125 !value->properties().is_conversion());
5126 DCHECK(CanElideWriteBarrier(object, value));
5127 if (store_mode != StoreTaggedMode::kInitializing) {
5128 TryBuildStoreTaggedFieldToAllocation(object, value, offset);
5129 }
5130 AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>({object, value}, offset,
5131 store_mode);
5132}
5133
5134void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreTrustedPointerField(
5135 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* value, int offset, IndirectPointerTag tag,
5136 StoreTaggedMode store_mode) {
5137#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5138 AddNewNode<StoreTrustedPointerFieldWithWriteBarrier>({object, value}, offset,
5139 tag, store_mode);
5140#else
5141 BuildStoreTaggedField(object, value, offset, store_mode);
5142#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5143}
5144
5145ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(ValueNode* elements,
5146 int index) {
5147 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant;
5148 if ((maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(elements)) &&
5149 maybe_constant.value().IsFixedArray()) {
5150 compiler::FixedArrayRef fixed_array_ref =
5151 maybe_constant.value().AsFixedArray();
5152 if (index >= 0 && static_cast<uint32_t>(index) < fixed_array_ref.length()) {
5153 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_value =
5154 fixed_array_ref.TryGet(broker(), index);
5155 if (maybe_value) return GetConstant(*maybe_value);
5156 } else {
5157 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5158 }
5159 }
5160 if (CanTrackObjectChanges(elements, TrackObjectMode::kLoad)) {
5161 VirtualObject* vobject =
5162 GetObjectFromAllocation(elements->Cast<InlinedAllocation>());
5163 CHECK_EQ(vobject->type(), VirtualObject::kDefault);
5164 DCHECK(vobject->map().IsFixedArrayMap());
5165 ValueNode* length_node = vobject->get(offsetof(FixedArray, length_));
5166 if (auto length = TryGetInt32Constant(length_node)) {
5167 if (index >= 0 && index < length.value()) {
5168 return vobject->get(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index));
5169 } else {
5170 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5171 }
5172 }
5173 }
5174 if (index < 0 || index >= FixedArray::kMaxLength) {
5175 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5176 }
5177 return AddNewNode<LoadTaggedField>({elements},
5178 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index));
5179}
5180
5181ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(ValueNode* elements,
5182 ValueNode* index) {
5183 if (auto constant = TryGetInt32Constant(index)) {
5184 return BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(elements, constant.value());
5185 }
5186 return AddNewNode<LoadFixedArrayElement>({elements, index});
5187}
5188
5189void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreFixedArrayElement(ValueNode* elements,
5190 ValueNode* index,
5191 ValueNode* value) {
5192 // TODO(victorgomes): Support storing element to a virtual object. If we
5193 // modify the elements array, we need to modify the original object to point
5194 // to the new elements array.
5195 if (CanElideWriteBarrier(elements, value)) {
5196 AddNewNode<StoreFixedArrayElementNoWriteBarrier>({elements, index, value});
5197 } else {
5198 AddNewNode<StoreFixedArrayElementWithWriteBarrier>(
5199 {elements, index, value});
5200 }
5201}
5202
5203ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(
5204 ValueNode* elements, int index) {
5205 if (CanTrackObjectChanges(elements, TrackObjectMode::kLoad)) {
5206 VirtualObject* vobject =
5207 GetObjectFromAllocation(elements->Cast<InlinedAllocation>());
5208 compiler::FixedDoubleArrayRef elements_array = vobject->double_elements();
5209 if (index >= 0 && static_cast<uint32_t>(index) < elements_array.length()) {
5210 Float64 value = elements_array.GetFromImmutableFixedDoubleArray(index);
5211 return GetFloat64Constant(value.get_scalar());
5212 } else {
5213 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5214 }
5215 }
5216 if (index < 0 || index >= FixedArray::kMaxLength) {
5217 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5218 }
5219 return AddNewNode<LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement>(
5220 {elements, GetInt32Constant(index)});
5221}
5222
5223ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(
5224 ValueNode* elements, ValueNode* index) {
5225 if (auto constant = TryGetInt32Constant(index)) {
5226 return BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(elements, constant.value());
5227 }
5228 return AddNewNode<LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement>({elements, index});
5229}

5231void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreFixedDoubleArrayElement(ValueNode* elements,
5232 ValueNode* index,
5233 ValueNode* value) {
5234 // TODO(victorgomes): Support storing double element to a virtual object.
5235 AddNewNode<StoreFixedDoubleArrayElement>({elements, index, value});
5236}

5238ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadHoleyFixedDoubleArrayElement(
5239 ValueNode* elements, ValueNode* index, bool convert_hole) {
5240 if (convert_hole) {
5241 return AddNewNode<LoadHoleyFixedDoubleArrayElement>({elements, index});
5242 } else {
5243 return AddNewNode<LoadHoleyFixedDoubleArrayElementCheckedNotHole>(
5244 {elements, index});

5247
5248bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(
5249 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> const& receiver_maps) {
5250 // Check if all {receiver_maps} have one of the initial Array.prototype
5251 // or Object.prototype objects as their prototype (in any of the current
5252 // native contexts, as the global Array protector works isolate-wide).
5253 for (compiler::MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
5254 compiler::ObjectRef receiver_prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
5255 if (!receiver_prototype.IsJSObject() ||
5256 !broker()->IsArrayOrObjectPrototype(receiver_prototype.AsJSObject())) {
5257 return false;
5258 }
5259 }
5260
5261 // Check if the array prototype chain is intact.
5262 return broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector();
5263}
5264
5265compiler::OptionalObjectRef
5266MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldLoadDictPrototypeConstant(
5267 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
5268 DCHECK(V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
5269 DCHECK(access_info.IsDictionaryProtoDataConstant());
5270 DCHECK(access_info.holder().has_value());
5271
5272 compiler::OptionalObjectRef constant =
5273 access_info.holder()->GetOwnDictionaryProperty(
5274 broker(), access_info.dictionary_index(), broker()->dependencies());
5275 if (!constant.has_value()) return {};
5276
5277 for (compiler::MapRef map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
5278 DirectHandle<Map> map_handle = map.object();
5279 // Non-JSReceivers that passed AccessInfoFactory::ComputePropertyAccessInfo
5280 // must have different lookup start map.
5281 if (!IsJSReceiverMap(*map_handle)) {
5282 // Perform the implicit ToObject for primitives here.
5283 // Implemented according to ES6 section 7.3.2 GetV (V, P).
5284 Tagged<JSFunction> constructor =
5285 Map::GetConstructorFunction(
5286 *map_handle, *broker()->target_native_context().object())
5287 .value();
5288 // {constructor.initial_map()} is loaded/stored with acquire-release
5289 // semantics for constructors.
5290 map = MakeRefAssumeMemoryFence(broker(), constructor->initial_map());
5291 DCHECK(IsJSObjectMap(*map.object()));
5292 }
5293 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnConstantInDictionaryPrototypeChain(
5294 map, access_info.name(), constant.value(), PropertyKind::kData);
5295 }
5296
5297 return constant;
5298}
5299
5300compiler::OptionalJSObjectRef MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetConstantDataFieldHolder(
5301 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info,
5302 ValueNode* lookup_start_object) {
5303 if (!access_info.IsFastDataConstant()) return {};
5304 if (access_info.holder().has_value()) {
5305 return access_info.holder();
5306 }
5307 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef c = TryGetConstant(lookup_start_object)) {
5308 if (c.value().IsJSObject()) {
5309 return c.value().AsJSObject();
5310 }
5311 }
5312 return {};
5313}
5314
5315compiler::OptionalObjectRef MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldLoadConstantDataField(
5316 compiler::JSObjectRef holder,
5317 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
5318 DCHECK(!access_info.field_representation().IsDouble());
5319 return holder.GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
5320 broker(), access_info.field_representation(), access_info.field_index(),
5321 broker()->dependencies());
5322}
5323
5324std::optional<Float64> MaglevGraphBuilder::TryFoldLoadConstantDoubleField(
5325 compiler::JSObjectRef holder,
5326 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
5327 DCHECK(access_info.field_representation().IsDouble());
5328 return holder.GetOwnFastConstantDoubleProperty(
5329 broker(), access_info.field_index(), broker()->dependencies());
5330}
5331
5332MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertyGetterCall(
5333 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info, ValueNode* receiver,
5334 ValueNode* lookup_start_object) {
5335 compiler::ObjectRef constant = access_info.constant().value();
5336
5337 if (access_info.IsDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant()) {
5338 // For fast mode holders we recorded dependencies in BuildPropertyLoad.
5339 for (const compiler::MapRef map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
5340 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnConstantInDictionaryPrototypeChain(
5341 map, access_info.name(), constant, PropertyKind::kAccessor);
5342 }
5343 }
5344
5345 // Introduce the call to the getter function.
5346 if (constant.IsJSFunction()) {
5347 ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode =
5348 receiver == lookup_start_object
5349 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined
5350 : ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
5351 CallArguments args(receiver_mode, {receiver});
5352 return TryReduceCallForConstant(constant.AsJSFunction(), args);
5353 } else {
5354 // Disable optimizations for super ICs using API getters, so that we get
5355 // the correct receiver checks.
5356 if (receiver != lookup_start_object) return {};
5357 compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef templ = constant.AsFunctionTemplateInfo();
5358 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, {receiver});
5359
5360 return TryReduceCallForApiFunction(templ, {}, access_info.api_holder(),
5361 args);
5362 }
5363}
5364
5365MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertySetterCall(
5366 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info, ValueNode* receiver,
5367 ValueNode* lookup_start_object, ValueNode* value) {
5368 // Setting super properties shouldn't end up here.
5369 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
5370 compiler::ObjectRef constant = access_info.constant().value();
5371 if (constant.IsJSFunction()) {
5372 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined,
5373 {receiver, value});
5374 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryReduceCallForConstant(constant.AsJSFunction(), args));
5375 } else {
5376 compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef templ = constant.AsFunctionTemplateInfo();
5377 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined,
5378 {receiver, value});
5379 RETURN_IF_ABORT(
5380 TryReduceCallForApiFunction(templ, {}, access_info.api_holder(), args));
5381 }
5382 // Ignore the return value of the setter call.
5383 return ReduceResult::Done();
5384}
5385
5386ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadField(
5387 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info,
5388 ValueNode* lookup_start_object, compiler::NameRef name) {
5389 compiler::OptionalJSObjectRef constant_holder =
5390 TryGetConstantDataFieldHolder(access_info, lookup_start_object);
5391 if (constant_holder) {
5392 if (access_info.field_representation().IsDouble()) {
5393 std::optional<Float64> constant =
5394 TryFoldLoadConstantDoubleField(constant_holder.value(), access_info);
5395 if (constant.has_value()) {
5396 return GetFloat64Constant(constant.value());
5397 }
5398 } else {
5399 compiler::OptionalObjectRef constant =
5400 TryFoldLoadConstantDataField(constant_holder.value(), access_info);
5401 if (constant.has_value()) {
5402 return GetConstant(constant.value());
5403 }
5404 }
5405 }
5406 // Resolve property holder.
5407 ValueNode* load_source;
5408 if (access_info.holder().has_value()) {
5409 load_source = GetConstant(access_info.holder().value());
5410 } else {
5411 load_source = lookup_start_object;
5412 }
5413
5414 FieldIndex field_index = access_info.field_index();
5415 if (!field_index.is_inobject()) {
5416 // The field is in the property array, first load it from there.
5417 load_source =
5418 BuildLoadTaggedField(load_source, JSReceiver::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
5419 }
5420
5421 // Do the load.
5422 if (field_index.is_double()) {
5423 return AddNewNode<LoadDoubleField>({load_source}, field_index.offset());
5424 }
5425 ValueNode* value = BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForProperty>(
5426 load_source, field_index.offset(), name);
5427 // Insert stable field information if present.
5428 if (access_info.field_representation().IsSmi()) {
5429 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
5430 known_info->CombineType(NodeType::kSmi);
5431 } else if (access_info.field_representation().IsHeapObject()) {
5432 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(value);
5433 if (access_info.field_map().has_value() &&
5434 access_info.field_map().value().is_stable()) {
5435 DCHECK(access_info.field_map().value().IsJSReceiverMap());
5436 auto map = access_info.field_map().value();
5437 known_info->SetPossibleMaps(PossibleMaps{map}, false,
5438 StaticTypeForMap(map, broker()), broker());
5439 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(map);
5440 } else {
5441 known_info->CombineType(NodeType::kAnyHeapObject);
5442 }
5443 }
5444 return value;
5445}
5446
5447ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(
5448 ValueNode* fixed_array) {
5449 ValueNode* length =
5450 BuildLoadTaggedField(fixed_array, offsetof(FixedArray, length_));
5451 EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
5452 return length;
5453}
5454
5455ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadJSArrayLength(ValueNode* js_array,
5456 NodeType length_type) {
5457 // TODO(leszeks): JSArray.length is known to be non-constant, don't bother
5458 // searching the constant values.
5459 MaybeReduceResult known_length =
5460 TryReuseKnownPropertyLoad(js_array, broker()->length_string());
5461 if (known_length.IsDone()) {
5462 DCHECK(known_length.IsDoneWithValue());
5463 return known_length.value();
5464 }
5465
5466 ValueNode* length = BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForProperty>(
5467 js_array, JSArray::kLengthOffset, broker()->length_string());
5468 GetOrCreateInfoFor(length)->CombineType(length_type);
5469 RecordKnownProperty(js_array, broker()->length_string(), length, false,
5470 compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
5471 return length;
5472}
5473
5474void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreMap(ValueNode* object, compiler::MapRef map,
5475 StoreMap::Kind kind) {
5476 AddNewNode<StoreMap>({object}, map, kind);
5477 NodeType object_type = StaticTypeForMap(map, broker());
5478 NodeInfo* node_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(object);
5479 if (map.is_stable()) {
5480 node_info->SetPossibleMaps(PossibleMaps{map}, false, object_type, broker());
5481 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(map);
5482 } else {
5483 node_info->SetPossibleMaps(PossibleMaps{map}, true, object_type, broker());
5484 known_node_aspects().any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable = true;
5485 }
5486}
5487
5488ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
5489 compiler::MapRef map, ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* property_array) {
5490 int length = map.NextFreePropertyIndex() - map.GetInObjectProperties();
5491 // Under normal circumstances, NextFreePropertyIndex() will always be larger
5492 // than GetInObjectProperties(). However, an attacker able to corrupt heap
5493 // memory can break this invariant, in which case we'll get confused here,
5494 // potentially causing a sandbox violation. This CHECK defends against that.
5495 SBXCHECK_GE(length, 0);
5496 return AddNewNode<ExtendPropertiesBackingStore>({property_array, receiver},
5497 length);
5498}
5499
5500MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildStoreField(
5501 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info, ValueNode* receiver,
5502 compiler::AccessMode access_mode) {
5503 FieldIndex field_index = access_info.field_index();
5504 Representation field_representation = access_info.field_representation();
5505
5506 compiler::OptionalMapRef original_map;
5507 if (access_info.HasTransitionMap()) {
5508 compiler::MapRef transition = access_info.transition_map().value();
5509 original_map = transition.GetBackPointer(broker()).AsMap();
5510
5511 if (original_map->UnusedPropertyFields() == 0) {
5512 DCHECK(!field_index.is_inobject());
5513 }
5514 if (!field_index.is_inobject()) {
5515 // If slack tracking ends after this compilation started but before it's
5516 // finished, then {original_map} could be out-of-sync with {transition}.
5517 // In particular, its UnusedPropertyFields could be non-zero, which would
5518 // lead us to not extend the property backing store, while the underlying
5519 // Map has actually zero UnusedPropertyFields. Thus, we install a
5520 // dependency on {orininal_map} now, so that if such a situation happens,
5521 // we'll throw away the code.
5522 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoSlackTrackingChange(*original_map);
5523 }
5524 } else if (access_info.IsFastDataConstant() &&
5525 access_mode == compiler::AccessMode::kStore) {
5526 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kStoreToConstant);
5527 }
5528
5529 ValueNode* store_target;
5530 if (field_index.is_inobject()) {
5531 store_target = receiver;
5532 } else {
5533 // The field is in the property array, first load it from there.
5534 store_target =
5535 BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, JSReceiver::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
5536 if (original_map && original_map->UnusedPropertyFields() == 0) {
5537 store_target = BuildExtendPropertiesBackingStore(*original_map, receiver,
5538 store_target);
5539 }
5540 }
5541
5542 if (field_representation.IsDouble()) {
5543 ValueNode* float64_value = GetAccumulator();
5544 if (access_info.HasTransitionMap()) {
5545 // Allocate the mutable double box owned by the field.
5546 ValueNode* value =
5547 AddNewNode<Float64ToHeapNumberForField>({float64_value});
5548 BuildStoreTaggedField(store_target, value, field_index.offset(),
5549 StoreTaggedMode::kTransitioning);
5550 BuildStoreMap(receiver, access_info.transition_map().value(),
5551 StoreMap::Kind::kTransitioning);
5552 } else {
5553 AddNewNode<StoreDoubleField>({store_target, float64_value},
5554 field_index.offset());
5555 }
5556 return ReduceResult::Done();
5557 }
5558
5559 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
5560 if (field_representation.IsSmi()) {
5561 RETURN_IF_ABORT(GetAccumulatorSmi());
5562 } else {
5563 if (field_representation.IsHeapObject()) {
5564 // Emit a map check for the field type, if needed, otherwise just a
5565 // HeapObject check.
5566 if (access_info.field_map().has_value()) {
5567 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(
5568 value, base::VectorOf({access_info.field_map().value()})));
5569 } else {
5570 BuildCheckHeapObject(value);
5571 }
5572 }
5573 }
5574
5575 StoreTaggedMode store_mode = access_info.HasTransitionMap()
5576 ? StoreTaggedMode::kTransitioning
5577 : StoreTaggedMode::kDefault;
5578 if (field_representation.IsSmi()) {
5579 BuildStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(store_target, value,
5580 field_index.offset(), store_mode);
5581 } else {
5582 DCHECK(field_representation.IsHeapObject() ||
5583 field_representation.IsTagged());
5584 BuildStoreTaggedField(store_target, value, field_index.offset(),
5585 store_mode);
5586 }
5587 if (access_info.HasTransitionMap()) {
5588 BuildStoreMap(receiver, access_info.transition_map().value(),
5589 StoreMap::Kind::kTransitioning);
5590 }
5591
5592 return ReduceResult::Done();
5593}
5594
5595namespace {
5596bool AccessInfoGuaranteedConst(
5597 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
5598 if (!access_info.IsFastDataConstant() && !access_info.IsStringLength()) {
5599 return false;
5600 }
5601
5602 // Even if we have a constant load, if the map is not stable, we cannot
5603 // guarantee that the load is preserved across side-effecting calls.
5604 // TODO(v8:7700): It might be possible to track it as const if we know
5605 // that we're still on the main transition tree; and if we add a
5606 // dependency on the stable end-maps of the entire tree.
5607 for (auto& map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
5608 if (!map.is_stable()) {
5609 return false;
5610 }
5611 }
5612 return true;
5613}
5614} // namespace
5615
5616MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertyLoad(
5617 ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* lookup_start_object, compiler::NameRef name,
5618 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
5619 if (access_info.holder().has_value() && !access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
5620 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
5621 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
5622 access_info.holder().value());
5623 }
5624
5625 switch (access_info.kind()) {
5626 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kInvalid:
5627 UNREACHABLE();
5628 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kNotFound:
5629 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5630 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kDataField:
5631 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kFastDataConstant: {
5632 ValueNode* result =
5633 BuildLoadField(access_info, lookup_start_object, name);
5634 RecordKnownProperty(lookup_start_object, name, result,
5635 AccessInfoGuaranteedConst(access_info),
5636 compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
5637 return result;
5638 }
5639 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kDictionaryProtoDataConstant: {
5640 compiler::OptionalObjectRef constant =
5641 TryFoldLoadDictPrototypeConstant(access_info);
5642 if (!constant.has_value()) return {};
5643 return GetConstant(constant.value());
5644 }
5645 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kFastAccessorConstant:
5646 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant:
5647 return TryBuildPropertyGetterCall(access_info, receiver,
5648 lookup_start_object);
5649 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kModuleExport: {
5650 ValueNode* cell = GetConstant(access_info.constant().value().AsCell());
5651 return BuildLoadTaggedField<LoadTaggedFieldForProperty>(
5652 cell, Cell::kValueOffset, name);
5653 }
5654 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kStringLength: {
5655 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
5656 ValueNode* result = BuildLoadStringLength(receiver);
5657 RecordKnownProperty(lookup_start_object, name, result,
5658 AccessInfoGuaranteedConst(access_info),
5659 compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
5660 return result;
5661 }
5662 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kStringWrapperLength: {
5663 // TODO(dmercadier): update KnownNodeInfo.
5664 ValueNode* string = BuildLoadTaggedField(
5665 lookup_start_object, JSPrimitiveWrapper::kValueOffset);
5666 return AddNewNode<StringLength>({string});
5667 }
5668 }
5669}
5670
5671MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertyStore(
5672 ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* lookup_start_object, compiler::NameRef name,
5673 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info,
5674 compiler::AccessMode access_mode) {
5675 if (access_info.holder().has_value()) {
5676 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
5677 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
5678 access_info.holder().value());
5679 }
5680
5681 switch (access_info.kind()) {
5682 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kFastAccessorConstant: {
5683 return TryBuildPropertySetterCall(access_info, receiver,
5684 lookup_start_object, GetAccumulator());
5685 }
5686 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kDataField:
5687 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kFastDataConstant: {
5688 MaybeReduceResult res =
5689 TryBuildStoreField(access_info, receiver, access_mode);
5690 if (res.IsDone()) {
5691 RecordKnownProperty(
5692 receiver, name, current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator(),
5693 AccessInfoGuaranteedConst(access_info), access_mode);
5694 return res;
5695 }
5696 return {};
5697 }
5698 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kInvalid:
5699 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kNotFound:
5700 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kDictionaryProtoDataConstant:
5701 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant:
5702 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kModuleExport:
5703 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kStringLength:
5704 case compiler::PropertyAccessInfo::kStringWrapperLength:
5705 UNREACHABLE();
5706 }
5707}
5708
5709MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPropertyAccess(
5710 ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* lookup_start_object, compiler::NameRef name,
5711 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info,
5712 compiler::AccessMode access_mode) {
5713 switch (access_mode) {
5714 case compiler::AccessMode::kLoad:
5715 return TryBuildPropertyLoad(receiver, lookup_start_object, name,
5716 access_info);
5717 case compiler::AccessMode::kStore:
5718 case compiler::AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
5719 case compiler::AccessMode::kDefine:
5720 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
5721 return TryBuildPropertyStore(receiver, lookup_start_object, name,
5722 access_info, access_mode);
5723 case compiler::AccessMode::kHas:
5724 // TODO(victorgomes): BuildPropertyTest.
5725 return {};
5726 }
5727}
5728
5729template <typename GenericAccessFunc>
5730MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildNamedAccess(
5731 ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* lookup_start_object,
5732 compiler::NamedAccessFeedback const& feedback,
5733 compiler::FeedbackSource const& feedback_source,
5734 compiler::AccessMode access_mode,
5735 GenericAccessFunc&& build_generic_access) {
5736 compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map> inferred_maps;
5737
5738 bool has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target = false;
5739 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef c = TryGetConstant(lookup_start_object)) {
5740 compiler::MapRef constant_map = c.value().map(broker());
5741 if (c.value().IsJSFunction() &&
5742 feedback.name().equals(broker()->prototype_string())) {
5743 compiler::JSFunctionRef function = c.value().AsJSFunction();
5744 if (!constant_map.has_prototype_slot() ||
5745 !function.has_instance_prototype(broker()) ||
5746 function.PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(broker()) ||
5747 access_mode != compiler::AccessMode::kLoad) {
5748 return {};
5749 }
5750 compiler::HeapObjectRef prototype =
5751 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnPrototypeProperty(function);
5752 return GetConstant(prototype);
5753 }
5754 inferred_maps = compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map>(constant_map);
5755 } else if (feedback.maps().empty()) {
5756 // The IC is megamorphic.
5757
5758 // We can't do megamorphic loads for lookups where the lookup start isn't
5759 // the receiver (e.g. load from super).
5760 if (receiver != lookup_start_object) return {};
5761
5762 // Use known possible maps if we have any.
5763 NodeInfo* object_info =
5764 known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(lookup_start_object);
5765 if (object_info && object_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
5766 inferred_maps = object_info->possible_maps();
5767 } else {
5768 // If we have no known maps, make the access megamorphic.
5769 switch (access_mode) {
5770 case compiler::AccessMode::kLoad:
5771 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kLoadIC_Megamorphic>(
5772 {GetTaggedValue(receiver), GetConstant(feedback.name())},
5773 feedback_source);
5774 case compiler::AccessMode::kStore:
5775 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStoreIC_Megamorphic>(
5776 {GetTaggedValue(receiver), GetConstant(feedback.name()),
5777 GetTaggedValue(GetAccumulator())},
5778 feedback_source);
5779 case compiler::AccessMode::kDefine:
5780 return {};
5781 case compiler::AccessMode::kHas:
5782 case compiler::AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
5783 UNREACHABLE();
5784 }
5785 }
5786 } else {
5787 // TODO(leszeks): This is doing duplicate work with BuildCheckMaps,
5788 // consider passing the merger into there.
5789 KnownMapsMerger merger(broker(), zone(), base::VectorOf(feedback.maps()));
5790 merger.IntersectWithKnownNodeAspects(lookup_start_object,
5791 known_node_aspects());
5792 inferred_maps = merger.intersect_set();
5793 has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target =
5794 feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target();
5795 }
5796
5797 if (inferred_maps.is_empty()) {
5798 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap);
5799 }
5800
5801 ZoneVector<compiler::PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(zone());
5802 ZoneVector<compiler::PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos_for_feedback(zone());
5803
5804 for (compiler::MapRef map : inferred_maps) {
5805 if (map.is_deprecated()) continue;
5806
5807 // TODO(v8:12547): Support writing to objects in shared space, which
5808 // need a write barrier that calls Object::Share to ensure the RHS is
5809 // shared.
5810 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(map.instance_type()) &&
5811 access_mode == compiler::AccessMode::kStore) {
5812 return {};
5813 }
5814
5815 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
5816 broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(map, feedback.name(), access_mode);
5817 access_infos_for_feedback.push_back(access_info);
5818 }
5819
5820 compiler::AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), zone());
5821 if (!access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfos(
5822 access_infos_for_feedback, access_mode, &access_infos)) {
5823 return {};
5824 }
5825
5826 // Check for monomorphic case.
5827 if (access_infos.size() == 1) {
5828 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos.front();
5829 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> maps =
5830 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
5831 if (HasOnlyStringMaps(maps)) {
5832 // Check for string maps before checking if we need to do an access
5833 // check. Primitive strings always get the prototype from the native
5834 // context they're operated on, so they don't need the access check.
5835 BuildCheckString(lookup_start_object);
5836 } else if (HasOnlyNumberMaps(maps)) {
5837 BuildCheckNumber(lookup_start_object);
5838 } else {
5839 RETURN_IF_ABORT(
5840 BuildCheckMaps(lookup_start_object, maps, {},
5841 has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target));
5842 }
5843
5844 // Generate the actual property
5845 return TryBuildPropertyAccess(receiver, lookup_start_object,
5846 feedback.name(), access_info, access_mode);
5847 } else {
5848 // TODO(victorgomes): Unify control flow logic with
5849 // TryBuildPolymorphicElementAccess.
5850 return TryBuildPolymorphicPropertyAccess(
5851 receiver, lookup_start_object, feedback, access_mode, access_infos,
5852 build_generic_access);
5853 }
5854}
5855
5856ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetInt32ElementIndex(ValueNode* object) {
5857 RecordUseReprHintIfPhi(object, UseRepresentation::kInt32);
5858
5859 switch (object->properties().value_representation()) {
5860 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
5861 UNREACHABLE();
5862 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
5863 NodeType old_type;
5864 if (SmiConstant* constant = object->TryCast<SmiConstant>()) {
5865 return GetInt32Constant(constant->value().value());
5866 } else if (CheckType(object, NodeType::kSmi, &old_type)) {
5867 auto& alternative = GetOrCreateInfoFor(object)->alternative();
5868 return alternative.get_or_set_int32(
5869 [&]() { return BuildSmiUntag(object); });
5870 } else {
5871 // TODO(leszeks): Cache this knowledge/converted value somehow on
5872 // the node info.
5873 return AddNewNode<CheckedObjectToIndex>({object},
5874 GetCheckType(old_type));
5875 }
5876 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
5877 // Already good.
5878 return object;
5879 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
5880 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
5881 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
5882 return GetInt32(object);
5883 }
5884}
5885
5886// TODO(victorgomes): Consider caching the values and adding an
5887// uint32_alternative in node_info.
5888ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::GetUint32ElementIndex(ValueNode* object) {
5889 // Don't record a Uint32 Phi use here, since the tagged path goes via
5890 // GetInt32ElementIndex, making this an Int32 Phi use.
5891
5892 switch (object->properties().value_representation()) {
5893 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
5894 UNREACHABLE();
5895 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
5896 // TODO(victorgomes): Consider creating a CheckedObjectToUnsignedIndex.
5897 if (SmiConstant* constant = object->TryCast<SmiConstant>()) {
5898 int32_t value = constant->value().value();
5899 if (value < 0) {
5900 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kNotUint32);
5901 }
5902 return GetUint32Constant(value);
5903 }
5904 return AddNewNode<CheckedInt32ToUint32>({GetInt32ElementIndex(object)});
5905 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
5906 if (Int32Constant* constant = object->TryCast<Int32Constant>()) {
5907 int32_t value = constant->value();
5908 if (value < 0) {
5909 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kNotUint32);
5910 }
5911 return GetUint32Constant(value);
5912 }
5913 return AddNewNode<CheckedInt32ToUint32>({object});
5914 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
5915 return object;
5916 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
5917 if (Float64Constant* constant = object->TryCast<Float64Constant>()) {
5918 double value = constant->value().get_scalar();
5919 uint32_t uint32_value;
5920 if (!DoubleToUint32IfEqualToSelf(value, &uint32_value)) {
5921 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kNotUint32);
5922 }
5923 if (Smi::IsValid(uint32_value)) {
5924 return GetUint32Constant(uint32_value);
5925 }
5926 }
5927 [[fallthrough]];
5928 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
5929 // CheckedTruncateFloat64ToUint32 will gracefully deopt on holes.
5930 return AddNewNode<CheckedTruncateFloat64ToUint32>({object});
5931 }
5932 }
5933}
5934
5935MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildElementAccessOnString(
5936 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object,
5937 compiler::KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode) {
5938 // Strings are immutable and `in` cannot be used on strings
5939 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() != compiler::AccessMode::kLoad) {
5940 return {};
5941 }
5942
5943 // Ensure that {object} is actually a String.
5944 BuildCheckString(object);
5945
5946 ValueNode* length = BuildLoadStringLength(object);
5947 ValueNode* index = GetInt32ElementIndex(index_object);
5948 auto emit_load = [&] { return AddNewNode<StringAt>({object, index}); };
5949
5950 if (LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode()) &&
5951 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
5952 ValueNode* positive_index;
5953 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(positive_index, GetUint32ElementIndex(index));
5954 ValueNode* uint32_length = AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({length});
5955 return Select(
5956 [&](auto& builder) {
5957 return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(builder, Operation::kLessThan,
5958 positive_index, uint32_length);
5959 },
5960 emit_load, [&] { return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue); });
5961 } else {
5962 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
5963 index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
5964 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
5965 return emit_load();
5966 }
5967}
5968
5969namespace {
5970MaybeReduceResult TryFindLoadedProperty(
5971 const KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMap& loaded_properties,
5972 ValueNode* lookup_start_object,
5973 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey name) {
5974 auto props_for_name = loaded_properties.find(name);
5975 if (props_for_name == loaded_properties.end()) return {};
5976
5977 auto it = props_for_name->second.find(lookup_start_object);
5978 if (it == props_for_name->second.end()) return {};
5979
5980 return it->second;
5981}
5982
5983bool CheckConditionIn32(int32_t lhs, int32_t rhs, AssertCondition condition) {
5984 switch (condition) {
5985 case AssertCondition::kEqual:
5986 return lhs == rhs;
5987 case AssertCondition::kNotEqual:
5988 return lhs != rhs;
5989 case AssertCondition::kLessThan:
5990 return lhs < rhs;
5991 case AssertCondition::kLessThanEqual:
5992 return lhs <= rhs;
5993 case AssertCondition::kGreaterThan:
5994 return lhs > rhs;
5995 case AssertCondition::kGreaterThanEqual:
5996 return lhs >= rhs;
5997 case AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan:
5998 return static_cast<uint32_t>(lhs) < static_cast<uint32_t>(rhs);
5999 case AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
6000 return static_cast<uint32_t>(lhs) <= static_cast<uint32_t>(rhs);
6001 case AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThan:
6002 return static_cast<uint32_t>(lhs) > static_cast<uint32_t>(rhs);
6003 case AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
6004 return static_cast<uint32_t>(lhs) >= static_cast<uint32_t>(rhs);
6005 }
6006}
6007
6008bool CompareInt32(int32_t lhs, int32_t rhs, Operation operation) {
6009 switch (operation) {
6010 case Operation::kEqual:
6011 case Operation::kStrictEqual:
6012 return lhs == rhs;
6013 case Operation::kLessThan:
6014 return lhs < rhs;
6015 case Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
6016 return lhs <= rhs;
6017 case Operation::kGreaterThan:
6018 return lhs > rhs;
6019 case Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
6020 return lhs >= rhs;
6021 default:
6022 UNREACHABLE();
6023 }
6024}
6025
6026bool CompareUint32(uint32_t lhs, uint32_t rhs, Operation operation) {
6027 switch (operation) {
6028 case Operation::kEqual:
6029 case Operation::kStrictEqual:
6030 return lhs == rhs;
6031 case Operation::kLessThan:
6032 return lhs < rhs;
6033 case Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
6034 return lhs <= rhs;
6035 case Operation::kGreaterThan:
6036 return lhs > rhs;
6037 case Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
6038 return lhs >= rhs;
6039 default:
6040 UNREACHABLE();
6041 }
6042}
6043
6044} // namespace
6045
6046MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
6047 ValueNode* lhs, ValueNode* rhs, AssertCondition condition,
6048 DeoptimizeReason reason) {
6049 auto lhs_const = TryGetInt32Constant(lhs);
6050 if (lhs_const) {
6051 auto rhs_const = TryGetInt32Constant(rhs);
6052 if (rhs_const) {
6053 if (CheckConditionIn32(lhs_const.value(), rhs_const.value(), condition)) {
6054 return ReduceResult::Done();
6055 }
6056 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(reason);
6057 }
6058 }
6059 AddNewNode<CheckInt32Condition>({lhs, rhs}, condition, reason);
6060 return ReduceResult::Done();
6061}
6062
6063ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadElements(ValueNode* object) {
6064 MaybeReduceResult known_elements =
6065 TryFindLoadedProperty(known_node_aspects().loaded_properties, object,
6066 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::Elements());
6067 if (known_elements.IsDone()) {
6068 DCHECK(known_elements.IsDoneWithValue());
6069 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
6070 std::cout << " * Reusing non-constant [Elements] "
6071 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), known_elements.value())
6072 << ": " << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), known_elements.value())
6073 << std::endl;
6074 }
6075 return known_elements.value();
6076 }
6077
6078 DCHECK_EQ(JSObject::kElementsOffset, JSArray::kElementsOffset);
6079 ValueNode* elements = BuildLoadTaggedField(object, JSObject::kElementsOffset);
6080 RecordKnownProperty(object,
6081 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::Elements(),
6082 elements, false, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
6083 return elements;
6084}
6085
6086ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadTypedArrayLength(
6087 ValueNode* object, ElementsKind elements_kind) {
6088 DCHECK(IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind));
6089 bool is_variable_length = IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind);
6090
6091 if (!is_variable_length) {
6092 // Note: We can't use broker()->length_string() here, because it could
6093 // conflict with redefinitions of the TypedArray length property.
6094 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryFindLoadedProperty(
6095 known_node_aspects().loaded_constant_properties, object,
6096 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::TypedArrayLength()));
6097 }
6098
6099 ValueNode* result = AddNewNode<LoadTypedArrayLength>({object}, elements_kind);
6100 if (!is_variable_length) {
6101 RecordKnownProperty(
6102 object, KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::TypedArrayLength(),
6103 result, true, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
6104 }
6105 return result;
6106}
6107
6108ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadTypedArrayElement(
6109 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index, ElementsKind elements_kind) {
6110#define BUILD_AND_RETURN_LOAD_TYPED_ARRAY(Type) \
6111 return AddNewNode<Load##Type##TypedArrayElement>({object, index}, \
6112 elements_kind);
6113
6114 switch (elements_kind) {
6115 case INT8_ELEMENTS:
6116 case INT16_ELEMENTS:
6117 case INT32_ELEMENTS:
6118 BUILD_AND_RETURN_LOAD_TYPED_ARRAY(SignedInt);
6119 case UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS:
6120 case UINT8_ELEMENTS:
6121 case UINT16_ELEMENTS:
6122 case UINT32_ELEMENTS:
6123 BUILD_AND_RETURN_LOAD_TYPED_ARRAY(UnsignedInt);
6124 case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
6125 case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
6126 BUILD_AND_RETURN_LOAD_TYPED_ARRAY(Double);
6127 default:
6128 UNREACHABLE();
6129 }
6130#undef BUILD_AND_RETURN_LOAD_TYPED_ARRAY
6131}
6132
6133void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildStoreTypedArrayElement(
6134 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index, ElementsKind elements_kind) {
6135#define BUILD_STORE_TYPED_ARRAY(Type, value) \
6136 AddNewNode<Store##Type##TypedArrayElement>({object, index, (value)}, \
6137 elements_kind);
6138
6139 // TODO(leszeks): These operations have a deopt loop when the ToNumber
6140 // conversion sees a type other than number or oddball. Turbofan has the same
6141 // deopt loop, but ideally we'd avoid it.
6142 switch (elements_kind) {
6143 case UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS: {
6144 BUILD_STORE_TYPED_ARRAY(Int, GetAccumulatorUint8ClampedForToNumber())
6145 break;
6146 }
6147 case INT8_ELEMENTS:
6148 case INT16_ELEMENTS:
6149 case INT32_ELEMENTS:
6150 case UINT8_ELEMENTS:
6151 case UINT16_ELEMENTS:
6152 case UINT32_ELEMENTS:
6153 BUILD_STORE_TYPED_ARRAY(
6154 Int, GetAccumulatorTruncatedInt32ForToNumber(
6155 NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
6156 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball))
6157 break;
6158 case FLOAT32_ELEMENTS:
6159 case FLOAT64_ELEMENTS:
6160 BUILD_STORE_TYPED_ARRAY(
6161 Double, GetAccumulatorHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
6162 NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
6163 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball))
6164 break;
6165 default:
6166 UNREACHABLE();
6167 }
6168#undef BUILD_STORE_TYPED_ARRAY
6169}
6170
6171MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildElementAccessOnTypedArray(
6172 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object,
6173 const compiler::ElementAccessInfo& access_info,
6174 compiler::KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode) {
6175 DCHECK(HasOnlyJSTypedArrayMaps(
6176 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())));
6177 ElementsKind elements_kind = access_info.elements_kind();
6178 if (elements_kind == FLOAT16_ELEMENTS ||
6179 elements_kind == BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS ||
6180 elements_kind == BIGINT64_ELEMENTS) {
6181 return {};
6182 }
6183 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kLoad &&
6184 LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode())) {
6185 // TODO(victorgomes): Handle OOB mode.
6186 return {};
6187 }
6188 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kStore &&
6189 StoreModeIgnoresTypeArrayOOB(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
6190 // TODO(victorgomes): Handle OOB mode.
6191 return {};
6192 }
6193 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kStore &&
6194 elements_kind == UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS &&
6195 !IsSupported(CpuOperation::kFloat64Round)) {
6196 // TODO(victorgomes): Technically we still support if value (in the
6197 // accumulator) is of type int32. It would be nice to have a roll back
6198 // mechanism instead, so that we do not need to check this early.
6199 return {};
6200 }
6201 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
6202 // TODO(leszeks): Eliminate this check.
6203 AddNewNode<CheckTypedArrayNotDetached>({object});
6204 }
6205 ValueNode* index;
6206 ValueNode* length;
6207 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(index, GetUint32ElementIndex(index_object));
6208 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(length, BuildLoadTypedArrayLength(object, elements_kind));
6209 AddNewNode<CheckTypedArrayBounds>({index, length});
6210 switch (keyed_mode.access_mode()) {
6211 case compiler::AccessMode::kLoad:
6212 DCHECK(!LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode()));
6213 return BuildLoadTypedArrayElement(object, index, elements_kind);
6214 case compiler::AccessMode::kStore:
6215 DCHECK(StoreModeIsInBounds(keyed_mode.store_mode()));
6216 BuildStoreTypedArrayElement(object, index, elements_kind);
6217 return ReduceResult::Done();
6218 case compiler::AccessMode::kHas:
6219 // TODO(victorgomes): Implement has element access.
6220 return {};
6221 case compiler::AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
6222 case compiler::AccessMode::kDefine:
6223 UNREACHABLE();
6224 }
6225}
6226
6227MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildElementLoadOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
6228 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object,
6229 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> maps, ElementsKind elements_kind,
6230 KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode) {
6231 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind));
6232 bool is_jsarray = HasOnlyJSArrayMaps(maps);
6233 DCHECK(is_jsarray || HasOnlyJSObjectMaps(maps));
6234
6235 ValueNode* elements_array = BuildLoadElements(object);
6236 ValueNode* index = GetInt32ElementIndex(index_object);
6237 ValueNode* length = is_jsarray ? GetInt32(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(object))
6238 : BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(elements_array);
6239
6240 auto emit_load = [&]() -> MaybeReduceResult {
6241 ValueNode* result;
6242 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
6243 result = BuildLoadHoleyFixedDoubleArrayElement(
6244 elements_array, index,
6245 CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(maps) && LoadModeHandlesHoles(load_mode));
6246 } else if (elements_kind == PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
6247 result = BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(elements_array, index);
6248 } else {
6249 DCHECK(!IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind));
6250 result = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(elements_array, index);
6251 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6252 if (CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(maps) && LoadModeHandlesHoles(load_mode)) {
6253 result = BuildConvertHoleToUndefined(result);
6254 } else {
6255 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckNotHole(result));
6256 if (IsSmiElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6257 EnsureType(result, NodeType::kSmi);
6258 }
6259 }
6260 } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6261 EnsureType(result, NodeType::kSmi);
6262 }
6263 }
6264 return result;
6265 };
6266
6267 if (CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(maps) && LoadModeHandlesOOB(load_mode)) {
6268 ValueNode* positive_index;
6269 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(positive_index, GetUint32ElementIndex(index));
6270 ValueNode* uint32_length = AddNewNode<UnsafeInt32ToUint32>({length});
6271 return SelectReduction(
6272 [&](auto& builder) {
6273 return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(builder, Operation::kLessThan,
6274 positive_index, uint32_length);
6275 },
6276 emit_load, [&] { return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue); });
6277 } else {
6278 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
6279 index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
6280 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
6281 return emit_load();
6282 }
6283}
6284
6285ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ConvertForStoring(ValueNode* value,
6286 ElementsKind kind) {
6287 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
6288 // Make sure we do not store signalling NaNs into double arrays.
6289 // TODO(leszeks): Consider making this a bit on StoreFixedDoubleArrayElement
6290 // rather than a separate node.
6291 return GetSilencedNaN(GetFloat64(value));
6292 }
6293 if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) return GetSmiValue(value);
6294 return value;
6295}
6296
6297MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildElementStoreOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
6298 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object, ValueNode* value,
6299 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> maps, ElementsKind elements_kind,
6300 const compiler::KeyedAccessMode& keyed_mode) {
6301 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind));
6302
6303 const bool is_jsarray = HasOnlyJSArrayMaps(maps);
6304 DCHECK(is_jsarray || HasOnlyJSObjectMaps(maps));
6305
6306 // Get the elements array.
6307 ValueNode* elements_array = BuildLoadElements(object);
6308 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(value, ConvertForStoring(value, elements_kind));
6309 ValueNode* index;
6310
6311 // TODO(verwaest): Loop peeling will turn the first iteration index of spread
6312 // literals into smi constants as well, breaking the assumption that we'll
6313 // have preallocated the space if we see known indices. Turn off this
6314 // optimization if loop peeling is on.
6315 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral &&
6316 index_object->Is<SmiConstant>() && is_jsarray && !any_peeled_loop_) {
6317 index = GetInt32ElementIndex(index_object);
6318 } else {
6319 // Check boundaries.
6320 ValueNode* elements_array_length = nullptr;
6321 ValueNode* length;
6322 if (is_jsarray) {
6323 length = GetInt32(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(object));
6324 } else {
6325 length = elements_array_length =
6326 BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(elements_array);
6327 }
6328 index = GetInt32ElementIndex(index_object);
6329 if (keyed_mode.store_mode() == KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW) {
6330 if (elements_array_length == nullptr) {
6331 elements_array_length = BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(elements_array);
6332 }
6333
6334 // Validate the {index} depending on holeyness:
6335 //
6336 // For HOLEY_*_ELEMENTS the {index} must not exceed the {elements}
6337 // backing store capacity plus the maximum allowed gap, as otherwise
6338 // the (potential) backing store growth would normalize and thus
6339 // the elements kind of the {receiver} would change to slow mode.
6340 //
6341 // For JSArray PACKED_*_ELEMENTS the {index} must be within the range
6342 // [0,length+1[ to be valid. In case {index} equals {length},
6343 // the {receiver} will be extended, but kept packed.
6344 //
6345 // Non-JSArray PACKED_*_ELEMENTS always grow by adding holes because they
6346 // lack the magical length property, which requires a map transition.
6347 // So we can assume that this did not happen if we did not see this map.
6348 ValueNode* limit =
6349 IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)
6350 ? AddNewNode<Int32AddWithOverflow>(
6351 {elements_array_length,
6352 GetInt32Constant(JSObject::kMaxGap)})
6353 : is_jsarray
6354 ? AddNewNode<Int32AddWithOverflow>({length, GetInt32Constant(1)})
6355 : elements_array_length;
