6356 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
6357 index, limit, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
6358 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
6359
6360 // Grow backing store if necessary and handle COW.
6361 elements_array = AddNewNode<MaybeGrowFastElements>(
6362 {elements_array, object, index, elements_array_length},
6363 elements_kind);
6364
6365 // If we didn't grow {elements}, it might still be COW, in which case we
6366 // copy it now.
6367 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6368 DCHECK_EQ(keyed_mode.store_mode(),
6369 KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW);
6370 elements_array =
6371 AddNewNode<EnsureWritableFastElements>({elements_array, object});
6372 }
6373
6374 // Update length if necessary.
6375 if (is_jsarray) {
6376 ValueNode* new_length =
6377 AddNewNode<UpdateJSArrayLength>({length, object, index});
6378 RecordKnownProperty(object, broker()->length_string(), new_length,
6379 false, compiler::AccessMode::kStore);
6380 }
6381 } else {
6382 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
6383 index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
6384 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
6385
6386 // Handle COW if needed.
6387 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6388 if (keyed_mode.store_mode() == KeyedAccessStoreMode::kHandleCOW) {
6389 elements_array =
6390 AddNewNode<EnsureWritableFastElements>({elements_array, object});
6391 } else {
6392 // Ensure that this is not a COW FixedArray.
6393 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(
6394 elements_array, base::VectorOf({broker()->fixed_array_map()})));
6395 }
6396 }
6397 }
6398 }
6399
6400 // Do the store.
6401 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6402 BuildStoreFixedDoubleArrayElement(elements_array, index, value);
6403 } else {
6404 BuildStoreFixedArrayElement(elements_array, index, value);
6405 }
6406
6407 return ReduceResult::Done();
6408}
6409
6410MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildElementAccessOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
6411 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object,
6412 const compiler::ElementAccessInfo& access_info,
6413 compiler::KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode) {
6414 if (!IsFastElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
6415 return {};
6416 }
6417 switch (keyed_mode.access_mode()) {
6418 case compiler::AccessMode::kLoad:
6419 return TryBuildElementLoadOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
6420 object, index_object,
6421 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()),
6422 access_info.elements_kind(), keyed_mode.load_mode());
6423 case compiler::AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
6424 case compiler::AccessMode::kStore: {
6425 base::Vector<const compiler::MapRef> maps =
6426 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
6427 ElementsKind elements_kind = access_info.elements_kind();
6428 return TryBuildElementStoreOnJSArrayOrJSObject(object, index_object,
6429 GetAccumulator(), maps,
6430 elements_kind, keyed_mode);
6431 }
6432 default:
6433 // TODO(victorgomes): Implement more access types.
6434 return {};
6435 }
6436}
6437
6438template <typename GenericAccessFunc>
6439MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildElementAccess(
6440 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object,
6441 compiler::ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback,
6442 compiler::FeedbackSource const& feedback_source,
6443 GenericAccessFunc&& build_generic_access) {
6444 const compiler::KeyedAccessMode& keyed_mode = feedback.keyed_mode();
6445 // Check for the megamorphic case.
6446 if (feedback.transition_groups().empty()) {
6447 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kLoad) {
6448 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic>(
6449 {GetTaggedValue(object), GetTaggedValue(index_object)},
6450 feedback_source);
6451 } else if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kStore) {
6452 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kKeyedStoreIC_Megamorphic>(
6453 {GetTaggedValue(object), GetTaggedValue(index_object),
6454 GetTaggedValue(GetAccumulator())},
6455 feedback_source);
6456 }
6457 return {};
6458 }
6459
6460 NodeInfo* object_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(object);
6461 compiler::ElementAccessFeedback refined_feedback =
6462 object_info && object_info->possible_maps_are_known()
6463 ? feedback.Refine(broker(), object_info->possible_maps())
6464 : feedback;
6465
6466 if (refined_feedback.HasOnlyStringMaps(broker())) {
6467 return TryBuildElementAccessOnString(object, index_object, keyed_mode);
6468 }
6469
6470 compiler::AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), zone());
6471 ZoneVector<compiler::ElementAccessInfo> access_infos(zone());
6472 if (!access_info_factory.ComputeElementAccessInfos(refined_feedback,
6473 &access_infos) ||
6474 access_infos.empty()) {
6475 return {};
6476 }
6477
6478 // TODO(leszeks): This is copied without changes from TurboFan's native
6479 // context specialization. We should figure out a way to share this code.
6480 //
6481 // For holey stores or growing stores, we need to check that the prototype
6482 // chain contains no setters for elements, and we need to guard those checks
6483 // via code dependencies on the relevant prototype maps.
6484 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kStore) {
6485 // TODO(v8:7700): We could have a fast path here, that checks for the
6486 // common case of Array or Object prototype only and therefore avoids
6487 // the zone allocation of this vector.
6488 ZoneVector<compiler::MapRef> prototype_maps(zone());
6489 for (compiler::ElementAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
6490 for (compiler::MapRef receiver_map :
6491 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
6492 // If the {receiver_map} has a prototype and its elements backing
6493 // store is either holey, or we have a potentially growing store,
6494 // then we need to check that all prototypes have stable maps with
6495 // with no element accessors and no throwing behavior for elements (and
6496 // we need to guard against changes to that below).
6497 if ((IsHoleyOrDictionaryElementsKind(receiver_map.elements_kind()) ||
6498 StoreModeCanGrow(refined_feedback.keyed_mode().store_mode())) &&
6499 !receiver_map.PrototypesElementsDoNotHaveAccessorsOrThrow(
6500 broker(), &prototype_maps)) {
6501 return {};
6502 }
6503
6504 // TODO(v8:12547): Support writing to objects in shared space, which
6505 // need a write barrier that calls Object::Share to ensure the RHS is
6506 // shared.
6507 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(
6508 receiver_map.instance_type())) {
6509 return {};
6510 }
6511 }
6512 }
6513 for (compiler::MapRef prototype_map : prototype_maps) {
6514 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(prototype_map);
6515 }
6516 }
6517
6518 // Check for monomorphic case.
6519 if (access_infos.size() == 1) {
6520 compiler::ElementAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos.front();
6521 // TODO(victorgomes): Support RAB/GSAB backed typed arrays.
6522 if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
6523 return {};
6524 }
6525
6526 if (!access_info.transition_sources().empty()) {
6527 compiler::MapRef transition_target =
6528 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
6529 const ZoneVector<compiler::MapRef>& transition_sources =
6530 access_info.transition_sources();
6531
6532 // There are no transitions in heap number maps. If `object` is a SMI, we
6533 // would anyway fail the transition and deopt later.
6534 DCHECK_NE(transition_target.instance_type(),
6535 InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE);
6536#ifdef DEBUG
6537 for (auto& transition_source : transition_sources) {
6538 DCHECK_NE(transition_source.instance_type(),
6539 InstanceType::HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE);
6540 }
6541#endif // DEBUG
6542
6543 BuildCheckHeapObject(object);
6544 ValueNode* object_map =
6545 BuildLoadTaggedField(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
6546
6547 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildTransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap(
6548 object, object_map, transition_sources, transition_target));
6549 } else {
6550 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(
6551 object, base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())));
6552 }
6553 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
6554 return TryBuildElementAccessOnTypedArray(object, index_object,
6555 access_info, keyed_mode);
6556 }
6557 return TryBuildElementAccessOnJSArrayOrJSObject(object, index_object,
6558 access_info, keyed_mode);
6559 } else {
6560 return TryBuildPolymorphicElementAccess(object, index_object, keyed_mode,
6561 access_infos, build_generic_access);
6562 }
6563}
6564
6565template <typename GenericAccessFunc>
6566MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPolymorphicElementAccess(
6567 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* index_object,
6568 const compiler::KeyedAccessMode& keyed_mode,
6569 const ZoneVector<compiler::ElementAccessInfo>& access_infos,
6570 GenericAccessFunc&& build_generic_access) {
6571 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == compiler::AccessMode::kLoad &&
6572 LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode())) {
6573 // TODO(victorgomes): Handle OOB mode.
6574 return {};
6575 }
6576
6577 const bool is_any_store = compiler::IsAnyStore(keyed_mode.access_mode());
6578 const int access_info_count = static_cast<int>(access_infos.size());
6579 // Stores don't return a value, so we don't need a variable for the result.
6580 MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, is_any_store ? 0 : 1);
6581 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable> ret_val;
6582 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> done;
6583 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> generic_access;
6584
6585 BuildCheckHeapObject(object);
6586 ValueNode* object_map = BuildLoadTaggedField(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
6587
6588 // TODO(pthier): We could do better here than just emitting code for each map,
6589 // as many different maps can produce the exact samce code (e.g. TypedArray
6590 // access for Uint16/Uint32/Int16/Int32/...).
6591 for (int i = 0; i < access_info_count; i++) {
6592 compiler::ElementAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[i];
6593 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> check_next_map;
6594 const bool handle_transitions = !access_info.transition_sources().empty();
6595 MaybeReduceResult map_check_result;
6596 if (i == access_info_count - 1) {
6597 if (handle_transitions) {
6598 compiler::MapRef transition_target =
6599 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
6600 map_check_result = BuildTransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap(
6601 object, object_map, access_info.transition_sources(),
6602 transition_target);
6603 } else {
6604 map_check_result = BuildCheckMaps(
6605 object, base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()),
6606 object_map);
6607 }
6608 } else {
6609 if (handle_transitions) {
6610 compiler::MapRef transition_target =
6611 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
6612 map_check_result = BuildTransitionElementsKindAndCompareMaps(
6613 object, object_map, access_info.transition_sources(),
6614 transition_target, &sub_graph, check_next_map);
6615 } else {
6616 map_check_result = BuildCompareMaps(
6617 object, object_map,
6618 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()), &sub_graph,
6619 check_next_map);
6620 }
6621 }
6622 if (map_check_result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
6623 // We know from known possible maps that this branch is not reachable,
6624 // so don't emit any code for it.
6625 continue;
6626 }
6627 MaybeReduceResult result;
6628 // TODO(victorgomes): Support RAB/GSAB backed typed arrays.
6629 if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
6630 result = MaybeReduceResult::Fail();
6631 } else if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
6632 result = TryBuildElementAccessOnTypedArray(object, index_object,
6633 access_info, keyed_mode);
6634 } else {
6635 result = TryBuildElementAccessOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
6636 object, index_object, access_info, keyed_mode);
6637 }
6638
6639 switch (result.kind()) {
6640 case MaybeReduceResult::kDoneWithValue:
6641 case MaybeReduceResult::kDoneWithoutValue:
6642 DCHECK_EQ(result.HasValue(), !is_any_store);
6643 if (!done.has_value()) {
6644 // We initialize the label {done} lazily on the first possible path.
6645 // If no possible path exists, it is guaranteed that BuildCheckMaps
6646 // emitted an unconditional deopt and we return DoneWithAbort at the
6647 // end. We need one extra predecessor to jump from the generic case.
6648 const int possible_predecessors = access_info_count - i + 1;
6649 if (is_any_store) {
6650 done.emplace(&sub_graph, possible_predecessors);
6651 } else {
6652 ret_val.emplace(0);
6653 done.emplace(
6654 &sub_graph, possible_predecessors,
6655 std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{
6656 &*ret_val});
6657 }
6658 }
6659 if (!is_any_store) {
6660 sub_graph.set(*ret_val, result.value());
6661 }
6662 sub_graph.Goto(&*done);
6663 break;
6664 case MaybeReduceResult::kFail:
6665 if (!generic_access.has_value()) {
6666 // Conservatively assume that all remaining branches can go into the
6667 // generic path, as we have to initialize the predecessors upfront.
6668 // TODO(pthier): Find a better way to do that.
6669 generic_access.emplace(&sub_graph, access_info_count - i);
6670 }
6671 sub_graph.Goto(&*generic_access);
6672 break;
6673 case MaybeReduceResult::kDoneWithAbort:
6674 break;
6675 }
6676 if (check_next_map.has_value()) {
6677 sub_graph.Bind(&*check_next_map);
6678 }
6679 }
6680 if (generic_access.has_value() &&
6681 !sub_graph.TrimPredecessorsAndBind(&*generic_access).IsDoneWithAbort()) {
6682 MaybeReduceResult generic_result = build_generic_access();
6683 DCHECK(generic_result.IsDone());
6684 DCHECK_EQ(generic_result.IsDoneWithValue(), !is_any_store);
6685 if (!done.has_value()) {
6686 return is_any_store ? ReduceResult::Done() : generic_result.value();
6687 }
6688 if (!is_any_store) {
6689 sub_graph.set(*ret_val, generic_result.value());
6690 }
6691 sub_graph.Goto(&*done);
6692 }
6693 if (done.has_value()) {
6694 RETURN_IF_ABORT(sub_graph.TrimPredecessorsAndBind(&*done));
6695 return is_any_store ? ReduceResult::Done() : sub_graph.get(*ret_val);
6696 } else {
6697 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
6698 }
6699}
6700
6701template <typename GenericAccessFunc>
6702MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildPolymorphicPropertyAccess(
6703 ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* lookup_start_object,
6704 compiler::NamedAccessFeedback const& feedback,
6705 compiler::AccessMode access_mode,
6706 const ZoneVector<compiler::PropertyAccessInfo>& access_infos,
6707 GenericAccessFunc&& build_generic_access) {
6708 const bool is_any_store = compiler::IsAnyStore(access_mode);
6709 const int access_info_count = static_cast<int>(access_infos.size());
6710 int number_map_index = -1;
6711
6712 bool needs_migration = false;
6713 bool has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target =
6714 feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target();
6715 for (int i = 0; i < access_info_count; i++) {
6716 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[i];
6717 DCHECK(!access_info.IsInvalid());
6718 for (compiler::MapRef map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
6719 if (map.is_migration_target()) {
6720 needs_migration = true;
6721 }
6722 if (map.IsHeapNumberMap()) {
6723 GetOrCreateInfoFor(lookup_start_object);
6724 base::SmallVector<compiler::MapRef, 1> known_maps = {map};
6725 KnownMapsMerger merger(broker(), zone(), base::VectorOf(known_maps));
6726 merger.IntersectWithKnownNodeAspects(lookup_start_object,
6727 known_node_aspects());
6728 if (!merger.intersect_set().is_empty()) {
6729 DCHECK_EQ(number_map_index, -1);
6730 number_map_index = i;
6731 }
6732 }
6733 }
6734 }
6735
6736 // Stores don't return a value, so we don't need a variable for the result.
6737 MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, is_any_store ? 0 : 1);
6738 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable> ret_val;
6739 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> done;
6740 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> is_number;
6741 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> generic_access;
6742
6743 if (number_map_index >= 0) {
6744 is_number.emplace(&sub_graph, 2);
6745 sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfSmi>(&*is_number, {lookup_start_object});
6746 } else {
6747 BuildCheckHeapObject(lookup_start_object);
6748 }
6749 ValueNode* lookup_start_object_map =
6750 BuildLoadTaggedField(lookup_start_object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
6751
6752 if (needs_migration &&
6753 !v8_flags.maglev_skip_migration_check_for_polymorphic_access) {
6754 // TODO(marja, v8:7700): Try migrating only if all comparisons failed.
6755 // TODO(marja, v8:7700): Investigate making polymoprhic map comparison (with
6756 // migration) a control node (like switch).
6757 lookup_start_object_map = AddNewNode<MigrateMapIfNeeded>(
6758 {lookup_start_object_map, lookup_start_object});
6759 }
6760
6761 for (int i = 0; i < access_info_count; i++) {
6762 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[i];
6763 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> check_next_map;
6764 MaybeReduceResult map_check_result;
6765 const auto& maps = access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
6766 if (i == access_info_count - 1) {
6767 map_check_result =
6768 BuildCheckMaps(lookup_start_object, base::VectorOf(maps), {},
6769 has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target);
6770 } else {
6771 map_check_result =
6772 BuildCompareMaps(lookup_start_object, lookup_start_object_map,
6773 base::VectorOf(maps), &sub_graph, check_next_map);
6774 }
6775 if (map_check_result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
6776 // We know from known possible maps that this branch is not reachable,
6777 // so don't emit any code for it.
6778 continue;
6779 }
6780 if (i == number_map_index) {
6781 DCHECK(is_number.has_value());
6782 sub_graph.Goto(&*is_number);
6783 sub_graph.Bind(&*is_number);
6784 }
6785
6786 MaybeReduceResult result;
6787 if (is_any_store) {
6788 result = TryBuildPropertyStore(receiver, lookup_start_object,
6789 feedback.name(), access_info, access_mode);
6790 } else {
6791 result = TryBuildPropertyLoad(receiver, lookup_start_object,
6792 feedback.name(), access_info);
6793 }
6794
6795 switch (result.kind()) {
6796 case MaybeReduceResult::kDoneWithValue:
6797 case MaybeReduceResult::kDoneWithoutValue:
6798 DCHECK_EQ(result.HasValue(), !is_any_store);
6799 if (!done.has_value()) {
6800 // We initialize the label {done} lazily on the first possible path.
6801 // If no possible path exists, it is guaranteed that BuildCheckMaps
6802 // emitted an unconditional deopt and we return DoneWithAbort at the
6803 // end. We need one extra predecessor to jump from the generic case.
6804 const int possible_predecessors = access_info_count - i + 1;
6805 if (is_any_store) {
6806 done.emplace(&sub_graph, possible_predecessors);
6807 } else {
6808 ret_val.emplace(0);
6809 done.emplace(
6810 &sub_graph, possible_predecessors,
6811 std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{
6812 &*ret_val});
6813 }
6814 }
6815
6816 if (!is_any_store) {
6817 sub_graph.set(*ret_val, result.value());
6818 }
6819 sub_graph.Goto(&*done);
6820 break;
6821 case MaybeReduceResult::kDoneWithAbort:
6822 break;
6823 case MaybeReduceResult::kFail:
6824 if (!generic_access.has_value()) {
6825 // Conservatively assume that all remaining branches can go into the
6826 // generic path, as we have to initialize the predecessors upfront.
6827 // TODO(pthier): Find a better way to do that.
6828 generic_access.emplace(&sub_graph, access_info_count - i);
6829 }
6830 sub_graph.Goto(&*generic_access);
6831 break;
6832 default:
6833 UNREACHABLE();
6834 }
6835
6836 if (check_next_map.has_value()) {
6837 sub_graph.Bind(&*check_next_map);
6838 }
6839 }
6840
6841 if (generic_access.has_value() &&
6842 !sub_graph.TrimPredecessorsAndBind(&*generic_access).IsDoneWithAbort()) {
6843 MaybeReduceResult generic_result = build_generic_access();
6844 DCHECK(generic_result.IsDone());
6845 DCHECK_EQ(generic_result.IsDoneWithValue(), !is_any_store);
6846 if (!done.has_value()) {
6847 return is_any_store ? ReduceResult::Done() : generic_result.value();
6848 }
6849 if (!is_any_store) {
6850 sub_graph.set(*ret_val, generic_result.value());
6851 }
6852 sub_graph.Goto(&*done);
6853 }
6854
6855 if (done.has_value()) {
6856 RETURN_IF_ABORT(sub_graph.TrimPredecessorsAndBind(&*done));
6857 return is_any_store ? ReduceResult::Done() : sub_graph.get(*ret_val);
6858 } else {
6859 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
6860 }
6861}
6862
6863void MaglevGraphBuilder::RecordKnownProperty(
6864 ValueNode* lookup_start_object, KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey key,
6865 ValueNode* value, bool is_const, compiler::AccessMode access_mode) {
6866 DCHECK(!value->properties().is_conversion());
6867 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMap& loaded_properties =
6868 is_const ? known_node_aspects().loaded_constant_properties
6869 : known_node_aspects().loaded_properties;
6870 // Try to get loaded_properties[key] if it already exists, otherwise
6871 // construct loaded_properties[key] = ZoneMap{zone()}.
6872 auto& props_for_key =
6873 loaded_properties.try_emplace(key, zone()).first->second;
6874
6875 if (!is_const && IsAnyStore(access_mode)) {
6876 if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
6877 loop_effects_->keys_cleared.insert(key);
6878 }
6879 // We don't do any aliasing analysis, so stores clobber all other cached
6880 // loads of a property with that key. We only need to do this for
6881 // non-constant properties, since constant properties are known not to
6882 // change and therefore can't be clobbered.
6883 // TODO(leszeks): Do some light aliasing analysis here, e.g. checking
6884 // whether there's an intersection of known maps.
6885 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
6886 std::cout << " * Removing all non-constant cached ";
6887 switch (key.type()) {
6888 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kName:
6889 std::cout << "properties with name " << *key.name().object();
6890 break;
6891 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kElements:
6892 std::cout << "Elements";
6893 break;
6894 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kTypedArrayLength:
6895 std::cout << "TypedArray length";
6896 break;
6897 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kStringLength:
6898 std::cout << "String length";
6899 break;
6900 }
6901 std::cout << std::endl;
6902 }
6903 props_for_key.clear();
6904 }
6905
6906 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
6907 std::cout << " * Recording " << (is_const ? "constant" : "non-constant")
6908 << " known property "
6909 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), lookup_start_object) << ": "
6910 << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), lookup_start_object) << " [";
6911 switch (key.type()) {
6912 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kName:
6913 std::cout << *key.name().object();
6914 break;
6915 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kElements:
6916 std::cout << "Elements";
6917 break;
6918 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kTypedArrayLength:
6919 std::cout << "TypedArray length";
6920 break;
6921 case KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::kStringLength:
6922 std::cout << "String length";
6923 break;
6924 }
6925 std::cout << "] = " << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), value) << ": "
6926 << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), value) << std::endl;
6927 }
6928
6929 if (IsAnyStore(access_mode) && !is_const && is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
6930 auto updated = props_for_key.emplace(lookup_start_object, value);
6931 if (updated.second) {
6932 loop_effects_->objects_written.insert(lookup_start_object);
6933 } else if (updated.first->second != value) {
6934 updated.first->second = value;
6935 loop_effects_->objects_written.insert(lookup_start_object);
6936 }
6937 } else {
6938 props_for_key[lookup_start_object] = value;
6939 }
6940}
6941
6942MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReuseKnownPropertyLoad(
6943 ValueNode* lookup_start_object, compiler::NameRef name) {
6944 if (MaybeReduceResult result = TryFindLoadedProperty(
6945 known_node_aspects().loaded_properties, lookup_start_object, name);
6946 result.IsDone()) {
6947 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building && result.IsDoneWithValue()) {
6948 std::cout << " * Reusing non-constant loaded property "
6949 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), result.value()) << ": "
6950 << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), result.value()) << std::endl;
6951 }
6952 return result;
6953 }
6954 if (MaybeReduceResult result =
6955 TryFindLoadedProperty(known_node_aspects().loaded_constant_properties,
6956 lookup_start_object, name);
6957 result.IsDone()) {
6958 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building && result.IsDoneWithValue()) {
6959 std::cout << " * Reusing constant loaded property "
6960 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), result.value()) << ": "
6961 << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), result.value()) << std::endl;
6962 }
6963 return result;
6964 }
6965 return {};
6966}
6967
6968ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadStringLength(ValueNode* string) {
6969 if (MaybeReduceResult result = TryFindLoadedProperty(
6970 known_node_aspects().loaded_constant_properties, string,
6971 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::StringLength());
6972 result.IsDone()) {
6973 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building && result.IsDoneWithValue()) {
6974 std::cout << " * Reusing constant [String length]"
6975 << PrintNodeLabel(graph_labeller(), result.value()) << ": "
6976 << PrintNode(graph_labeller(), result.value()) << std::endl;
6977 }
6978 return result.value();
6979 }
6980 ValueNode* result = AddNewNode<StringLength>({string});
6981 RecordKnownProperty(string,
6982 KnownNodeAspects::LoadedPropertyMapKey::StringLength(),
6983 result, true, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
6984 return result;
6985}
6986
6987template <typename GenericAccessFunc>
6988MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(
6989 ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* lookup_start_object, compiler::NameRef name,
6990 compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source,
6991 GenericAccessFunc&& build_generic_access) {
6992 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
6993 broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(feedback_source,
6994 compiler::AccessMode::kLoad, name);
6995 switch (processed_feedback.kind()) {
6996 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
6997 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
6998 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
6999 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kNamedAccess: {
7000 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReuseKnownPropertyLoad(lookup_start_object, name));
7001 return TryBuildNamedAccess(
7002 receiver, lookup_start_object, processed_feedback.AsNamedAccess(),
7003 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad, build_generic_access);
7004 }
7005 default:
7006 return {};
7007 }
7008}
7009
7010MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(
7011 ValueNode* receiver, compiler::NameRef name,
7012 compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
7013 auto build_generic_access = [this, &receiver, &name, &feedback_source]() {
7014 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7015 return AddNewNode<LoadNamedGeneric>({context, receiver}, name,
7016 feedback_source);
7017 };
7018 return TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(receiver, receiver, name, feedback_source,
7019 build_generic_access);
7020}
7021
7022ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetNamedProperty() {
7023 // GetNamedProperty <object> <name_index> <slot>
7024 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7025 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(1);
7026 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
7027 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7028 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
7029 TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(object, name, feedback_source), SetAccumulator);
7030 // Create a generic load in the fallthrough.
7031 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7032 SetAccumulator(
7033 AddNewNode<LoadNamedGeneric>({context, object}, name, feedback_source));
7034 return ReduceResult::Done();
7035}
7036
7037ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetConstant(compiler::ObjectRef ref) {
7038 if (ref.IsSmi()) return GetSmiConstant(ref.AsSmi());
7039 compiler::HeapObjectRef constant = ref.AsHeapObject();
7040
7041 if (IsThinString(*constant.object())) {
7042 constant = MakeRefAssumeMemoryFence(
7043 broker(), Cast<ThinString>(*constant.object())->actual());
7044 }
7045
7046 auto root_index = broker()->FindRootIndex(constant);
7047 if (root_index.has_value()) {
7048 return GetRootConstant(*root_index);
7049 }
7050
7051 auto it = graph_->constants().find(constant);
7052 if (it == graph_->constants().end()) {
7053 Constant* node = CreateNewConstantNode<Constant>(0, constant);
7054 graph_->constants().emplace(constant, node);
7055 return node;
7056 }
7057 return it->second;
7058}
7059
7060ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetTrustedConstant(compiler::HeapObjectRef ref,
7061 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
7062#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7063 auto it = graph_->trusted_constants().find(ref);
7064 if (it == graph_->trusted_constants().end()) {
7065 TrustedConstant* node = CreateNewConstantNode<TrustedConstant>(0, ref, tag);
7066 graph_->trusted_constants().emplace(ref, node);
7067 return node;
7068 }
7069 SBXCHECK_EQ(it->second->tag(), tag);
7070 return it->second;
7071#else
7072 return GetConstant(ref);
7073#endif
7074}
7075
7076ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetNamedPropertyFromSuper() {
7077 // GetNamedPropertyFromSuper <receiver> <name_index> <slot>
7078 ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
7079 ValueNode* home_object = GetAccumulator();
7080 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(1);
7081 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
7082 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7083 // {home_object} is guaranteed to be a HeapObject.
7084 ValueNode* home_object_map =
7085 BuildLoadTaggedField(home_object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
7086 ValueNode* lookup_start_object =
7087 BuildLoadTaggedField(home_object_map, Map::kPrototypeOffset);
7088
7089 auto build_generic_access = [this, &receiver, &lookup_start_object, &name,
7090 &feedback_source]() {
7091 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7092 return AddNewNode<LoadNamedFromSuperGeneric>(
7093 {context, receiver, lookup_start_object}, name, feedback_source);
7094 };
7095
7096 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
7097 TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(receiver, lookup_start_object, name,
7098 feedback_source, build_generic_access),
7099 SetAccumulator);
7100 // Create a generic load.
7101 SetAccumulator(build_generic_access());
7102 return ReduceResult::Done();
7103}
7104
7105bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildGetKeyedPropertyWithEnumeratedKey(
7106 ValueNode* object, const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source,
7107 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback) {
7108 if (current_for_in_state.index != nullptr &&
7109 current_for_in_state.enum_cache_indices != nullptr &&
7110 current_for_in_state.key == current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator()) {
7111 bool speculating_receiver_map_matches = false;
7112 if (current_for_in_state.receiver != object) {
7113 // When the feedback is uninitialized, it is either a keyed load which
7114 // always hits the enum cache, or a keyed load that had never been
7115 // reached. In either case, we can check the map of the receiver and use
7116 // the enum cache if the map match the {cache_type}.
7117 if (processed_feedback.kind() !=
7118 compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient) {
7119 return false;
7120 }
7121 BuildCheckHeapObject(object);
7122 speculating_receiver_map_matches = true;
7123 }
7124
7125 if (current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check ||
7126 speculating_receiver_map_matches) {
7127 auto* receiver_map = BuildLoadTaggedField(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
7128 AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>(
7129 {receiver_map, current_for_in_state.cache_type});
7130 if (current_for_in_state.receiver == object) {
7131 current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check = false;
7132 }
7133 }
7134 // TODO(leszeks): Cache the field index per iteration.
7135 auto* field_index = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(
7136 current_for_in_state.enum_cache_indices, current_for_in_state.index);
7137 SetAccumulator(
7138 AddNewNode<LoadTaggedFieldByFieldIndex>({object, field_index}));
7139 return true;
7140 }
7141 return false;
7142}
7143
7144ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGetKeyedProperty(
7145 ValueNode* object, const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source,
7146 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback) {
7147 if (TryBuildGetKeyedPropertyWithEnumeratedKey(object, feedback_source,
7148 processed_feedback)) {
7149 return ReduceResult::Done();
7150 }
7151
7152 auto build_generic_access = [this, object, &feedback_source]() {
7153 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7154 ValueNode* key = GetAccumulator();
7155 return AddNewNode<GetKeyedGeneric>({context, object, key}, feedback_source);
7156 };
7157
7158 switch (processed_feedback.kind()) {
7159 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
7160 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7161 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericKeyedAccess);
7162
7163 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess: {
7164 // Get the accumulator without conversion. TryBuildElementAccess
7165 // will try to pick the best representation.
7166 ValueNode* index = current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator();
7167 MaybeReduceResult result = TryBuildElementAccess(
7168 object, index, processed_feedback.AsElementAccess(), feedback_source,
7169 build_generic_access);
7170 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
7171 break;
7172 }
7173
7174 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kNamedAccess: {
7175 ValueNode* key = GetAccumulator();
7176 compiler::NameRef name = processed_feedback.AsNamedAccess().name();
7177 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(key, name));
7178
7179 MaybeReduceResult result = TryReuseKnownPropertyLoad(object, name);
7180 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
7181
7182 result = TryBuildNamedAccess(
7183 object, object, processed_feedback.AsNamedAccess(), feedback_source,
7184 compiler::AccessMode::kLoad, build_generic_access);
7185 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
7186 break;
7187 }
7188
7189 default:
7190 break;
7191 }
7192
7193 // Create a generic load in the fallthrough.
7194 SetAccumulator(build_generic_access());
7195 return ReduceResult::Done();
7196}
7197
7198ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetKeyedProperty() {
7199 // GetKeyedProperty <object> <slot>
7200 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7201 // TODO(leszeks): We don't need to tag the key if it's an Int32 and a simple
7202 // monomorphic element load.
7203 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
7204 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7205
7206 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback* processed_feedback =
7207 &broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
7208 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad, std::nullopt);
7209 if (processed_feedback->kind() ==
7210 compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess &&
7211 processed_feedback->AsElementAccess().transition_groups().empty()) {
7212 if (auto constant = TryGetConstant(GetAccumulator());
7213 constant.has_value() && constant->IsName()) {
7214 compiler::NameRef name = constant->AsName();
7215 if (name.IsUniqueName() && !name.object()->IsArrayIndex()) {
7216 processed_feedback =
7217 &processed_feedback->AsElementAccess().Refine(broker(), name);
7218 }
7219 }
7220 }
7221
7222 return BuildGetKeyedProperty(object, feedback_source, *processed_feedback);
7223}
7224
7225ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetEnumeratedKeyedProperty() {
7226 // GetEnumeratedKeyedProperty <object> <enum_index> <cache_type> <slot>
7227 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7228 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
7229 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7230
7231 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
7232 broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
7233 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad, std::nullopt);
7234
7235 return BuildGetKeyedProperty(object, feedback_source, processed_feedback);
7236}
7237
7238ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLdaModuleVariable() {
7239 // LdaModuleVariable <cell_index> <depth>
7240 int cell_index = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0);
7241 size_t depth = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(1);
7242 ValueNode* context = GetContextAtDepth(GetContext(), depth);
7243
7244 ValueNode* module = LoadAndCacheContextSlot(
7245 context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX, kImmutable, ContextKind::kDefault);
7246 ValueNode* exports_or_imports;
7247 if (cell_index > 0) {
7248 exports_or_imports =
7249 BuildLoadTaggedField(module, SourceTextModule::kRegularExportsOffset);
7250 // The actual array index is (cell_index - 1).
7251 cell_index -= 1;
7252 } else {
7253 exports_or_imports =
7254 BuildLoadTaggedField(module, SourceTextModule::kRegularImportsOffset);
7255 // The actual array index is (-cell_index - 1).
7256 cell_index = -cell_index - 1;
7257 }
7258 ValueNode* cell = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(exports_or_imports, cell_index);
7259 SetAccumulator(BuildLoadTaggedField(cell, Cell::kValueOffset));
7260 return ReduceResult::Done();
7261}
7262
7263ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetContextAtDepth(ValueNode* context,
7264 size_t depth) {
7265 MinimizeContextChainDepth(&context, &depth);
7266
7267 if (compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context()) {
7268 compiler::OptionalContextRef maybe_ref =
7269 FunctionContextSpecialization::TryToRef(compilation_unit_, context,
7270 &depth);
7271 if (maybe_ref.has_value()) {
7272 context = GetConstant(maybe_ref.value());
7273 }
7274 }
7275
7276 for (size_t i = 0; i < depth; i++) {
7277 context = LoadAndCacheContextSlot(context, Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX,
7278 kImmutable, ContextKind::kDefault);
7279 }
7280 return context;
7281}
7282
7283ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitStaModuleVariable() {
7284 // StaModuleVariable <cell_index> <depth>
7285 int cell_index = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(0);
7286 if (V8_UNLIKELY(cell_index < 0)) {
7287 // TODO(verwaest): Make this fail as well.
7288 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kAbort,
7289 {GetSmiConstant(static_cast<int>(
7290 AbortReason::kUnsupportedModuleOperation))});
7291 }
7292
7293 size_t depth = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(1);
7294 ValueNode* context = GetContextAtDepth(GetContext(), depth);
7295
7296 ValueNode* module = LoadAndCacheContextSlot(
7297 context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX, kImmutable, ContextKind::kDefault);
7298 ValueNode* exports =
7299 BuildLoadTaggedField(module, SourceTextModule::kRegularExportsOffset);
7300 // The actual array index is (cell_index - 1).
7301 cell_index -= 1;
7302 ValueNode* cell = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(exports, cell_index);
7303 BuildStoreTaggedField(cell, GetAccumulator(), Cell::kValueOffset,
7304 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
7305 return ReduceResult::Done();
7306}
7307
7308ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoadGlobal(
7309 compiler::NameRef name, compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source,
7310 TypeofMode typeof_mode) {
7311 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& access_feedback =
7312 broker()->GetFeedbackForGlobalAccess(feedback_source);
7313
7314 if (access_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
7315 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7316 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericGlobalAccess);
7317 }
7318
7319 const compiler::GlobalAccessFeedback& global_access_feedback =
7320 access_feedback.AsGlobalAccess();
7321 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildGlobalLoad(global_access_feedback),
7322 SetAccumulator);
7323
7324 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7325 SetAccumulator(
7326 AddNewNode<LoadGlobal>({context}, name, feedback_source, typeof_mode));
7327 return ReduceResult::Done();
7328}
7329
7330ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSetNamedProperty() {
7331 // SetNamedProperty <object> <name_index> <slot>
7332 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7333 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(1);
7334 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
7335 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7336
7337 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
7338 broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
7339 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kStore, name);
7340
7341 auto build_generic_access = [this, object, &name, &feedback_source]() {
7342 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7343 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
7344 AddNewNode<SetNamedGeneric>({context, object, value}, name,
7345 feedback_source);
7346 return ReduceResult::Done();
7347 };
7348
7349 switch (processed_feedback.kind()) {
7350 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
7351 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7352 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
7353
7354 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kNamedAccess:
7355 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildNamedAccess(
7356 object, object, processed_feedback.AsNamedAccess(), feedback_source,
7357 compiler::AccessMode::kStore, build_generic_access));
7358 break;
7359 default:
7360 break;
7361 }
7362
7363 // Create a generic store in the fallthrough.
7364 return build_generic_access();
7365}

7367ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitDefineNamedOwnProperty() {
7368 // DefineNamedOwnProperty <object> <name_index> <slot>
7369 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7370 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(1);
7371 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
7372 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7373
7374 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
7375 broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
7376 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kStore, name);
7377
7378 auto build_generic_access = [this, object, &name, &feedback_source]() {
7379 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7380 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
7381 AddNewNode<DefineNamedOwnGeneric>({context, object, value}, name,
7382 feedback_source);
7383 return ReduceResult::Done();
7384 };
7385 switch (processed_feedback.kind()) {
7386 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
7387 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7388 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
7389
7390 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kNamedAccess:
7391 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildNamedAccess(
7392 object, object, processed_feedback.AsNamedAccess(), feedback_source,
7393 compiler::AccessMode::kDefine, build_generic_access));
7394 break;
7395
7396 default:
7397 break;
7398 }
7399
7400 // Create a generic store in the fallthrough.
7401 return build_generic_access();
7402}

7404ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSetKeyedProperty() {
7405 // SetKeyedProperty <object> <key> <slot>
7406 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7407 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
7408 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7409
7410 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
7411 broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
7412 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kStore, std::nullopt);
7413
7414 auto build_generic_access = [this, object, &feedback_source]() {
7415 ValueNode* key = LoadRegister(1);
7416 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7417 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
7418 AddNewNode<SetKeyedGeneric>({context, object, key, value}, feedback_source);
7419 return ReduceResult::Done();
7420 };
7421
7422 switch (processed_feedback.kind()) {
7423 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
7424 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7425 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericKeyedAccess);
7426
7427 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess: {
7428 // Get the key without conversion. TryBuildElementAccess will try to pick
7429 // the best representation.
7430 ValueNode* index =
7431 current_interpreter_frame_.get(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(1));
7432 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildElementAccess(
7433 object, index, processed_feedback.AsElementAccess(), feedback_source,
7434 build_generic_access));
7435 } break;
7436
7437 default:
7438 break;
7439 }
7440
7441 // Create a generic store in the fallthrough.
7442 return build_generic_access();
7443}

7445ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitDefineKeyedOwnProperty() {
7446 // DefineKeyedOwnProperty <object> <key> <flags> <slot>
7447 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7448 ValueNode* key = LoadRegister(1);
7449 ValueNode* flags = GetSmiConstant(GetFlag8Operand(2));
7450 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
7451 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7452
7453 // TODO(victorgomes): Add monomorphic fast path.
7454
7455 // Create a generic store in the fallthrough.
7456 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7457 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
7458 AddNewNode<DefineKeyedOwnGeneric>({context, object, key, value, flags},
7459 feedback_source);
7460 return ReduceResult::Done();
7461}

7463ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitStaInArrayLiteral() {
7464 // StaInArrayLiteral <object> <index> <slot>
7465 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
7466 ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
7467 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
7468 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
7469
7470 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
7471 broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
7472 feedback_source, compiler::AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral, std::nullopt);
7473
7474 auto build_generic_access = [this, object, index, &feedback_source]() {
7475 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7476 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
7477 AddNewNode<StoreInArrayLiteralGeneric>({context, object, index, value},
7478 feedback_source);
7479 return ReduceResult::Done();
7480 };
7481
7482 switch (processed_feedback.kind()) {
7483 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
7484 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7485 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericKeyedAccess);
7486
7487 case compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess: {
7488 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildElementAccess(
7489 object, index, processed_feedback.AsElementAccess(), feedback_source,
7490 build_generic_access));
7491 break;
7492 }
7493
7494 default:
7495 break;
7496 }
7497
7498 // Create a generic store in the fallthrough.
7499 return build_generic_access();
7500}

7604
7605ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLogicalNot(ValueNode* value) {
7606 // TODO(victorgomes): Use NodeInfo to add more type optimizations here.
7607 switch (value->opcode()) {
7608#define CASE(Name) \
7609 case Opcode::k##Name: { \
7610 return GetBooleanConstant( \
7611 !value->Cast<Name>()->ToBoolean(local_isolate())); \
7612 }
7613 CONSTANT_VALUE_NODE_LIST(CASE)
7614#undef CASE
7615 default:
7616 return AddNewNode<LogicalNot>({value});
7617 }
7618}
7619
7620ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitLogicalNot() {
7621 // Invariant: accumulator must already be a boolean value.
7622 SetAccumulator(BuildLogicalNot(GetAccumulator()));
7623 return ReduceResult::Done();
7624}
7625
7626ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTypeOf() {
7627 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
7628 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReduceTypeOf(value), SetAccumulator);
7629
7630 FeedbackNexus nexus = FeedbackNexusForOperand(0);
7631 TypeOfFeedback::Result feedback = nexus.GetTypeOfFeedback();
7632 switch (feedback) {
7633 case TypeOfFeedback::kNone:
7634 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
7635 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForTypeOf);
7636 case TypeOfFeedback::kNumber:
7637 BuildCheckNumber(value);
7638 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::knumber_string));
7639 return ReduceResult::Done();
7640 case TypeOfFeedback::kString:
7641 BuildCheckString(value);
7642 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kstring_string));
7643 return ReduceResult::Done();
7644 case TypeOfFeedback::kFunction:
7645 AddNewNode<CheckDetectableCallable>({value},
7646 GetCheckType(GetType(value)));
7647 EnsureType(value, NodeType::kCallable);
7648 SetAccumulator(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kfunction_string));
7649 return ReduceResult::Done();
7650 default:
7651 break;
7652 }
7653
7654 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kTypeof>({GetTaggedValue(value)}));
7655 return ReduceResult::Done();
7656}

7660 ValueNode* key = GetAccumulator();
7661 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
7662 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<DeleteProperty>({context, object, key},
7663 LanguageMode::kStrict));
7664 return ReduceResult::Done();
7665}

7672 LanguageMode::kSloppy));
7673 return ReduceResult::Done();
