7675
7676ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetSuperConstructor() {
7677 ValueNode* active_function = GetAccumulator();
7678 // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe BuildLoadTaggedField should support constants
7679 // instead.
7680 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef constant =
7681 TryGetConstant(active_function)) {
7682 compiler::MapRef map = constant->map(broker());
7683 if (map.is_stable()) {
7684 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(map);
7685 ValueNode* map_proto = GetConstant(map.prototype(broker()));
7686 StoreRegister(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0), map_proto);
7687 return ReduceResult::Done();
7688 }
7689 }
7690 ValueNode* map =
7691 BuildLoadTaggedField(active_function, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
7692 ValueNode* map_proto = BuildLoadTaggedField(map, Map::kPrototypeOffset);
7693 StoreRegister(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0), map_proto);
7694 return ReduceResult::Done();
7695}
7696
7697bool MaglevGraphBuilder::HasValidInitialMap(
7698 compiler::JSFunctionRef new_target, compiler::JSFunctionRef constructor) {
7699 if (!new_target.map(broker()).has_prototype_slot()) return false;
7700 if (!new_target.has_initial_map(broker())) return false;
7701 compiler::MapRef initial_map = new_target.initial_map(broker());
7702 return initial_map.GetConstructor(broker()).equals(constructor);
7703}
7704
7705bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(
7706 ValueNode* this_function, ValueNode* new_target,
7707 std::pair<interpreter::Register, interpreter::Register> result) {
7708 // See also:
7709 // JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct
7710
7711 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
7712 TryGetConstant(this_function);
7713 if (!maybe_constant) return false;
7714
7715 compiler::MapRef function_map = maybe_constant->map(broker());
7716 compiler::HeapObjectRef current = function_map.prototype(broker());
7717
7718 // TODO(v8:13091): Don't produce incomplete stack traces when debug is active.
7719 // We already deopt when a breakpoint is set. But it would be even nicer to
7720 // avoid producting incomplete stack traces when when debug is active, even if
7721 // there are no breakpoints - then a user inspecting stack traces via Dev
7722 // Tools would always see the full stack trace.
7723
7724 while (true) {
7725 if (!current.IsJSFunction()) return false;
7726 compiler::JSFunctionRef current_function = current.AsJSFunction();
7727
7728 // If there are class fields, bail out. TODO(v8:13091): Handle them here.
7729 if (current_function.shared(broker())
7730 .requires_instance_members_initializer()) {
7731 return false;
7732 }
7733
7734 // If there are private methods, bail out. TODO(v8:13091): Handle them here.
7735 if (current_function.context(broker())
7736 .scope_info(broker())
7737 .ClassScopeHasPrivateBrand()) {
7738 return false;
7739 }
7740
7741 FunctionKind kind = current_function.shared(broker()).kind();
7742 if (kind != FunctionKind::kDefaultDerivedConstructor) {
7743 // The hierarchy walk will end here; this is the last change to bail out
7744 // before creating new nodes.
7745 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) {
7746 return false;
7747 }
7748
7749 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef new_target_function =
7750 TryGetConstant(new_target);
7751 if (kind == FunctionKind::kDefaultBaseConstructor) {
7752 // Store the result register first, so that a lazy deopt in
7753 // `FastNewObject` writes `true` to this register.
7754 StoreRegister(result.first, GetBooleanConstant(true));
7755
7756 ValueNode* object;
7757 if (new_target_function && new_target_function->IsJSFunction() &&
7758 HasValidInitialMap(new_target_function->AsJSFunction(),
7759 current_function)) {
7760 object = BuildInlinedAllocation(
7761 CreateJSConstructor(new_target_function->AsJSFunction()),
7762 AllocationType::kYoung);
7763 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
7764 } else {
7765 object = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kFastNewObject>(
7766 {GetConstant(current_function), GetTaggedValue(new_target)});
7767 // We've already stored "true" into result.first, so a deopt here just
7768 // has to store result.second. Also mark result.first as being used,
7769 // since the lazy deopt frame won't have marked it since it used to be
7770 // a result register.
7771 AddDeoptUse(current_interpreter_frame_.get(result.first));
7772 object->lazy_deopt_info()->UpdateResultLocation(result.second, 1);
7773 }
7774 StoreRegister(result.second, object);
7775 } else {
7776 StoreRegister(result.first, GetBooleanConstant(false));
7777 StoreRegister(result.second, GetConstant(current));
7778 }
7779
7780 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChain(
7781 function_map, WhereToStart::kStartAtReceiver, current_function);
7782 return true;
7783 }
7784
7785 // Keep walking up the class tree.
7786 current = current_function.map(broker()).prototype(broker());
7787 }
7788}
7789
7790ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct() {
7791 ValueNode* this_function = LoadRegister(0);
7792 ValueNode* new_target = LoadRegister(1);
7793
7794 auto register_pair = iterator_.GetRegisterPairOperand(2);
7795
7796 if (TryBuildFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(this_function, new_target,
7797 register_pair)) {
7798 return ReduceResult::Done();
7799 }
7800
7801 CallBuiltin* result =
7802 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct>(
7803 {GetTaggedValue(this_function), GetTaggedValue(new_target)});
7804 StoreRegisterPair(register_pair, result);
7805 return ReduceResult::Done();
7806}
7807
7808namespace {
7809void ForceEscapeIfAllocation(ValueNode* value) {
7810 if (InlinedAllocation* alloc = value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
7811 alloc->ForceEscaping();
7812 }
7813}
7814} // namespace
7815
7816ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlined(ValueNode* context,
7817 ValueNode* function,
7818 ValueNode* new_target,
7819 const CallArguments& args) {
7820 DCHECK(is_inline());
7821
7822 // Manually create the prologue of the inner function graph, so that we
7823 // can manually set up the arguments.
7824 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_block_);
7825
7826 // Set receiver.
7827 ValueNode* receiver =
7828 GetConvertReceiver(compilation_unit_->shared_function_info(), args);
7829 SetArgument(0, receiver);
7830
7831 // The inlined function could call a builtin that iterates the frame, the
7832 // receiver needs to have been materialized.
7833 // TODO(victorgomes): Can we relax this requirement? Maybe we can allocate the
7834 // object lazily? This is also only required if the inlined function is not a
7835 // leaf (ie. it calls other functions).
7836 ForceEscapeIfAllocation(receiver);
7837
7838 // Set remaining arguments.
7839 RootConstant* undefined_constant =
7840 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
7841 int arg_count = static_cast<int>(args.count());
7842 int formal_parameter_count = compilation_unit_->parameter_count() - 1;
7843 for (int i = 0; i < formal_parameter_count; i++) {
7844 ValueNode* arg_value = args[i];
7845 if (arg_value == nullptr) arg_value = undefined_constant;
7846 SetArgument(i + 1, arg_value);
7847 }
7848
7849 // Save all arguments if we have a mismatch between arguments count and
7850 // parameter count.
7851 inlined_arguments_ = zone()->AllocateVector<ValueNode*>(arg_count + 1);
7852 inlined_arguments_[0] = receiver;
7853 for (int i = 0; i < arg_count; i++) {
7854 inlined_arguments_[i + 1] = args[i];
7855 }
7856
7857 inlined_new_target_ = new_target;
7858
7859 BuildRegisterFrameInitialization(context, function, new_target);
7860 BuildMergeStates();
7861 EndPrologue();
7862 in_prologue_ = false;
7863
7864 // Build the inlined function body.
7865 BuildBody();
7866
7867 // All returns in the inlined body jump to a merge point one past the bytecode
7868 // length (i.e. at offset bytecode.length()). If there isn't one already,
7869 // create a block at this fake offset and have it jump out of the inlined
7870 // function, into a new block that we create which resumes execution of the
7871 // outer function.
7872 if (!current_block_) {
7873 // If we don't have a merge state at the inline_exit_offset, then there is
7874 // no control flow that reaches the end of the inlined function, either
7875 // because of infinite loops or deopts
7876 if (merge_states_[inline_exit_offset()] == nullptr) {
7877 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
7878 }
7879
7880 ProcessMergePoint(inline_exit_offset(), /*preserve_kna*/ false);
7881 StartNewBlock(inline_exit_offset(), /*predecessor*/ nullptr);
7882 }
7883
7884 // Pull the returned accumulator value out of the inlined function's final
7885 // merged return state.
7886 return current_interpreter_frame_.accumulator();
7887}
7888
7889#define TRACE_INLINING(...) \
7890 do { \
7891 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_inlining) \
7892 StdoutStream{} << __VA_ARGS__ << std::endl; \
7893 } while (false)
7894
7895#define TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE(...) \
7896 TRACE_INLINING(" cannot inline " << shared << ": " << __VA_ARGS__)
7897
7898bool MaglevGraphBuilder::ShouldInlineCall(
7899 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
7900 compiler::OptionalFeedbackVectorRef feedback_vector, float call_frequency) {
7901 if (graph()->total_inlined_bytecode_size() >
7902 v8_flags.max_maglev_inlined_bytecode_size_cumulative) {
7903 compilation_unit_->info()->set_could_not_inline_all_candidates();
7904 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("maximum inlined bytecode size");
7905 return false;
7906 }
7907 if (!feedback_vector) {
7908 // TODO(verwaest): Soft deopt instead?
7909 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("it has not been compiled/run with feedback yet");
7910 return false;
7911 }
7912 // TODO(olivf): This is a temporary stopgap to prevent infinite recursion when
7913 // inlining, because we currently excempt small functions from some of the
7914 // negative heuristics. We should refactor these heuristics and make sure they
7915 // make sense in the presence of (mutually) recursive inlining. Please do
7916 // *not* return true before this check.
7917 if (inlining_depth() > v8_flags.max_maglev_hard_inline_depth) {
7918 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("inlining depth ("
7919 << inlining_depth() << ") >= hard-max-depth ("
7920 << v8_flags.max_maglev_hard_inline_depth << ")");
7921 return false;
7922 }
7923 if (compilation_unit_->shared_function_info().equals(shared)) {
7924 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("direct recursion");
7925 return false;
7926 }
7927 SharedFunctionInfo::Inlineability inlineability =
7928 shared.GetInlineability(broker());
7929 if (inlineability != SharedFunctionInfo::Inlineability::kIsInlineable) {
7930 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE(inlineability);
7931 return false;
7932 }
7933 // TODO(victorgomes): Support NewTarget/RegisterInput in inlined functions.
7934 compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker());
7935 if (bytecode.incoming_new_target_or_generator_register().is_valid()) {
7936 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("use unsupported NewTargetOrGenerator register");
7937 return false;
7938 }
7939 if (call_frequency < v8_flags.min_maglev_inlining_frequency) {
7940 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("call frequency ("
7941 << call_frequency << ") < minimum threshold ("
7942 << v8_flags.min_maglev_inlining_frequency << ")");
7943 return false;
7944 }
7945 if (bytecode.length() < v8_flags.max_maglev_inlined_bytecode_size_small) {
7946 TRACE_INLINING(" inlining "
7947 << shared
7948 << ": small function, skipping max-size and max-depth");
7949 return true;
7950 }
7951 if (bytecode.length() > v8_flags.max_maglev_inlined_bytecode_size) {
7952 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("big function, size ("
7953 << bytecode.length() << ") >= max-size ("
7954 << v8_flags.max_maglev_inlined_bytecode_size << ")");
7955 return false;
7956 }
7957 if (inlining_depth() > v8_flags.max_maglev_inline_depth) {
7958 TRACE_CANNOT_INLINE("inlining depth ("
7959 << inlining_depth() << ") >= max-depth ("
7960 << v8_flags.max_maglev_inline_depth << ")");
7961 return false;
7962 }
7963 TRACE_INLINING(" inlining " << shared);
7964 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_inlining_verbose) {
7965 BytecodeArray::Disassemble(bytecode.object(), std::cout);
7966 i::Print(*feedback_vector->object(), std::cout);
7967 }
7968 graph()->add_inlined_bytecode_size(bytecode.length());
7969 return true;
7970}
7971
7972MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildInlinedCall(
7973 ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
7974 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
7975 compiler::OptionalFeedbackVectorRef feedback_vector, CallArguments& args,
7976 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
7977 DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kDefault);
7978 float feedback_frequency = 0.0f;
7979 if (feedback_source.IsValid()) {
7980 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
7981 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
7982 feedback_frequency =
7983 feedback.IsInsufficient() ? 0.0f : feedback.AsCall().frequency();
7984 }
7985 float call_frequency = feedback_frequency * call_frequency_;
7986 if (!ShouldInlineCall(shared, feedback_vector, call_frequency)) {
7987 return {};
7988 }
7989
7990 compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode = shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker());
7991
7992 if (v8_flags.maglev_print_inlined &&
7993 TopLevelFunctionPassMaglevPrintFilter() &&
7994 (v8_flags.print_maglev_code || v8_flags.print_maglev_graph ||
7995 v8_flags.print_maglev_graphs)) {
7996 std::cout << "== Inlining " << Brief(*shared.object()) << std::endl;
7997 BytecodeArray::Disassemble(bytecode.object(), std::cout);
7998 if (v8_flags.maglev_print_feedback) {
7999 i::Print(*feedback_vector->object(), std::cout);
8000 }
8001 } else if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8002 std::cout << "== Inlining " << shared.object() << std::endl;
8003 }
8004
8005 graph()->inlined_functions().push_back(
8006 OptimizedCompilationInfo::InlinedFunctionHolder(
8007 shared.object(), bytecode.object(), current_source_position_));
8008 if (feedback_vector->object()->invocation_count_before_stable(kRelaxedLoad) >
8009 v8_flags.invocation_count_for_early_optimization) {
8010 compilation_unit_->info()->set_could_not_inline_all_candidates();
8011 }
8012 int inlining_id = static_cast<int>(graph()->inlined_functions().size() - 1);
8013
8014 // Create a new compilation unit and graph builder for the inlined
8015 // function.
8016 MaglevCompilationUnit* inner_unit = MaglevCompilationUnit::NewInner(
8017 zone(), compilation_unit_, shared, feedback_vector.value());
8018 MaglevGraphBuilder inner_graph_builder(
8019 local_isolate_, inner_unit, graph_, call_frequency,
8020 BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()), IsInsideLoop(), inlining_id,
8021 this);
8022
8023 // Merge catch block state if needed.
8024 CatchBlockDetails catch_block = GetCurrentTryCatchBlock();
8025 if (catch_block.ref && catch_block.state->exception_handler_was_used()) {
8026 // Merge the current state into the handler state.
8027 catch_block.state->MergeThrow(
8028 GetCurrentCatchBlockGraphBuilder(), catch_block.unit,
8029 *current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects(),
8030 current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects());
8031 }
8032
8033 // Propagate catch block.
8034 inner_graph_builder.parent_catch_ = catch_block;
8035 inner_graph_builder.parent_catch_deopt_frame_distance_ =
8036 1 + (IsInsideTryBlock() ? 0 : parent_catch_deopt_frame_distance_);
8037
8038 // Set the inner graph builder to build in the current block.
8039 inner_graph_builder.current_block_ = current_block_;
8040
8041 MaybeReduceResult result =
8042 inner_graph_builder.BuildInlined(context, function, new_target, args);
8043 if (result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8044 DCHECK_NULL(inner_graph_builder.current_block_);
8045 current_block_ = nullptr;
8046 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8047 std::cout << "== Finished inlining (abort) " << shared.object()
8048 << std::endl;
8049 }
8050 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
8051 }
8052
8053 // Propagate KnownNodeAspects back to the caller.
8054 current_interpreter_frame_.set_known_node_aspects(
8055 inner_graph_builder.current_interpreter_frame_.known_node_aspects());
8056 unobserved_context_slot_stores_ =
8057 inner_graph_builder.unobserved_context_slot_stores_;
8058
8059 // Propagate virtual object lists back to the caller.
8060 current_interpreter_frame_.set_virtual_objects(
8061 inner_graph_builder.current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects());
8062
8063 DCHECK(result.IsDoneWithValue());
8064 // Resume execution using the final block of the inner builder.
8065 current_block_ = inner_graph_builder.current_block_;
8066
8067 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8068 std::cout << "== Finished inlining " << shared.object() << std::endl;
8069 }
8070 return result;
8071}
8072
8073namespace {
8074
8075bool CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
8076 const PossibleMaps& maps,
8077 ElementsKind* kind_return) {
8078 DCHECK_NE(0, maps.size());
8079 *kind_return = maps.at(0).elements_kind();
8080 for (compiler::MapRef map : maps) {
8081 if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker) ||
8082 !UnionElementsKindUptoSize(kind_return, map.elements_kind())) {
8083 return false;
8084 }
8085 }
8086 return true;
8087}
8088
8089} // namespace
8090
8091MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayIsArray(
8092 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8093 if (args.count() == 0) return GetBooleanConstant(false);
8094
8095 ValueNode* node = args[0];
8096
8097 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kJSArray)) {
8098 return GetBooleanConstant(true);
8099 }
8100
8101 auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
8102 if (node_info && node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8103 bool has_array_map = false;
8104 bool has_proxy_map = false;
8105 bool has_other_map = false;
8106 for (compiler::MapRef map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
8107 InstanceType type = map.instance_type();
8108 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSArray(type)) {
8109 has_array_map = true;
8110 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSProxy(type)) {
8111 has_proxy_map = true;
8112 } else {
8113 has_other_map = true;
8114 }
8115 }
8116 if ((has_array_map ^ has_other_map) && !has_proxy_map) {
8117 if (has_array_map) node_info->CombineType(NodeType::kJSArray);
8118 return GetBooleanConstant(has_array_map);
8119 }
8120 }
8121
8122 // TODO(verwaest): Add a node that checks the instance type.
8123 return {};
8124}
8125
8126MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayForEach(
8127 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8128 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8129
8130 ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
8131 if (!receiver) return {};
8132
8133 if (args.count() < 1) {
8134 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8135 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - not enough "
8136 "arguments"
8137 << std::endl;
8138 }
8139 return {};
8140 }
8141
8142 auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
8143 if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8144 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8145 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - receiver "
8146 "map is unknown"
8147 << std::endl;
8148 }
8149 return {};
8150 }
8151
8152 ElementsKind elements_kind;
8153 if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), node_info->possible_maps(),
8154 &elements_kind)) {
8155 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8156 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - doesn't "
8157 "support fast array iteration or incompatible maps"
8158 << std::endl;
8159 }
8160 return {};
8161 }
8162
8163 // TODO(leszeks): May only be needed for holey elements kinds.
8164 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
8165 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8166 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - invalidated "
8167 "no elements protector"
8168 << std::endl;
8169 }
8170 return {};
8171 }
8172
8173 ValueNode* callback = args[0];
8174 if (!callback->is_tagged()) {
8175 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8176 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.forEach - callback is "
8177 "untagged value"
8178 << std::endl;
8179 }
8180 return {};
8181 }
8182
8183 ValueNode* this_arg =
8184 args.count() > 1 ? args[1] : GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8185
8186 ValueNode* original_length = BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver);
8187
8188 // Elide the callable check if the node is known callable.
8189 EnsureType(callback, NodeType::kCallable, [&](NodeType old_type) {
8190 // ThrowIfNotCallable is wrapped in a lazy_deopt_scope to make sure the
8191 // exception has the right call stack.
8192 DeoptFrameScope lazy_deopt_scope(
8193 this, Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
8194 base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, callback, this_arg,
8195 GetSmiConstant(0), original_length}));
8196 AddNewNode<ThrowIfNotCallable>({callback});
8197 });
8198
8199 ValueNode* original_length_int32 = GetInt32(original_length);
8200
8201 // Remember the receiver map set before entering the loop the call.
8202 bool receiver_maps_were_unstable = node_info->possible_maps_are_unstable();
8203 PossibleMaps receiver_maps_before_loop(node_info->possible_maps());
8204
8205 // Create a sub graph builder with two variable (index and length)
8206 MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_builder(this, 2);
8207 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_index(0);
8208 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_length(1);
8209
8210 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label loop_end(&sub_builder, 1);
8211
8212 // ```
8213 // index = 0
8214 // bind loop_header
8215 // ```
8216 sub_builder.set(var_index, GetSmiConstant(0));
8217 sub_builder.set(var_length, original_length);
8218 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::LoopLabel loop_header =
8219 sub_builder.BeginLoop({&var_index, &var_length});
8220
8221 // Reset known state that is cleared by BeginLoop, but is known to be true on
8222 // the first iteration, and will be re-checked at the end of the loop.
8223
8224 // Reset the known receiver maps if necessary.
8225 if (receiver_maps_were_unstable) {
8226 node_info->SetPossibleMaps(receiver_maps_before_loop,
8227 receiver_maps_were_unstable,
8228 // Node type is monotonic, no need to reset it.
8229 NodeType::kUnknown, broker());
8230 known_node_aspects().any_map_for_any_node_is_unstable = true;
8231 } else {
8232 DCHECK_EQ(node_info->possible_maps().size(),
8233 receiver_maps_before_loop.size());
8234 }
8235 // Reset the cached loaded array length to the length var.
8236 RecordKnownProperty(receiver, broker()->length_string(),
8237 sub_builder.get(var_length), false,
8238 compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
8239
8240 // ```
8241 // if (index_int32 < length_int32)
8242 // fallthrough
8243 // else
8244 // goto end
8245 // ```
8246 Phi* index_tagged = sub_builder.get(var_index)->Cast<Phi>();
8247 EnsureType(index_tagged, NodeType::kSmi);
8248 ValueNode* index_int32 = GetInt32(index_tagged);
8249
8250 sub_builder.GotoIfFalse<BranchIfInt32Compare>(
8251 &loop_end, {index_int32, original_length_int32}, Operation::kLessThan);
8252
8253 // ```
8254 // next_index = index + 1
8255 // ```
8256 ValueNode* next_index_int32 = nullptr;
8257 {
8258 // Eager deopt scope for index increment overflow.
8259 // TODO(pthier): In practice this increment can never overflow, as the max
8260 // possible array length is less than int32 max value. Add a new
8261 // Int32Increment that asserts no overflow instead of deopting.
8262 DeoptFrameScope eager_deopt_scope(
8263 this, Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopEagerDeoptContinuation, target,
8264 base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>(
8265 {receiver, callback, this_arg, index_int32, original_length}));
8266 next_index_int32 = AddNewNode<Int32IncrementWithOverflow>({index_int32});
8267 EnsureType(next_index_int32, NodeType::kSmi);
8268 }
8269 // TODO(leszeks): Assert Smi.
8270
8271 // ```
8272 // element = array.elements[index]
8273 // ```
8274 ValueNode* elements = BuildLoadElements(receiver);
8275 ValueNode* element;
8276 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
8277 element = BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(elements, index_int32);
8278 } else {
8279 element = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(elements, index_int32);
8280 }
8281
8282 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> skip_call;
8283 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
8284 // ```
8285 // if (element is hole) goto skip_call
8286 // ```
8287 skip_call.emplace(
8288 &sub_builder, 2,
8289 std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{&var_length});
8290 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
8291 sub_builder.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfFloat64IsHole>(&*skip_call, {element});
8292 } else {
8293 sub_builder.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfRootConstant>(&*skip_call, {element},
8294 RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
8295 }
8296 }
8297
8298 // ```
8299 // callback(this_arg, element, array)
8300 // ```
8301 MaybeReduceResult result;
8302 {
8303 DeoptFrameScope lazy_deopt_scope(
8304 this, Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
8305 base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>(
8306 {receiver, callback, this_arg, next_index_int32, original_length}));
8307
8308 CallArguments call_args =
8309 args.count() < 2
8310 ? CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined,
8311 {element, index_tagged, receiver})
8312 : CallArguments(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
8313 {this_arg, element, index_tagged, receiver});
8314
8315 SaveCallSpeculationScope saved(this);
8316 result = ReduceCall(callback, call_args, saved.value());
8317 }
8318
8319 // ```
8320 // index = next_index
8321 // jump loop_header
8322 // ```
8323 DCHECK_IMPLIES(result.IsDoneWithAbort(), current_block_ == nullptr);
8324
8325 // No need to finish the loop if this code is unreachable.
8326 if (!result.IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8327 // If any of the receiver's maps were unstable maps, we have to re-check the
8328 // maps on each iteration, in case the callback changed them. That said, we
8329 // know that the maps are valid on the first iteration, so we can rotate the
8330 // check to _after_ the callback, and then elide it if the receiver maps are
8331 // still known to be valid (i.e. the known maps after the call are contained
8332 // inside the known maps before the call).
8333 bool recheck_maps_after_call = receiver_maps_were_unstable;
8334 if (recheck_maps_after_call) {
8335 // No need to recheck maps if there are known maps...
8336 if (auto receiver_info_after_call =
8337 known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver)) {
8338 // ... and those known maps are equal to, or a subset of, the maps
8339 // before the call.
8340 if (receiver_info_after_call &&
8341 receiver_info_after_call->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8342 recheck_maps_after_call = !receiver_maps_before_loop.contains(
8343 receiver_info_after_call->possible_maps());
8344 }
8345 }
8346 }
8347
8348 // Make sure to finish the loop if we eager deopt in the map check or index
8349 // check.
8350 DeoptFrameScope eager_deopt_scope(
8351 this, Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopEagerDeoptContinuation, target,
8352 base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>(
8353 {receiver, callback, this_arg, next_index_int32, original_length}));
8354
8355 if (recheck_maps_after_call) {
8356 // Build the CheckMap manually, since we're doing it with already known
8357 // maps rather than feedback, and we don't need to update known node
8358 // aspects or types since we're at the end of the loop anyway.
8359 bool emit_check_with_migration = std::any_of(
8360 receiver_maps_before_loop.begin(), receiver_maps_before_loop.end(),
8361 [](compiler::MapRef map) { return map.is_migration_target(); });
8362 if (emit_check_with_migration) {
8363 AddNewNode<CheckMapsWithMigration>({receiver},
8364 receiver_maps_before_loop,
8365 CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck);
8366 } else {
8367 AddNewNode<CheckMaps>({receiver}, receiver_maps_before_loop,
8368 CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck);
8369 }
8370 }
8371
8372 // Check if the index is still in bounds, in case the callback changed the
8373 // length.
8374 ValueNode* current_length = BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver);
8375 sub_builder.set(var_length, current_length);
8376
8377 // Reference compare the loaded length against the original length. If this
8378 // is the same value node, then we didn't have any side effects and didn't
8379 // clear the cached length.
8380 if (current_length != original_length) {
8381 RETURN_IF_ABORT(
8382 TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(original_length_int32, current_length,
8383 AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual,
8384 DeoptimizeReason::kArrayLengthChanged));
8385 }
8386 }
8387
8388 if (skip_call.has_value()) {
8389 sub_builder.GotoOrTrim(&*skip_call);
8390 sub_builder.Bind(&*skip_call);
8391 }
8392
8393 sub_builder.set(var_index, next_index_int32);
8394 sub_builder.EndLoop(&loop_header);
8395
8396 // ```
8397 // bind end
8398 // ```
8399 sub_builder.Bind(&loop_end);
8400
8401 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8402}
8403
8404MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(
8405 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8406 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8407
8408 ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
8409 if (!receiver) return {};
8410
8411 if (!receiver->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) return {};
8412 VirtualObject* iterator = receiver->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->object();
8413 if (!iterator->map().IsJSArrayIteratorMap()) {
8414 FAIL("iterator is not a JS array iterator object");
8415 }
8416
8417 ValueNode* iterated_object =
8418 iterator->get(JSArrayIterator::kIteratedObjectOffset);
8419 ElementsKind elements_kind;
8420 base::SmallVector<compiler::MapRef, 4> maps;
8421 if (iterated_object->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) {
8422 VirtualObject* array = iterated_object->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->object();
8423 // TODO(victorgomes): Remove this once we track changes in the inlined
8424 // allocated object.
8425 if (iterated_object->Cast<InlinedAllocation>()->IsEscaping()) {
8426 FAIL("allocation is escaping, map could have been changed");
8427 }
8428 // TODO(victorgomes): This effectively disable the optimization for `for-of`
8429 // loops. We need to figure it out a way to re-enable this.
8430 if (IsInsideLoop()) {
8431 FAIL("we're inside a loop, iterated object map could change");
8432 }
8433 auto map = array->map();
8434 if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
8435 FAIL("no fast array iteration support");
8436 }
8437 elements_kind = map.elements_kind();
8438 maps.push_back(map);
8439 } else {
8440 auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(iterated_object);
8441 if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8442 FAIL("iterated object is unknown");
8443 }
8444 if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), node_info->possible_maps(),
8445 &elements_kind)) {
8446 FAIL("no fast array iteration support or incompatible maps");
8447 }
8448 for (auto map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
8449 maps.push_back(map);
8450 }
8451 }
8452
8453 // TODO(victorgomes): Support typed arrays.
8454 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
8455 FAIL("no typed arrays support");
8456 }
8457
8458 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
8459 !broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
8460 FAIL("no elements protector");
8461 }
8462
8463 // Load the [[NextIndex]] from the {iterator}.
8464 // We can assume index and length fit in Uint32.
8465 ValueNode* index =
8466 BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset);
8467 ValueNode* uint32_index;
8468 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(uint32_index, GetUint32ElementIndex(index));
8469 ValueNode* uint32_length;
8470 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(uint32_length,
8471 GetUint32ElementIndex(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(
8472 iterated_object, IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind)
8473 ? NodeType::kSmi
8474 : NodeType::kNumber)));
8475
8476 // Check next index is below length
8477 MaglevSubGraphBuilder subgraph(this, 2);
8478 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable is_done(0);
8479 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable ret_value(1);
8480 RETURN_IF_ABORT(subgraph.Branch(
8481 {&is_done, &ret_value},
8482 [&](auto& builder) {
8483 return BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(builder, Operation::kLessThan,
8484 uint32_index, uint32_length);
8485 },
8486 [&] {
8487 ValueNode* int32_index = GetInt32(uint32_index);
8488 subgraph.set(is_done, GetBooleanConstant(false));
8489 DCHECK(
8490 iterator->get(JSArrayIterator::kKindOffset)->Is<Int32Constant>());
8491 IterationKind iteration_kind = static_cast<IterationKind>(
8492 iterator->get(JSArrayIterator::kKindOffset)
8493 ->Cast<Int32Constant>()
8494 ->value());
8495 if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kKeys) {
8496 subgraph.set(ret_value, index);
8497 } else {
8498 ValueNode* value;
8499 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
8500 value,
8501 TryBuildElementLoadOnJSArrayOrJSObject(
8502 iterated_object, int32_index, base::VectorOf(maps),
8503 elements_kind, KeyedAccessLoadMode::kHandleOOBAndHoles));
8504 if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries) {
8505 ValueNode* key_value_array;
8506 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(key_value_array,
8507 BuildAndAllocateKeyValueArray(index, value));
8508 subgraph.set(ret_value, key_value_array);
8509 } else {
8510 subgraph.set(ret_value, value);
8511 }
8512 }
8513 // Add 1 to index
8514 ValueNode* next_index = AddNewNode<Int32AddWithOverflow>(
8515 {int32_index, GetInt32Constant(1)});
8516 EnsureType(next_index, NodeType::kSmi);
8517 // Update [[NextIndex]]
8518 BuildStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(receiver, next_index,
8519 JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset,
8520 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
8521 return ReduceResult::Done();
8522 },
8523 [&] {
8524 // Index is greater or equal than length.
8525 subgraph.set(is_done, GetBooleanConstant(true));
8526 subgraph.set(ret_value, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
8527 if (!IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
8528 // Mark the {iterator} as exhausted by setting the [[NextIndex]] to a
8529 // value that will never pass the length check again (aka the maximum
8530 // value possible for the specific iterated object). Note that this is
8531 // different from what the specification says, which is changing the
8532 // [[IteratedObject]] field to undefined, but that makes it difficult
8533 // to eliminate the map checks and "length" accesses in for..of loops.
8534 //
8535 // This is not necessary for JSTypedArray's, since the length of those
8536 // cannot change later and so if we were ever out of bounds for them
8537 // we will stay out-of-bounds forever.
8538 BuildStoreTaggedField(receiver, GetFloat64Constant(kMaxUInt32),
8539 JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset,
8540 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
8541 }
8542 return ReduceResult::Done();
8543 }));
8544
8545 // Allocate result object and return.
8546 compiler::MapRef map =
8547 broker()->target_native_context().iterator_result_map(broker());
8548 VirtualObject* iter_result = CreateJSIteratorResult(
8549 map, subgraph.get(ret_value), subgraph.get(is_done));
8550 ValueNode* allocation =
8551 BuildInlinedAllocation(iter_result, AllocationType::kYoung);
8552 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
8553 // next side effect clear it.
8554 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
8555 return allocation;
8556}

8597MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeCharCodeAt(
8598 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8599 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8600 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8601 ValueNode* index;
8602 if (args.count() == 0) {
8603 // Index is the undefined object. ToIntegerOrInfinity(undefined) = 0.
8604 index = GetInt32Constant(0);
8605 } else {
8606 index = GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]);
8607 }
8608 // Any other argument is ignored.
8609
8610 // Try to constant-fold if receiver and index are constant
8611 if (auto cst = TryGetConstant(receiver)) {
8612 if (cst->IsString() && index->Is<Int32Constant>()) {
8613 compiler::StringRef str = cst->AsString();
8614 int idx = index->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value();
8615 if (idx >= 0 && static_cast<uint32_t>(idx) < str.length()) {
8616 if (std::optional<uint16_t> value = str.GetChar(broker(), idx)) {
8617 return GetSmiConstant(*value);
8618 }
8619 }
8620 }
8621 }
8622
8623 // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
8624 BuildCheckString(receiver);
8625 // And index is below length.
8626 ValueNode* length = BuildLoadStringLength(receiver);
8627 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
8628 index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
8629 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
8630 return AddNewNode<BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt>(
8631 {receiver, index},
8632 BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::kCharCodeAt);
8633}
8634
8635MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeCodePointAt(
8636 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8637 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8638 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8639 ValueNode* index;
8640 if (args.count() == 0) {
8641 // Index is the undefined object. ToIntegerOrInfinity(undefined) = 0.
8642 index = GetInt32Constant(0);
8643 } else {
8644 index = GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]);
8645 }
8646 // Any other argument is ignored.
8647 // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
8648 BuildCheckString(receiver);
8649 // And index is below length.
8650 ValueNode* length = BuildLoadStringLength(receiver);
8651 RETURN_IF_ABORT(TryBuildCheckInt32Condition(
8652 index, length, AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan,
8653 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds));
8654 return AddNewNode<BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt>(
8655 {receiver, index},
8656 BuiltinStringPrototypeCharCodeOrCodePointAt::kCodePointAt);
8657}

8659MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeIterator(
8660 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8661 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8662 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8663 // Ensure that {receiver} is actually a String.
8664 BuildCheckString(receiver);
8665 compiler::MapRef map =
8666 broker()->target_native_context().initial_string_iterator_map(broker());
8667 VirtualObject* string_iterator = CreateJSStringIterator(map, receiver);
8668 ValueNode* allocation =
8669 BuildInlinedAllocation(string_iterator, AllocationType::kYoung);
8670 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
8671 // next side effect clear it.
8672 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
8673 return allocation;
8674}

8677
8678MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringPrototypeLocaleCompareIntl(
8679 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8680 if (args.count() < 1 || args.count() > 3) return {};
8681
8682 LocalFactory* factory = local_isolate()->factory();
8683 compiler::ObjectRef undefined_ref = broker()->undefined_value();
8684
8685 DirectHandle<Object> locales_handle;
8686 ValueNode* locales_node = nullptr;
8687 if (args.count() > 1) {
8688 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_locales = TryGetConstant(args[1]);
8689 if (!maybe_locales) return {};
8690 compiler::HeapObjectRef locales = maybe_locales.value();
8691 if (locales.equals(undefined_ref)) {
8692 locales_handle = factory->undefined_value();
8693 locales_node = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8694 } else {
8695 if (!locales.IsString()) return {};
8696 compiler::StringRef sref = locales.AsString();
8697 std::optional<Handle<String>> maybe_locales_handle =
8698 sref.ObjectIfContentAccessible(broker());
8699 if (!maybe_locales_handle) return {};
8700 locales_handle = *maybe_locales_handle;
8701 locales_node = args[1];
8702 }
8703 } else {
8704 locales_handle = factory->undefined_value();
8705 locales_node = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8706 }
8707
8708 if (args.count() > 2) {
8709 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_options = TryGetConstant(args[2]);
8710 if (!maybe_options) return {};
8711 if (!maybe_options.value().equals(undefined_ref)) return {};
8712 }
8713
8714 DCHECK(!locales_handle.is_null());
8715 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(locales_node);
8716
8717 if (Intl::CompareStringsOptionsFor(local_isolate(), locales_handle,
8718 factory->undefined_value()) !=
8719 Intl::CompareStringsOptions::kTryFastPath) {
8720 return {};
8721 }
8722 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kStringFastLocaleCompare>(
8723 {GetConstant(target),
8724 GetTaggedValue(GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver())),
8725 GetTaggedValue(args[0]), GetTaggedValue(locales_node)});
8726}
8727
8728#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT

8747template <typename LoadNode>
8748MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildLoadDataView(
8749 const CallArguments& args, ExternalArrayType type) {
8750 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8751 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
8752 // TODO(victorgomes): Add checks whether the array has been detached.
8753 return {};
8754 }
8755 // TODO(victorgomes): Add data view to known types.
8756 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8757 AddNewNode<CheckInstanceType>({receiver}, CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
8758 JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE, JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
8759 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
8760 ValueNode* offset =
8761 args[0] ? GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]) : GetInt32Constant(0);
8762 AddNewNode<CheckJSDataViewBounds>({receiver, offset}, type);
8763 ValueNode* is_little_endian = args[1] ? args[1] : GetBooleanConstant(false);
8764 return AddNewNode<LoadNode>({receiver, offset, is_little_endian}, type);
8765}
8766
8767template <typename StoreNode, typename Function>
8768MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildStoreDataView(
8769 const CallArguments& args, ExternalArrayType type, Function&& getValue) {
8770 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8771 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
8772 // TODO(victorgomes): Add checks whether the array has been detached.
8773 return {};
8774 }
8775 // TODO(victorgomes): Add data view to known types.
8776 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8777 AddNewNode<CheckInstanceType>({receiver}, CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
8778 JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE, JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
8779 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
8780 ValueNode* offset =
8781 args[0] ? GetInt32ElementIndex(args[0]) : GetInt32Constant(0);
8782 AddNewNode<CheckJSDataViewBounds>({receiver, offset},
8783 ExternalArrayType::kExternalFloat64Array);
8784 ValueNode* value = getValue(args[1]);
8785 ValueNode* is_little_endian = args[2] ? args[2] : GetBooleanConstant(false);
8786 AddNewNode<StoreNode>({receiver, offset, value, is_little_endian}, type);
8787 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8788}

8840MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(
8841 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8842 // We can't reduce Function#call when there is no receiver function.
8843 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
8844 return {};
8845 }
8846 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8847 args.PopReceiver(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
8848
8849 SaveCallSpeculationScope saved(this);
8850 return ReduceCall(receiver, args, saved.value());
8851}
8852
8853MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(
8854 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8855 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_receiver;
8856 if (current_speculation_feedback_.IsValid()) {
8857 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
8858 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(current_speculation_feedback_);
8859 DCHECK_EQ(processed_feedback.kind(), compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kCall);
8860 const compiler::CallFeedback& call_feedback = processed_feedback.AsCall();
8861 if (call_feedback.call_feedback_content() ==
8862 CallFeedbackContent::kReceiver) {
8863 maybe_receiver = call_feedback.target();
8864 }
8865 }
8866 return TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApplyCallWithReceiver(
8867 maybe_receiver, args, current_speculation_feedback_);
8868}
8869
8870namespace {
8871
8872template <size_t MaxKindCount, typename KindsToIndexFunc>
8873bool CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(
8874 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker, const PossibleMaps& possible_maps,
8875 std::array<SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>, MaxKindCount>& map_kinds,
8876 KindsToIndexFunc&& elements_kind_to_index, int* unique_kind_count,
8877 bool is_loading) {
8878 uint8_t kind_bitmap = 0;
8879 for (compiler::MapRef map : possible_maps) {
8880 if (!map.supports_fast_array_resize(broker)) {
8881 return false;
8882 }
8883 ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
8884 if (is_loading && kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
8885 return false;
8886 }
8887 // Group maps by elements kind, using the provided function to translate
8888 // elements kinds to indices.
8889 // kind_bitmap is used to get the unique kinds (predecessor count for the
8890 // next block).
8891 uint8_t kind_index = elements_kind_to_index(kind);
8892 kind_bitmap |= 1 << kind_index;
8893 map_kinds[kind_index].push_back(map);
8894 }
8895
8896 *unique_kind_count = base::bits::CountPopulation(kind_bitmap);
8897 DCHECK_GE(*unique_kind_count, 1);
8898 return true;
8899}
8900
8901} // namespace
8902
8903template <typename MapKindsT, typename IndexToElementsKindFunc,
8904 typename BuildKindSpecificFunc>
8905MaybeReduceResult
8906MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildJSArrayBuiltinMapSwitchOnElementsKind(
8907 ValueNode* receiver, const MapKindsT& map_kinds,
8908 MaglevSubGraphBuilder& sub_graph,
8909 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label>& do_return,
8910 int unique_kind_count, IndexToElementsKindFunc&& index_to_elements_kind,
8911 BuildKindSpecificFunc&& build_kind_specific) {
8912 // TODO(pthier): Support map packing.
8913 DCHECK(!V8_MAP_PACKING_BOOL);
8914 ValueNode* receiver_map =
8915 BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
8916 int emitted_kind_checks = 0;
8917 bool any_successful = false;
8918 for (size_t kind_index = 0; kind_index < map_kinds.size(); kind_index++) {
8919 const auto& maps = map_kinds[kind_index];
8920 // Skip kinds we haven't observed.
8921 if (maps.empty()) continue;
8922 ElementsKind kind = index_to_elements_kind(kind_index);
8923 // Create branches for all but the last elements kind. We don't need
8924 // to check the maps of the last kind, as all possible maps have already
8925 // been checked when the property (builtin name) was loaded.
8926 if (++emitted_kind_checks < unique_kind_count) {
8927 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label check_next_map(&sub_graph, 1);
8928 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> do_push;
8929 if (maps.size() > 1) {
8930 do_push.emplace(&sub_graph, static_cast<int>(maps.size()));
8931 for (size_t map_index = 1; map_index < maps.size(); map_index++) {
8932 sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
8933 &*do_push, {receiver_map, GetConstant(maps[map_index])});
8934 }
8935 }
8936 sub_graph.GotoIfFalse<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
8937 &check_next_map, {receiver_map, GetConstant(maps[0])});
8938 if (do_push.has_value()) {
8939 sub_graph.Goto(&*do_push);
8940 sub_graph.Bind(&*do_push);
8941 }
8942 if (!build_kind_specific(kind).IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8943 any_successful = true;
8944 }
8945 DCHECK(do_return.has_value());
8946 sub_graph.GotoOrTrim(&*do_return);
8947 sub_graph.Bind(&check_next_map);
8948 } else {
8949 if (!build_kind_specific(kind).IsDoneWithAbort()) {
8950 any_successful = true;
8951 }
8952 if (do_return.has_value()) {
8953 sub_graph.GotoOrTrim(&*do_return);
8954 }
8955 }
8956 }
8957 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!any_successful, !current_block_);
8958 return any_successful ? ReduceResult::Done() : ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
8959}
8960
8961MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayPrototypePush(
8962 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
8963 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
8964 // We can't reduce Function#call when there is no receiver function.
8965 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
8966 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8967 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - no receiver"
8968 << std::endl;
8969 }
8970 return {};
8971 }
8972 // TODO(pthier): Support multiple arguments.
8973 if (args.count() != 1) {
8974 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8975 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - invalid "
8976 "argument count"
8977 << std::endl;
8978 }
8979 return {};
8980 }
8981 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
8982
8983 auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
8984 // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
8985 // the receiver, so bail.
8986 if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
8987 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
8988 std::cout
8989 << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - unknown receiver map"
8990 << std::endl;
8991 }
8992 return {};
8993 }
8994
8995 const PossibleMaps& possible_maps = node_info->possible_maps();
8996 // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
8997 // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
8998 // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
8999 // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
9000 // unconditionally deopt.
9001 if (possible_maps.is_empty()) {
9002 // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
9003 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
9004 }
9005
9006 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
9007 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9008 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - "
9009 "NoElementsProtector invalidated"
9010 << std::endl;
9011 }
9012 return {};
9013 }
9014
9015 // Check that inlining resizing array builtins is supported and group maps
9016 // by elements kind.
9017 std::array<SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>, 3> map_kinds = {
9018 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
9019 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
9020 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone())};
9021 // Function to group maps by elements kind, ignoring packedness. Packedness
9022 // doesn't matter for push().
9023 // Kinds we care about are all paired in the first 6 values of ElementsKind,
9024 // so we can use integer division to truncate holeyness.
9025 auto elements_kind_to_index = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
9026 static_assert(kFastElementsKindCount <= 6);
9027 static_assert(kFastElementsKindPackedToHoley == 1);
9028 return static_cast<uint8_t>(kind) / 2;
9029 };
9030 auto index_to_elements_kind = [&](uint8_t kind_index) {
9031 return static_cast<ElementsKind>(kind_index * 2);
9032 };
9033 int unique_kind_count;
9034 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), possible_maps, map_kinds,
9035 elements_kind_to_index, &unique_kind_count,
9036 false)) {
9037 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9038 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.push - Map doesn't "
9039 "support fast resizing"
9040 << std::endl;
9041 }
9042 return {};
9043 }
9044
9045 MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, 0);
9046
9047 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> do_return;
9048 if (unique_kind_count > 1) {
9049 do_return.emplace(&sub_graph, unique_kind_count);
9050 }
9051
9052 ValueNode* old_array_length_smi;
9053 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(old_array_length_smi,
9054 GetSmiValue(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver)));
9055 ValueNode* old_array_length =
9056 AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({old_array_length_smi});
9057 ValueNode* new_array_length_smi =
9058 AddNewNode<CheckedSmiIncrement>({old_array_length_smi});
9059
9060 ValueNode* elements_array = BuildLoadElements(receiver);
9061 ValueNode* elements_array_length = BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(elements_array);
9062
9063 auto build_array_push = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
9064 ValueNode* value;
9065 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(value, ConvertForStoring(args[0], kind));
9066
9067 ValueNode* writable_elements_array = AddNewNode<MaybeGrowFastElements>(
9068 {elements_array, receiver, old_array_length, elements_array_length},
9069 kind);
9070
9071 AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>({receiver, new_array_length_smi},
9072 JSArray::kLengthOffset,
9073 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
9074
9075 // Do the store
9076 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
9077 BuildStoreFixedDoubleArrayElement(writable_elements_array,
9078 old_array_length, value);
9079 } else {
9080 DCHECK(IsSmiElementsKind(kind) || IsObjectElementsKind(kind));
9081 BuildStoreFixedArrayElement(writable_elements_array, old_array_length,
9082 value);
9083 }
9084 return ReduceResult::Done();
9085 };
9086
9087 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildJSArrayBuiltinMapSwitchOnElementsKind(
9088 receiver, map_kinds, sub_graph, do_return, unique_kind_count,
9089 index_to_elements_kind, build_array_push));
9090
9091 if (do_return.has_value()) {
9092 sub_graph.Bind(&*do_return);
9093 }
9094 RecordKnownProperty(receiver, broker()->length_string(), new_array_length_smi,
9095 false, compiler::AccessMode::kStore);
9096 return new_array_length_smi;
9097}
9098
9099MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayPrototypePop(
9100 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9101 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9102 // We can't reduce Function#call when there is no receiver function.
9103 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
9104 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9105 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - no receiver"
9106 << std::endl;
9107 }
9108 return {};
9109 }
9110
9111 ValueNode* receiver = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
9112
9113 auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
9114 // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
9115 // the receiver, so bail.
9116 if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
9117 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9118 std::cout
9119 << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - unknown receiver map"
9120 << std::endl;
9121 }
9122 return {};
9123 }
9124
9125 const PossibleMaps& possible_maps = node_info->possible_maps();
9126
9127 // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
9128 // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
9129 // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
9130 // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
9131 // unconditionally deopt.
9132 if (possible_maps.is_empty()) {
9133 // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
9134 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
9135 }
9136
9137 if (!broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
9138 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9139 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - "
9140 "NoElementsProtector invalidated"
9141 << std::endl;
9142 }
9143 return {};
9144 }
9145
9146 constexpr int max_kind_count = 4;
9147 std::array<SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>, max_kind_count> map_kinds = {
9148 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
9149 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
9150 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone()),
9151 SmallZoneVector<compiler::MapRef, 2>(zone())};
9152 // Smi and Object elements kinds are treated as identical for pop, so we can
9153 // group them together without differentiation.
9154 // ElementsKind is mapped to an index in the 4 element array using:
9155 // - Bit 2 (Only set for double in the fast element range) is mapped to bit
9156 // 1)
9157 // - Bit 0 (packedness)
9158 // The complete mapping:
9159 // +-------+----------------------------------------------+
9160 // | Index | ElementsKinds |
9161 // +-------+----------------------------------------------+
9162 // | 0 | PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS and PACKED_ELEMENTS |
9163 // | 1 | HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENETS and HOLEY_ELEMENTS |
9164 // | 2 | PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS |
9165 // | 3 | HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS |
9166 // +-------+----------------------------------------------+
9167 auto elements_kind_to_index = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
9168 uint8_t kind_int = static_cast<uint8_t>(kind);
9169 uint8_t kind_index = ((kind_int & 0x4) >> 1) | (kind_int & 0x1);
9170 DCHECK_LT(kind_index, max_kind_count);
9171 return kind_index;
9172 };
9173 auto index_to_elements_kind = [&](uint8_t kind_index) {
9174 uint8_t kind_int;
9175 kind_int = ((kind_index & 0x2) << 1) | (kind_index & 0x1);
9176 return static_cast<ElementsKind>(kind_int);
9177 };
9178
9179 int unique_kind_count;
9180 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), possible_maps, map_kinds,
9181 elements_kind_to_index, &unique_kind_count,
9182 true)) {
9183 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9184 std::cout << " ! Failed to reduce Array.prototype.pop - Map doesn't "
9185 "support fast resizing"
9186 << std::endl;
9187 }
9188 return {};
9189 }
9190
9191 MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, 2);
9192 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_value(0);
9193 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_new_array_length(1);
9194
9195 std::optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label> do_return =
9196 std::make_optional<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label>(
9197 &sub_graph, unique_kind_count + 1,
9198 std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{
9199 &var_value, &var_new_array_length});
9200 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label empty_array(&sub_graph, 1);
9201
9202 ValueNode* old_array_length_smi;
9203 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(old_array_length_smi,
9204 GetSmiValue(BuildLoadJSArrayLength(receiver)));
9205
9206 // If the array is empty, skip the pop and return undefined.
9207 sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(
9208 &empty_array, {old_array_length_smi, GetSmiConstant(0)});
9209
9210 ValueNode* elements_array = BuildLoadElements(receiver);
9211 ValueNode* new_array_length_smi =
9212 AddNewNode<CheckedSmiDecrement>({old_array_length_smi});
9213 ValueNode* new_array_length =
9214 AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({new_array_length_smi});
9215 sub_graph.set(var_new_array_length, new_array_length_smi);
9216
9217 auto build_array_pop = [&](ElementsKind kind) {
9218 // Handle COW if needed.
9219 ValueNode* writable_elements_array =
9220 IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)
9221 ? AddNewNode<EnsureWritableFastElements>({elements_array, receiver})
9222 : elements_array;
9223
9224 // Store new length.
9225 AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>({receiver, new_array_length_smi},
9226 JSArray::kLengthOffset,
9227 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
9228
9229 // Load the value and store the hole in it's place.
9230 ValueNode* value;
9231 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
9232 value = BuildLoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(writable_elements_array,
9233 new_array_length);
9234 BuildStoreFixedDoubleArrayElement(
9235 writable_elements_array, new_array_length,
9236 GetFloat64Constant(Float64::FromBits(kHoleNanInt64)));
9237 } else {
9238 DCHECK(IsSmiElementsKind(kind) || IsObjectElementsKind(kind));
9239 value =
9240 BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(writable_elements_array, new_array_length);
9241 BuildStoreFixedArrayElement(writable_elements_array, new_array_length,
9242 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue));
9243 }
9244
9245 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
9246 value = AddNewNode<ConvertHoleToUndefined>({value});
9247 }
9248 sub_graph.set(var_value, value);
9249 return ReduceResult::Done();
9250 };
9251
9252 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildJSArrayBuiltinMapSwitchOnElementsKind(
9253 receiver, map_kinds, sub_graph, do_return, unique_kind_count,
9254 index_to_elements_kind, build_array_pop));
9255
9256 sub_graph.Bind(&empty_array);
9257 sub_graph.set(var_new_array_length, GetSmiConstant(0));
9258 sub_graph.set(var_value, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
9259 sub_graph.Goto(&*do_return);
9260
9261 sub_graph.Bind(&*do_return);
9262 RecordKnownProperty(receiver, broker()->length_string(),
9263 sub_graph.get(var_new_array_length), false,
9264 compiler::AccessMode::kStore);
9265 return sub_graph.get(var_value);
9266}
9267
9268MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(
9269 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9270 // We can't reduce Function#hasInstance when there is no receiver function.
9271 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
9272 return {};
9273 }
9274 if (args.count() != 1) {
9275 return {};
9276 }
9277 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_receiver_constant =
9278 TryGetConstant(args.receiver());
9279 if (!maybe_receiver_constant) {
9280 return {};
9281 }
9282 compiler::HeapObjectRef receiver_object = maybe_receiver_constant.value();
9283 if (!receiver_object.IsJSObject() ||
9284 !receiver_object.map(broker()).is_callable()) {
9285 return {};
9286 }
9287 return BuildOrdinaryHasInstance(args[0], receiver_object.AsJSObject(),
9288 nullptr);
9289}
9290
9291MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(
9292 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9293 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9294 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
9295 return {};
9296 }
9297
9298 // We can constant-fold the {receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)} builtin call to
9299 // the {True} node in this case:
9300
9301 // for (name in receiver) {
9302 // if (receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
9303 // ...
9304 // }
9305 // }
9306
9307 if (args.count() != 1 || args[0] != current_for_in_state.key) {
9308 return {};
9309 }
9310 ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
9311 if (receiver == current_for_in_state.receiver) {
9312 if (current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check) {
9313 auto* receiver_map =
9314 BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
9315 AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>(
9316 {receiver_map, current_for_in_state.cache_type});
9317 current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check = false;
9318 }
9319 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTrueValue);
9320 }
9321
9322 // We can also optimize for this case below:
9323
9324 // receiver(is a heap constant with fast map)
9325 // ^
9326 // | object(all keys are enumerable)
9327 // | ^
9328 // | |
9329 // | JSForInNext
9330 // | ^
9331 // +----+ |
9332 // | |
9333 // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
9334
9335 // We can replace the {JSCall} with several internalized string
9336 // comparisons.
9337
9338 compiler::OptionalMapRef maybe_receiver_map;
9339 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef receiver_ref = TryGetConstant(receiver);
9340 if (receiver_ref.has_value()) {
9341 compiler::HeapObjectRef receiver_object = receiver_ref.value();
9342 compiler::MapRef receiver_map = receiver_object.map(broker());
9343 maybe_receiver_map = receiver_map;
9344 } else {
9345 NodeInfo* known_info = GetOrCreateInfoFor(receiver);
9346 if (known_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
9347 compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map> possible_maps = known_info->possible_maps();
9348 if (possible_maps.size() == 1) {
9349 compiler::MapRef receiver_map = *(possible_maps.begin());
9350 maybe_receiver_map = receiver_map;
9351 }
9352 }
9353 }
9354 if (!maybe_receiver_map.has_value()) return {};
9355
9356 compiler::MapRef receiver_map = maybe_receiver_map.value();
9357 InstanceType instance_type = receiver_map.instance_type();
9358 int const nof = receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
9359 // We set a heuristic value to limit the compare instructions number.
9360 if (nof > 4 || IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(instance_type) ||
9361 receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) {
9362 return {};
9363 }
9364 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(receiver, base::VectorOf({receiver_map})));
9365 // Replace builtin call with several internalized string comparisons.
9366 MaglevSubGraphBuilder sub_graph(this, 1);
9367 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable var_result(0);
9368 MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Label done(
9369 &sub_graph, nof + 1,
9370 std::initializer_list<MaglevSubGraphBuilder::Variable*>{&var_result});
9371 const compiler::DescriptorArrayRef descriptor_array =
9372 receiver_map.instance_descriptors(broker());
9373 for (InternalIndex key_index : InternalIndex::Range(nof)) {
9374 compiler::NameRef receiver_key =
9375 descriptor_array.GetPropertyKey(broker(), key_index);
9376 ValueNode* lhs = GetConstant(receiver_key);
9377 sub_graph.set(var_result, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTrueValue));
9378 sub_graph.GotoIfTrue<BranchIfReferenceEqual>(&done, {lhs, args[0]});
9379 }
9380 sub_graph.set(var_result, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kFalseValue));
9381 sub_graph.Goto(&done);
9382 sub_graph.Bind(&done);
9383 return sub_graph.get(var_result);
9384}
9385
9386MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceGetProto(ValueNode* object) {
9387 NodeInfo* info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(object);
9388 if (!info || !info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
9389 return {};
9390 }
9391 auto& possible_maps = info->possible_maps();
9392 if (possible_maps.is_empty()) {
9393 return ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort();
9394 }
9395 auto it = possible_maps.begin();
9396 compiler::MapRef map = *it;
9397 if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type())) {
9398 return {};
9399 }
9400 DCHECK(!map.IsPrimitiveMap() && map.IsJSReceiverMap());
9401 compiler::HeapObjectRef proto = map.prototype(broker());
9402 ++it;
9403 for (; it != possible_maps.end(); ++it) {
9404 map = *it;
9405 if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type()) ||
9406 !proto.equals(map.prototype(broker()))) {
9407 return {};
9408 }
9409 DCHECK(!map.IsPrimitiveMap() && map.IsJSReceiverMap());
9410 }
9411 return GetConstant(proto);
9412}
9413
9414MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceObjectPrototypeGetProto(
9415 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9416 if (args.count() != 0) return {};
9417 return TryReduceGetProto(args.receiver());
9418}
9419
9420MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceObjectGetPrototypeOf(
9421 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9422 if (args.count() != 1) return {};
9423 return TryReduceGetProto(args[0]);
9424}
9425
9426MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceReflectGetPrototypeOf(
9427 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9428 return TryReduceObjectGetPrototypeOf(target, args);
9429}
