9431MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathRound(
9432 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9433 return DoTryReduceMathRound(args, Float64Round::Kind::kNearest);
9434}
9435
9436MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceNumberParseInt(
9437 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9438 if (args.count() == 0) {
9439 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
9440 }
9441 if (args.count() != 1) {
9442 if (RootConstant* root_cst = args[1]->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
9443 if (root_cst->index() != RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) {
9444 return {};
9445 }
9446 } else if (SmiConstant* smi_cst = args[1]->TryCast<SmiConstant>()) {
9447 if (smi_cst->value().value() != 10 && smi_cst->value().value() != 0) {
9448 return {};
9449 }
9450 } else {
9451 return {};
9452 }
9453 }
9454
9455 ValueNode* arg = args[0];
9456
9457 switch (arg->value_representation()) {
9458 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
9459 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
9460 return arg;
9461 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
9462 switch (CheckTypes(arg, {NodeType::kSmi})) {
9463 case NodeType::kSmi:
9464 return arg;
9465 default:
9466 // TODO(verwaest): Support actually parsing strings, converting
9467 // doubles to ints, ...
9468 return {};
9469 }
9470 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
9471 UNREACHABLE();
9472 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
9473 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
9474 return {};
9475 }
9476}
9477
9478MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathAbs(
9479 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9480 if (args.count() == 0) {
9481 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
9482 }
9483 ValueNode* arg = args[0];
9484
9485 switch (arg->value_representation()) {
9486 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
9487 return arg;
9488 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
9489 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9490 return AddNewNode<Int32AbsWithOverflow>({arg});
9491 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
9492 switch (CheckTypes(arg, {NodeType::kSmi, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball})) {
9493 case NodeType::kSmi:
9494 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9495 return AddNewNode<Int32AbsWithOverflow>({arg});
9496 case NodeType::kNumberOrOddball:
9497 return AddNewNode<Float64Abs>({GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
9498 arg, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
9499 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball)});
9500 // TODO(verwaest): Add support for ToNumberOrNumeric and deopt.
9501 default:
9502 break;
9503 }
9504 break;
9505 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
9506 UNREACHABLE();
9507 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
9508 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
9509 return AddNewNode<Float64Abs>({arg});
9510 }
9511 return {};
9512}
9513
9514MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathFloor(
9515 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9516 return DoTryReduceMathRound(args, Float64Round::Kind::kFloor);
9517}
9518
9519MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathCeil(
9520 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9521 return DoTryReduceMathRound(args, Float64Round::Kind::kCeil);
9522}
9523
9524MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::DoTryReduceMathRound(
9525 CallArguments& args, Float64Round::Kind kind) {
9526 if (args.count() == 0) {
9527 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
9528 }
9529 ValueNode* arg = args[0];
9530 auto arg_repr = arg->value_representation();
9531 if (arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kInt32 ||
9532 arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kUint32) {
9533 return arg;
9534 }
9535 if (CheckType(arg, NodeType::kSmi)) return arg;
9536 if (!IsSupported(CpuOperation::kFloat64Round)) {
9537 return {};
9538 }
9539 if (arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kFloat64 ||
9540 arg_repr == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
9541 return AddNewNode<Float64Round>({arg}, kind);
9542 }
9543 DCHECK_EQ(arg_repr, ValueRepresentation::kTagged);
9544 if (CheckType(arg, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball)) {
9545 return AddNewNode<Float64Round>(
9546 {GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
9547 arg, NodeType::kNumberOrOddball,
9548 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball)},
9549 kind);
9550 }
9551 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9552 DeoptFrameScope continuation_scope(this, Float64Round::continuation(kind));
9553 ToNumberOrNumeric* conversion =
9554 AddNewNode<ToNumberOrNumeric>({arg}, Object::Conversion::kToNumber);
9555 ValueNode* float64_value = AddNewNode<UncheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64>(
9556 {conversion}, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
9557 return AddNewNode<Float64Round>({float64_value}, kind);
9558}
9559
9560MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceArrayConstructor(
9561 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9562 return TryReduceConstructArrayConstructor(target, args);
9563}
9564
9565MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceStringConstructor(
9566 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9567 if (args.count() == 0) {
9568 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kempty_string);
9569 }
9570
9571 return BuildToString(args[0], ToString::kConvertSymbol);
9572}
9573
9574MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceMathPow(
9575 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) {
9576 if (args.count() < 2) {
9577 // For < 2 args, we'll be calculating Math.Pow(arg[0], undefined), which is
9578 // ToNumber(arg[0]) ** NaN == NaN. So we can just return NaN.
9579 // However, if there is a single argument and it's tagged, we have to call
9580 // ToNumber on it before returning NaN, for side effects. This call could
9581 // lazy deopt, which would mean we'd need a continuation to actually set
9582 // the NaN return value... it's easier to just bail out, this should be
9583 // an uncommon case anyway.
9584 if (args.count() == 1 && args[0]->properties().is_tagged()) {
9585 return {};
9586 }
9587 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue);
9588 }
9589 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) return {};
9590 // If both arguments are tagged, it is cheaper to call Math.Pow builtin,
9591 // instead of Float64Exponentiate, since we are still making a call and we
9592 // don't need to unbox both inputs. See https://crbug.com/1393643.
9593 if (args[0]->properties().is_tagged() && args[1]->properties().is_tagged()) {
9594 // The Math.pow call will be created in CallKnownJSFunction reduction.
9595 return {};
9596 }
9597 ValueNode* left = GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
9598 args[0], NodeType::kNumber, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
9599 ValueNode* right = GetHoleyFloat64ForToNumber(
9600 args[1], NodeType::kNumber, TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber);
9601 return AddNewNode<Float64Exponentiate>({left, right});
9602}
9603
9604#define MATH_UNARY_IEEE_BUILTIN_REDUCER(MathName, ExtName, EnumName) \
9605 MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduce##MathName( \
9606 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args) { \
9607 if (args.count() < 1) { \
9608 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kNanValue); \
9609 } \
9610 if (!CanSpeculateCall()) { \
9611 ValueRepresentation rep = args[0]->properties().value_representation(); \
9612 if (rep == ValueRepresentation::kTagged || \
9613 rep == ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) { \
9614 return {}; \
9615 } \
9616 } \
9617 ValueNode* value = \
9618 GetFloat64ForToNumber(args[0], NodeType::kNumber, \
9619 TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber); \
9620 return AddNewNode<Float64Ieee754Unary>( \
9621 {value}, Float64Ieee754Unary::Ieee754Function::k##EnumName); \
9622 }
9623
9624IEEE_754_UNARY_LIST(MATH_UNARY_IEEE_BUILTIN_REDUCER)
9625#undef MATH_UNARY_IEEE_BUILTIN_REDUCER
9626
9627MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceBuiltin(
9628 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
9629 CallArguments& args, const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
9630 if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
9631 // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
9632 // directly if arguments list is an array.
9633 return {};
9634 }
9635 SaveCallSpeculationScope speculate(this, feedback_source);
9636 if (!shared.HasBuiltinId()) return {};
9637 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
9638 std::cout << " ! Trying to reduce builtin "
9639 << Builtins::name(shared.builtin_id()) << std::endl;
9640 }
9641 switch (shared.builtin_id()) {
9642#define CASE(Name, ...) \
9643 case Builtin::k##Name: \
9644 return TryReduce##Name(target, args);
9645 MAGLEV_REDUCED_BUILTIN(CASE)
9646#undef CASE
9647 default:
9648 // TODO(v8:7700): Inline more builtins.
9649 return {};
9650 }
9651}
9652
9653ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::GetConvertReceiver(
9654 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, const CallArguments& args) {
9655 if (shared.native() || shared.language_mode() == LanguageMode::kStrict) {
9656 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
9657 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
9658 } else {
9659 return args.receiver();
9660 }
9661 }
9662 if (args.receiver_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) {
9663 return GetConstant(
9664 broker()->target_native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()));
9665 }
9666 ValueNode* receiver = args.receiver();
9667 if (CheckType(receiver, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) return receiver;
9668 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
9669 TryGetConstant(receiver)) {
9670 compiler::HeapObjectRef constant = maybe_constant.value();
9671 if (constant.IsNullOrUndefined()) {
9672 return GetConstant(
9673 broker()->target_native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()));
9674 }
9675 }
9676 return AddNewNode<ConvertReceiver>(
9677 {receiver}, broker()->target_native_context(), args.receiver_mode());
9678}
9679
9680template <typename CallNode, typename... Args>
9681CallNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::AddNewCallNode(const CallArguments& args,
9682 Args&&... extra_args) {
9683 size_t input_count = args.count_with_receiver() + CallNode::kFixedInputCount;
9684 return AddNewNode<CallNode>(
9685 input_count,
9686 [&](CallNode* call) {
9687 int arg_index = 0;
9688 call->set_arg(arg_index++,
9689 GetTaggedValue(GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver())));
9690 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.count(); ++i) {
9691 call->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
9692 }
9693 },
9694 std::forward<Args>(extra_args)...);
9695}
9696
9697ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericCall(ValueNode* target,
9698 Call::TargetType target_type,
9699 const CallArguments& args) {
9700 // TODO(victorgomes): We do not collect call feedback from optimized/inlined
9701 // calls. In order to be consistent, we don't pass the feedback_source to the
9702 // IR, so that we avoid collecting for generic calls as well. We might want to
9703 // revisit this in the future.
9704 switch (args.mode()) {
9705 case CallArguments::kDefault:
9706 return AddNewCallNode<Call>(args, args.receiver_mode(), target_type,
9707 GetTaggedValue(target),
9708 GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
9709 case CallArguments::kWithSpread:
9710 DCHECK_EQ(args.receiver_mode(), ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
9711 return AddNewCallNode<CallWithSpread>(args, GetTaggedValue(target),
9712 GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
9713 case CallArguments::kWithArrayLike:
9714 DCHECK_EQ(args.receiver_mode(), ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
9715 // We don't use AddNewCallNode here, because the number of required
9716 // arguments is known statically.
9717 return AddNewNode<CallWithArrayLike>(
9718 {target, GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver()), args[0],
9719 GetContext()});
9720 }
9721}
9722
9723ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallSelf(
9724 ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
9725 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, CallArguments& args) {
9726 ValueNode* receiver = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
9727 size_t input_count = args.count() + CallSelf::kFixedInputCount;
9728 graph()->set_has_recursive_calls(true);
9729 DCHECK_EQ(
9730 compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_compilation_unit()->parameter_count(),
9731 shared.internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver());
9732 return AddNewNode<CallSelf>(
9733 input_count,
9734 [&](CallSelf* call) {
9735 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
9736 call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
9737 }
9738 },
9739 compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_compilation_unit()->parameter_count(),
9740 GetTaggedValue(function), GetTaggedValue(context),
9741 GetTaggedValue(receiver), GetTaggedValue(new_target));
9742}
9743
9744bool MaglevGraphBuilder::TargetIsCurrentCompilingUnit(
9745 compiler::JSFunctionRef target) {
9746 if (compilation_unit_->info()->specialize_to_function_context()) {
9747 return target.object().equals(
9748 compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_function());
9749 }
9750 return target.object()->shared() ==
9751 compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_function()->shared();
9752}
9753
9754MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForApiFunction(
9755 compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef api_callback,
9756 compiler::OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef maybe_shared,
9757 compiler::OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder, CallArguments& args) {
9758 if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
9759 // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
9760 // directly if arguments list is an array.
9761 return {};
9762 }
9763 // Check if the function has an associated C++ code to execute.
9764 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_callback_data =
9765 api_callback.callback_data(broker());
9766 if (!maybe_callback_data.has_value()) {
9767 // TODO(ishell): consider generating "return undefined" for empty function
9768 // instead of failing.
9769 return {};
9770 }
9771
9772 size_t input_count = args.count() + CallKnownApiFunction::kFixedInputCount;
9773 ValueNode* receiver;
9774 if (maybe_shared.has_value()) {
9775 receiver = GetConvertReceiver(maybe_shared.value(), args);
9776 } else {
9777 receiver = args.receiver();
9778 CHECK_NOT_NULL(receiver);
9779 }
9780
9781 CallKnownApiFunction::Mode mode =
9782 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector()
9783 ? (v8_flags.maglev_inline_api_calls
9784 ? CallKnownApiFunction::kNoProfilingInlined
9785 : CallKnownApiFunction::kNoProfiling)
9786 : CallKnownApiFunction::kGeneric;
9787
9788 return AddNewNode<CallKnownApiFunction>(
9789 input_count,
9790 [&](CallKnownApiFunction* call) {
9791 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
9792 call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
9793 }
9794 },
9795 mode, api_callback, api_holder, GetTaggedValue(GetContext()),
9796 GetTaggedValue(receiver));
9797}
9798
9799MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCallKnownApiFunction(
9800 compiler::JSFunctionRef function, compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
9801 CallArguments& args) {
9802 compiler::OptionalFunctionTemplateInfoRef maybe_function_template_info =
9803 shared.function_template_info(broker());
9804 if (!maybe_function_template_info.has_value()) {
9805 // Not an Api function.
9806 return {};
9807 }
9808
9809 // See if we can optimize this API call.
9810 compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info =
9811 maybe_function_template_info.value();
9812
9813 compiler::HolderLookupResult api_holder;
9814 if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver() &&
9815 function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
9816 // We might be able to optimize the API call depending on the
9817 // {function_template_info}.
9818 // If the API function accepts any kind of {receiver}, we only need to
9819 // ensure that the {receiver} is actually a JSReceiver at this point,
9820 // and also pass that as the {holder}. There are two independent bits
9821 // here:
9822 //
9823 // a. When the "accept any receiver" bit is set, it means we don't
9824 // need to perform access checks, even if the {receiver}'s map
9825 // has the "needs access check" bit set.
9826 // b. When the {function_template_info} has no signature, we don't
9827 // need to do the compatible receiver check, since all receivers
9828 // are considered compatible at that point, and the {receiver}
9829 // will be pass as the {holder}.
9830
9831 api_holder =
9832 compiler::HolderLookupResult{CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver};
9833 } else {
9834 // Try to infer API holder from the known aspects of the {receiver}.
9835 api_holder =
9836 TryInferApiHolderValue(function_template_info, args.receiver());
9837 }
9838
9839 switch (api_holder.lookup) {
9840 case CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver:
9841 case CallOptimization::kHolderFound:
9842 return TryReduceCallForApiFunction(function_template_info, shared,
9843 api_holder.holder, args);
9844
9845 case CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound:
9846 break;
9847 }
9848
9849 // We don't have enough information to eliminate the access check
9850 // and/or the compatible receiver check, so use the generic builtin
9851 // that does those checks dynamically. This is still significantly
9852 // faster than the generic call sequence.
9853 Builtin builtin_name;
9854 // TODO(ishell): create no-profiling versions of kCallFunctionTemplate
9855 // builtins and use them here based on DependOnNoProfilingProtector()
9856 // dependency state.
9857 if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()) {
9858 DCHECK(!function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker()));
9859 builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver;
9860 } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
9861 builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccess;
9862 } else {
9863 builtin_name =
9864 Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccessAndCompatibleReceiver;
9865 }
9866
9867 // The CallFunctionTemplate builtin requires the {receiver} to be
9868 // an actual JSReceiver, so make sure we do the proper conversion
9869 // first if necessary.
9870 ValueNode* receiver = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
9871 int kContext = 1;
9872 int kFunctionTemplateInfo = 1;
9873 int kArgc = 1;
9874 return AddNewNode<CallBuiltin>(
9875 kFunctionTemplateInfo + kArgc + kContext + args.count_with_receiver(),
9876 [&](CallBuiltin* call_builtin) {
9877 int arg_index = 0;
9878 call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetConstant(function_template_info));
9879 call_builtin->set_arg(
9880 arg_index++,
9881 GetInt32Constant(JSParameterCount(static_cast<int>(args.count()))));
9882
9883 call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(receiver));
9884 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
9885 call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
9886 }
9887 },
9888 builtin_name, GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
9889}
9890
9891MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
9892 compiler::JSFunctionRef function, ValueNode* new_target,
9893 CallArguments& args, const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
9894 // Don't inline CallFunction stub across native contexts.
9895 if (function.native_context(broker()) != broker()->target_native_context()) {
9896 return {};
9897 }
9898 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
9899 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildCallKnownApiFunction(function, shared, args));
9900
9901 ValueNode* closure = GetConstant(function);
9902 compiler::ContextRef context = function.context(broker());
9903 ValueNode* context_node = GetConstant(context);
9904 MaybeReduceResult res;
9905 if (MaglevIsTopTier() && TargetIsCurrentCompilingUnit(function) &&
9906 !graph_->is_osr()) {
9907 DCHECK(!shared.HasBuiltinId());
9908 res = BuildCallSelf(context_node, closure, new_target, shared, args);
9909 } else {
9910 res = TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
9911 context_node, closure, new_target,
9912#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
9913 function.dispatch_handle(),
9914#endif
9915 shared, function.feedback_vector(broker()), args, feedback_source);
9916 }
9917 return res;
9918}
9919
9920MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
9921 ValueNode* context, ValueNode* function, ValueNode* new_target,
9922#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
9923 JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
9924#endif
9925 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
9926 compiler::OptionalFeedbackVectorRef feedback_vector, CallArguments& args,
9927 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
9928 if (v8_flags.maglev_inlining) {
9929 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildInlinedCall(context, function, new_target, shared,
9930 feedback_vector, args, feedback_source));
9931 }
9932 ValueNode* receiver = GetConvertReceiver(shared, args);
9933 size_t input_count = args.count() + CallKnownJSFunction::kFixedInputCount;
9934 return AddNewNode<CallKnownJSFunction>(
9935 input_count,
9936 [&](CallKnownJSFunction* call) {
9937 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
9938 call->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
9939 }
9940 },
9941#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
9942 dispatch_handle,
9943#endif
9944 shared, GetTaggedValue(function), GetTaggedValue(context),
9945 GetTaggedValue(receiver), GetTaggedValue(new_target));
9946}
9947
9948ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckValue(ValueNode* node,
9949 compiler::HeapObjectRef ref) {
9950 DCHECK(!ref.IsSmi());
9951 DCHECK(!ref.IsHeapNumber());
9952
9953 if (!IsInstanceOfNodeType(ref.map(broker()), GetType(node), broker())) {
9954 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kValueMismatch);
9955 }
9956 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node)) {
9957 if (maybe_constant.value().equals(ref)) {
9958 return ReduceResult::Done();
9959 }
9960 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kUnknown);
9961 }
9962 if (ref.IsString()) {
9963 DCHECK(ref.IsInternalizedString());
9964 AddNewNode<CheckValueEqualsString>({node}, ref.AsInternalizedString());
9965 SetKnownValue(node, ref, NodeType::kString);
9966 } else {
9967 AddNewNode<CheckValue>({node}, ref);
9968 SetKnownValue(node, ref, StaticTypeForConstant(broker(), ref));
9969 }
9970
9971 return ReduceResult::Done();
9972}
9973
9974ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckValue(ValueNode* node,
9975 compiler::ObjectRef ref) {
9976 if (ref.IsHeapObject() && !ref.IsHeapNumber()) {
9977 return BuildCheckValue(node, ref.AsHeapObject());
9978 }
9979 return BuildCheckNumericalValue(node, ref);
9980}
9981
9982ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckNumericalValue(
9983 ValueNode* node, compiler::ObjectRef ref) {
9984 DCHECK(ref.IsSmi() || ref.IsHeapNumber());
9985 if (ref.IsSmi()) {
9986 int ref_value = ref.AsSmi();
9987 if (IsConstantNode(node->opcode())) {
9988 if (node->Is<SmiConstant>() &&
9989 node->Cast<SmiConstant>()->value().value() == ref_value) {
9990 return ReduceResult::Done();
9991 }
9992 if (node->Is<Int32Constant>() &&
9993 node->Cast<Int32Constant>()->value() == ref_value) {
9994 return ReduceResult::Done();
9995 }
9996 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kUnknown);
9997 }
9998 if (NodeTypeIs(GetType(node), NodeType::kAnyHeapObject)) {
9999 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kValueMismatch);
10000 }
10001 AddNewNode<CheckValueEqualsInt32>({node}, ref_value);
10002 } else {
10003 DCHECK(ref.IsHeapNumber());
10004 Float64 ref_value = Float64::FromBits(ref.AsHeapNumber().value_as_bits());
10005 DCHECK(!ref_value.is_hole_nan());
10006 if (node->Is<Float64Constant>()) {
10007 Float64 f64 = node->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value();
10008 DCHECK(!f64.is_hole_nan());
10009 if (f64 == ref_value) {
10010 return ReduceResult::Done();
10011 }
10012 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kUnknown);
10013 } else if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef constant =
10014 TryGetConstant(node)) {
10015 if (constant.value().IsHeapNumber()) {
10016 Float64 f64 =
10017 Float64::FromBits(constant.value().AsHeapNumber().value_as_bits());
10018 DCHECK(!f64.is_hole_nan());
10019 if (f64 == ref_value) {
10020 return ReduceResult::Done();
10021 }
10022 }
10023 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kUnknown);
10024 }
10025 if (!NodeTypeIs(NodeType::kNumber, GetType(node))) {
10026 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kValueMismatch);
10027 }
10028 if (ref_value.is_nan()) {
10029 AddNewNode<CheckFloat64IsNan>({node});
10030 } else {
10031 AddNewNode<CheckValueEqualsFloat64>({node}, ref_value);
10032 }
10033 }
10034
10035 SetKnownValue(node, ref, NodeType::kNumber);
10036 return ReduceResult::Done();
10037}
10038
10039ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildConvertHoleToUndefined(ValueNode* node) {
10040 if (!node->is_tagged()) return node;
10041 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node);
10042 if (maybe_constant) {
10043 return maybe_constant.value().IsTheHole()
10044 ? GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue)
10045 : node;
10046 }
10047 return AddNewNode<ConvertHoleToUndefined>({node});
10048}
10049
10050ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCheckNotHole(ValueNode* node) {
10051 if (!node->is_tagged()) return ReduceResult::Done();
10052 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node);
10053 if (maybe_constant) {
10054 if (maybe_constant.value().IsTheHole()) {
10055 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(DeoptimizeReason::kHole);
10056 }
10057 return ReduceResult::Done();
10058 }
10059 AddNewNode<CheckNotHole>({node});
10060 return ReduceResult::Done();
10061}
10062
10063MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForConstant(
10064 compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args,
10065 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10066 if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
10067 // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
10068 // directly if arguments list is an array.
10069 return {};
10070 }
10071 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = target.shared(broker());
10072 ValueNode* target_node = GetConstant(target);
10073 // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
10074 if (!shared.HasBreakInfo(broker())) {
10075 if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
10076 // If we have a class constructor, we should raise an exception.
10077 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError,
10078 {target_node});
10079 }
10080 DCHECK(IsCallable(*target.object()));
10081 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReduceBuiltin(target, shared, args, feedback_source));
10082 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
10083 target, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue), args,
10084 feedback_source));
10085 }
10086 return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kJSFunction, args);
10087}
10088
10089compiler::HolderLookupResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryInferApiHolderValue(
10090 compiler::FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info,
10091 ValueNode* receiver) {
10092 const compiler::HolderLookupResult not_found;
10093
10094 auto receiver_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
10095 if (!receiver_info || !receiver_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
10096 // No info about receiver, can't infer API holder.
10097 return not_found;
10098 }
10099 DCHECK(!receiver_info->possible_maps().is_empty());
10100 compiler::MapRef first_receiver_map = receiver_info->possible_maps()[0];
10101
10102 // See if we can constant-fold the compatible receiver checks.
10103 compiler::HolderLookupResult api_holder =
10104 function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
10105 first_receiver_map);
10106 if (api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) {
10107 // Can't infer API holder.
10108 return not_found;
10109 }
10110
10111 // Check that all {receiver_maps} are actually JSReceiver maps and
10112 // that the {function_template_info} accepts them without access
10113 // checks (even if "access check needed" is set for {receiver}).
10114 //
10115 // API holder might be a receivers's hidden prototype (i.e. the receiver is
10116 // a global proxy), so in this case the map check or stability dependency on
10117 // the receiver guard us from detaching a global object from global proxy.
10118 CHECK(first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
10119 CHECK(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
10120 function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
10121
10122 for (compiler::MapRef receiver_map : receiver_info->possible_maps()) {
10123 compiler::HolderLookupResult holder_i =
10124 function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
10125 receiver_map);
10126
10127 if (api_holder.lookup != holder_i.lookup) {
10128 // Different API holders, dynamic lookup is required.
10129 return not_found;
10130 }
10131 DCHECK(holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound ||
10132 holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver);
10133 if (holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound) {
10134 DCHECK(api_holder.holder.has_value() && holder_i.holder.has_value());
10135 if (!api_holder.holder->equals(*holder_i.holder)) {
10136 // Different API holders, dynamic lookup is required.
10137 return not_found;
10138 }
10139 }
10140
10141 CHECK(receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
10142 CHECK(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
10143 function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
10144 }
10145 return api_holder;
10146}
10147
10148MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForTarget(
10149 ValueNode* target_node, compiler::JSFunctionRef target, CallArguments& args,
10150 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10151 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(target_node, target));
10152 return TryReduceCallForConstant(target, args, feedback_source);
10153}
10154
10155MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceCallForNewClosure(
10156 ValueNode* target_node, ValueNode* target_context,
10157#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
10158 JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
10159#endif
10160 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
10161 compiler::OptionalFeedbackVectorRef feedback_vector, CallArguments& args,
10162 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10163 // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
10164 if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
10165 // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known function
10166 // directly if arguments list is an array.
10167 return {};
10168 }
10169 if (!shared.HasBreakInfo(broker())) {
10170 if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
10171 // If we have a class constructor, we should raise an exception.
10172 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError,
10173 {target_node});
10174 }
10175 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
10176 target_context, target_node,
10177 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue),
10178#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
10179 dispatch_handle,
10180#endif
10181 shared, feedback_vector, args, feedback_source));
10182 }
10183 return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kJSFunction, args);
10184}
10185
10186MaybeReduceResult
10187MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApplyCallWithReceiver(
10188 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_receiver, CallArguments& args,
10189 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10190 if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) return {};
10191
10192 ValueNode* function = GetValueOrUndefined(args.receiver());
10193 if (maybe_receiver.has_value()) {
10194 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(function, maybe_receiver.value()));
10195 function = GetConstant(maybe_receiver.value());
10196 }
10197
10198 SaveCallSpeculationScope saved(this);
10199 if (args.count() == 0) {
10200 CallArguments empty_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10201 return ReduceCall(function, empty_args, feedback_source);
10202 }
10203 auto build_call_only_with_new_receiver = [&] {
10204 CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {args[0]});
10205 return ReduceCall(function, new_args, feedback_source);
10206 };
10207 if (args.count() == 1 || IsNullValue(args[1]) || IsUndefinedValue(args[1])) {
10208 return build_call_only_with_new_receiver();
10209 }
10210 auto build_call_with_array_like = [&] {
10211 CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {args[0], args[1]},
10212 CallArguments::kWithArrayLike);
10213 return ReduceCallWithArrayLike(function, new_args, feedback_source);
10214 };
10215 if (!MayBeNullOrUndefined(args[1])) {
10216 return build_call_with_array_like();
10217 }
10218 return SelectReduction(
10219 [&](auto& builder) {
10220 return BuildBranchIfUndefinedOrNull(builder, args[1]);
10221 },
10222 build_call_only_with_new_receiver, build_call_with_array_like);
10223}
10224
10225ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallWithFeedback(
10226 ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
10227 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10228 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& processed_feedback =
10229 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
10230 if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
10231 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
10232 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
10233 }
10234
10235 DCHECK_EQ(processed_feedback.kind(), compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kCall);
10236 const compiler::CallFeedback& call_feedback = processed_feedback.AsCall();
10237
10238 if (call_feedback.target().has_value() &&
10239 call_feedback.target()->IsJSFunction()) {
10240 CallFeedbackContent content = call_feedback.call_feedback_content();
10241 compiler::JSFunctionRef feedback_target =
10242 call_feedback.target()->AsJSFunction();
10243 if (content == CallFeedbackContent::kReceiver) {
10244 compiler::NativeContextRef native_context =
10245 broker()->target_native_context();
10246 compiler::JSFunctionRef apply_function =
10247 native_context.function_prototype_apply(broker());
10248 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(target_node, apply_function));
10249 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
10250 TryReduceFunctionPrototypeApplyCallWithReceiver(feedback_target, args,
10251 feedback_source),
10252 SetAccumulator);
10253 feedback_target = apply_function;
10254 } else {
10255 DCHECK_EQ(CallFeedbackContent::kTarget, content);
10256 }
10257 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(target_node, feedback_target));
10258 }
10259
10260 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(ReduceCall(target_node, args, feedback_source),
10261 SetAccumulator);
10262 UNREACHABLE();
10263}
10264
10265ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ReduceCallWithArrayLikeForArgumentsObject(
10266 ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
10267 VirtualObject* arguments_object,
10268 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10269 DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kWithArrayLike);
10270 DCHECK(arguments_object->map().IsJSArgumentsObjectMap() ||
10271 arguments_object->map().IsJSArrayMap());
10272 args.PopArrayLikeArgument();
10273 ValueNode* elements_value =
10274 arguments_object->get(JSArgumentsObject::kElementsOffset);
10275 if (elements_value->Is<ArgumentsElements>()) {
10276 Call::TargetType target_type = Call::TargetType::kAny;
10277 // TODO(victorgomes): Add JSFunction node type in KNA and use the info here.
10278 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
10279 TryGetConstant(target_node)) {
10280 if (maybe_constant->IsJSFunction()) {
10281 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
10282 maybe_constant->AsJSFunction().shared(broker());
10283 if (!IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
10284 target_type = Call::TargetType::kJSFunction;
10285 }
10286 }
10287 }
10288 int start_index = 0;
10289 if (elements_value->Cast<ArgumentsElements>()->type() ==
10290 CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter) {
10291 start_index =
10292 elements_value->Cast<ArgumentsElements>()->formal_parameter_count();
10293 }
10294 return AddNewCallNode<CallForwardVarargs>(args, GetTaggedValue(target_node),
10295 GetTaggedValue(GetContext()),
10296 start_index, target_type);
10297 }
10298
10299 if (elements_value->Is<RootConstant>()) {
10300 // It is a RootConstant, Elements can only be the empty fixed array.
10301 DCHECK_EQ(elements_value->Cast<RootConstant>()->index(),
10302 RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
10303 CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {args.receiver()});
10304 return ReduceCall(target_node, new_args, feedback_source);
10305 }
10306
10307 if (Constant* constant_value = elements_value->TryCast<Constant>()) {
10308 DCHECK(constant_value->object().IsFixedArray());
10309 compiler::FixedArrayRef elements = constant_value->object().AsFixedArray();
10310 base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> arg_list;
10311 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(args.receiver());
10312 arg_list.push_back(args.receiver());
10313 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
10314 arg_list.push_back(args[i]);
10315 }
10316 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elements.length(); i++) {
10317 arg_list.push_back(GetConstant(*elements.TryGet(broker(), i)));
10318 }
10319 CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, std::move(arg_list));
10320 return ReduceCall(target_node, new_args, feedback_source);
10321 }
10322
10323 DCHECK(elements_value->Is<InlinedAllocation>());
10324 InlinedAllocation* allocation = elements_value->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
10325 VirtualObject* elements = allocation->object();
10326
10327 base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> arg_list;
10328 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(args.receiver());
10329 arg_list.push_back(args.receiver());
10330 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(args.count()); i++) {
10331 arg_list.push_back(args[i]);
10332 }
10333 DCHECK(elements->get(offsetof(FixedArray, length_))->Is<Int32Constant>());
10334 int length = elements->get(offsetof(FixedArray, length_))
10335 ->Cast<Int32Constant>()
10336 ->value();
10337 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
10338 arg_list.push_back(elements->get(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i)));
10339 }
10340 CallArguments new_args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, std::move(arg_list));
10341 return ReduceCall(target_node, new_args, feedback_source);
10342}
10343
10344namespace {
10345bool IsSloppyMappedArgumentsObject(compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker,
10346 compiler::MapRef map) {
10347 return broker->target_native_context()
10348 .fast_aliased_arguments_map(broker)
10349 .equals(map);
10350}
10351} // namespace
10352
10353std::optional<VirtualObject*>
10354MaglevGraphBuilder::TryGetNonEscapingArgumentsObject(ValueNode* value) {
10355 if (!value->Is<InlinedAllocation>()) return {};
10356 InlinedAllocation* alloc = value->Cast<InlinedAllocation>();
10357 // Although the arguments object has not been changed so far, since it is not
10358 // escaping, it could be modified after this bytecode if it is inside a loop.
10359 if (IsInsideLoop()) {
10360 if (!is_loop_effect_tracking() ||
10361 !loop_effects_->allocations.contains(alloc)) {
10362 return {};
10363 }
10364 }
10365 // TODO(victorgomes): We can probably loosen the IsNotEscaping requirement if
10366 // we keep track of the arguments object changes so far.
10367 if (alloc->IsEscaping()) return {};
10368 VirtualObject* object = alloc->object();
10369 // TODO(victorgomes): Support simple JSArray forwarding.
10370 compiler::MapRef map = object->map();
10371 // It is a rest parameter, if it is an array with ArgumentsElements node as
10372 // the elements array.
10373 if (map.IsJSArrayMap() && object->get(JSArgumentsObject::kElementsOffset)
10374 ->Is<ArgumentsElements>()) {
10375 return object;
10376 }
10377 // TODO(victorgomes): We can loosen the IsSloppyMappedArgumentsObject
10378 // requirement if there is no stores to the mapped arguments.
10379 if (map.IsJSArgumentsObjectMap() &&
10380 !IsSloppyMappedArgumentsObject(broker(), map)) {
10381 return object;
10382 }
10383 return {};
10384}
10385
10386ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ReduceCallWithArrayLike(
10387 ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
10388 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10389 DCHECK_EQ(args.mode(), CallArguments::kWithArrayLike);
10390
10391 // TODO(victorgomes): Add the case for JSArrays and Rest parameter.
10392 if (std::optional<VirtualObject*> arguments_object =
10393 TryGetNonEscapingArgumentsObject(args.array_like_argument())) {
10394 RETURN_IF_DONE(ReduceCallWithArrayLikeForArgumentsObject(
10395 target_node, args, *arguments_object, feedback_source));
10396 }
10397
10398 // On fallthrough, create a generic call.
10399 return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kAny, args);
10400}
10401
10402ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::ReduceCall(
10403 ValueNode* target_node, CallArguments& args,
10404 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10405 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
10406 TryGetConstant(target_node)) {
10407 if (maybe_constant->IsJSFunction()) {
10408 MaybeReduceResult result = TryReduceCallForTarget(
10409 target_node, maybe_constant->AsJSFunction(), args, feedback_source);
10410 RETURN_IF_DONE(result);
10411 }
10412 }
10413
10414 // If the implementation here becomes more complex, we could probably
10415 // deduplicate the code for FastCreateClosure and CreateClosure by using
10416 // templates or giving them a shared base class.
10417 if (FastCreateClosure* fast_create_closure =
10418 target_node->TryCast<FastCreateClosure>()) {
10419 MaybeReduceResult result = TryReduceCallForNewClosure(
10420 fast_create_closure, fast_create_closure->context().node(),
10421#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
10422 fast_create_closure->feedback_cell().dispatch_handle(),
10423#endif
10424 fast_create_closure->shared_function_info(),
10425 fast_create_closure->feedback_cell().feedback_vector(broker()), args,
10426 feedback_source);
10427 RETURN_IF_DONE(result);
10428 } else if (CreateClosure* create_closure =
10429 target_node->TryCast<CreateClosure>()) {
10430 MaybeReduceResult result = TryReduceCallForNewClosure(
10431 create_closure, create_closure->context().node(),
10432#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
10433 create_closure->feedback_cell().dispatch_handle(),
10434#endif
10435 create_closure->shared_function_info(),
10436 create_closure->feedback_cell().feedback_vector(broker()), args,
10437 feedback_source);
10438 RETURN_IF_DONE(result);
10439 }
10440
10441 // On fallthrough, create a generic call.
10442 return BuildGenericCall(target_node, Call::TargetType::kAny, args);
10443}
10444
10445ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallFromRegisterList(
10446 ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode) {
10447 ValueNode* target = LoadRegister(0);
10448 interpreter::RegisterList reg_list = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
10449 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
10450 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot);
10451 CallArguments args(receiver_mode, reg_list, current_interpreter_frame_);
10452 return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
10453}
10454
10455ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildCallFromRegisters(
10456 int arg_count, ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode) {
10457 ValueNode* target = LoadRegister(0);
10458 const int receiver_count =
10459 (receiver_mode == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined) ? 0 : 1;
10460 const int reg_count = arg_count + receiver_count;
10461 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(reg_count + 1);
10462 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot);
10463 switch (reg_count) {
10464 case 0: {
10465 DCHECK_EQ(receiver_mode, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10466 CallArguments args(receiver_mode);
10467 return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
10468 }
10469 case 1: {
10470 CallArguments args(receiver_mode, {LoadRegister(1)});
10471 return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
10472 }
10473 case 2: {
10474 CallArguments args(receiver_mode, {LoadRegister(1), LoadRegister(2)});
10475 return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
10476 }
10477 case 3: {
10478 CallArguments args(receiver_mode,
10479 {LoadRegister(1), LoadRegister(2), LoadRegister(3)});
10480 return BuildCallWithFeedback(target, args, feedback_source);
10481 }
10482 default:
10483 UNREACHABLE();
10484 }
10485}
10486
10487ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallAnyReceiver() {
10488 return BuildCallFromRegisterList(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny);
10489}
10490ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallProperty() {
10491 return BuildCallFromRegisterList(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
10492}
10493ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallProperty0() {
10494 return BuildCallFromRegisters(0, ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
10495}
10496ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallProperty1() {
10497 return BuildCallFromRegisters(1, ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
10498}
10499ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallProperty2() {
10500 return BuildCallFromRegisters(2, ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined);
10501}
10502ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallUndefinedReceiver() {
10503 return BuildCallFromRegisterList(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10504}
10505ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallUndefinedReceiver0() {
10506 return BuildCallFromRegisters(0, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10507}
10508ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallUndefinedReceiver1() {
10509 return BuildCallFromRegisters(1, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10510}
10511ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallUndefinedReceiver2() {
10512 return BuildCallFromRegisters(2, ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10513}

10515ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallWithSpread() {
10516 ValueNode* function = LoadRegister(0);
10517 interpreter::RegisterList reglist = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
10518 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
10519 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot);
10520 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, reglist,
10521 current_interpreter_frame_, CallArguments::kWithSpread);
10522 return BuildCallWithFeedback(function, args, feedback_source);
10523}
10524
10525ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallRuntime() {
10526 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = iterator_.GetRuntimeIdOperand(0);
10527 interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
10528 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
10529 size_t input_count = args.register_count() + CallRuntime::kFixedInputCount;
10530 CallRuntime* call_runtime = AddNewNode<CallRuntime>(
10531 input_count,
10532 [&](CallRuntime* call_runtime) {
10533 for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); ++i) {
10534 call_runtime->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
10535 }
10536 },
10537 function_id, context);
10538 SetAccumulator(call_runtime);
10539
10540 if (RuntimeFunctionCanThrow(function_id)) {
10541 return BuildAbort(AbortReason::kUnexpectedReturnFromThrow);
10542 }
10543 return ReduceResult::Done();
10544}
10545
10546ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallJSRuntime() {
10547 // Get the function to call from the native context.
10548 compiler::NativeContextRef native_context = broker()->target_native_context();
10549 ValueNode* context = GetConstant(native_context);
10550 uint32_t slot = iterator_.GetNativeContextIndexOperand(0);
10551 ValueNode* callee =
10552 LoadAndCacheContextSlot(context, slot, kMutable, ContextKind::kDefault);
10553 // Call the function.
10554 interpreter::RegisterList reglist = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
10555 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined, reglist,
10556 current_interpreter_frame_);
10557 SetAccumulator(BuildGenericCall(callee, Call::TargetType::kJSFunction, args));
10558 return ReduceResult::Done();
10559}
10560
10561ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCallRuntimeForPair() {
10562 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = iterator_.GetRuntimeIdOperand(0);
10563 interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
10564 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
10565
10566 size_t input_count = args.register_count() + CallRuntime::kFixedInputCount;
10567 CallRuntime* call_runtime = AddNewNode<CallRuntime>(
10568 input_count,
10569 [&](CallRuntime* call_runtime) {
10570 for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); ++i) {
10571 call_runtime->set_arg(i, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
10572 }
10573 },
10574 function_id, context);
10575 auto result = iterator_.GetRegisterPairOperand(3);
10576 StoreRegisterPair(result, call_runtime);
10577 return ReduceResult::Done();
10578}
10579
10580ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitInvokeIntrinsic() {
10581 // InvokeIntrinsic <function_id> <first_arg> <arg_count>
10582 Runtime::FunctionId intrinsic_id = iterator_.GetIntrinsicIdOperand(0);
10583 interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
10584 switch (intrinsic_id) {
10585#define CASE(Name, _, arg_count) \
10586 case Runtime::kInline##Name: \
10587 DCHECK_IMPLIES(arg_count != -1, arg_count == args.register_count()); \
10588 return VisitIntrinsic##Name(args);
10589 INTRINSICS_LIST(CASE)
10590#undef CASE
10591 default:
10592 UNREACHABLE();
10593 }
10594}

10596ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIntrinsicCopyDataProperties(
10597 interpreter::RegisterList args) {
10598 DCHECK_EQ(args.register_count(), 2);
10599 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kCopyDataProperties>(
10600 {GetTaggedValue(args[0]), GetTaggedValue(args[1])}));
10601 return ReduceResult::Done();
10602}
10603
10604ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::
10605 VisitIntrinsicCopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedPropertiesOnStack(
10606 interpreter::RegisterList args) {
10607 SmiConstant* excluded_property_count =
10608 GetSmiConstant(args.register_count() - 1);
10609 int kContext = 1;
10610 int kExcludedPropertyCount = 1;
10611 CallBuiltin* call_builtin = AddNewNode<CallBuiltin>(
10612 args.register_count() + kContext + kExcludedPropertyCount,
10613 [&](CallBuiltin* call_builtin) {
10614 int arg_index = 0;
10615 call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[0]));
10616 call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, excluded_property_count);
10617 for (int i = 1; i < args.register_count(); i++) {
10618 call_builtin->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
10619 }
10620 },
10621 Builtin::kCopyDataPropertiesWithExcludedProperties,
10622 GetTaggedValue(GetContext()));
10623 SetAccumulator(call_builtin);
10624 return ReduceResult::Done();
10625}
10626
10627ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIntrinsicCreateIterResultObject(
10628 interpreter::RegisterList args) {
10629 DCHECK_EQ(args.register_count(), 2);
10630 ValueNode* value = current_interpreter_frame_.get(args[0]);
10631 ValueNode* done = current_interpreter_frame_.get(args[1]);
10632 compiler::MapRef map =
10633 broker()->target_native_context().iterator_result_map(broker());
10634 VirtualObject* iter_result = CreateJSIteratorResult(map, value, done);
10635 ValueNode* allocation =
10636 BuildInlinedAllocation(iter_result, AllocationType::kYoung);
10637 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
10638 // next side effect clear it.
10639 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
10640 SetAccumulator(allocation);
10641 return ReduceResult::Done();
10642}

10647 SetAccumulator(
10648 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kCreateAsyncFromSyncIteratorBaseline>(

10651}

10653ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIntrinsicCreateJSGeneratorObject(
10654 interpreter::RegisterList args) {

10656 ValueNode* closure = current_interpreter_frame_.get(args[0]);
10657 ValueNode* receiver = current_interpreter_frame_.get(args[1]);
10658 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
10659 TryBuildAndAllocateJSGeneratorObject(closure, receiver), SetAccumulator);
10660 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kCreateGeneratorObject>(
10661 {GetTaggedValue(closure), GetTaggedValue(receiver)}));

10701ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIntrinsicAsyncFunctionEnter(

10703 DCHECK_EQ(args.register_count(), 2);
10704 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kAsyncFunctionEnter>(
10705 {GetTaggedValue(args[0]), GetTaggedValue(args[1])}));
10706 return ReduceResult::Done();
10707}
