10757
10758ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildGenericConstruct(
10759 ValueNode* target, ValueNode* new_target, ValueNode* context,
10760 const CallArguments& args,
10761 const compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
10762 size_t input_count = args.count_with_receiver() + Construct::kFixedInputCount;
10763 DCHECK_EQ(args.receiver_mode(), ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined);
10764 return AddNewNode<Construct>(
10765 input_count,
10766 [&](Construct* construct) {
10767 int arg_index = 0;
10768 // Add undefined receiver.
10769 construct->set_arg(arg_index++,
10770 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
10771 for (size_t i = 0; i < args.count(); i++) {
10772 construct->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
10773 }
10774 },
10775 feedback_source, GetTaggedValue(target), GetTaggedValue(new_target),
10776 GetTaggedValue(context));
10777}
10778
10779ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildAndAllocateKeyValueArray(
10780 ValueNode* key, ValueNode* value) {
10781 VirtualObject* elements = CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), 2);
10782 elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(0), key);
10783 elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(1), value);
10784 compiler::MapRef map =
10785 broker()->target_native_context().js_array_packed_elements_map(broker());
10786 VirtualObject* array;
10787 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
10788 array, CreateJSArray(map, map.instance_size(), GetInt32Constant(2)));
10789 array->set(JSArray::kElementsOffset, elements);
10790 ValueNode* allocation = BuildInlinedAllocation(array, AllocationType::kYoung);
10791 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
10792 // next side effect clear it.
10793 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
10794 return allocation;
10795}
10796
10797ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildAndAllocateJSArray(
10798 compiler::MapRef map, ValueNode* length, ValueNode* elements,
10799 const compiler::SlackTrackingPrediction& slack_tracking_prediction,
10800 AllocationType allocation_type) {
10801 VirtualObject* array;
10802 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
10803 array,
10804 CreateJSArray(map, slack_tracking_prediction.instance_size(), length));
10805 array->set(JSArray::kElementsOffset, elements);
10806 for (int i = 0; i < slack_tracking_prediction.inobject_property_count();
10807 i++) {
10808 array->set(map.GetInObjectPropertyOffset(i),
10809 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
10810 }
10811 ValueNode* allocation = BuildInlinedAllocation(array, allocation_type);
10812 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
10813 // next side effect clear it.
10814 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
10815 return allocation;
10816}
10817
10818ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildAndAllocateJSArrayIterator(
10819 ValueNode* array, IterationKind iteration_kind) {
10820 compiler::MapRef map =
10821 broker()->target_native_context().initial_array_iterator_map(broker());
10822 VirtualObject* iterator = CreateJSArrayIterator(map, array, iteration_kind);
10823 ValueNode* allocation =
10824 BuildInlinedAllocation(iterator, AllocationType::kYoung);
10825 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
10826 // next side effect clear it.
10827 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
10828 return allocation;
10829}
10830
10831MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildAndAllocateJSGeneratorObject(
10832 ValueNode* closure, ValueNode* receiver) {
10833 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(closure);
10834 if (!maybe_constant.has_value()) return {};
10835 if (!maybe_constant->IsJSFunction()) return {};
10836 compiler::JSFunctionRef function = maybe_constant->AsJSFunction();
10837 if (!function.has_initial_map(broker())) return {};
10838
10839 // Create the register file.
10840 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
10841 DCHECK(shared.HasBytecodeArray());
10842 compiler::BytecodeArrayRef bytecode_array = shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker());
10843 int parameter_count_no_receiver = bytecode_array.parameter_count() - 1;
10844 int length = parameter_count_no_receiver + bytecode_array.register_count();
10845 if (FixedArray::SizeFor(length) > kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize) {
10846 return {};
10847 }
10848 auto undefined = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
10849 VirtualObject* register_file =
10850 CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), length);
10851 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
10852 register_file->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), undefined);
10853 }
10854
10855 // Create the JS[Async]GeneratorObject instance.
10856 compiler::SlackTrackingPrediction slack_tracking_prediction =
10857 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnInitialMapInstanceSizePrediction(
10858 function);
10859 compiler::MapRef initial_map = function.initial_map(broker());
10860 VirtualObject* generator = CreateJSGeneratorObject(
10861 initial_map, slack_tracking_prediction.instance_size(), GetContext(),
10862 closure, receiver, register_file);
10863
10864 // Handle in-object properties.
10865 for (int i = 0; i < slack_tracking_prediction.inobject_property_count();
10866 i++) {
10867 generator->set(initial_map.GetInObjectPropertyOffset(i), undefined);
10868 }
10869
10870 ValueNode* allocation =
10871 BuildInlinedAllocation(generator, AllocationType::kYoung);
10872 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
10873 // next side effect clear it.
10874 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
10875 return allocation;
10876}
10877
10878namespace {
10879
10880compiler::OptionalMapRef GetArrayConstructorInitialMap(
10881 compiler::JSHeapBroker* broker, compiler::JSFunctionRef array_function,
10882 ElementsKind elements_kind, size_t argc, std::optional<int> maybe_length) {
10883 compiler::MapRef initial_map = array_function.initial_map(broker);
10884 if (argc == 1 && (!maybe_length.has_value() || *maybe_length > 0)) {
10885 // Constructing an Array via new Array(N) where N is an unsigned
10886 // integer, always creates a holey backing store.
10887 elements_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind);
10888 }
10889 return initial_map.AsElementsKind(broker, elements_kind);
10890}
10891
10892} // namespace
10893
10894ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildElementsArray(int length) {
10895 if (length == 0) {
10896 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
10897 }
10898 VirtualObject* elements =
10899 CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), length);
10900 auto hole = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
10901 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
10902 elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), hole);
10903 }
10904 return elements;
10905}
10906
10907MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceConstructArrayConstructor(
10908 compiler::JSFunctionRef array_function, CallArguments& args,
10909 compiler::OptionalAllocationSiteRef maybe_allocation_site) {
10910 ElementsKind elements_kind =
10911 maybe_allocation_site.has_value()
10912 ? maybe_allocation_site->GetElementsKind()
10913 : array_function.initial_map(broker()).elements_kind();
10914 // TODO(victorgomes): Support double elements array.
10915 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) return {};
10916 DCHECK(IsFastElementsKind(elements_kind));
10917
10918 std::optional<int> maybe_length;
10919 if (args.count() == 1) {
10920 maybe_length = TryGetInt32Constant(args[0]);
10921 }
10922 compiler::OptionalMapRef maybe_initial_map = GetArrayConstructorInitialMap(
10923 broker(), array_function, elements_kind, args.count(), maybe_length);
10924 if (!maybe_initial_map.has_value()) return {};
10925 compiler::MapRef initial_map = maybe_initial_map.value();
10926 compiler::SlackTrackingPrediction slack_tracking_prediction =
10927 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnInitialMapInstanceSizePrediction(
10928 array_function);
10929
10930 // Tells whether we are protected by either the {site} or a
10931 // protector cell to do certain speculative optimizations.
10932 bool can_inline_call = false;
10933 AllocationType allocation_type = AllocationType::kYoung;
10934
10935 if (maybe_allocation_site) {
10936 can_inline_call = maybe_allocation_site->CanInlineCall();
10937 allocation_type =
10938 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnPretenureMode(*maybe_allocation_site);
10939 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnElementsKind(*maybe_allocation_site);
10940 } else {
10941 compiler::PropertyCellRef array_constructor_protector = MakeRef(
10942 broker(), local_isolate()->factory()->array_constructor_protector());
10943 array_constructor_protector.CacheAsProtector(broker());
10944 can_inline_call = array_constructor_protector.value(broker()).AsSmi() ==
10945 Protectors::kProtectorValid;
10946 }
10947
10948 if (args.count() == 0) {
10949 return BuildAndAllocateJSArray(
10950 initial_map, GetSmiConstant(0),
10951 BuildElementsArray(JSArray::kPreallocatedArrayElements),
10952 slack_tracking_prediction, allocation_type);
10953 }
10954
10955 if (maybe_length.has_value() && *maybe_length >= 0 &&
10956 *maybe_length < JSArray::kInitialMaxFastElementArray) {
10957 return BuildAndAllocateJSArray(initial_map, GetSmiConstant(*maybe_length),
10958 BuildElementsArray(*maybe_length),
10959 slack_tracking_prediction, allocation_type);
10960 }
10961
10962 // TODO(victorgomes): If we know the argument cannot be a number, we should
10963 // allocate an array with one element.
10964 // We don't know anything about the length, so we rely on the allocation
10965 // site to avoid deopt loops.
10966 if (args.count() == 1 && can_inline_call) {
10967 return SelectReduction(
10968 [&](auto& builder) {
10969 return BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(builder,
10970 Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual,
10971 args[0], GetInt32Constant(0));
10972 },
10973 [&] {
10974 ValueNode* elements =
10975 AddNewNode<AllocateElementsArray>({args[0]}, allocation_type);
10976 return BuildAndAllocateJSArray(initial_map, args[0], elements,
10977 slack_tracking_prediction,
10978 allocation_type);
10979 },
10980 [&] {
10981 ValueNode* error = GetSmiConstant(
10982 static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kInvalidArrayLength));
10983 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowRangeError, {error});
10984 });
10985 }
10986
10987 // TODO(victorgomes): Support the constructor with argument count larger
10988 // than 1.
10989 return {};
10990}
10991
10992MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceConstructBuiltin(
10993 compiler::JSFunctionRef builtin,
10994 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info, ValueNode* target,
10995 CallArguments& args) {
10996 // TODO(victorgomes): specialize more known constants builtin targets.
10997 switch (shared_function_info.builtin_id()) {
10998 case Builtin::kArrayConstructor: {
10999 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReduceConstructArrayConstructor(builtin, args));
11000 break;
11001 }
11002 case Builtin::kObjectConstructor: {
11003 // If no value is passed, we can immediately lower to a simple
11004 // constructor.
11005 if (args.count() == 0) {
11006 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(target, builtin));
11007 ValueNode* result = BuildInlinedAllocation(CreateJSConstructor(builtin),
11008 AllocationType::kYoung);
11009 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
11010 // next side effect clear it.
11011 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
11012 return result;
11013 }
11014 break;
11015 }
11016 default:
11017 break;
11018 }
11019 return {};
11020}
11021
11022MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceConstructGeneric(
11023 compiler::JSFunctionRef function,
11024 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info, ValueNode* target,
11025 ValueNode* new_target, CallArguments& args,
11026 compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11027 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(target, function));
11028
11029 int construct_arg_count = static_cast<int>(args.count());
11030 base::Vector<ValueNode*> construct_arguments_without_receiver =
11031 zone()->AllocateVector<ValueNode*>(construct_arg_count);
11032 for (int i = 0; i < construct_arg_count; i++) {
11033 construct_arguments_without_receiver[i] = args[i];
11034 }
11035
11036 if (IsDerivedConstructor(shared_function_info.kind())) {
11037 ValueNode* implicit_receiver = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
11038 args.set_receiver(implicit_receiver);
11039 ValueNode* call_result;
11040 {
11041 DeoptFrameScope construct(this, implicit_receiver);
11042 MaybeReduceResult result = TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11043 function, new_target, args, feedback_source);
11044 RETURN_IF_ABORT(result);
11045 call_result = result.value();
11046 }
11047 if (CheckType(call_result, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) return call_result;
11048 ValueNode* constant_node;
11049 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
11050 TryGetConstant(call_result, &constant_node)) {
11051 compiler::HeapObjectRef constant = maybe_constant.value();
11052 if (constant.IsJSReceiver()) return constant_node;
11053 }
11054 if (!call_result->properties().is_tagged()) {
11055 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowConstructorReturnedNonObject, {});
11056 }
11057 return AddNewNode<CheckDerivedConstructResult>({call_result});
11058 }
11059
11060 // We do not create a construct stub lazy deopt frame, since
11061 // FastNewObject cannot fail if target is a JSFunction.
11062 ValueNode* implicit_receiver = nullptr;
11063 if (function.has_initial_map(broker())) {
11064 compiler::MapRef map = function.initial_map(broker());
11065 if (map.GetConstructor(broker()).equals(function)) {
11066 implicit_receiver = BuildInlinedAllocation(CreateJSConstructor(function),
11067 AllocationType::kYoung);
11068 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the
11069 // next side effect clear it.
11070 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
11071 }
11072 }
11073 if (implicit_receiver == nullptr) {
11074 implicit_receiver = BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kFastNewObject>(
11075 {GetTaggedValue(target), GetTaggedValue(new_target)});
11076 }
11077 EnsureType(implicit_receiver, NodeType::kJSReceiver);
11078
11079 args.set_receiver(implicit_receiver);
11080 ValueNode* call_result;
11081 {
11082 DeoptFrameScope construct(this, implicit_receiver);
11083 MaybeReduceResult result = TryBuildCallKnownJSFunction(
11084 function, new_target, args, feedback_source);
11085 RETURN_IF_ABORT(result);
11086 call_result = result.value();
11087 }
11088 if (CheckType(call_result, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) return call_result;
11089 if (!call_result->properties().is_tagged()) return implicit_receiver;
11090 ValueNode* constant_node;
11091 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
11092 TryGetConstant(call_result, &constant_node)) {
11093 compiler::HeapObjectRef constant = maybe_constant.value();
11094 DCHECK(CheckType(implicit_receiver, NodeType::kJSReceiver));
11095 if (constant.IsJSReceiver()) return constant_node;
11096 return implicit_receiver;
11097 }
11098 return AddNewNode<CheckConstructResult>({call_result, implicit_receiver});
11099}
11100
11101MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceConstruct(
11102 compiler::HeapObjectRef feedback_target, ValueNode* target,
11103 ValueNode* new_target, CallArguments& args,
11104 compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11105 DCHECK(!feedback_target.IsAllocationSite());
11106 if (!feedback_target.map(broker()).is_constructor()) {
11107 // TODO(victorgomes): Deal the case where target is not a constructor.
11108 return {};
11109 }
11110
11111 if (target != new_target) return {};
11112
11113 // TODO(v8:7700): Add fast paths for other callables.
11114 if (!feedback_target.IsJSFunction()) return {};
11115 compiler::JSFunctionRef function = feedback_target.AsJSFunction();
11116
11117 // Do not inline constructors with break points.
11118 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info =
11119 function.shared(broker());
11120 if (shared_function_info.HasBreakInfo(broker())) {
11121 return {};
11122 }
11123
11124 // Do not inline cross natives context.
11125 if (function.native_context(broker()) != broker()->target_native_context()) {
11126 return {};
11127 }
11128
11129 if (args.mode() != CallArguments::kDefault) {
11130 // TODO(victorgomes): Maybe inline the spread stub? Or call known
11131 // function directly if arguments list is an array.
11132 return {};
11133 }
11134
11135 if (shared_function_info.HasBuiltinId()) {
11136 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryReduceConstructBuiltin(function, shared_function_info,
11137 target, args));
11138 }
11139
11140 if (shared_function_info.construct_as_builtin()) {
11141 // TODO(victorgomes): Inline JSBuiltinsConstructStub.
11142 return {};
11143 }
11144
11145 return TryReduceConstructGeneric(function, shared_function_info, target,
11146 new_target, args, feedback_source);
11147}
11148
11149ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildConstruct(
11150 ValueNode* target, ValueNode* new_target, CallArguments& args,
11151 compiler::FeedbackSource& feedback_source) {
11152 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
11153 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(feedback_source);
11154 if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
11155 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
11156 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForConstruct);
11157 }
11158
11159 DCHECK_EQ(processed_feedback.kind(), compiler::ProcessedFeedback::kCall);
11160 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target =
11161 processed_feedback.AsCall().target();
11162 if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsAllocationSite()) {
11163 // The feedback is an AllocationSite, which means we have called the
11164 // Array function and collected transition (and pretenuring) feedback
11165 // for the resulting arrays.
11166 compiler::JSFunctionRef array_function =
11167 broker()->target_native_context().array_function(broker());
11168 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(target, array_function));
11169 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
11170 TryReduceConstructArrayConstructor(array_function, args,
11171 feedback_target->AsAllocationSite()),
11172 SetAccumulator);
11173 } else {
11174 if (feedback_target.has_value()) {
11175 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
11176 TryReduceConstruct(feedback_target.value(), target, new_target, args,
11177 feedback_source),
11178 SetAccumulator);
11179 }
11180 if (compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant =
11181 TryGetConstant(target)) {
11182 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
11183 TryReduceConstruct(maybe_constant.value(), target, new_target, args,
11184 feedback_source),
11185 SetAccumulator);
11186 }
11187 }
11188 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
11189 SetAccumulator(BuildGenericConstruct(target, new_target, context, args,
11190 feedback_source));
11191 return ReduceResult::Done();
11192}
11193
11194ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitConstruct() {
11195 ValueNode* new_target = GetAccumulator();
11196 ValueNode* target = LoadRegister(0);
11197 interpreter::RegisterList reg_list = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11198 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
11199 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
11200 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined, reg_list,
11201 current_interpreter_frame_);
11202 return BuildConstruct(target, new_target, args, feedback_source);
11203}
11204
11205ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitConstructWithSpread() {
11206 ValueNode* new_target = GetAccumulator();
11207 ValueNode* constructor = LoadRegister(0);
11208 interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
11209 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
11210 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
11211 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot);
11212
11213 int kReceiver = 1;
11214 size_t input_count =
11215 args.register_count() + kReceiver + ConstructWithSpread::kFixedInputCount;
11216 ConstructWithSpread* construct = AddNewNode<ConstructWithSpread>(
11217 input_count,
11218 [&](ConstructWithSpread* construct) {
11219 int arg_index = 0;
11220 // Add undefined receiver.
11221 construct->set_arg(arg_index++,
11222 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
11223 for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); i++) {
11224 construct->set_arg(arg_index++, GetTaggedValue(args[i]));
11225 }
11226 },
11227 feedback_source, GetTaggedValue(constructor), GetTaggedValue(new_target),
11228 GetTaggedValue(context));
11229 SetAccumulator(construct);
11230 return ReduceResult::Done();
11231}
11232
11233ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitConstructForwardAllArgs() {
11234 ValueNode* new_target = GetAccumulator();
11235 ValueNode* target = LoadRegister(0);
11236 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
11237 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
11238
11239 if (is_inline()) {
11240 base::SmallVector<ValueNode*, 8> forwarded_args(argument_count());
11241 for (int i = 1 /* skip receiver */; i < argument_count(); ++i) {
11242 forwarded_args[i] = GetInlinedArgument(i);
11243 }
11244 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined,
11245 std::move(forwarded_args));
11246 return BuildConstruct(target, new_target, args, feedback_source);
11247 } else {
11248 // TODO(syg): Add ConstructForwardAllArgs reductions and support inlining.
11249 SetAccumulator(
11250 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kConstructForwardAllArgs_WithFeedback>(
11251 {GetTaggedValue(target), GetTaggedValue(new_target)},
11252 feedback_source));
11253 return ReduceResult::Done();
11254 }
11255}
11256
11257ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestEqual() {
11258 return VisitCompareOperation<Operation::kEqual>();
11259}
11260ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestEqualStrict() {
11261 return VisitCompareOperation<Operation::kStrictEqual>();
11262}
11263ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestLessThan() {
11264 return VisitCompareOperation<Operation::kLessThan>();
11265}
11266ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestLessThanOrEqual() {
11267 return VisitCompareOperation<Operation::kLessThanOrEqual>();
11268}
11269ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestGreaterThan() {
11270 return VisitCompareOperation<Operation::kGreaterThan>();
11271}
11272ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestGreaterThanOrEqual() {
11273 return VisitCompareOperation<Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual>();
11274}
11275
11276MaglevGraphBuilder::InferHasInPrototypeChainResult
11277MaglevGraphBuilder::InferHasInPrototypeChain(
11278 ValueNode* receiver, compiler::HeapObjectRef prototype) {
11279 auto node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(receiver);
11280 // If the map set is not found, then we don't know anything about the map of
11281 // the receiver, so bail.
11282 if (!node_info || !node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
11283 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
11284 }
11285
11286 // If the set of possible maps is empty, then there's no possible map for this
11287 // receiver, therefore this path is unreachable at runtime. We're unlikely to
11288 // ever hit this case, BuildCheckMaps should already unconditionally deopt,
11289 // but check it in case another checking operation fails to statically
11290 // unconditionally deopt.
11291 if (node_info->possible_maps().is_empty()) {
11292 // TODO(leszeks): Add an unreachable assert here.
11293 return kIsNotInPrototypeChain;
11294 }
11295
11296 ZoneVector<compiler::MapRef> receiver_map_refs(zone());
11297
11298 // Try to determine either that all of the {receiver_maps} have the given
11299 // {prototype} in their chain, or that none do. If we can't tell, return
11300 // kMayBeInPrototypeChain.
11301 bool all = true;
11302 bool none = true;
11303 for (compiler::MapRef map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
11304 receiver_map_refs.push_back(map);
11305 while (true) {
11306 if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type())) {
11307 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
11308 }
11309 if (!map.IsJSObjectMap()) {
11310 all = false;
11311 break;
11312 }
11313 compiler::HeapObjectRef map_prototype = map.prototype(broker());
11314 if (map_prototype.equals(prototype)) {
11315 none = false;
11316 break;
11317 }
11318 map = map_prototype.map(broker());
11319 // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode protoypes here.
11320 if (!map.is_stable() || map.is_dictionary_map()) {
11321 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
11322 }
11323 if (map.oddball_type(broker()) == compiler::OddballType::kNull) {
11324 all = false;
11325 break;
11326 }
11327 }
11328 }
11329 DCHECK(!receiver_map_refs.empty());
11330 DCHECK_IMPLIES(all, !none);
11331 if (!all && !none) return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
11332
11333 {
11334 compiler::OptionalJSObjectRef last_prototype;
11335 if (all) {
11336 // We don't need to protect the full chain if we found the prototype, we
11337 // can stop at {prototype}. In fact we could stop at the one before
11338 // {prototype} but since we're dealing with multiple receiver maps this
11339 // might be a different object each time, so it's much simpler to include
11340 // {prototype}. That does, however, mean that we must check {prototype}'s
11341 // map stability.
11342 if (!prototype.IsJSObject() || !prototype.map(broker()).is_stable()) {
11343 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
11344 }
11345 last_prototype = prototype.AsJSObject();
11346 }
11347 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
11348 receiver_map_refs, kStartAtPrototype, last_prototype);
11349 }
11350
11351 DCHECK_EQ(all, !none);
11352 return all ? kIsInPrototypeChain : kIsNotInPrototypeChain;
11353}
11354
11355MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFastHasInPrototypeChain(
11356 ValueNode* object, compiler::HeapObjectRef prototype) {
11357 auto in_prototype_chain = InferHasInPrototypeChain(object, prototype);
11358 if (in_prototype_chain == kMayBeInPrototypeChain) return {};
11359
11360 return GetBooleanConstant(in_prototype_chain == kIsInPrototypeChain);
11361}
11362
11363ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildHasInPrototypeChain(
11364 ValueNode* object, compiler::HeapObjectRef prototype) {
11365 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildFastHasInPrototypeChain(object, prototype));
11366 return AddNewNode<HasInPrototypeChain>({object}, prototype);
11367}
11368
11369MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFastOrdinaryHasInstance(
11370 ValueNode* object, compiler::JSObjectRef callable,
11371 ValueNode* callable_node_if_not_constant) {
11372 const bool is_constant = callable_node_if_not_constant == nullptr;
11373 if (!is_constant) return {};
11374
11375 if (callable.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
11376 // OrdinaryHasInstance on bound functions turns into a recursive
11377 // invocation of the instanceof operator again.
11378 compiler::JSBoundFunctionRef function = callable.AsJSBoundFunction();
11379 compiler::JSReceiverRef bound_target_function =
11380 function.bound_target_function(broker());
11381
11382 if (bound_target_function.IsJSObject()) {
11383 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildFastInstanceOf(
11384 object, bound_target_function.AsJSObject(), nullptr));
11385 }
11386
11387 // If we can't build a fast instance-of, build a slow one with the
11388 // partial optimisation of using the bound target function constant.
11389 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kInstanceOf>(
11390 {GetTaggedValue(object), GetConstant(bound_target_function)});
11391 }
11392
11393 if (callable.IsJSFunction()) {
11394 // Optimize if we currently know the "prototype" property.
11395 compiler::JSFunctionRef function = callable.AsJSFunction();
11396
11397 // TODO(v8:7700): Remove the has_prototype_slot condition once the broker
11398 // is always enabled.
11399 if (!function.map(broker()).has_prototype_slot() ||
11400 !function.has_instance_prototype(broker()) ||
11401 function.PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(broker())) {
11402 return {};
11403 }
11404
11405 compiler::HeapObjectRef prototype =
11406 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnPrototypeProperty(function);
11407 return BuildHasInPrototypeChain(object, prototype);
11408 }
11409
11410 return {};
11411}
11412
11413ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildOrdinaryHasInstance(
11414 ValueNode* object, compiler::JSObjectRef callable,
11415 ValueNode* callable_node_if_not_constant) {
11416 RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildFastOrdinaryHasInstance(
11417 object, callable, callable_node_if_not_constant));
11418
11419 return BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kOrdinaryHasInstance>(
11420 {callable_node_if_not_constant
11421 ? GetTaggedValue(callable_node_if_not_constant)
11422 : GetConstant(callable),
11423 GetTaggedValue(object)});
11424}
11425
11426MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFastInstanceOf(
11427 ValueNode* object, compiler::JSObjectRef callable,
11428 ValueNode* callable_node_if_not_constant) {
11429 compiler::MapRef receiver_map = callable.map(broker());
11430 compiler::NameRef name = broker()->has_instance_symbol();
11431 compiler::PropertyAccessInfo access_info = broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(
11432 receiver_map, name, compiler::AccessMode::kLoad);
11433
11434 // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode holders here.
11435 if (access_info.IsInvalid() || access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
11436 return {};
11437 }
11438 access_info.RecordDependencies(broker()->dependencies());
11439
11440 if (access_info.IsNotFound()) {
11441 // If there's no @@hasInstance handler, the OrdinaryHasInstance operation
11442 // takes over, but that requires the constructor to be callable.
11443 if (!receiver_map.is_callable()) return {};
11444
11445 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
11446 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype);
11447
11448 // Monomorphic property access.
11449 if (callable_node_if_not_constant) {
11450 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(
11451 callable_node_if_not_constant,
11452 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())));
11453 } else {
11454 // Even if we have a constant receiver, we still have to make sure its
11455 // map is correct, in case it migrates.
11456 if (receiver_map.is_stable()) {
11457 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(receiver_map);
11458 } else {
11459 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(
11460 GetConstant(callable),
11461 base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())));
11462 }
11463 }
11464
11465 return BuildOrdinaryHasInstance(object, callable,
11466 callable_node_if_not_constant);
11467 }
11468
11469 if (access_info.IsFastDataConstant()) {
11470 compiler::OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
11471 bool found_on_proto = holder.has_value();
11472 compiler::JSObjectRef holder_ref =
11473 found_on_proto ? holder.value() : callable;
11474 if (access_info.field_representation().IsDouble()) return {};
11475 compiler::OptionalObjectRef has_instance_field =
11476 holder_ref.GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
11477 broker(), access_info.field_representation(),
11478 access_info.field_index(), broker()->dependencies());
11479 if (!has_instance_field.has_value() ||
11480 !has_instance_field->IsHeapObject() ||
11481 !has_instance_field->AsHeapObject().map(broker()).is_callable()) {
11482 return {};
11483 }
11484
11485 if (found_on_proto) {
11486 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
11487 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
11488 holder.value());
11489 }
11490
11491 ValueNode* callable_node;
11492 if (callable_node_if_not_constant) {
11493 // Check that {callable_node_if_not_constant} is actually {callable}.
11494 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckValue(callable_node_if_not_constant, callable));
11495 callable_node = callable_node_if_not_constant;
11496 } else {
11497 callable_node = GetConstant(callable);
11498 }
11499 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckMaps(
11500 callable_node, base::VectorOf(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())));
11501
11502 // Special case the common case, where @@hasInstance is
11503 // Function.p.hasInstance. In this case we don't need to call ToBoolean (or
11504 // use the continuation), since OrdinaryHasInstance is guaranteed to return
11505 // a boolean.
11506 if (has_instance_field->IsJSFunction()) {
11507 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
11508 has_instance_field->AsJSFunction().shared(broker());
11509 if (shared.HasBuiltinId() &&
11510 shared.builtin_id() == Builtin::kFunctionPrototypeHasInstance) {
11511 return BuildOrdinaryHasInstance(object, callable,
11512 callable_node_if_not_constant);
11513 }
11514 }
11515
11516 // Call @@hasInstance
11517 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined,
11518 {callable_node, object});
11519 ValueNode* call_result;
11520 {
11521 // Make sure that a lazy deopt after the @@hasInstance call also performs
11522 // ToBoolean before returning to the interpreter.
11523 DeoptFrameScope continuation_scope(
11524 this, Builtin::kToBooleanLazyDeoptContinuation);
11525
11526 if (has_instance_field->IsJSFunction()) {
11527 SaveCallSpeculationScope saved(this);
11528 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
11529 call_result,
11530 TryReduceCallForConstant(has_instance_field->AsJSFunction(), args));
11531 } else {
11532 call_result = BuildGenericCall(GetConstant(*has_instance_field),
11533 Call::TargetType::kAny, args);
11534 }
11535 // TODO(victorgomes): Propagate the case if we need to soft deopt.
11536 }
11537
11538 return BuildToBoolean(call_result);
11539 }
11540
11541 return {};
11542}
11543
11544template <bool flip>
11545ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildToBoolean(ValueNode* value) {
11546 if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
11547 return GetBooleanConstant(FromConstantToBool(local_isolate(), value) ^
11548 flip);
11549 }
11550
11551 switch (value->value_representation()) {
11552 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
11553 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
11554 // The ToBoolean of both the_hole and NaN is false, so we can use the
11555 // same operation for HoleyFloat64 and Float64.
11556 return AddNewNode<Float64ToBoolean>({value}, flip);
11557
11558 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
11559 // Uint32 has the same logic as Int32 when converting ToBoolean, namely
11560 // comparison against zero, so we can cast it and ignore the signedness.
11561 value = AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({value});
11562 [[fallthrough]];
11563 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
11564 return AddNewNode<Int32ToBoolean>({value}, flip);
11565
11566 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
11567 UNREACHABLE();
11568
11569 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
11570 break;
11571 }
11572
11573 NodeInfo* node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(value);
11574 if (node_info) {
11575 if (ValueNode* as_int32 = node_info->alternative().int32()) {
11576 return AddNewNode<Int32ToBoolean>({as_int32}, flip);
11577 }
11578 if (ValueNode* as_float64 = node_info->alternative().float64()) {
11579 return AddNewNode<Float64ToBoolean>({as_float64}, flip);
11580 }
11581 }
11582
11583 NodeType value_type;
11584 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver, &value_type)) {
11585 ValueNode* result = BuildTestUndetectable(value);
11586 // TODO(victorgomes): Check if it is worth to create
11587 // TestUndetectableLogicalNot or to remove ToBooleanLogicalNot, since we
11588 // already optimize LogicalNots by swapping the branches.
11589 if constexpr (!flip) {
11590 result = BuildLogicalNot(result);
11591 }
11592 return result;
11593 }
11594 ValueNode* falsy_value = nullptr;
11595 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kString)) {
11596 falsy_value = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kempty_string);
11597 } else if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kSmi)) {
11598 falsy_value = GetSmiConstant(0);
11599 }
11600 if (falsy_value != nullptr) {
11601 return AddNewNode<std::conditional_t<flip, TaggedEqual, TaggedNotEqual>>(
11602 {value, falsy_value});
11603 }
11604 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kBoolean)) {
11605 if constexpr (flip) {
11606 value = BuildLogicalNot(value);
11607 }
11608 return value;
11609 }
11610 return AddNewNode<std::conditional_t<flip, ToBooleanLogicalNot, ToBoolean>>(
11611 {value}, GetCheckType(value_type));
11612}
11613
11614MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFastInstanceOfWithFeedback(
11615 ValueNode* object, ValueNode* callable,
11616 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source) {
11617 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
11618 broker()->GetFeedbackForInstanceOf(feedback_source);
11619
11620 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
11621 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
11622 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForInstanceOf);
11623 }
11624
11625 // Check if the right hand side is a known receiver, or
11626 // we have feedback from the InstanceOfIC.
11627 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant;
11628 if ((maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(callable)) &&
11629 maybe_constant.value().IsJSObject()) {
11630 compiler::JSObjectRef callable_ref = maybe_constant.value().AsJSObject();
11631 return TryBuildFastInstanceOf(object, callable_ref, nullptr);
11632 }
11633 if (feedback_source.IsValid()) {
11634 compiler::OptionalJSObjectRef callable_from_feedback =
11635 feedback.AsInstanceOf().value();
11636 if (callable_from_feedback) {
11637 return TryBuildFastInstanceOf(object, *callable_from_feedback, callable);
11638 }
11639 }
11640 return {};
11641}
11642
11643ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestInstanceOf() {
11644 // TestInstanceOf <src> <feedback_slot>
11645 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
11646 ValueNode* callable = GetAccumulator();
11647 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
11648 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
11649
11650 MaybeReduceResult result =
11651 TryBuildFastInstanceOfWithFeedback(object, callable, feedback_source);
11652 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
11653
11654 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
11655 SetAccumulator(
11656 AddNewNode<TestInstanceOf>({context, object, callable}, feedback_source));
11657 return ReduceResult::Done();
11658}
11659
11660ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitTestIn() {
11661 // TestIn <src> <feedback_slot>
11662 ValueNode* object = GetAccumulator();
11663 ValueNode* name = LoadRegister(0);
11664 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
11665 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
11666
11667 // TODO(victorgomes): Create fast path using feedback.
11668 USE(feedback_source);
11669
11670 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kKeyedHasIC>(
11671 {GetTaggedValue(object), GetTaggedValue(name)}, feedback_source));
11672 return ReduceResult::Done();
11673}

11675ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitToName() {
11676 // ToObject <dst>
11677 if (!CheckType(GetAccumulator(), NodeType::kName)) {
11678 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<ToName>({GetContext(), GetAccumulator()}));
11679 }
11680 return ReduceResult::Done();
11681}
11682
11683ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildToString(ValueNode* value,
11684 ToString::ConversionMode mode) {
11685 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kString)) return value;
11686 // TODO(victorgomes): Add fast path for constant primitives.
11687 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kNumber)) {
11688 // TODO(verwaest): Float64ToString if float.
11689 return AddNewNode<NumberToString>({value});
11690 }
11691 return AddNewNode<ToString>({GetContext(), value}, mode);
11692}
11693
11694ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildToNumberOrToNumeric(
11695 Object::Conversion mode) {
11696 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
11697 switch (value->value_representation()) {
11698 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
11699 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
11700 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
11701 return ReduceResult::Done();
11702
11703 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64: {
11704 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<HoleyFloat64ToMaybeNanFloat64>({value}));
11705 return ReduceResult::Done();
11706 }
11707
11708 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
11709 // We'll insert the required checks depending on the feedback.
11710 break;
11711
11712 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
11713 UNREACHABLE();
11714 }
11715
11716 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(0);
11717 switch (broker()->GetFeedbackForBinaryOperation(
11718 compiler::FeedbackSource(feedback(), slot))) {
11719 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
11720 RETURN_IF_ABORT(BuildCheckSmi(value));
11721 break;
11722 case BinaryOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
11723 UNREACHABLE();
11724 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumber:
11725 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt:
11726 case BinaryOperationHint::kBigInt64:
11727 if (mode == Object::Conversion::kToNumber &&
11728 EnsureType(value, NodeType::kNumber)) {
11729 return ReduceResult::Done();
11730 }
11731 AddNewNode<CheckNumber>({value}, mode);
11732 break;
11733 case BinaryOperationHint::kNone:
11734 // TODO(leszeks): Faster ToNumber for kNumberOrOddball
11735 case BinaryOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
11736 case BinaryOperationHint::kString:
11737 case BinaryOperationHint::kStringOrStringWrapper:
11738 case BinaryOperationHint::kAny:
11739 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kNumber)) return ReduceResult::Done();
11740 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<ToNumberOrNumeric>({value}, mode));
11741 break;
11742 }
11743 return ReduceResult::Done();
11744}
11745
11746ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitToNumber() {
11747 return BuildToNumberOrToNumeric(Object::Conversion::kToNumber);
11748}
11749ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitToNumeric() {
11750 return BuildToNumberOrToNumeric(Object::Conversion::kToNumeric);
11751}
11752
11753ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitToObject() {
11754 // ToObject <dst>
11755 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
11756 interpreter::Register destination = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0);
11757 NodeType old_type;
11758 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver, &old_type)) {
11759 MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
11760 destination);
11761 } else {
11762 StoreRegister(destination, AddNewNode<ToObject>({GetContext(), value},
11763 GetCheckType(old_type)));
11764 }
11765 return ReduceResult::Done();
11766}
11767
11768ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitToString() {
11769 // ToString
11770 SetAccumulator(BuildToString(GetAccumulator(), ToString::kThrowOnSymbol));
11771 return ReduceResult::Done();
11772}
11773
11774ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitToBoolean() {
11775 SetAccumulator(BuildToBoolean(GetAccumulator()));
11776 return ReduceResult::Done();
11777}
11778
11779ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateRegExpLiteral() {
11780 // CreateRegExpLiteral <pattern_idx> <literal_idx> <flags>
11781 compiler::StringRef pattern = GetRefOperand<String>(0);
11782 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
11783 uint32_t flags = GetFlag16Operand(2);
11784 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
11785 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
11786 broker()->GetFeedbackForRegExpLiteral(feedback_source);
11787 if (!processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
11788 compiler::RegExpBoilerplateDescriptionRef literal =
11789 processed_feedback.AsRegExpLiteral().value();
11790 compiler::NativeContextRef native_context =
11791 broker()->target_native_context();
11792 compiler::MapRef map =
11793 native_context.regexp_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
11794 SetAccumulator(BuildInlinedAllocation(
11795 CreateRegExpLiteralObject(map, literal), AllocationType::kYoung));
11796 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
11797 // effect clear it.
11798 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
11799 return ReduceResult::Done();
11800 }
11801 // Fallback.
11802 SetAccumulator(
11803 AddNewNode<CreateRegExpLiteral>({}, pattern, feedback_source, flags));
11804 return ReduceResult::Done();
11805}
11806
11807ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateArrayLiteral() {
11808 compiler::HeapObjectRef constant_elements = GetRefOperand<HeapObject>(0);
11809 FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(1);
11810 int bytecode_flags = GetFlag8Operand(2);
11811 int literal_flags =
11812 interpreter::CreateArrayLiteralFlags::FlagsBits::decode(bytecode_flags);
11813 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot_index);
11814
11815 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
11816 broker()->GetFeedbackForArrayOrObjectLiteral(feedback_source);
11817
11818 if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
11819 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
11820 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForArrayLiteral);
11821 }
11822
11823 MaybeReduceResult result =
11824 TryBuildFastCreateObjectOrArrayLiteral(processed_feedback.AsLiteral());
11825 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
11826
11827 if (interpreter::CreateArrayLiteralFlags::FastCloneSupportedBit::decode(
11828 bytecode_flags)) {
11829 // TODO(victorgomes): CreateShallowArrayLiteral should not need the
11830 // boilerplate descriptor. However the current builtin checks that the
11831 // feedback exists and fallsback to CreateArrayLiteral if it doesn't.
11832 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateShallowArrayLiteral>(
11833 {}, constant_elements, feedback_source, literal_flags));
11834 } else {
11835 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateArrayLiteral>(
11836 {}, constant_elements, feedback_source, literal_flags));
11837 }
11838 return ReduceResult::Done();
11839}
11840
11841ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateArrayFromIterable() {
11842 ValueNode* iterable = GetAccumulator();
11843 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kIterableToListWithSymbolLookup>(
11844 {GetTaggedValue(iterable)}));
11845 return ReduceResult::Done();
11846}
11847
11848ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateEmptyArrayLiteral() {
11849 FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(0);
11850 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot_index);
11851 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
11852 broker()->GetFeedbackForArrayOrObjectLiteral(feedback_source);
11853 if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
11854 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
11855 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForArrayLiteral);
11856 }
11857 compiler::AllocationSiteRef site = processed_feedback.AsLiteral().value();
11858
11859 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnElementsKind(site);
11860 ElementsKind kind = site.GetElementsKind();
11861
11862 compiler::NativeContextRef native_context = broker()->target_native_context();
11863 compiler::MapRef map = native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), kind);
11864 // Initial JSArray map shouldn't have any in-object properties.
11865 SBXCHECK_EQ(map.GetInObjectProperties(), 0);
11866 VirtualObject* array;
11867 GET_VALUE_OR_ABORT(
11868 array, CreateJSArray(map, map.instance_size(), GetSmiConstant(0)));
11869 SetAccumulator(BuildInlinedAllocation(array, AllocationType::kYoung));
11870 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
11871 // effect clear it.
11872 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
11873 return ReduceResult::Done();
11874}
11875
11876std::optional<VirtualObject*>
11877MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReadBoilerplateForFastLiteral(
11878 compiler::JSObjectRef boilerplate, AllocationType allocation, int max_depth,
11879 int* max_properties) {
11880 DCHECK_GE(max_depth, 0);
11881 DCHECK_GE(*max_properties, 0);
11882
11883 if (max_depth == 0) return {};
11884
11885 // Prevent concurrent migrations of boilerplate objects.
11886 compiler::JSHeapBroker::BoilerplateMigrationGuardIfNeeded
11887 boilerplate_access_guard(broker());
11888
11889 // Now that we hold the migration lock, get the current map.
11890 compiler::MapRef boilerplate_map = boilerplate.map(broker());
11891 // Protect against concurrent changes to the boilerplate object by checking
11892 // for an identical value at the end of the compilation.
11893 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnObjectSlotValue(
11894 boilerplate, HeapObject::kMapOffset, boilerplate_map);
11895 {
11896 compiler::OptionalMapRef current_boilerplate_map =
11897 boilerplate.map_direct_read(broker());
11898 if (!current_boilerplate_map.has_value() ||
11899 !current_boilerplate_map->equals(boilerplate_map)) {
11900 // TODO(leszeks): Emit an eager deopt for this case, so that we can
11901 // re-learn the boilerplate. This will be easier once we get rid of the
11902 // two-pass approach, since we'll be able to create the eager deopt here
11903 // and return a ReduceResult::DoneWithAbort().
11904 return {};
11905 }
11906 }
11907
11908 // Bail out if the boilerplate map has been deprecated. The map could of
11909 // course be deprecated at some point after the line below, but it's not a
11910 // correctness issue -- it only means the literal won't be created with the
11911 // most up to date map(s).
11912 if (boilerplate_map.is_deprecated()) return {};
11913
11914 // We currently only support in-object properties.
11915 if (boilerplate.map(broker()).elements_kind() == DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS ||
11916 boilerplate.map(broker()).is_dictionary_map() ||
11917 !boilerplate.raw_properties_or_hash(broker()).has_value()) {
11918 return {};
11919 }
11920 {
11921 compiler::ObjectRef properties =
11922 *boilerplate.raw_properties_or_hash(broker());
11923 bool const empty =
11924 properties.IsSmi() ||
11925 properties.equals(MakeRef(
11926 broker(), local_isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array())) ||
11927 properties.equals(MakeRef(
11928 broker(),
11929 Cast<Object>(local_isolate()->factory()->empty_property_array())));
11930 if (!empty) return {};
11931 }
11932
11933 compiler::OptionalFixedArrayBaseRef maybe_elements =
11934 boilerplate.elements(broker(), kRelaxedLoad);
11935 if (!maybe_elements.has_value()) return {};
11936 compiler::FixedArrayBaseRef boilerplate_elements = maybe_elements.value();
11937 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnObjectSlotValue(
11938 boilerplate, JSObject::kElementsOffset, boilerplate_elements);
11939 const uint32_t elements_length = boilerplate_elements.length();
11940
11941 VirtualObject* fast_literal;
11942 if (boilerplate_map.IsJSArrayMap()) {
11943 MaybeReduceResult fast_array = CreateJSArray(
11944 boilerplate_map, boilerplate_map.instance_size(),
11945 GetConstant(boilerplate.AsJSArray().GetBoilerplateLength(broker())));
11946 CHECK(fast_array.HasValue());
11947 fast_literal = fast_array.value()->Cast<VirtualObject>();
11948 } else {
11949 fast_literal = CreateJSObject(boilerplate_map);
11950 }
11951
11952 int inobject_properties = boilerplate_map.GetInObjectProperties();
11953
11954 // Compute the in-object properties to store first.
11955 int index = 0;
11956 for (InternalIndex i :
11957 InternalIndex::Range(boilerplate_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors())) {
11958 PropertyDetails const property_details =
11959 boilerplate_map.GetPropertyDetails(broker(), i);
11960 if (property_details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField) continue;
11961 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, property_details.kind());
11962 if ((*max_properties)-- == 0) return {};
11963
11964 int offset = boilerplate_map.GetInObjectPropertyOffset(index);
11965#ifdef DEBUG
11966 FieldIndex field_index =
11967 FieldIndex::ForDetails(*boilerplate_map.object(), property_details);
11968 DCHECK(field_index.is_inobject());
11969 DCHECK_EQ(index, field_index.property_index());
11970 DCHECK_EQ(field_index.offset(), offset);
11971#endif
11972
11973 // The index is derived from the in-sandbox `NumberOfOwnDescriptors` value,
11974 // but the access is out-of-sandbox fast_literal fields.
11975 SBXCHECK_LT(index, inobject_properties);
11976
11977 // Note: the use of RawInobjectPropertyAt (vs. the higher-level
11978 // GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty) here is necessary, since the underlying
11979 // value may be `uninitialized`, which the latter explicitly does not
11980 // support.
11981 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_boilerplate_value =
11982 boilerplate.RawInobjectPropertyAt(
11983 broker(),
11984 FieldIndex::ForInObjectOffset(offset, FieldIndex::kTagged));
11985 if (!maybe_boilerplate_value.has_value()) return {};
11986
11987 // Note: We don't need to take a compilation dependency verifying the value
11988 // of `boilerplate_value`, since boilerplate properties are constant after
11989 // initialization modulo map migration. We protect against concurrent map
11990 // migrations (other than elements kind transition, which don't affect us)
11991 // via the boilerplate_migration_access lock.
11992 compiler::ObjectRef boilerplate_value = maybe_boilerplate_value.value();
11993
11994 if (boilerplate_value.IsJSObject()) {
11995 compiler::JSObjectRef boilerplate_object = boilerplate_value.AsJSObject();
11996 std::optional<VirtualObject*> maybe_object_value =
11997 TryReadBoilerplateForFastLiteral(boilerplate_object, allocation,
11998 max_depth - 1, max_properties);
11999 if (!maybe_object_value.has_value()) return {};
12000 fast_literal->set(offset, maybe_object_value.value());
12001 } else if (property_details.representation().IsDouble()) {
12002 fast_literal->set(offset,
12003 CreateHeapNumber(Float64::FromBits(
12004 boilerplate_value.AsHeapNumber().value_as_bits())));
12005 } else {
12006 // It's fine to store the 'uninitialized' Oddball into a Smi field since
12007 // it will get overwritten anyway.
12008 DCHECK_IMPLIES(property_details.representation().IsSmi() &&
12009 !boilerplate_value.IsSmi(),
12010 IsUninitialized(*boilerplate_value.object()));
12011 fast_literal->set(offset, GetConstant(boilerplate_value));
12012 }
12013 index++;
12014 }
12015
12016 // Fill slack at the end of the boilerplate object with filler maps.
12017 for (; index < inobject_properties; ++index) {
12018 DCHECK(!V8_MAP_PACKING_BOOL);
12019 // TODO(wenyuzhao): Fix incorrect MachineType when V8_MAP_PACKING is
12020 // enabled.
12021 int offset = boilerplate_map.GetInObjectPropertyOffset(index);
12022 fast_literal->set(offset, GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOnePointerFillerMap));
12023 }
12024
12025 DCHECK_EQ(JSObject::kElementsOffset, JSArray::kElementsOffset);
12026 // Empty or copy-on-write elements just store a constant.
12027 compiler::MapRef elements_map = boilerplate_elements.map(broker());
12028 // Protect against concurrent changes to the boilerplate object by checking
12029 // for an identical value at the end of the compilation.
12030 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnObjectSlotValue(
12031 boilerplate_elements, HeapObject::kMapOffset, elements_map);
12032 if (boilerplate_elements.length() == 0 ||
12033 elements_map.IsFixedCowArrayMap(broker())) {
12034 if (allocation == AllocationType::kOld &&
12035 !boilerplate.IsElementsTenured(boilerplate_elements)) {
12036 return {};
12037 }
12038 fast_literal->set(JSObject::kElementsOffset,
12039 GetConstant(boilerplate_elements));
12040 } else {
12041 // Compute the elements to store first (might have effects).
12042 if (boilerplate_elements.IsFixedDoubleArray()) {
12043 int const size = FixedDoubleArray::SizeFor(elements_length);
12044 if (size > kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize) return {};
12045 fast_literal->set(
12046 JSObject::kElementsOffset,
12047 CreateDoubleFixedArray(elements_length,
12048 boilerplate_elements.AsFixedDoubleArray()));
12049 } else {
12050 int const size = FixedArray::SizeFor(elements_length);
12051 if (size > kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize) return {};
12052 VirtualObject* elements =
12053 CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), elements_length);
12054 compiler::FixedArrayRef boilerplate_elements_as_fixed_array =
12055 boilerplate_elements.AsFixedArray();
12056 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elements_length; ++i) {
12057 if ((*max_properties)-- == 0) return {};
12058 compiler::OptionalObjectRef element_value =
12059 boilerplate_elements_as_fixed_array.TryGet(broker(), i);
12060 if (!element_value.has_value()) return {};
12061 if (element_value->IsJSObject()) {
12062 std::optional<VirtualObject*> object =
12063 TryReadBoilerplateForFastLiteral(element_value->AsJSObject(),
12064 allocation, max_depth - 1,
12065 max_properties);
12066 if (!object.has_value()) return {};
12067 elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i), *object);
12068 } else {
12069 elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
12070 GetConstant(*element_value));
12071 }
12072 }
12073
12074 fast_literal->set(JSObject::kElementsOffset, elements);
12075 }
12076 }
12077
12078 return fast_literal;
12079}
12080
12081VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::DeepCopyVirtualObject(VirtualObject* old) {
12082 CHECK_EQ(old->type(), VirtualObject::kDefault);
12083 ValueNode** slots = zone()->AllocateArray<ValueNode*>(old->slot_count());
12084 VirtualObject* vobject = NodeBase::New<VirtualObject>(
12085 zone(), 0, old->map(), NewObjectId(), old->slot_count(), slots);
12086 current_interpreter_frame_.add_object(vobject);
12087 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(old->slot_count()); i++) {
12088 vobject->set_by_index(i, old->get_by_index(i));
12089 }
12090 vobject->set_allocation(old->allocation());
12091 old->allocation()->UpdateObject(vobject);
12092 return vobject;
12093}

12097 ValueNode** slots = zone()->AllocateArray<ValueNode*>(slot_count);
12098 VirtualObject* vobject = NodeBase::New<VirtualObject>(
12099 zone(), 0, map, NewObjectId(), slot_count, slots);
12100 return vobject;
12101}

12103VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateVirtualObject(
12104 compiler::MapRef map, uint32_t slot_count_including_map) {
12105 // VirtualObjects are not added to the Maglev graph.
12106 DCHECK_GT(slot_count_including_map, 0);
12107 uint32_t slot_count = slot_count_including_map - 1;
12108 ValueNode** slots = zone()->AllocateArray<ValueNode*>(slot_count);
12109 VirtualObject* vobject = NodeBase::New<VirtualObject>(
12110 zone(), 0, map, NewObjectId(), slot_count, slots);
12111 return vobject;
12112}

12129
12130VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSObject(compiler::MapRef map) {
12131 DCHECK(!map.is_dictionary_map());
12132 DCHECK(!map.IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
12133 int slot_count = map.instance_size() / kTaggedSize;
12134 SBXCHECK_GE(slot_count, 3);
12135 VirtualObject* object = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12136 object->set(JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12137 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12138 object->set(JSObject::kElementsOffset,
12139 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12140 object->ClearSlots(JSObject::kElementsOffset,
12141 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOnePointerFillerMap));
12142 return object;
12143}
12144
12145ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSArray(compiler::MapRef map,
12146 int instance_size,
12147 ValueNode* length) {
12148 int slot_count = instance_size / kTaggedSize;
12149 SBXCHECK_GE(slot_count, 4);
12150 VirtualObject* object = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12151 object->set(JSArray::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12152 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12153 // Either the value is a Smi already, or we force a conversion to Smi and
12154 // cache the value in its alternative representation node.
12155 RETURN_IF_ABORT(GetSmiValue(length));
12156 object->set(JSArray::kElementsOffset,
12157 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12158 object->set(JSArray::kLengthOffset, length);
12159 object->ClearSlots(JSArray::kLengthOffset,
12160 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOnePointerFillerMap));
12161 return object;
12162}
12163
12164VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSArrayIterator(
12165 compiler::MapRef map, ValueNode* iterated_object, IterationKind kind) {
12166 int slot_count = map.instance_size() / kTaggedSize;
12167 SBXCHECK_EQ(slot_count, 6);
12168 VirtualObject* object = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12169 object->set(JSArrayIterator::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12170 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12171 object->set(JSArrayIterator::kElementsOffset,
12172 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12173 object->set(JSArrayIterator::kIteratedObjectOffset, iterated_object);
12174 object->set(JSArrayIterator::kNextIndexOffset, GetInt32Constant(0));
12175 object->set(JSArrayIterator::kKindOffset,
12176 GetInt32Constant(static_cast<int>(kind)));
12177 return object;
12178}
12179
12180VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSConstructor(
12181 compiler::JSFunctionRef constructor) {
12182 compiler::SlackTrackingPrediction prediction =
12183 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnInitialMapInstanceSizePrediction(
12184 constructor);
12185 int slot_count = prediction.instance_size() / kTaggedSize;
12186 VirtualObject* object =
12187 CreateVirtualObject(constructor.initial_map(broker()), slot_count);
12188 SBXCHECK_GE(slot_count, 3);
12189 object->set(JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12190 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12191 object->set(JSObject::kElementsOffset,
12192 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12193 object->ClearSlots(JSObject::kElementsOffset,
12194 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOnePointerFillerMap));
12195 return object;
12196}
12197
12198VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateFixedArray(compiler::MapRef map,
12199 int length) {
12200 int slot_count = FixedArray::SizeFor(length) / kTaggedSize;
12201 VirtualObject* array = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12202 array->set(offsetof(FixedArray, length_), GetInt32Constant(length));
12203 array->ClearSlots(offsetof(FixedArray, length_),
12204 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOnePointerFillerMap));
12205 return array;
12206}
12207
12208VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateContext(
12209 compiler::MapRef map, int length, compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info,
12210 ValueNode* previous_context, std::optional<ValueNode*> extension) {
12211 int slot_count = FixedArray::SizeFor(length) / kTaggedSize;
12212 VirtualObject* context = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12213 context->set(Context::kLengthOffset, GetInt32Constant(length));
12214 context->set(Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX),
12215 GetConstant(scope_info));
12216 context->set(Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX),
12217 previous_context);
12218 int index = Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX + 1;
12219 if (extension.has_value()) {
12220 context->set(Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX),
12221 extension.value());
12222 index++;
12223 }
12224 for (; index < length; index++) {
12225 context->set(Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index),
12226 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
12227 }
12228 return context;
12229}
12230
12231VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateArgumentsObject(
12232 compiler::MapRef map, ValueNode* length, ValueNode* elements,
12233 std::optional<ValueNode*> callee) {
12234 DCHECK_EQ(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset, JSArray::kLengthOffset);
12235 DCHECK_EQ(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset, JSArray::kLengthOffset);
12236 int slot_count = map.instance_size() / kTaggedSize;
12237 SBXCHECK_EQ(slot_count, callee.has_value() ? 5 : 4);
12238 VirtualObject* arguments = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12239 arguments->set(JSArray::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12240 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12241 arguments->set(JSArray::kElementsOffset, elements);
12242 CHECK(length->Is<Int32Constant>() || length->Is<ArgumentsLength>() ||
12243 length->Is<RestLength>());
12244 arguments->set(JSArray::kLengthOffset, length);
12245 if (callee.has_value()) {
12246 arguments->set(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kCalleeOffset, callee.value());
12247 }
12248 DCHECK(arguments->map().IsJSArgumentsObjectMap() ||
12249 arguments->map().IsJSArrayMap());
12250 return arguments;
12251}
12252
12253VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateMappedArgumentsElements(
12254 compiler::MapRef map, int mapped_count, ValueNode* context,
12255 ValueNode* unmapped_elements) {
12256 int slot_count = SloppyArgumentsElements::SizeFor(mapped_count) / kTaggedSize;
12257 VirtualObject* elements = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12258 elements->set(offsetof(SloppyArgumentsElements, length_),
12259 GetInt32Constant(mapped_count));
12260 elements->set(offsetof(SloppyArgumentsElements, context_), context);
12261 elements->set(offsetof(SloppyArgumentsElements, arguments_),
12262 unmapped_elements);
12263 return elements;
12264}

12266VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateRegExpLiteralObject(
12267 compiler::MapRef map, compiler::RegExpBoilerplateDescriptionRef literal) {
12268 DCHECK_EQ(JSRegExp::Size(), JSRegExp::kLastIndexOffset + kTaggedSize);
12269 int slot_count = JSRegExp::Size() / kTaggedSize;
12270 VirtualObject* regexp = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12271 regexp->set(JSRegExp::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12272 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12273 regexp->set(JSRegExp::kElementsOffset,
12274 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12275 regexp->set(JSRegExp::kDataOffset,
12276 GetTrustedConstant(literal.data(broker()),
12277 kRegExpDataIndirectPointerTag));
12278 regexp->set(JSRegExp::kSourceOffset, GetConstant(literal.source(broker())));
12279 regexp->set(JSRegExp::kFlagsOffset, GetInt32Constant(literal.flags()));
12280 regexp->set(JSRegExp::kLastIndexOffset,
12281 GetInt32Constant(JSRegExp::kInitialLastIndexValue));
12282 return regexp;
12283}
12284
12285VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSGeneratorObject(
12286 compiler::MapRef map, int instance_size, ValueNode* context,
12287 ValueNode* closure, ValueNode* receiver, ValueNode* register_file) {
12288 int slot_count = instance_size / kTaggedSize;
12289 InstanceType instance_type = map.instance_type();
12290 DCHECK(instance_type == JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE ||
12291 instance_type == JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE);
12292 SBXCHECK_GE(slot_count, instance_type == JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE ? 10 : 12);
12293 VirtualObject* object = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12294 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12295 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12296 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kElementsOffset,
12297 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12298 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset, context);
12299 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kFunctionOffset, closure);
12300 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kReceiverOffset, receiver);
12301 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kInputOrDebugPosOffset,
12302 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
12303 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kResumeModeOffset,
12304 GetInt32Constant(JSGeneratorObject::kNext));
12305 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset,
12306 GetInt32Constant(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting));
12307 object->set(JSGeneratorObject::kParametersAndRegistersOffset, register_file);
12308 if (instance_type == JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE) {
12309 object->set(JSAsyncGeneratorObject::kQueueOffset,
12310 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue));
12311 object->set(JSAsyncGeneratorObject::kIsAwaitingOffset, GetInt32Constant(0));
12312 }
12313 return object;
12314}

12316VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSIteratorResult(compiler::MapRef map,
12317 ValueNode* value,

12319 static_assert(JSIteratorResult::kSize == 5 * kTaggedSize);
12320 int slot_count = JSIteratorResult::kSize / kTaggedSize;
12321 VirtualObject* iter_result = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12322 iter_result->set(JSIteratorResult::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12323 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12324 iter_result->set(JSIteratorResult::kElementsOffset,
12325 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12326 iter_result->set(JSIteratorResult::kValueOffset, value);
12327 iter_result->set(JSIteratorResult::kDoneOffset, done);
12328 return iter_result;
12329}

12331VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::CreateJSStringIterator(compiler::MapRef map,
12332 ValueNode* string) {
12333 static_assert(JSStringIterator::kHeaderSize == 5 * kTaggedSize);
12334 int slot_count = JSStringIterator::kHeaderSize / kTaggedSize;
12335 VirtualObject* string_iter = CreateVirtualObject(map, slot_count);
12336 string_iter->set(JSStringIterator::kPropertiesOrHashOffset,
12337 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12338 string_iter->set(JSStringIterator::kElementsOffset,
12339 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray));
12340 string_iter->set(JSStringIterator::kStringOffset, string);
12341 string_iter->set(JSStringIterator::kIndexOffset, GetInt32Constant(0));
12342 return string_iter;
