12344
12345InlinedAllocation* MaglevGraphBuilder::ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(
12346 AllocationType allocation_type, VirtualObject* vobject) {
12347 DCHECK_LE(vobject->size(), kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize);
12348 if (!current_allocation_block_ ||
12349 current_allocation_block_->allocation_type() != allocation_type ||
12350 !v8_flags.inline_new ||
12351 compilation_unit()->info()->for_turboshaft_frontend()) {
12352 current_allocation_block_ =
12353 AddNewNode<AllocationBlock>({}, allocation_type);
12354 }
12355
12356 int current_size = current_allocation_block_->size();
12357 if (current_size + vobject->size() > kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize) {
12358 current_allocation_block_ =
12359 AddNewNode<AllocationBlock>({}, allocation_type);
12360 }
12361
12362 DCHECK_GE(current_size, 0);
12363 InlinedAllocation* allocation =
12364 AddNewNode<InlinedAllocation>({current_allocation_block_}, vobject);
12365 graph()->allocations_escape_map().emplace(allocation, zone());
12366 current_allocation_block_->Add(allocation);
12367 vobject->set_allocation(allocation);
12368 return allocation;
12369}
12370
12371void MaglevGraphBuilder::ClearCurrentAllocationBlock() {
12372 current_allocation_block_ = nullptr;
12373}
12374
12375void MaglevGraphBuilder::AddNonEscapingUses(InlinedAllocation* allocation,
12376 int use_count) {
12377 if (!v8_flags.maglev_escape_analysis) return;
12378 allocation->AddNonEscapingUses(use_count);
12379}
12380
12381void MaglevGraphBuilder::AddDeoptUse(VirtualObject* vobject) {
12382 if (vobject->type() != VirtualObject::kDefault) return;
12383 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < vobject->slot_count(); i++) {
12384 ValueNode* value = vobject->get_by_index(i);
12385 if (InlinedAllocation* nested_allocation =
12386 value->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
12387 VirtualObject* nested_object =
12388 current_interpreter_frame_.virtual_objects().FindAllocatedWith(
12389 nested_allocation);
12390 CHECK_NOT_NULL(nested_object);
12391 AddDeoptUse(nested_object);
12392 } else if (!IsConstantNode(value->opcode()) &&
12393 value->opcode() != Opcode::kArgumentsElements &&
12394 value->opcode() != Opcode::kArgumentsLength &&
12395 value->opcode() != Opcode::kRestLength) {
12396 AddDeoptUse(value);
12397 }
12398 }
12399}
12400
12401ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocationForHeapNumber(
12402 VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
12403 DCHECK(vobject->map().IsHeapNumberMap());
12404 InlinedAllocation* allocation =
12405 ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
12406 AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, 2);
12407 BuildStoreMap(allocation, broker()->heap_number_map(),
12408 StoreMap::initializing_kind(allocation_type));
12409 AddNewNode<StoreFloat64>({allocation, GetFloat64Constant(vobject->number())},
12410 static_cast<int>(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_)));
12411 return allocation;
12412}
12413
12414ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocationForDoubleFixedArray(
12415 VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
12416 DCHECK(vobject->map().IsFixedDoubleArrayMap());
12417 InlinedAllocation* allocation =
12418 ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
12419 int length = vobject->double_elements_length();
12420 AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, length + 2);
12421 BuildStoreMap(allocation, broker()->fixed_double_array_map(),
12422 StoreMap::initializing_kind(allocation_type));
12423 AddNewNode<StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier>(
12424 {allocation, GetSmiConstant(length)},
12425 static_cast<int>(offsetof(FixedDoubleArray, length_)),
12426 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
12427 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
12428 AddNewNode<StoreFloat64>(
12429 {allocation,
12430 GetFloat64Constant(
12431 vobject->double_elements().GetFromImmutableFixedDoubleArray(i))},
12432 FixedDoubleArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i));
12433 }
12434 return allocation;
12435}
12436
12437ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedAllocation(
12438 VirtualObject* vobject, AllocationType allocation_type) {
12439 current_interpreter_frame_.add_object(vobject);
12440 if (vobject->type() == VirtualObject::kHeapNumber) {
12441 return BuildInlinedAllocationForHeapNumber(vobject, allocation_type);
12442 }
12443 if (vobject->type() == VirtualObject::kFixedDoubleArray) {
12444 return BuildInlinedAllocationForDoubleFixedArray(vobject, allocation_type);
12445 }
12446 SmallZoneVector<ValueNode*, 8> values(vobject->slot_count(), zone());
12447 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < vobject->slot_count(); i++) {
12448 ValueNode* node = vobject->get_by_index(i);
12449 if (node->Is<VirtualObject>()) {
12450 VirtualObject* nested = node->Cast<VirtualObject>();
12451 node = BuildInlinedAllocation(nested, allocation_type);
12452 vobject->set_by_index(i, node);
12453 } else if (node->Is<Float64Constant>()) {
12454 node = BuildInlinedAllocationForHeapNumber(
12455 CreateHeapNumber(node->Cast<Float64Constant>()->value()),
12456 allocation_type);
12457 } else {
12458 node = GetTaggedValue(node);
12459 }
12460 values[i] = node;
12461 }
12462 InlinedAllocation* allocation =
12463 ExtendOrReallocateCurrentAllocationBlock(allocation_type, vobject);
12464 AddNonEscapingUses(allocation, vobject->slot_count() + 1);
12465 BuildStoreMap(allocation, vobject->map(),
12466 StoreMap::initializing_kind(allocation_type));
12467 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < vobject->slot_count(); i++) {
12468 BuildInitializeStore(allocation, values[i], (i + 1) * kTaggedSize);
12469 }
12470 if (is_loop_effect_tracking()) {
12471 loop_effects_->allocations.insert(allocation);
12472 }
12473 return allocation;
12474}
12475
12476ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(int start_index,
12477 int length) {
12478 DCHECK(is_inline());
12479 if (length == 0) {
12480 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
12481 }
12482 VirtualObject* elements =
12483 CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), length);
12484 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
12485 elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
12486 inlined_arguments_[i + start_index + 1]);
12487 }
12488 return elements;
12489}
12490
12491ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildInlinedUnmappedArgumentsElements(
12492 int mapped_count) {
12493 int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
12494 if (length == 0) {
12495 return GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
12496 }
12497 VirtualObject* unmapped_elements =
12498 CreateFixedArray(broker()->fixed_array_map(), length);
12499 int i = 0;
12500 for (; i < mapped_count; i++) {
12501 unmapped_elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
12502 GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kTheHoleValue));
12503 }
12504 for (; i < length; i++) {
12505 unmapped_elements->set(FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
12506 inlined_arguments_[i + 1]);
12507 }
12508 return unmapped_elements;
12509}
12510
12511template <CreateArgumentsType type>
12512VirtualObject* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildVirtualArgumentsObject() {
12513 switch (type) {
12514 case CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments:
12515 if (parameter_count_without_receiver() == 0) {
12516 // If there is no aliasing, the arguments object elements are not
12517 // special in any way, we can just return an unmapped backing store.
12518 if (is_inline()) {
12519 int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
12520 ValueNode* elements = BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(0, length);
12521 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12522 broker()->target_native_context().sloppy_arguments_map(broker()),
12523 GetInt32Constant(length), elements, GetClosure());
12524 } else {
12525 ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
12526 EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
12527 ArgumentsElements* elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
12528 {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments,
12529 parameter_count_without_receiver());
12530 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12531 broker()->target_native_context().sloppy_arguments_map(broker()),
12532 length, elements, GetClosure());
12533 }
12534 } else {
12535 // If the parameter count is zero, we should have used the unmapped
12536 // backing store.
12537 int param_count = parameter_count_without_receiver();
12538 DCHECK_GT(param_count, 0);
12539 DCHECK(CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements());
12540 int param_idx_in_ctxt = compilation_unit_->shared_function_info()
12541 .context_parameters_start() +
12542 param_count - 1;
12543 // The {unmapped_elements} correspond to the extra arguments
12544 // (overapplication) that do not need be "mapped" to the actual
12545 // arguments. Mapped arguments are accessed via the context, whereas
12546 // unmapped arguments are simply accessed via this fixed array. See
12547 // SloppyArgumentsElements in src/object/arguments.h.
12548 if (is_inline()) {
12549 int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
12550 int mapped_count = std::min(param_count, length);
12551 ValueNode* unmapped_elements =
12552 BuildInlinedUnmappedArgumentsElements(mapped_count);
12553 VirtualObject* elements = CreateMappedArgumentsElements(
12554 broker()->sloppy_arguments_elements_map(), mapped_count,
12555 GetContext(), unmapped_elements);
12556 for (int i = 0; i < mapped_count; i++, param_idx_in_ctxt--) {
12557 elements->set(SloppyArgumentsElements::OffsetOfElementAt(i),
12558 GetInt32Constant(param_idx_in_ctxt));
12559 }
12560 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12561 broker()->target_native_context().fast_aliased_arguments_map(
12562 broker()),
12563 GetInt32Constant(length), elements, GetClosure());
12564 } else {
12565 ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
12566 EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
12567 ArgumentsElements* unmapped_elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
12568 {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments, param_count);
12569 VirtualObject* elements = CreateMappedArgumentsElements(
12570 broker()->sloppy_arguments_elements_map(), param_count,
12571 GetContext(), unmapped_elements);
12572 ValueNode* the_hole_value = GetConstant(broker()->the_hole_value());
12573 for (int i = 0; i < param_count; i++, param_idx_in_ctxt--) {
12574 ValueNode* value = Select(
12575 [&](auto& builder) {
12576 return BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(builder,
12577 Operation::kLessThan,
12578 GetInt32Constant(i), length);
12579 },
12580 [&] { return GetSmiConstant(param_idx_in_ctxt); },
12581 [&] { return the_hole_value; });
12582 elements->set(SloppyArgumentsElements::OffsetOfElementAt(i), value);
12583 }
12584 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12585 broker()->target_native_context().fast_aliased_arguments_map(
12586 broker()),
12587 length, elements, GetClosure());
12588 }
12589 }
12590 case CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments:
12591 if (is_inline()) {
12592 int length = argument_count_without_receiver();
12593 ValueNode* elements = BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(0, length);
12594 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12595 broker()->target_native_context().strict_arguments_map(broker()),
12596 GetInt32Constant(length), elements);
12597 } else {
12598 ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
12599 EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
12600 ArgumentsElements* elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
12601 {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments,
12602 parameter_count_without_receiver());
12603 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12604 broker()->target_native_context().strict_arguments_map(broker()),
12605 length, elements);
12606 }
12607 case CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter:
12608 if (is_inline()) {
12609 int start_index = parameter_count_without_receiver();
12610 int length =
12611 std::max(0, argument_count_without_receiver() - start_index);
12612 ValueNode* elements =
12613 BuildInlinedArgumentsElements(start_index, length);
12614 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12615 broker()->target_native_context().js_array_packed_elements_map(
12616 broker()),
12617 GetInt32Constant(length), elements);
12618 } else {
12619 ArgumentsLength* length = AddNewNode<ArgumentsLength>({});
12620 EnsureType(length, NodeType::kSmi);
12621 ArgumentsElements* elements = AddNewNode<ArgumentsElements>(
12622 {length}, CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter,
12623 parameter_count_without_receiver());
12624 RestLength* rest_length =
12625 AddNewNode<RestLength>({}, parameter_count_without_receiver());
12626 return CreateArgumentsObject(
12627 broker()->target_native_context().js_array_packed_elements_map(
12628 broker()),
12629 rest_length, elements);
12630 }
12631 }
12632}
12633
12634template <CreateArgumentsType type>
12635ValueNode* MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject() {
12636 auto arguments = BuildVirtualArgumentsObject<type>();
12637 ValueNode* allocation =
12638 BuildInlinedAllocation(arguments, AllocationType::kYoung);
12639 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
12640 // effect clear it.
12641 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
12642 return allocation;
12643}
12644
12645MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildFastCreateObjectOrArrayLiteral(
12646 const compiler::LiteralFeedback& feedback) {
12647 compiler::AllocationSiteRef site = feedback.value();
12648 if (!site.boilerplate(broker()).has_value()) return {};
12649 AllocationType allocation_type =
12650 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnPretenureMode(site);
12651
12652 // First try to extract out the shape and values of the boilerplate, bailing
12653 // out on complex boilerplates.
12654 int max_properties = compiler::kMaxFastLiteralProperties;
12655 std::optional<VirtualObject*> maybe_value = TryReadBoilerplateForFastLiteral(
12656 *site.boilerplate(broker()), allocation_type,
12657 compiler::kMaxFastLiteralDepth, &max_properties);
12658 if (!maybe_value.has_value()) return {};
12659
12660 // Then, use the collected information to actually create nodes in the graph.
12661 // TODO(leszeks): Add support for unwinding graph modifications, so that we
12662 // can get rid of this two pass approach.
12663 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnElementsKinds(site);
12664 MaybeReduceResult result =
12665 BuildInlinedAllocation(*maybe_value, allocation_type);
12666 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
12667 // effect clear it.
12668 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
12669 return result;
12670}
12671
12672ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateObjectLiteral() {
12673 compiler::ObjectBoilerplateDescriptionRef boilerplate_desc =
12674 GetRefOperand<ObjectBoilerplateDescription>(0);
12675 FeedbackSlot slot_index = GetSlotOperand(1);
12676 int bytecode_flags = GetFlag8Operand(2);
12677 int literal_flags =
12678 interpreter::CreateObjectLiteralFlags::FlagsBits::decode(bytecode_flags);
12679 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source(feedback(), slot_index);
12680
12681 compiler::ProcessedFeedback const& processed_feedback =
12682 broker()->GetFeedbackForArrayOrObjectLiteral(feedback_source);
12683 if (processed_feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
12684 return EmitUnconditionalDeopt(
12685 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForObjectLiteral);
12686 }
12687
12688 MaybeReduceResult result =
12689 TryBuildFastCreateObjectOrArrayLiteral(processed_feedback.AsLiteral());
12690 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(result, SetAccumulator);
12691
12692 if (interpreter::CreateObjectLiteralFlags::FastCloneSupportedBit::decode(
12693 bytecode_flags)) {
12694 // TODO(victorgomes): CreateShallowObjectLiteral should not need the
12695 // boilerplate descriptor. However the current builtin checks that the
12696 // feedback exists and fallsback to CreateObjectLiteral if it doesn't.
12697 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateShallowObjectLiteral>(
12698 {}, boilerplate_desc, feedback_source, literal_flags));
12699 } else {
12700 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateObjectLiteral>(
12701 {}, boilerplate_desc, feedback_source, literal_flags));
12702 }
12703
12704 return ReduceResult::Done();
12705}
12706
12707ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateEmptyObjectLiteral() {
12708 compiler::NativeContextRef native_context = broker()->target_native_context();
12709 compiler::MapRef map =
12710 native_context.object_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
12711 DCHECK(!map.is_dictionary_map());
12712 DCHECK(!map.IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress());
12713 SetAccumulator(
12714 BuildInlinedAllocation(CreateJSObject(map), AllocationType::kYoung));
12715 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
12716 // effect clear it.
12717 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
12718 return ReduceResult::Done();
12719}
12720
12721ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCloneObject() {
12722 // CloneObject <source_idx> <flags> <feedback_slot>
12723 ValueNode* source = LoadRegister(0);
12724 ValueNode* flags =
12725 GetSmiConstant(interpreter::CreateObjectLiteralFlags::FlagsBits::decode(
12726 GetFlag8Operand(1)));
12727 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(2);
12728 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
12729 SetAccumulator(BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kCloneObjectIC>(
12730 {GetTaggedValue(source), flags}, feedback_source));
12731 return ReduceResult::Done();
12732}
12733
12734ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetTemplateObject() {
12735 // GetTemplateObject <descriptor_idx> <literal_idx>
12736 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info =
12737 compilation_unit_->shared_function_info();
12738 ValueNode* description = GetConstant(GetRefOperand<HeapObject>(0));
12739 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
12740 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
12741
12742 const compiler::ProcessedFeedback& feedback =
12743 broker()->GetFeedbackForTemplateObject(feedback_source);
12744 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
12745 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GetTemplateObject>(
12746 {description}, shared_function_info, feedback_source));
12747 return ReduceResult::Done();
12748 }
12749 compiler::JSArrayRef template_object = feedback.AsTemplateObject().value();
12750 SetAccumulator(GetConstant(template_object));
12751 return ReduceResult::Done();
12752}
12753
12754ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateClosure() {
12755 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_function_info =
12756 GetRefOperand<SharedFunctionInfo>(0);
12757 compiler::FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell =
12758 feedback().GetClosureFeedbackCell(broker(), iterator_.GetIndexOperand(1));
12759 uint32_t flags = GetFlag8Operand(2);
12760
12761 if (interpreter::CreateClosureFlags::FastNewClosureBit::decode(flags)) {
12762 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<FastCreateClosure>(
12763 {GetContext()}, shared_function_info, feedback_cell));
12764 } else {
12765 bool pretenured =
12766 interpreter::CreateClosureFlags::PretenuredBit::decode(flags);
12767 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<CreateClosure>(
12768 {GetContext()}, shared_function_info, feedback_cell, pretenured));
12769 }
12770 return ReduceResult::Done();
12771}
12772
12773MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(
12774 compiler::MapRef map, compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope, int context_length) {
12775 const int kContextAllocationLimit = 16;
12776 if (context_length > kContextAllocationLimit) return {};
12777 DCHECK_GE(context_length, Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS);
12778 auto context = CreateContext(map, context_length, scope, GetContext());
12779 ValueNode* result = BuildInlinedAllocation(context, AllocationType::kYoung);
12780 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
12781 // effect clear it.
12782 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
12783 return result;
12784}
12785
12786ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateBlockContext() {
12787 // CreateBlockContext <scope_info_idx>
12788 compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(0);
12789 compiler::MapRef map =
12790 broker()->target_native_context().block_context_map(broker());
12791
12792 auto done = [&](ValueNode* res) {
12793 graph()->record_scope_info(res, scope_info);
12794 SetAccumulator(res);
12795 };
12796
12797 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(
12798 map, scope_info, scope_info.ContextLength()),
12799 done);
12800 // Fallback.
12801 done(BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kPushBlockContext, {GetConstant(scope_info)})
12802 .value());
12803 return ReduceResult::Done();
12804}
12805
12806ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateCatchContext() {
12807 // CreateCatchContext <exception> <scope_info_idx>
12808 ValueNode* exception = LoadRegister(0);
12809 compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(1);
12810 auto context = CreateContext(
12811 broker()->target_native_context().catch_context_map(broker()),
12812 Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS, scope_info, GetContext(), exception);
12813 SetAccumulator(BuildInlinedAllocation(context, AllocationType::kYoung));
12814 graph()->record_scope_info(GetAccumulator(), scope_info);
12815 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
12816 // effect clear it.
12817 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
12818 return ReduceResult::Done();
12819}
12820
12821ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateFunctionContext() {
12822 compiler::ScopeInfoRef info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(0);
12823 uint32_t slot_count = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(1);
12824 compiler::MapRef map =
12825 broker()->target_native_context().function_context_map(broker());
12826
12827 auto done = [&](ValueNode* res) {
12828 graph()->record_scope_info(res, info);
12829 SetAccumulator(res);
12830 };
12831
12832 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
12833 TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(map, info,
12834 slot_count + Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS),
12835 done);
12836 // Fallback.
12837 done(AddNewNode<CreateFunctionContext>({GetContext()}, info, slot_count,
12838 ScopeType::FUNCTION_SCOPE));
12839 return ReduceResult::Done();
12840}
12841
12842ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateEvalContext() {
12843 compiler::ScopeInfoRef info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(0);
12844 uint32_t slot_count = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(1);
12845 compiler::MapRef map =
12846 broker()->target_native_context().eval_context_map(broker());
12847
12848 auto done = [&](ValueNode* res) {
12849 graph()->record_scope_info(res, info);
12850 SetAccumulator(res);
12851 };
12852
12853 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
12854 TryBuildInlinedAllocatedContext(map, info,
12855 slot_count + Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS),
12856 done);
12857 if (slot_count <= static_cast<uint32_t>(
12858 ConstructorBuiltins::MaximumFunctionContextSlots())) {
12859 done(AddNewNode<CreateFunctionContext>({GetContext()}, info, slot_count,
12860 ScopeType::EVAL_SCOPE));
12861 } else {
12862 done(BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewFunctionContext, {GetConstant(info)})
12863 .value());
12864 }
12865 return ReduceResult::Done();
12866}
12867
12868ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateWithContext() {
12869 // CreateWithContext <register> <scope_info_idx>
12870 ValueNode* object = LoadRegister(0);
12871 compiler::ScopeInfoRef scope_info = GetRefOperand<ScopeInfo>(1);
12872 auto context = CreateContext(
12873 broker()->target_native_context().with_context_map(broker()),
12874 Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS, scope_info, GetContext(), object);
12875 SetAccumulator(BuildInlinedAllocation(context, AllocationType::kYoung));
12876 graph()->record_scope_info(GetAccumulator(), scope_info);
12877 // TODO(leszeks): Don't eagerly clear the raw allocation, have the next side
12878 // effect clear it.
12879 ClearCurrentAllocationBlock();
12880 return ReduceResult::Done();
12881}
12882
12883bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements() {
12884 return SloppyArgumentsElements::SizeFor(parameter_count()) <=
12885 kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize;
12886}
12887
12888bool MaglevGraphBuilder::CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements() {
12889 DCHECK(is_inline());
12890 return FixedArray::SizeFor(argument_count_without_receiver()) <=
12891 kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize;
12892}
12893
12894ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateMappedArguments() {
12895 compiler::SharedFunctionInfoRef shared =
12896 compilation_unit_->shared_function_info();
12897 if (!shared.object()->has_duplicate_parameters()) {
12898 if (((is_inline() && CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements()) ||
12899 (!is_inline() && CanAllocateSloppyArgumentElements()))) {
12900 SetAccumulator(BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject<
12901 CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments>());
12902 return ReduceResult::Done();
12903 } else if (!is_inline()) {
12904 SetAccumulator(
12905 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kFastNewSloppyArguments>({GetClosure()}));
12906 return ReduceResult::Done();
12907 }
12908 }
12909 // Generic fallback.
12910 SetAccumulator(
12911 BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewSloppyArguments, {GetClosure()}).value());
12912 return ReduceResult::Done();
12913}
12914
12915ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateUnmappedArguments() {
12916 if (!is_inline() || CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements()) {
12917 SetAccumulator(BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject<
12918 CreateArgumentsType::kUnmappedArguments>());
12919 return ReduceResult::Done();
12920 }
12921 // Generic fallback.
12922 SetAccumulator(
12923 BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewStrictArguments, {GetClosure()}).value());
12924 return ReduceResult::Done();
12925}
12926
12927ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitCreateRestParameter() {
12928 if (!is_inline() || CanAllocateInlinedArgumentElements()) {
12929 SetAccumulator(
12930 BuildAndAllocateArgumentsObject<CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter>());
12931 return ReduceResult::Done();
12932 }
12933 // Generic fallback.
12934 SetAccumulator(
12935 BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kNewRestParameter, {GetClosure()}).value());
12936 return ReduceResult::Done();
12937}
12938
12939void MaglevGraphBuilder::PeelLoop() {
12940 int loop_header = iterator_.current_offset();
12941 DCHECK(loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(loop_header));
12942 DCHECK(!in_peeled_iteration());
12943 peeled_iteration_count_ = v8_flags.maglev_optimistic_peeled_loops ? 2 : 1;
12944 any_peeled_loop_ = true;
12945 allow_loop_peeling_ = false;
12946
12947 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
12948 std::cout << " * Begin loop peeling...." << std::endl;
12949 }
12950
12951 while (in_peeled_iteration()) {
12952 BuildLoopForPeeling();
12953 }
12954 // Emit the actual (not peeled) loop if needed.
12955 if (loop_header == iterator_.current_offset()) {
12956 BuildLoopForPeeling();
12957 }
12958 allow_loop_peeling_ = true;
12959}
12960
12961void MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildLoopForPeeling() {
12962 int loop_header = iterator_.current_offset();
12963 DCHECK(loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(loop_header));
12964
12965 // Since peeled loops do not start with a loop merge state, we need to
12966 // explicitly enter e loop effect tracking scope for the peeled iteration.
12967 bool track_peeled_effects =
12968 v8_flags.maglev_optimistic_peeled_loops && peeled_iteration_count_ == 2;
12969 if (track_peeled_effects) {
12970 BeginLoopEffects(loop_header);
12971 }
12972
12973#ifdef DEBUG
12974 bool was_in_peeled_iteration = in_peeled_iteration();
12975#endif // DEBUG
12976
12977 while (iterator_.current_bytecode() != interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpLoop) {
12978 local_isolate_->heap()->Safepoint();
12979 VisitSingleBytecode();
12980 iterator_.Advance();
12981 }
12982
12983 VisitSingleBytecode(); // VisitJumpLoop
12984
12985 DCHECK_EQ(was_in_peeled_iteration, in_peeled_iteration());
12986 if (!in_peeled_iteration()) {
12987 return;
12988 }
12989
12990 // In case the peeled iteration was mergeable (see TryMergeLoop) or the
12991 // JumpLoop was dead, we are done.
12992 if (!current_block_) {
12993 decremented_predecessor_offsets_.clear();
12994 KillPeeledLoopTargets(peeled_iteration_count_);
12995 peeled_iteration_count_ = 0;
12996 if (track_peeled_effects) {
12997 EndLoopEffects(loop_header);
12998 }
12999 return;
13000 }
13001
13002 peeled_iteration_count_--;
13003
13004 // After processing the peeled iteration and reaching the `JumpLoop`, we
13005 // re-process the loop body. For this, we need to reset the graph building
13006 // state roughly as if we didn't process it yet.
13007
13008 // Reset position in exception handler table to before the loop.
13009 HandlerTable table(*bytecode().object());
13010 while (next_handler_table_index_ > 0) {
13011 next_handler_table_index_--;
13012 int start = table.GetRangeStart(next_handler_table_index_);
13013 if (start < loop_header) break;
13014 }
13015
13016 // Re-create catch handler merge states.
13017 for (int offset = loop_header; offset <= iterator_.current_offset();
13018 ++offset) {
13019 if (auto& merge_state = merge_states_[offset]) {
13020 if (merge_state->is_exception_handler()) {
13021 merge_state = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForCatchBlock(
13022 *compilation_unit_, merge_state->frame_state().liveness(), offset,
13023 merge_state->exception_handler_was_used(),
13024 merge_state->catch_block_context_register(), graph_);
13025 } else {
13026 // We only peel innermost loops.
13027 DCHECK(!merge_state->is_loop());
13028 merge_state = nullptr;
13029 }
13030 }
13031 new (&jump_targets_[offset]) BasicBlockRef();
13032 }
13033
13034 // Reset predecessors as if the loop body had not been visited.
13035 for (int offset : decremented_predecessor_offsets_) {
13036 DCHECK_GE(offset, loop_header);
13037 if (offset <= iterator_.current_offset()) {
13038 UpdatePredecessorCount(offset, 1);
13039 }
13040 }
13041 decremented_predecessor_offsets_.clear();
13042
13043 DCHECK(current_block_);
13044 // After resetting, the actual loop header always has exactly 2
13045 // predecessors: the two copies of `JumpLoop`.
13046 InitializePredecessorCount(loop_header, 2);
13047 merge_states_[loop_header] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::NewForLoop(
13048 current_interpreter_frame_, *compilation_unit_, loop_header, 2,
13049 GetInLivenessFor(loop_header),
13050 &bytecode_analysis_.GetLoopInfoFor(loop_header),
13051 /* has_been_peeled */ true);
13052
13053 BasicBlock* block = FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[loop_header]);
13054 // If we ever want more peelings, we should ensure that only the last one
13055 // creates a loop header.
13056 DCHECK_LE(peeled_iteration_count_, 1);
13057 DCHECK_IMPLIES(in_peeled_iteration(),
13058 v8_flags.maglev_optimistic_peeled_loops);
13059 merge_states_[loop_header]->InitializeLoop(
13060 this, *compilation_unit_, current_interpreter_frame_, block,
13061 in_peeled_iteration(), loop_effects_);
13062
13063 if (track_peeled_effects) {
13064 EndLoopEffects(loop_header);
13065 }
13066 DCHECK_NE(iterator_.current_offset(), loop_header);
13067 iterator_.SetOffset(loop_header);
13068}
13069
13070void MaglevGraphBuilder::OsrAnalyzePrequel() {
13071 DCHECK_EQ(compilation_unit_->info()->toplevel_compilation_unit(),
13072 compilation_unit_);
13073
13074 // TODO(olivf) We might want to start collecting known_node_aspects_ here.
13075 for (iterator_.SetOffset(0); iterator_.current_offset() != entrypoint_;
13076 iterator_.Advance()) {
13077 switch (iterator_.current_bytecode()) {
13078 case interpreter::Bytecode::kPushContext: {
13079 graph()->record_scope_info(GetContext(), {});
13080 // Nothing left to analyze...
13081 return;
13082 }
13083 default:
13084 continue;
13085 }
13086 }
13087}
13088
13089void MaglevGraphBuilder::BeginLoopEffects(int loop_header) {
13090 loop_effects_stack_.push_back(zone()->New<LoopEffects>(loop_header, zone()));
13091 loop_effects_ = loop_effects_stack_.back();
13092}
13093
13094void MaglevGraphBuilder::EndLoopEffects(int loop_header) {
13095 DCHECK_EQ(loop_effects_, loop_effects_stack_.back());
13096 DCHECK_EQ(loop_effects_->loop_header, loop_header);
13097 // TODO(olivf): Update merge states dominated by the loop header with
13098 // information we know to be unaffected by the loop.
13099 if (merge_states_[loop_header] && merge_states_[loop_header]->is_loop()) {
13100 merge_states_[loop_header]->set_loop_effects(loop_effects_);
13101 }
13102 if (loop_effects_stack_.size() > 1) {
13103 LoopEffects* inner_effects = loop_effects_;
13104 loop_effects_ = *(loop_effects_stack_.end() - 2);
13105 loop_effects_->Merge(inner_effects);
13106 } else {
13107 loop_effects_ = nullptr;
13108 }
13109 loop_effects_stack_.pop_back();
13110}
13111
13112ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpLoop() {
13113 const uint32_t relative_jump_bytecode_offset =
13114 iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(0);
13115 const int32_t loop_offset = iterator_.GetImmediateOperand(1);
13116 const FeedbackSlot feedback_slot = iterator_.GetSlotOperand(2);
13117 int target = iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset();
13118
13119 if (ShouldEmitInterruptBudgetChecks()) {
13120 int reduction = relative_jump_bytecode_offset *
13121 v8_flags.osr_from_maglev_interrupt_scale_factor;
13122 AddNewNode<ReduceInterruptBudgetForLoop>({}, reduction > 0 ? reduction : 1);
13123 } else {
13124 AddNewNode<HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupt>({});
13125 }
13126
13127 if (ShouldEmitOsrInterruptBudgetChecks()) {
13128 AddNewNode<TryOnStackReplacement>(
13129 {GetClosure()}, loop_offset, feedback_slot,
13130 BytecodeOffset(iterator_.current_offset()), compilation_unit_);
13131 }
13132
13133 bool is_peeled_loop = loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(target);
13134 auto FinishLoopBlock = [&]() {
13135 return FinishBlock<JumpLoop>({}, jump_targets_[target].block_ptr());
13136 };
13137 if (is_peeled_loop && in_peeled_iteration()) {
13138 ClobberAccumulator();
13139 if (in_optimistic_peeling_iteration()) {
13140 // Let's see if we can finish this loop without peeling it.
13141 if (!merge_states_[target]->TryMergeLoop(this, current_interpreter_frame_,
13142 FinishLoopBlock)) {
13143 merge_states_[target]->MergeDeadLoop(*compilation_unit());
13144 }
13145 if (is_loop_effect_tracking_enabled()) {
13146 EndLoopEffects(target);
13147 }
13148 }
13149 } else {
13150 BasicBlock* block = FinishLoopBlock();
13151 merge_states_[target]->MergeLoop(this, current_interpreter_frame_, block);
13152 block->set_predecessor_id(merge_states_[target]->predecessor_count() - 1);
13153 if (is_peeled_loop) {
13154 DCHECK(!in_peeled_iteration());
13155 }
13156 if (is_loop_effect_tracking_enabled()) {
13157 EndLoopEffects(target);
13158 }
13159 }
13160 return ReduceResult::Done();
13161}
13162ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJump() {
13163 BasicBlock* block =
13164 FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset()]);
13165 MergeIntoFrameState(block, iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset());
13166 DCHECK_EQ(current_block_, nullptr);
13167 DCHECK_LT(next_offset(), bytecode().length());
13168 return ReduceResult::Done();
13169}
13170ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpConstant() { return VisitJump(); }
13171ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfNullConstant() {
13172 return VisitJumpIfNull();
13173}
13174ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfNotNullConstant() {
13175 return VisitJumpIfNotNull();
13176}
13177ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfUndefinedConstant() {
13178 return VisitJumpIfUndefined();
13179}
13180ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfNotUndefinedConstant() {
13181 return VisitJumpIfNotUndefined();
13182}
13183ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfUndefinedOrNullConstant() {
13184 return VisitJumpIfUndefinedOrNull();
13185}
13186ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfTrueConstant() {
13187 return VisitJumpIfTrue();
13188}
13189ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfFalseConstant() {
13190 return VisitJumpIfFalse();
13191}
13192ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfJSReceiverConstant() {
13193 return VisitJumpIfJSReceiver();
13194}
13195ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfForInDoneConstant() {
13196 return VisitJumpIfForInDone();
13197}
13198ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfToBooleanTrueConstant() {
13199 return VisitJumpIfToBooleanTrue();
13200}
13201ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfToBooleanFalseConstant() {
13202 return VisitJumpIfToBooleanFalse();
13203}
13204
13205void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeIntoFrameState(BasicBlock* predecessor,
13206 int target) {
13207 if (merge_states_[target] == nullptr) {
13208 bool jumping_to_peeled_iteration = bytecode_analysis().IsLoopHeader(target);
13209 DCHECK_EQ(jumping_to_peeled_iteration,
13210 loop_headers_to_peel_.Contains(target));
13211 const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetInLivenessFor(target);
13212 if (jumping_to_peeled_iteration) {
13213 // The peeled iteration is missing the backedge.
13214 DecrementDeadPredecessorAndAccountForPeeling(target);
13215 }
13216 // If there's no target frame state, allocate a new one.
13217 merge_states_[target] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::New(
13218 *compilation_unit_, current_interpreter_frame_, target,
13219 predecessor_count(target), predecessor, liveness);
13220 } else {
13221 // If there already is a frame state, merge.
13222 merge_states_[target]->Merge(this, current_interpreter_frame_, predecessor);
13223 }
13224}
13225
13226void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeDeadIntoFrameState(int target) {
13227 // If there already is a frame state, merge.
13228 if (merge_states_[target]) {
13229 DCHECK_EQ(merge_states_[target]->predecessor_count(),
13230 predecessor_count(target));
13231 merge_states_[target]->MergeDead(*compilation_unit_);
13232 // If this merge is the last one which kills a loop merge, remove that
13233 // merge state.
13234 if (merge_states_[target]->is_unmerged_unreachable_loop()) {
13235 if (v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building) {
13236 std::cout << "! Killing loop merge state at @" << target << std::endl;
13237 }
13238 merge_states_[target] = nullptr;
13239 }
13240 }
13241 // If there is no merge state yet, don't create one, but just reduce the
13242 // number of possible predecessors to zero.
13243 DecrementDeadPredecessorAndAccountForPeeling(target);
13244}
13245
13246void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeDeadLoopIntoFrameState(int target) {
13247 // Check if the Loop entry is dead already (e.g. an outer loop from OSR).
13248 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!merge_states_[target]) && predecessor_count(target) == 0) {
13249 static_assert(kLoopsMustBeEnteredThroughHeader);
13250 return;
13251 }
13252 // If there already is a frame state, merge.
13253 if (V8_LIKELY(merge_states_[target])) {
13254 DCHECK_EQ(merge_states_[target]->predecessor_count(),
13255 predecessor_count(target));
13256 if (is_loop_effect_tracking_enabled() &&
13257 !merge_states_[target]->is_unmerged_unreachable_loop()) {
13258 EndLoopEffects(target);
13259 }
13260 merge_states_[target]->MergeDeadLoop(*compilation_unit_);
13261 }
13262 // If there is no merge state yet, don't create one, but just reduce the
13263 // number of possible predecessors to zero.
13264 DecrementDeadPredecessorAndAccountForPeeling(target);
13265}
13266
13267void MaglevGraphBuilder::MergeIntoInlinedReturnFrameState(
13268 BasicBlock* predecessor) {
13269 int target = inline_exit_offset();
13270 if (merge_states_[target] == nullptr) {
13271 // All returns should have the same liveness, which is that only the
13272 // accumulator is live.
13273 const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetInLiveness();
13274 DCHECK(liveness->AccumulatorIsLive());
13275 DCHECK_EQ(liveness->live_value_count(), 1);
13276
13277 // If there's no target frame state, allocate a new one.
13278 merge_states_[target] = MergePointInterpreterFrameState::New(
13279 *compilation_unit_, current_interpreter_frame_, target,
13280 predecessor_count(target), predecessor, liveness);
13281 } else {
13282 // Again, all returns should have the same liveness, so double check this.
13283 DCHECK(GetInLiveness()->Equals(
13284 *merge_states_[target]->frame_state().liveness()));
13285 merge_states_[target]->Merge(this, current_interpreter_frame_, predecessor);
13286 }
13287}
13288
13289MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult
13290MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfReferenceEqual(BranchBuilder& builder,
13291 ValueNode* lhs,
13292 ValueNode* rhs) {
13293 if (RootConstant* root_constant = rhs->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
13294 return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({lhs}, root_constant->index());
13295 }
13296 if (RootConstant* root_constant = lhs->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
13297 return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({rhs}, root_constant->index());
13298 }
13299 if (InlinedAllocation* alloc_lhs = lhs->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
13300 if (InlinedAllocation* alloc_rhs = rhs->TryCast<InlinedAllocation>()) {
13301 return builder.FromBool(alloc_lhs == alloc_rhs);
13302 }
13303 }
13304
13305 return builder.Build<BranchIfReferenceEqual>({lhs, rhs});
13306}
13307
13308void MaglevGraphBuilder::MarkBranchDeadAndJumpIfNeeded(bool is_jump_taken) {
13309 int jump_offset = iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset();
13310 if (is_jump_taken) {
13311 BasicBlock* block = FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[jump_offset]);
13312 MergeDeadIntoFrameState(next_offset());
13313 MergeIntoFrameState(block, jump_offset);
13314 } else {
13315 MergeDeadIntoFrameState(jump_offset);
13316 }
13317}

13319#ifdef DEBUG
13320namespace {
13321bool IsNumberRootConstant(RootIndex root_index) {
13322 switch (root_index) {
13323#define CASE(type, name, label) case RootIndex::k##label:
13324 SMI_ROOT_LIST(CASE)
13325 STRONG_READ_ONLY_HEAP_NUMBER_ROOT_LIST(CASE)
13326 return true;
13327 default:
13328 return false;
13329 }
13330#undef CASE
13331}
13332} // namespace
13333#endif
13334
13335MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfRootConstant(
13336 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node, RootIndex root_index) {
13337 // We assume that Maglev never emits a comparison to a root number.
13338 DCHECK(!IsNumberRootConstant(root_index));
13339
13340 // If the node we're checking is in the accumulator, swap it in the branch
13341 // with the checked value. Cache whether we want to swap, since after we've
13342 // swapped the accumulator isn't the original node anymore.
13343 BranchBuilder::PatchAccumulatorInBranchScope scope(builder, node, root_index);
13344
13345 if (node->properties().value_representation() ==
13346 ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
13347 if (root_index == RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) {
13348 return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64IsHole>({node});
13349 }
13350 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13351 }
13352
13353 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kNumber)) {
13354 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13355 }
13356 CHECK(node->is_tagged());
13357
13358 if (root_index != RootIndex::kTrueValue &&
13359 root_index != RootIndex::kFalseValue &&
13360 CheckType(node, NodeType::kBoolean)) {
13361 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13362 }
13363
13364 while (LogicalNot* logical_not = node->TryCast<LogicalNot>()) {
13365 // Bypassing logical not(s) on the input and swapping true/false
13366 // destinations.
13367 node = logical_not->value().node();
13368 builder.SwapTargets();
13369 }
13370
13371 if (RootConstant* constant = node->TryCast<RootConstant>()) {
13372 return builder.FromBool(constant->index() == root_index);
13373 }
13374
13375 if (root_index == RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) {
13376 if (Constant* constant = node->TryCast<Constant>()) {
13377 return builder.FromBool(constant->object().IsUndefined());
13378 }
13379 }
13380
13381 if (root_index != RootIndex::kTrueValue &&
13382 root_index != RootIndex::kFalseValue) {
13383 return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node}, root_index);
13384 }
13385 if (root_index == RootIndex::kFalseValue) {
13386 builder.SwapTargets();
13387 }
13388 switch (node->opcode()) {
13389 case Opcode::kTaggedEqual:
13390 return BuildBranchIfReferenceEqual(
13391 builder, node->Cast<TaggedEqual>()->lhs().node(),
13392 node->Cast<TaggedEqual>()->rhs().node());
13393 case Opcode::kTaggedNotEqual:
13394 // Swapped true and false targets.
13395 builder.SwapTargets();
13396 return BuildBranchIfReferenceEqual(
13397 builder, node->Cast<TaggedNotEqual>()->lhs().node(),
13398 node->Cast<TaggedNotEqual>()->rhs().node());
13399 case Opcode::kInt32Compare:
13400 return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32Compare>(
13401 {node->Cast<Int32Compare>()->left_input().node(),
13402 node->Cast<Int32Compare>()->right_input().node()},
13403 node->Cast<Int32Compare>()->operation());
13404 case Opcode::kFloat64Compare:
13405 return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64Compare>(
13406 {node->Cast<Float64Compare>()->left_input().node(),
13407 node->Cast<Float64Compare>()->right_input().node()},
13408 node->Cast<Float64Compare>()->operation());
13409 case Opcode::kInt32ToBoolean:
13410 if (node->Cast<Int32ToBoolean>()->flip()) {
13411 builder.SwapTargets();
13412 }
13413 return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue>(
13414 {node->Cast<Int32ToBoolean>()->value().node()});
13415 case Opcode::kFloat64ToBoolean:
13416 if (node->Cast<Float64ToBoolean>()->flip()) {
13417 builder.SwapTargets();
13418 }
13419 return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue>(
13420 {node->Cast<Float64ToBoolean>()->value().node()});
13421 case Opcode::kTestUndetectable:
13422 return builder.Build<BranchIfUndetectable>(
13423 {node->Cast<TestUndetectable>()->value().node()},
13424 node->Cast<TestUndetectable>()->check_type());
13425 case Opcode::kHoleyFloat64IsHole:
13426 return builder.Build<BranchIfFloat64IsHole>(
13427 {node->Cast<HoleyFloat64IsHole>()->input().node()});
13428 default:
13429 return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node}, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
13430 }
13431}
13432
13433MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfTrue(
13434 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
13435 builder.SetBranchSpecializationMode(BranchSpecializationMode::kAlwaysBoolean);
13436 return BuildBranchIfRootConstant(builder, node, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
13437}
13438
13439MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfNull(
13440 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
13441 return BuildBranchIfRootConstant(builder, node, RootIndex::kNullValue);
13442}
13443
13444MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUndefined(
13445 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
13446 return BuildBranchIfRootConstant(builder, node, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
13447}
13448
13449MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult
13450MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUndefinedOrNull(BranchBuilder& builder,
13451 ValueNode* node) {
13452 compiler::OptionalHeapObjectRef maybe_constant = TryGetConstant(node);
13453 if (maybe_constant.has_value()) {
13454 return builder.FromBool(maybe_constant->IsNullOrUndefined());
13455 }
13456 if (!node->is_tagged()) {
13457 if (node->properties().value_representation() ==
13458 ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
13459 return BuildBranchIfFloat64IsHole(builder, node);
13460 }
13461 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13462 }
13463 if (HasDifferentType(node, NodeType::kOddball)) {
13464 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13465 }
13466 return builder.Build<BranchIfUndefinedOrNull>({node});
13467}
13468
13469MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfToBooleanTrue(
13470 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* node) {
13471 // If this is a known boolean, use the non-ToBoolean version.
13472 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kBoolean)) {
13473 return BuildBranchIfTrue(builder, node);
13474 }
13475
13476 // There shouldn't be any LogicalNots here, for swapping true/false, since
13477 // these are known to be boolean and should have gone throught the
13478 // non-ToBoolean path.
13479 DCHECK(!node->Is<LogicalNot>());
13480
13481 bool known_to_boolean_value = false;
13482 bool direction_is_true = true;
13483 if (IsConstantNode(node->opcode())) {
13484 known_to_boolean_value = true;
13485 direction_is_true = FromConstantToBool(local_isolate(), node);
13486 } else {
13487 // TODO(victorgomes): Unify this with TestUndetectable?
13488 // JSReceivers are true iff they are not marked as undetectable. Check if
13489 // all maps have the same detectability, and if yes, the boolean value is
13490 // known.
13491 NodeInfo* node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
13492 if (node_info && NodeTypeIs(node_info->type(), NodeType::kJSReceiver) &&
13493 node_info->possible_maps_are_known()) {
13494 bool all_detectable = true;
13495 bool all_undetectable = true;
13496 for (compiler::MapRef map : node_info->possible_maps()) {
13497 bool is_undetectable = map.is_undetectable();
13498 all_detectable &= !is_undetectable;
13499 all_undetectable &= is_undetectable;
13500 }
13501 if (all_detectable || all_undetectable) {
13502 known_to_boolean_value = true;
13503 direction_is_true = all_detectable;
13504 }
13505 }
13506 }
13507 if (known_to_boolean_value) {
13508 return builder.FromBool(direction_is_true);
13509 }
13510
13511 switch (node->value_representation()) {
13512 // The ToBoolean of both the_hole and NaN is false, so we can use the
13513 // same operation for HoleyFloat64 and Float64.
13514 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
13515 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
13516 return BuildBranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue(builder, node);
13517
13518 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
13519 // Uint32 has the same logic as Int32 when converting ToBoolean, namely
13520 // comparison against zero, so we can cast it and ignore the signedness.
13521 node = AddNewNode<TruncateUint32ToInt32>({node});
13522 [[fallthrough]];
13523 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
13524 return BuildBranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue(builder, node);
13525
13526 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
13527 UNREACHABLE();
13528
13529 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
13530 break;
13531 }
13532
13533 NodeInfo* node_info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(node);
13534 if (node_info) {
13535 if (ValueNode* as_int32 = node_info->alternative().int32()) {
13536 return BuildBranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue(builder, as_int32);
13537 }
13538 if (ValueNode* as_float64 = node_info->alternative().float64()) {
13539 return BuildBranchIfFloat64ToBooleanTrue(builder, as_float64);
13540 }
13541 }
13542
13543 NodeType old_type;
13544 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kBoolean, &old_type)) {
13545 return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node}, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
13546 }
13547 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kSmi)) {
13548 builder.SwapTargets();
13549 return builder.Build<BranchIfReferenceEqual>({node, GetSmiConstant(0)});
13550 }
13551 if (CheckType(node, NodeType::kString)) {
13552 builder.SwapTargets();
13553 return builder.Build<BranchIfRootConstant>({node},
13554 RootIndex::kempty_string);
13555 }
13556 // TODO(verwaest): Number or oddball.
13557 return builder.Build<BranchIfToBooleanTrue>({node}, GetCheckType(old_type));
13558}
13559
13560MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult
13561MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue(BranchBuilder& builder,
13562 ValueNode* node) {
13563 // TODO(victorgomes): Optimize.
13564 return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32ToBooleanTrue>({node});
13565}

13625
13626MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfJSReceiver(
13627 BranchBuilder& builder, ValueNode* value) {
13628 if (!value->is_tagged() && value->properties().value_representation() !=
13629 ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64) {
13630 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13631 }
13632 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) {
13633 return builder.AlwaysTrue();
13634 } else if (HasDifferentType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) {
13635 return builder.AlwaysFalse();
13636 }
13637 return builder.Build<BranchIfJSReceiver>({value});
13638}
13639
13640MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(
13641 BranchBuilder& builder, Operation op, ValueNode* lhs, ValueNode* rhs) {
13642 auto lhs_const = TryGetInt32Constant(lhs);
13643 if (lhs_const) {
13644 auto rhs_const = TryGetInt32Constant(rhs);
13645 if (rhs_const) {
13646 return builder.FromBool(
13647 CompareInt32(lhs_const.value(), rhs_const.value(), op));
13648 }
13649 }
13650 return builder.Build<BranchIfInt32Compare>({lhs, rhs}, op);
13651}
13652
13653MaglevGraphBuilder::BranchResult MaglevGraphBuilder::BuildBranchIfUint32Compare(
13654 BranchBuilder& builder, Operation op, ValueNode* lhs, ValueNode* rhs) {
13655 auto lhs_const = TryGetUint32Constant(lhs);
13656 if (lhs_const) {
13657 auto rhs_const = TryGetUint32Constant(rhs);
13658 if (rhs_const) {
13659 return builder.FromBool(
13660 CompareUint32(lhs_const.value(), rhs_const.value(), op));
13661 }
13662 }
13663 return builder.Build<BranchIfUint32Compare>({lhs, rhs}, op);
13664}
13665
13666ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfJSReceiver() {
13667 auto branch_builder = CreateBranchBuilder();
13668 BuildBranchIfJSReceiver(branch_builder, GetAccumulator());
13669 return ReduceResult::Done();
13670}
13671
13672ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitJumpIfForInDone() {
13673 // JumpIfForInDone <target> <index> <cache_length>
13674 ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
13675 ValueNode* cache_length = LoadRegister(2);
13676 auto branch_builder = CreateBranchBuilder();
13677 BuildBranchIfInt32Compare(branch_builder, Operation::kEqual, index,
13678 cache_length);
13679 return ReduceResult::Done();
13680}
13681
13682ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSwitchOnSmiNoFeedback() {
13683 // SwitchOnSmiNoFeedback <table_start> <table_length> <case_value_base>
13684 interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffsets offsets =
13685 iterator_.GetJumpTableTargetOffsets();
13686
13687 if (offsets.size() == 0) return ReduceResult::Done();
13688
13689 int case_value_base = (*offsets.begin()).case_value;
13690 BasicBlockRef* targets = zone()->AllocateArray<BasicBlockRef>(offsets.size());
13691 for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
13692 BasicBlockRef* ref = &targets[offset.case_value - case_value_base];
13693 new (ref) BasicBlockRef(&jump_targets_[offset.target_offset]);
13694 }
13695
13696 ValueNode* case_value = GetAccumulator();
13697 BasicBlock* block =
13698 FinishBlock<Switch>({case_value}, case_value_base, targets,
13699 offsets.size(), &jump_targets_[next_offset()]);
13700 for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
13701 MergeIntoFrameState(block, offset.target_offset);
13702 }
13703 StartFallthroughBlock(next_offset(), block);
13704 return ReduceResult::Done();
13705}
13706
13707ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInEnumerate() {
13708 // ForInEnumerate <receiver>
13709 ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
13710 // Pass receiver to ForInPrepare.
13711 current_for_in_state.receiver = receiver;
13712 SetAccumulator(
13713 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kForInEnumerate>({GetTaggedValue(receiver)}));
13714 return ReduceResult::Done();
13715}
13716
13717ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInPrepare() {
13718 // ForInPrepare <cache_info_triple>
13719 ValueNode* enumerator = GetAccumulator();
13720 // Catch the receiver value passed from ForInEnumerate.
13721 ValueNode* receiver = current_for_in_state.receiver;
13722 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(1);
13723 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
13724 // TODO(v8:7700): Use feedback and create fast path.
13725 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
13726 interpreter::Register cache_type_reg = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0);
13727 interpreter::Register cache_array_reg{cache_type_reg.index() + 1};
13728 interpreter::Register cache_length_reg{cache_type_reg.index() + 2};
13729
13730 ForInHint hint = broker()->GetFeedbackForForIn(feedback_source);
13731
13732 current_for_in_state = ForInState();
13733 switch (hint) {
13734 case ForInHint::kNone:
13735 case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices:
13736 case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeys: {
13737 // Check that the {enumerator} is a Map.
13738 // The direct IsMap check requires reading of an instance type, so in
13739 // order to avoid additional load we compare the {enumerator} against
13740 // receiver's Map instead (by definition, the {enumerator} is either
13741 // the receiver's Map or a FixedArray).
13742 auto* receiver_map =
13743 BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
13744 AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>({receiver_map, enumerator});
13745
13746 auto* descriptor_array =
13747 BuildLoadTaggedField(enumerator, Map::kInstanceDescriptorsOffset);
13748 auto* enum_cache = BuildLoadTaggedField(
13749 descriptor_array, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheOffset);
13750 auto* cache_array =
13751 BuildLoadTaggedField(enum_cache, EnumCache::kKeysOffset);
13752
13753 auto* cache_length = AddNewNode<LoadEnumCacheLength>({enumerator});
13754
13755 if (hint == ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices) {
13756 auto* cache_indices =
13757 BuildLoadTaggedField(enum_cache, EnumCache::kIndicesOffset);
13758 current_for_in_state.enum_cache_indices = cache_indices;
13759 AddNewNode<CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared>({cache_indices, cache_length});
13760 } else {
13761 current_for_in_state.enum_cache_indices = nullptr;
13762 }
13763
13764 MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
13765 cache_type_reg);
13766 StoreRegister(cache_array_reg, cache_array);
13767 StoreRegister(cache_length_reg, cache_length);
13768 break;
13769 }
13770 case ForInHint::kAny: {
13771 // The result of the bytecode is output in registers |cache_info_triple|
13772 // to |cache_info_triple + 2|, with the registers holding cache_type,
13773 // cache_array, and cache_length respectively.
13774 //
13775 // We set the cache type first (to the accumulator value), and write
13776 // the other two with a ForInPrepare builtin call. This can lazy deopt,
13777 // which will write to cache_array and cache_length, with cache_type
13778 // already set on the translation frame.
13779
13780 // This move needs to happen before ForInPrepare to avoid lazy deopt
13781 // extending the lifetime of the {cache_type} register.
13782 MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
13783 cache_type_reg);
13784 ForInPrepare* result =
13785 AddNewNode<ForInPrepare>({context, enumerator}, feedback_source);
13786 StoreRegisterPair({cache_array_reg, cache_length_reg}, result);
13787 // Force a conversion to Int32 for the cache length value.
13788 EnsureInt32(cache_length_reg);
13789 break;
13790 }
13791 }
13792 return ReduceResult::Done();
13793}
13794
13795ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInNext() {
13796 // ForInNext <receiver> <index> <cache_info_pair>
13797 ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
13798 interpreter::Register cache_type_reg, cache_array_reg;
13799 std::tie(cache_type_reg, cache_array_reg) =
13800 iterator_.GetRegisterPairOperand(2);
13801 ValueNode* cache_type = current_interpreter_frame_.get(cache_type_reg);
13802 ValueNode* cache_array = current_interpreter_frame_.get(cache_array_reg);
13803 FeedbackSlot slot = GetSlotOperand(3);
13804 compiler::FeedbackSource feedback_source{feedback(), slot};
13805
13806 ForInHint hint = broker()->GetFeedbackForForIn(feedback_source);
13807
13808 switch (hint) {
13809 case ForInHint::kNone:
13810 case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices:
13811 case ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeys: {
13812 ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
13813 // Ensure that the expected map still matches that of the {receiver}.
13814 auto* receiver_map =
13815 BuildLoadTaggedField(receiver, HeapObject::kMapOffset);
13816 AddNewNode<CheckDynamicValue>({receiver_map, cache_type});
13817 auto* key = BuildLoadFixedArrayElement(cache_array, index);
13818 EnsureType(key, NodeType::kInternalizedString);
13819 SetAccumulator(key);
13820
13821 current_for_in_state.receiver = receiver;
13822 if (ToObject* to_object =
13823 current_for_in_state.receiver->TryCast<ToObject>()) {
13824 current_for_in_state.receiver = to_object->value_input().node();
13825 }
13826 current_for_in_state.receiver_needs_map_check = false;
13827 current_for_in_state.cache_type = cache_type;
13828 current_for_in_state.key = key;
13829 if (hint == ForInHint::kEnumCacheKeysAndIndices) {
13830 current_for_in_state.index = index;
13831 }
13832 // We know that the enum cache entry is not undefined, so skip over the
13833 // next JumpIfUndefined.
13834 DCHECK(iterator_.next_bytecode() ==
13835 interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpIfUndefined ||
13836 iterator_.next_bytecode() ==
13837 interpreter::Bytecode::kJumpIfUndefinedConstant);
13838 iterator_.Advance();
13839 MergeDeadIntoFrameState(iterator_.GetJumpTargetOffset());
13840 break;
13841 }
13842 case ForInHint::kAny: {
13843 ValueNode* index = LoadRegister(1);
13844 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
13845 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<ForInNext>(
13846 {context, receiver, cache_array, cache_type, index},
13847 feedback_source));
13848 break;
13849 };
13850 }
13851 return ReduceResult::Done();
13852}
13853
13854ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitForInStep() {
13855 interpreter::Register index_reg = iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0);
13856 ValueNode* index = current_interpreter_frame_.get(index_reg);
13857 StoreRegister(index_reg,
13858 AddNewNode<Int32NodeFor<Operation::kIncrement>>({index}));
13859 if (!in_peeled_iteration()) {
13860 // With loop peeling, only the `ForInStep` in the non-peeled loop body marks
13861 // the end of for-in.
13862 current_for_in_state = ForInState();
13863 }
13864 return ReduceResult::Done();
13865}
13866
13867ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSetPendingMessage() {
13868 ValueNode* message = GetAccumulator();
13869 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<SetPendingMessage>({message}));
13870 return ReduceResult::Done();
13871}
13872
13873ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrow() {
13874 ValueNode* exception = GetAccumulator();
13875 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrow, {exception});
13876}
13877ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitReThrow() {
13878 ValueNode* exception = GetAccumulator();
13879 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kReThrow, {exception});
13880}
13881
13882ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitReturn() {
13883 // See also: InterpreterAssembler::UpdateInterruptBudgetOnReturn.
13884 const uint32_t relative_jump_bytecode_offset = iterator_.current_offset();
13885 if (ShouldEmitInterruptBudgetChecks() && relative_jump_bytecode_offset > 0) {
13886 AddNewNode<ReduceInterruptBudgetForReturn>({},
13887 relative_jump_bytecode_offset);
13888 }
13889
13890 if (!is_inline()) {
13891 FinishBlock<Return>({GetAccumulator()});
13892 return ReduceResult::Done();
13893 }
13894
13895 // All inlined function returns instead jump to one past the end of the
13896 // bytecode, where we'll later create a final basic block which resumes
13897 // execution of the caller. If there is only one return, at the end of the
13898 // function, we can elide this jump and just continue in the same basic block.
13899 if (iterator_.next_offset() != inline_exit_offset() ||
13900 predecessor_count(inline_exit_offset()) > 1) {
13901 BasicBlock* block =
13902 FinishBlock<Jump>({}, &jump_targets_[inline_exit_offset()]);
13903 // The context is dead by now, set it to optimized out to avoid creating
13904 // unnecessary phis.
13905 SetContext(GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOptimizedOut));
13906 MergeIntoInlinedReturnFrameState(block);
13907 }
13908 return ReduceResult::Done();
13909}
13910
13911ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowReferenceErrorIfHole() {
13912 // ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole <variable_name>
13913 compiler::NameRef name = GetRefOperand<Name>(0);
13914 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
13915
13916 // Avoid the check if we know it is not the hole.
13917 if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
13918 if (IsTheHoleValue(value)) {
13919 ValueNode* constant = GetConstant(name);
13920 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowAccessedUninitializedVariable,
13921 {constant});
13922 }
13923 return ReduceResult::Done();
13924 }
13925
13926 // Avoid the check if {value}'s representation doesn't allow the hole.
13927 switch (value->value_representation()) {
13928 case ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
13929 case ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
13930 case ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
13931 case ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
13932 // Can't be the hole.
13933 // Note that HoleyFloat64 when converted to Tagged becomes Undefined
13934 // rather than the_hole, hence the early return for HoleyFloat64.
13935 return ReduceResult::Done();
13936
13937 case ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
13938 // Could be the hole.
13939 break;
13940
13941 case ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
13942 UNREACHABLE();
13943 }
13944
13945 // Avoid the check if {value} has an alternative whose representation doesn't
13946 // allow the hole.
13947 if (const NodeInfo* info = known_node_aspects().TryGetInfoFor(value)) {
13948 auto& alt = info->alternative();
13949 if (alt.int32() || alt.truncated_int32_to_number() || alt.float64()) {
13950 return ReduceResult::Done();
13951 }
13952 }
13953
13954 DCHECK(value->value_representation() == ValueRepresentation::kTagged);
13955 AddNewNode<ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole>({value}, name);
13956 return ReduceResult::Done();
13957}
13958
13959ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole() {
13960 // ThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole
13961 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
13962 if (CheckType(value, NodeType::kJSReceiver)) return ReduceResult::Done();
13963 // Avoid the check if we know it is not the hole.
13964 if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
13965 if (IsTheHoleValue(value)) {
13966 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSuperNotCalled, {});
13967 }
13968 return ReduceResult::Done();
13969 }
13970 AddNewNode<ThrowSuperNotCalledIfHole>({value});
13971 return ReduceResult::Done();
13972}
13973ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole() {
13974 // ThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole
13975 ValueNode* value = GetAccumulator();
13976 // Avoid the check if we know it is the hole.
13977 if (IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
13978 if (!IsTheHoleValue(value)) {
13979 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSuperAlreadyCalledError, {});
13980 }
13981 return ReduceResult::Done();
13982 }
13983 AddNewNode<ThrowSuperAlreadyCalledIfNotHole>({value});
13984 return ReduceResult::Done();
13985}
13986ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitThrowIfNotSuperConstructor() {
13987 // ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor <constructor>
13988 ValueNode* constructor = LoadRegister(0);
13989 ValueNode* function = GetClosure();
13990 AddNewNode<ThrowIfNotSuperConstructor>({constructor, function});
13991 return ReduceResult::Done();
13992}
13993
13994ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSwitchOnGeneratorState() {
13995 // SwitchOnGeneratorState <generator> <table_start> <table_length>
13996 // It should be the first bytecode in the bytecode array.
13997 DCHECK_EQ(iterator_.current_offset(), 0);
13998 int generator_prologue_block_offset = 1;
13999 DCHECK_LT(generator_prologue_block_offset, next_offset());
14000
14001 interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffsets offsets =
14002 iterator_.GetJumpTableTargetOffsets();
14003 // If there are no jump offsets, then this generator is not resumable, which
14004 // means we can skip checking for it and switching on its state.
14005 if (offsets.size() == 0) return ReduceResult::Done();
14006
14007 graph()->set_has_resumable_generator();
14008
14009 // We create an initial block that checks if the generator is undefined.
14010 ValueNode* maybe_generator = LoadRegister(0);
14011 // Neither the true nor the false path jump over any bytecode
14012 BasicBlock* block_is_generator_undefined = FinishBlock<BranchIfRootConstant>(
14013 {maybe_generator}, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue,
14014 &jump_targets_[next_offset()],
14015 &jump_targets_[generator_prologue_block_offset]);
14016 MergeIntoFrameState(block_is_generator_undefined, next_offset());
14017
14018 // We create the generator prologue block.
14019 StartNewBlock(generator_prologue_block_offset, block_is_generator_undefined);
14020
14021 // Generator prologue.
14022 ValueNode* generator = maybe_generator;
14023 ValueNode* state =
14024 BuildLoadTaggedField(generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset);
14025 ValueNode* new_state = GetSmiConstant(JSGeneratorObject::kGeneratorExecuting);
14026 BuildStoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(generator, new_state,
14027 JSGeneratorObject::kContinuationOffset,
14028 StoreTaggedMode::kDefault);
14029 ValueNode* context =
14030 BuildLoadTaggedField(generator, JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset);
14031 graph()->record_scope_info(context, {});
14032 SetContext(context);
14033
14034 // Guarantee that we have something in the accumulator.
14035 MoveNodeBetweenRegisters(iterator_.GetRegisterOperand(0),
14036 interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
14037
14038 // Switch on generator state.
14039 int case_value_base = (*offsets.begin()).case_value;
14040 BasicBlockRef* targets = zone()->AllocateArray<BasicBlockRef>(offsets.size());
14041 for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
14042 BasicBlockRef* ref = &targets[offset.case_value - case_value_base];
14043 new (ref) BasicBlockRef(&jump_targets_[offset.target_offset]);
14044 }
14045 ValueNode* case_value =
14046 state->is_tagged() ? AddNewNode<UnsafeSmiUntag>({state}) : state;
14047 BasicBlock* generator_prologue_block = FinishBlock<Switch>(
14048 {case_value}, case_value_base, targets, offsets.size());
14049 for (interpreter::JumpTableTargetOffset offset : offsets) {
14050 MergeIntoFrameState(generator_prologue_block, offset.target_offset);
14051 }
14052 return ReduceResult::Done();
14053}
14054
14055ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitSuspendGenerator() {
14056 // SuspendGenerator <generator> <first input register> <register count>
14057 // <suspend_id>
14058 ValueNode* generator = LoadRegister(0);
14059 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
14060 interpreter::RegisterList args = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
14061 uint32_t suspend_id = iterator_.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(3);
14062
14063 int input_count = parameter_count_without_receiver() + args.register_count() +
14064 GeneratorStore::kFixedInputCount;
14065 int debug_pos_offset = iterator_.current_offset() +
14066 (BytecodeArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag);
14067 AddNewNode<GeneratorStore>(
14068 input_count,
14069 [&](GeneratorStore* node) {
14070 int arg_index = 0;
14071 for (int i = 1 /* skip receiver */; i < parameter_count(); ++i) {
14072 node->set_parameters_and_registers(arg_index++,
14073 GetTaggedValue(GetArgument(i)));
14074 }
14075 const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness = GetOutLiveness();
14076 for (int i = 0; i < args.register_count(); ++i) {
14077 ValueNode* value = liveness->RegisterIsLive(args[i].index())
14078 ? GetTaggedValue(args[i])
14079 : GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kOptimizedOut);
14080 node->set_parameters_and_registers(arg_index++, value);
14081 }
14082 },
14083
14084 context, generator, suspend_id, debug_pos_offset);
14085
14086 FinishBlock<Return>({GetAccumulator()});
14087 return ReduceResult::Done();
14088}
14089
14090ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitResumeGenerator() {
14091 // ResumeGenerator <generator> <first output register> <register count>
14092 ValueNode* generator = LoadRegister(0);
14093 ValueNode* array = BuildLoadTaggedField(
14094 generator, JSGeneratorObject::kParametersAndRegistersOffset);
14095 interpreter::RegisterList registers = iterator_.GetRegisterListOperand(1);
14096
14097 if (v8_flags.maglev_assert) {
14098 // Check if register count is invalid, that is, larger than the
14099 // register file length.
14100 ValueNode* array_length = BuildLoadFixedArrayLength(array);
14101 ValueNode* register_size = GetInt32Constant(
14102 parameter_count_without_receiver() + registers.register_count());
14103 AddNewNode<AssertInt32>(
14104 {register_size, array_length}, AssertCondition::kLessThanEqual,
14105 AbortReason::kInvalidParametersAndRegistersInGenerator);
14106 }
14107
14108 const compiler::BytecodeLivenessState* liveness =
14109 GetOutLivenessFor(next_offset());
14110 RootConstant* stale = GetRootConstant(RootIndex::kStaleRegister);
14111 for (int i = 0; i < registers.register_count(); ++i) {
14112 if (liveness->RegisterIsLive(registers[i].index())) {
14113 int array_index = parameter_count_without_receiver() + i;
14114 StoreRegister(registers[i], AddNewNode<GeneratorRestoreRegister>(
14115 {array, stale}, array_index));
14116 }
14117 }
14118 SetAccumulator(BuildLoadTaggedField(
14119 generator, JSGeneratorObject::kInputOrDebugPosOffset));
14120 return ReduceResult::Done();
14121}
14122
14123MaybeReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::TryReduceGetIterator(
14124 ValueNode* receiver, int load_slot_index, int call_slot_index) {
14125 // Load iterator method property.
14126 FeedbackSlot load_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(load_slot_index);
14127 compiler::FeedbackSource load_feedback{feedback(), load_slot};
14128 compiler::NameRef iterator_symbol = broker()->iterator_symbol();
14129 ValueNode* iterator_method;
14130 {
14131 DeoptFrameScope deopt_continuation(
14132 this, Builtin::kGetIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation, {},
14133 base::VectorOf<ValueNode*>({receiver, GetSmiConstant(call_slot_index),
14134 GetConstant(feedback())}));
14135 MaybeReduceResult result_load =
14136 TryBuildLoadNamedProperty(receiver, iterator_symbol, load_feedback);
14137 if (result_load.IsDoneWithAbort() || result_load.IsFail()) {
14138 return result_load;
14139 }
14140 DCHECK(result_load.IsDoneWithValue());
14141 iterator_method = result_load.value();
14142 }
14143 auto throw_iterator_error = [&] {
14144 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorError, {receiver});
14145 };
14146 if (!iterator_method->is_tagged()) {
14147 return throw_iterator_error();
14148 }
14149 auto throw_symbol_iterator_invalid = [&] {
14150 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSymbolIteratorInvalid, {});
14151 };
14152 auto call_iterator_method = [&] {
14153 DeoptFrameScope deopt_continuation(
14154 this, Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation);
14155
14156 FeedbackSlot call_slot = FeedbackVector::ToSlot(call_slot_index);
14157 compiler::FeedbackSource call_feedback{feedback(), call_slot};
14158 CallArguments args(ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, {receiver});
14159 MaybeReduceResult result_call =
14160 ReduceCall(iterator_method, args, call_feedback);
14161
14162 if (result_call.IsDoneWithAbort()) return result_call;
14163 DCHECK(result_call.IsDoneWithValue());
14164 return SelectReduction(
14165 [&](auto& builder) {
14166 return BuildBranchIfJSReceiver(builder, result_call.value());
14167 },
14168 [&] { return result_call; }, throw_symbol_iterator_invalid);
14169 };
14170 // Check if the iterator_method is undefined and call the method otherwise.
14171 return SelectReduction(
14172 [&](auto& builder) {
14173 return BuildBranchIfUndefined(builder, iterator_method);
14174 },
14175 throw_iterator_error, call_iterator_method);
14176}
14177
14178ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitGetIterator() {
14179 // GetIterator <object>
14180 ValueNode* receiver = LoadRegister(0);
14181 int load_slot = iterator_.GetIndexOperand(1);
14182 int call_slot = iterator_.GetIndexOperand(2);
14183 PROCESS_AND_RETURN_IF_DONE(
14184 TryReduceGetIterator(receiver, load_slot, call_slot), SetAccumulator);
14185 // Fallback to the builtin.
14186 ValueNode* context = GetContext();
14187 SetAccumulator(AddNewNode<GetIterator>({context, receiver}, load_slot,
14188 call_slot, feedback()));
14189 return ReduceResult::Done();
14190}
14191
14192ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitDebugger() {
14193 return BuildCallRuntime(Runtime::kHandleDebuggerStatement, {});
14194}
14195
14196ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitIncBlockCounter() {
14197 ValueNode* closure = GetClosure();
14198 ValueNode* coverage_array_slot = GetSmiConstant(iterator_.GetIndexOperand(0));
14199 BuildCallBuiltin<Builtin::kIncBlockCounter>(
14200 {GetTaggedValue(closure), coverage_array_slot});
14201 return ReduceResult::Done();
14202}
14203
14204ReduceResult MaglevGraphBuilder::VisitAbort() {
14205 AbortReason reason = static_cast<AbortReason>(GetFlag8Operand(0));
14206 return BuildAbort(reason);
14207}
